{"id": "50370", "revid": "53595577", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50370", "title": "Qilue", "text": "Qilue is a &lt;a href=\"Drow\"&gt;Drow&lt;/a&gt; Priestess Cleric that resides in her residence along with several servant mages. If you enter her dwelling at the behest of the &lt;a href=\"Aboleth\"&gt;Aboleth&lt;/a&gt; then you are most likely trying to complete a task to retrieve her brain. This can only be accomplished by violence. As soon as the party enters the home, all denizens will be hostile and attack.\nGameplay.\nQilue can melee with her enchanted drow armor, shield and flail. This creature will cast a self-defensive buff and then offensive/disabling spells in combat, if not disrupted.\nAt the start of hostilities, she will instantly (and cannot be interrupted) launch &lt;a href=\"Defensive%20Harmony\"&gt;Defensive Harmony&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Righteous%20Magic\"&gt;Righteous Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Strength%20of%20One\"&gt;Strength of One&lt;/a&gt; in the area, which will buff herself any allied creatures close by.\nShe will attempt a &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Dispel Magic (priest)&lt;/a&gt; at a party member. A &lt;a href=\"True%20Seeing\"&gt;True Seeing&lt;/a&gt; will be attempted as well. She will probably try and conjure in some help with an &lt;a href=\"Animate%20Dead\"&gt;Animate Dead&lt;/a&gt; spell. Further spell attacks include &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Hold Person (priest)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mental%20Domination\"&gt;Mental Domination&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Person%20or%20Mammal\"&gt;Charm Person or Mammal&lt;/a&gt;. \nIf damaged to certain thresholds she will attempt &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Serious%20Wounds\"&gt;Cure Serious Wounds&lt;/a&gt; on self, and &lt;a href=\"Mass%20Cure\"&gt;Mass Cure&lt;/a&gt; on allies and self.\nThis is all she is scripted to do other than close quarters melee combat.\nGame note.\nIn the original game, Qilue's script contained a global setting launch of three other Drow Servant Wizard's who would use the &lt;a href=\"Dimension%20Door\"&gt;Dimension Door&lt;/a&gt; animation to come to assist against the intruding party. Because the spell caused game errors, Dimension Door is now deprecated from the game, and the Drow Servants are just added to the area instead.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes a few changes to this creature. Her weapon proficiencies are corrected to 1 pip in flail and 1 pip in sword and shield style. She is now a level 20 Cleric, with adjusted saving throws and a better THAC0. A complete compliment of divine spells is memorized from levels 1 through 7. Some of the spells are different than the unmodded creature. A default SCS cleric AI script is installed for \"Smarter Cleric\" behavior. An SCS random treasure is in the creature's inventory as well. Qilue will now aggressively cast as many spells as possible unless disrupted or killed. She will heal herself, cast True Seeing and self-buffs, and summon creatures.\nShe will open with the following (previously cast) instantly applied buffs: &lt;a href=\"Regeneration%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Regeneration (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Draw Upon Holy Might (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Fire%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Protection From Fire (priest)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Mirror\"&gt;Physical Mirror&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Free Action (spell)&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt;.\nAn Animate Skeleton warrior spell will follow. From then on, further spell casting will be determined by the AI's threat assessment and opponent vulnerability evaluations. This includes more summoned creatures, offensive spell casts and disabling type spells. Healing spells are also available to mitigate damage on self and allies.\nIf the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; Mod is installed, the drow's memorized spells will be the SR versions."}
{"id": "31220", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31220", "title": "Qilue's Brain", "text": "Qilue's Brain is dropped by &lt;a href=\"Qilue\"&gt;Qilue&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Qilue%27s%20Home\"&gt;her home&lt;/a&gt; when you kill her under &lt;a href=\"Aboleth\"&gt;Aboleth&lt;/a&gt;'s orders in the Drow city of &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt;. The Aboleth asks for her brain as blackmail for not revealing your true identity to the Drow city."}
{"id": "45020", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45020", "title": "Qilue's Home", "text": "Qilue's Home is where the &lt;a href=\"Drow\"&gt;Drow&lt;/a&gt; priestess &lt;a href=\"Qilue\"&gt;Qilue&lt;/a&gt; resides with her servants. You are commanded to obtain and deliver &lt;a href=\"Qilue%27s%20Brain\"&gt;Qilue's Brain&lt;/a&gt; to the &lt;a href=\"Aboleth\"&gt;Aboleth&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt;, or your disguise will be revealed to the drow city inhabitants. Obtaining a living brain requires some violence, so go 'ahead' and get cracking. \nGameplay.\nUpon entry to Qilue's home you will observe several hostile mages and Qilue the priestess. Spells will be cast and a battle will ensue. Qilue will shout: \"Die, one and all!\".\nThere are two allies with Qilue on the entry platform, and another three further into the home on a lower platform.\nPlunder.\nAside from personal items that can be obtained from defeated bodies, there are six containers that can be examined in the home, you may find some random treasures.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod revises the creatures in the home. See individual linked creature pages (above) for a summary of those revisions."}
