{"id": "25631", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=25631", "title": "Quallo", "text": "Quallo is a human man dwelling in the &lt;a href=\"The%20Sewers%20Beneath%20the%20Slums\"&gt;sewers&lt;/a&gt; with his 'friend', a &lt;a href=\"Carrion%20Crawler\"&gt;Carrion Crawler&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nThe party can speak with this emaciated and disheveled man before and after finding out about the strange \"Glowing Pool\" and its mysterious drainpipes.\nMuch conversation including questions and answers are offered by this strange encounter. Certain core companions may have interjections as well. Navigate the information and tales given by Quallo as well as from the \"disembodied voice in your head\" when within the Glowing Pool chamber. Sorting through all the clues, the found Severed Hand, Lover's Ring and Shaman Staff can lead to solving the riddle. The riddle speaks of a famous blade.\nMore information is provided in the &lt;a href=\"Solve%20the%20Riddle%20of%20the%20Sewers\"&gt;Solve the Riddle of the Sewers&lt;/a&gt; quest page.\nIf the quest is solved and the party returns to check on Quallo, the party finds that he is now free of some kind of domination over his mind. The poor sod will say:\nQuallo will then make for the surface and leave behind this tragic event in his life.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Alternatives\"&gt;Alternatives&lt;/a&gt; mod adds content so that if you would like to avoid killing Quallo's \"friend\", you will see new options in Quallo's dialogue."}
