{"id": "2138", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2138", "title": "Quarterstaff", "text": "The Quarterstaff is the starting weapon for all player classes in the games of Baldur's Gate and Baldur's Gate: Enhanced Edition. Quarterstaves can be used by all classes, except &lt;a href=\"Monk\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt;s. They require two hands to use them, along with a strength of 5 points for most quarterstaves. They weigh 4 pounds, inflict 1-6 points of crushing damage, and have a speed factor of 4. The proficiency for their use is Quarterstaff for all games except in Baldur's Gate, where it's in the Blunt Weapons proficiency. This item appears in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, , &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;, and ."}
{"id": "2492", "revid": "78773", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2492", "title": "Quarterstaff +1", "text": "The\u00a0Quarterstaff +1 is an enchanted weapon. Compared with a normal &lt;a href=\"quarterstaff\"&gt;quarterstaff&lt;/a&gt;, it does +1 greater damage, has +1 to &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; and a speed factor of 3 rather than 4. Both staves have the same weight of 4 lbs. This weapon is in the Quarterstaff proficiency, with the exception of \"classic\" Baldur's Gate, where it is in the Blunt Weapons proficiency instead. This item appears in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nThe\u00a0Quarterstaff +1 is an enchanted weapon. Compared with a normal &lt;a href=\"quarterstaff\"&gt;quarterstaff&lt;/a&gt;, it does +1 greater damage, has +1 to &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; and a speed factor of 3 rather than 4. Both staves have the same weight of 4 lbs. This weapon is in the Quarterstaff proficiency, with the exception of \"classic\" Baldur's Gate, where it is in the Blunt Weapons proficiency instead. This item appears in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "7811", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7811", "title": "Quarterstaff +2", "text": "The Quarterstaff +2 is an enchanted weapon. It can deal 1D6+2 (3-8) points of damage, has -2 THAC0 bonus, a speed factor of 2 and it weighs 3 lbs. This item appears in , and .\nin\u00a0Baldur's Gate: Enhanced Edition it is wielded by &lt;a href=\"Laskal\"&gt;Laskal&lt;/a&gt; in the third &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood\"&gt;Cloakwood&lt;/a&gt; area.\nIn Baldur's Gate II it is sold at the &lt;a href=\"Adventurer%27s%20Mart\"&gt;Adventurer's Mart&lt;/a&gt;, at the &lt;a href=\"Tankard%20Tree\"&gt;Tankard Tree&lt;/a&gt; and by &lt;a href=\"Karthis%20al-Hezzar\"&gt;Karthis al-Hezzar&lt;/a&gt;. It is also dropped by &lt;a href=\"Rayic%20Gethras\"&gt;Rayic Gethras&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Karun%20the%20Black\"&gt;Karun the Black&lt;/a&gt;."}
