{"id": "3751", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3751", "title": "Quayle", "text": "Quayle is a chaotic neutral gnome &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Multi-class\"&gt;multi-class&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Cleric%20/%20Mage\"&gt;cleric / illusionist&lt;/a&gt; and a potential &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt; in .\n&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; &amp;.\nRecruitment.\nQuayle is available from &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Five\"&gt;Chapter Five&lt;/a&gt; on. He's found on the paved road near the city gate of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and will join the party if you let him. His starting equipment is a club, a sling and 20 bullets.\nTrivia.\nIf you reject the offer for Quayle to join your group, your answer is \"No, and don't call me Shirley\". This is a reference to a classic gag from the 1980 movie \"\".\nSome time after the defeat of &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%20Anchev\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt; Quayle began travelling with a circus, where he met &lt;a href=\"Aerie\"&gt;Aerie&lt;/a&gt;. Taking the young &lt;a href=\"Elf%23Avariel\"&gt;avariel&lt;/a&gt; under his wing, he became her guardian and tutor, helping her recover from the loss of her wings. In turn Aerie lovingly refers to him as \"uncle Quayle\".\nHe can be found in the circus tent in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; being transformed into &lt;a href=\"Mustard%20Jelly\"&gt;Mustard Jelly&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href=\"Kalah\"&gt;Kalah&lt;/a&gt;. He regains his true physical form once the party finishes &lt;a href=\"Investigate%20the%20circus%20tent\"&gt;dealing with Kalah&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "56984", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56984", "title": "Quayle has called for Aerie", "text": "Quayle has called for Aerie is a companion quest that may or may not occur in two days after &lt;a href=\"Aerie\"&gt;Aerie&lt;/a&gt; has been recruited into the party.\nIn reality, this isn't much of a quest at all, but simply a notification/introduction of another potential quest.\nAquisition.\nThis minor companion quest occurs only if Aerie is a companion, and at least two days has elapsed since she joined the party.\nThe quest won't be acquired if the party has already initiated the &lt;a href=\"Free%20Haer%27Dalis%20from%20Imprisonment%20by%20Mekrath\"&gt;Free Haer'Dalis from Imprisonment by Mekrath&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nIf that situation isn't the case, then when travelling outdoors in the city of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; or in the other outdoor &lt;a href=\"World%20Map\"&gt;World Map&lt;/a&gt; locations - a messenger will approach the party and initiate dialogue.\nThe messenger will relay that uncle &lt;a href=\"Quayle\"&gt;Quayle&lt;/a&gt; wants Aerie to visit him in the &lt;a href=\"Circus%20Tent\"&gt;Circus Tent&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt;. The following journal entry is registered:\nIf uncle Quayle is dead, the messenger instead delivers a letter from &lt;a href=\"Raelis%20Shai\"&gt;Raelis Shai&lt;/a&gt; originally sent to Quayle, asking for assistance. The following journal entry is registered.\nGameplay.\nShould the party decide to go and visit Quayle, then just travel to the Circus Tent and he'll initiate dialogue with Aerie.\nQuayle will explain that one his old friends is in need of some aid. He believes Aerie and &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; are more suited to help then he and asks the party to go see Raelis Shai to find out what might be done to lend a hand.\nIf Aerie replies that they've already spoken to Raelis, then Quayle is pleased and just carry on and offer what help they can.\nAt the end of the discussion, the journal registers a new entry, and also a new &lt;a href=\"A%20friend%20of%20Quayle%27s%20needs%20help\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;:\nNote.\nIf the party doesn't visit and speak with Quayle after two days, Aerie will bring up the subject and remind the Ward about the message. There really are no repercussions if the party never gets around to following up on the quest or just chooses not to engage with Quayle it at all."}
{"id": "45088", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45088", "title": "Queen", "text": "Queen is one of the chess pieces encountered on the Chessboard when transitioning between the &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28Labyrinth%20Level%20Three%29\"&gt;third&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28Labyrinth%20Level%20Four%29\"&gt;fourth&lt;/a&gt; labyrinth levels beneath &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt;. As in regular chess, there is one of them on the board.\nGameplay.\nBe aware that during the fighting, if a &lt;a href=\"Pawn\"&gt;Pawn&lt;/a&gt; makes it to your side of the chessboard it will be promoted to a queen.\nNotes.\nEven though its race is classified as a golem, its appearance is that of an Elf mage."}
{"id": "8672", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8672", "title": "Quenash", "text": "Quenash is a prostitute who was a favored consort of an elven mercenary named &lt;a href=\"Vail\"&gt;Vail&lt;/a&gt; before he was petrified during an attempted breakin some years ago of the mage &lt;a href=\"Ramazith\"&gt;Ramazith&lt;/a&gt;s &lt;a href=\"Ramazith%27s%20Tower\"&gt;home&lt;/a&gt;. Before Vail pulled this assault, he gave her the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;Cloak of Balduran&lt;/a&gt;, an item as dear to him as the &lt;a href=\"Helm%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;Helm of Balduran&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nAfter Vail has revealed that the Cloak of Balduran is in Quenash's possession, she can be convinced to relinquish it. With a &lt;a href=\"reaction\"&gt;reaction&lt;/a&gt; result of 8 or higher, she can be convinced to talk about the Helm of Balduran as well. The correct dialogue options to get the cloak and the hint to the whereabouts of the helm are 3\u20136\u20132\u20131.\nIf Vail was not let go, she can't be talked to about the cloak even though a letter on Vail's body reveals that she has it. She can however be pick-pocketed for it (with a minimum of 50% pick-pocketing skill) or killed. The easiest way to have her killed without reputation loss is to charm her and make her attack a guard."}
