{"id": "11844", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11844", "title": "Radiant Mephit", "text": "Radiant Mephits are small, minor elemental creatures that are first encountered in &lt;a href=\"Irenicus%27s%20Dungeon%201st%20Floor\"&gt;Irenicus's Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;. Every 16 seconds, they can cast a version of &lt;a href=\"Color%20Spray\"&gt;Color Spray&lt;/a&gt; able to put targets to sleep regardless of level.\nGameplay.\nA Radiant Mephit can attack twice per round in melee for 1d3 damage. It also has the &lt;a href=\"Color%20Spray%20%28innate%29\"&gt;Color Spray (innate)&lt;/a&gt; ability. \nThe mephit will initiate the \"Color Spray\" attack, which launches a multi-colored fan projectile at a single target in range and it can potentially affect any creature within the spreading arc of the spray. A &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Spells is required or the creature will be subjected to an effect that will make them &lt;a href=\"Unconscious\"&gt;Unconscious&lt;/a&gt; for five rounds. Unlike the arcane spell &lt;a href=\"Color%20Spray\"&gt;Color Spray&lt;/a&gt;, this version can affect any creature regardless of their Hit dice/Experience level. The creature will attempt a spray as soon as a creature is in range. After a 16 second delay interval, where the mephit will attack in melee, it will then attempt another spray. It has an unlimited supply of this ability.\nThis mephit can regenerate 1 HP per round and moves faster than a typical creatures speed.\nThis type of mephit has no magic, physical damage or elemental resistance. The InfoBox summarizes their special abilities and immunities to certain status effects. The game has the creature with a memorized &lt;a href=\"Blur\"&gt;Blur&lt;/a&gt; spell but it isn't scripted to use it, so it is probably just a developer creature file copy-paste remnant. "}
{"id": "6456", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6456", "title": "Raelis Shai", "text": "Raelis Shai is a &lt;a href=\"tiefling\"&gt;tiefling&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"bard\"&gt;bard&lt;/a&gt; and the leader of the Sigil actors Troupe. She and the rest of her troupe, &lt;a href=\"Kirinaldo\"&gt;Kirinaldo&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lunisia\"&gt;Lunisia&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Biff%20the%20Understudy\"&gt;Biff the Understudy&lt;/a&gt;, perform plays at the &lt;a href=\"Five%20Flagons%20Theatre\"&gt;Five Flagons Theatre&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe first time the player enters the Five Flagons Theater the party will observe a portion of a play via a cut scene. The play is curtailed early due to poor performance issues stemming from unprepared actors, mainly Biff. Raelis will apologize to the audience and offer a full refund. She also takes the opportunity to ask for assistance, as follows:\nAfter this message, a Journal Entry display as follows:\nVisit her at the rear of the theater, and initiate conversation. A number of dialogue options are available. In the end, if you accept the quest to assist the Actor Troupe, and agree to &lt;a href=\"Free%20Haer%27Dalis%20from%20Imprisonment%20by%20Mekrath\"&gt;Free Haer'Dalis from Imprisonment by Mekrath&lt;/a&gt;, Raelis will wish you well with a promise of a reward.\nIf you are able to rescue Haer'Dalis, and visit her again (whether if he's a companion now or not), she's going to reward the party and check if the &lt;a href=\"Portal%20Gem\"&gt;Portal Gem&lt;/a&gt; was recovered as well. That gem is needed by Raelis (and Hae'rdalis will attest to that if a companion or not).\nIf the party is not going to return it, or tries to extort a better reward, then a different dialogue path will present. This could lead to a poor reaction and cutting off the &lt;a href=\"Rescue%20Raelis%20and%20Haer%27Dalis%20from%20the%20Planar%20Prison\"&gt;Rescue Raelis and Haer'Dalis from the Planar Prison&lt;/a&gt; quest - which is a fun adventure with much loot and potential experience.\nIf the party is reasonable, and provides the Portal Gem, she will then ask for one more favor after attempting to open a planar tunnel to transport away. She needs help in case something comes through the open portal until the correct tunnel form. The party can refuse to help, ask what kind of payment you'll receive, or just agree to help by saying:\nIf the party doesn't wish to help or be involved, then a final statement is said by Raelis, and she'll wait for the party to depart before undertaking their travel to the planes alone (and the whole Troupe will be gone from the game for good and the associated quest is also shuttered). If the protagonist is a bard, then she will also leave the player the &lt;a href=\"Playhouse%20Deed\"&gt;Playhouse Deed&lt;/a&gt;.\nAnd finally, the party will be able to converse with Raelis a last time if they are rescued from the Planar Prison, along with an experience point award.\nNotes.\nRaelis has different dialogue available if Haer'Dalis is dead and his corpse is lost/left behind/chunked. Or if he is dead and still part of the party (not resurrected yet). She will be able to bring him back to life.\nThere is also a number of angry and disappointed dialogue quips if the party is trying to extort more money or not live up to their bargain.\nIf at any time the party attacks, or is caught stealing from, anyone in the Playhouse, including the &lt;a href=\"Receptionist\"&gt;Receptionist&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Usher\"&gt;Usher&lt;/a&gt;s or theatergoers, Raelis and her Troupe will turn hostile and attack the party. Effectively, this makes the Sigil Troupe the Authority for the playhouse up until they are abducted by bounty hunters through the extra-planar portal that opens up in the archway, stage-right (from the performers' perspective). Therefore, it is also possible to close off access to the &lt;a href=\"Planar%20Prison\"&gt;Planar Prison&lt;/a&gt; and the quest to rescue the Troupe, thereby missing out on much experience, treasure, a valuable &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;Companion&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Haer%27Dalis\"&gt;Haer'Dalis&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Running%20the%20Five%20Flagons%20Playhouse\"&gt;ownership of the Playhouse&lt;/a&gt; as a potential &lt;a href=\"Stronghold\"&gt;Stronghold&lt;/a&gt; (assuming the protagonist is a &lt;a href=\"Bard\"&gt;Bard&lt;/a&gt;)."}
{"id": "7872", "revid": "8506165", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7872", "title": "Raemon", "text": "Raemon is a unique &lt;a href=\"bandit\"&gt;bandit&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". He is a likely second-in-command of the &lt;a href=\"Blacktalons\"&gt;Blacktalons&lt;/a&gt; mercenary group, and can be found along with three other mercenaries - &lt;a href=\"Venkt\"&gt;Venkt&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Britik\"&gt;Britik&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hakt\"&gt;Hakt&lt;/a&gt; - within &lt;a href=\"Tazok\"&gt;Tazok&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Tazok%27s%20Tent\"&gt;tent&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Bandit%20Camp\"&gt;Bandit Camp&lt;/a&gt;. They are guarding a captured spy named &lt;a href=\"Ender%20Sai\"&gt;Ender Sai&lt;/a&gt;.\nSeemingly able to identify &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; by sight (if the party attempts to deceive him), he will greet the party upon entry, only to eventually turn hostile."}
{"id": "47187", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47187", "title": "Raevilin Strathi", "text": "Raevilin Strathi is one of the people you can save from the drow Soul Prison device in the center area of the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%205\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 5&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nFree this creature by manipulating the second facet on the soul entrapment device. Where \"second facet\" corresponds to a west to east (or left to right) orientation if facing the device.\nUpon being released from the device, he seems severely mentally challenged, making only incoherent broken sentences and noises and then attacking you after a few rounds. This is the likely outcome for a first-time player who has no knowledge of the encounter ahead of time and who didn't do on-line research ahead of gameplay - such as this wiki article - to instead attempt a different course of action.\nThe game gives no clues or helpful hints that this mental condition might be curable. However, setting aside the extremely low probability that a player without any foreknowledge would actually attempt to cast a &lt;a href=\"Heal\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt; spell upon this creature - then doing that exact action (if done successfully) will open up more gameplay options. \nOnly the spell Heal cast upon him will cure his ailments. A &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Disease\"&gt;Cure Disease&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Restoration\"&gt;Greater Restoration&lt;/a&gt; won't suffice. The mental illness is most likely caused by prolonged imprisonment in a subterranean void. There is a short period to be able to do this action. The Heal spell will revert the mage from being hostile and to initiate meaningful dialogue.\nIf the mage isn't affected by the Heal spell, he'll eventually turn hostile and self-buff with &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;, then &lt;a href=\"Mislead\"&gt;Mislead&lt;/a&gt;. All the spells listed on the InfoBox are scripted for use, so beware the &lt;a href=\"Imprisonment\"&gt;Imprisonment&lt;/a&gt; spell cast and other attacks.\nAfter curing his mental ailment, Raevilin will speak. Should the party be currently under the drow disguise enchantment, then different dialogue will present. \nAfter questions by the party are asked and answers given in an understanding and empathetic way then an award of is bestowed, as well as a gift of the &lt;a href=\"Albruin\"&gt;Albruin&lt;/a&gt; bastard sword. \nIf the party wishes him well and accepts his thanks for a good deed well done, the mage will eventually leave on his own accord. A journal entry will display:\nAnother option available through initial dialogue once he has had the Heal spell applied, is to select the dialogue choice to demand that he must make payment for his rescue. This will lead to a response from the mage, as follows:\nThis dialogue track leads to hostilities. There will be no quest reward XP or the sword Albruin item granted. Killing him nets only his death award and the carried scrolls in his inventory - &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Earth%20Elemental%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Conjure Earth Elemental (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Efreeti\"&gt;Summon Efreeti&lt;/a&gt;. A journal entry will then display:\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod changes this mage. Some new memorized spells are added. Ready to use sequencer, spell trigger and contingency are available to deploy via the new SCS \"Improved Mages\" component. Raevilin is granted one pip in quarterstaff weapon proficiency. Two additional Icewind Dale Wizard spell scrolls are added if you have that SCS component installed, and two SCS random treasures are in the creature's inventory.\nWith this mod installed, there is almost no chance of getting a Heal spell applied to Raevilin before he goes hostile and gets up his spell buffs. The party will then be faced with taking down his protections/invisibility, and surviving his spell attacks, without killing the mage, and then getting a Heal spell applied to end his hostility. This will take some micromanagement and a bit of luck/tactics to do. Depending on the player's party it might be very difficult or frustratingly impossible.\nRaevilin, after a few moments (and if not cured of his mental afflictions) will initiate a group of (cast previously) protective buffs to include &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;SI: Divination&lt;/a&gt; (or \"Dispelling Screen\" with &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt;), &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Cold%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Protection From Cold (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter this, if able to function and not impaired he may attempt further protections from his Spell Trigger, such as &lt;a href=\"Mantle\"&gt;Mantle&lt;/a&gt; (or {\"Prismatic Mantle\" with SR) and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;. After that, offensive spells casts and summoned help. The mage can employe a few prepared sequencers in the thick of combat.\nInstalling &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; will change all memorized spells to the SR versions."}
{"id": "49838", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49838", "title": "Raffiyah", "text": "Raffiyah is within her lair, along with two &lt;a href=\"Spider%20%28Tomb%20of%20the%20Unproved%29\"&gt;Spider&lt;/a&gt; attendants named Jabira and Sundus that are capable of speech and refer to Raffiyah as \"Mistress\". Raffiyah is an ugly, immobile, bloated creature, similar in form to &lt;a href=\"Centeol\"&gt;Centeol&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nRaffiyah will address the party when it enters the lair. There are several paths of dialogue which can occur. Depending on how you address her, and your tone, will determine the outcome of the encounter. If Raffiyah has deemed you to be a threat or not respectful enough (or flattering enough) she will turn hostile as well as the attending spiders.\nOnce hostile, Raffiyah will begin casting Priest Spells. She often begins with a fast casting of &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Mirror\"&gt;Physical Mirror&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Good\"&gt;Protection From Good, 10' Radius&lt;/a&gt; (which boosts her attending spiders). The spiders move quickly and will try and engage in melee attacks to whomever is closest. The script for Raffiyah provides her with a casting speed modifier bonus of 5. She is also given a hidden spell power by her script to &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Spawn\"&gt;summon spiders&lt;/a&gt;. The script allows her to continually summon a &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Spider\"&gt;spider&lt;/a&gt; once every 2 rounds. If you don't dispose of her quickly, Raffiyah will try &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Strike\"&gt;Flame Strike&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Confusion%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Confusion&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Finger%20of%20Death%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Finger of Death&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bolt%20of%20Glory\"&gt;Bolt of Glory&lt;/a&gt;. She can be overwhelmed by multiple physical attacks, even with her formidable physical attack damage resistance.\nRaffiyah can melee attack if you are next to her. Her &lt;a href=\"SPSPID3.ITM\"&gt;attack&lt;/a&gt; has a range of 1, speed 3, is a +2 enchanted piercing attack inflicting 2d4+2 damage, with a +2 THAC0. A save vs. Death at -3 penalty is needed to avoid 5 poison damage per second for 30 seconds. She can attack twice per round.\nOnce defeated, get the &lt;a href=\"Shroud%20of%20the%20Unproved\"&gt;Shroud of the Unproved&lt;/a&gt; from the sarcophagus in the lair. Hexxat will then ask if you are ready to travel back to the Athkatla Graveyard via the Tomb Walk ability provided by the &lt;a href=\"Casque%20of%20Dragomir\"&gt;Casque of Dragomir&lt;/a&gt;. \nParty banter quotes when first seeing Raffiyah.\nJan Jansen\nViconia DeVir"}
{"id": "8582", "revid": "26182140", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8582", "title": "Ragefast", "text": "Ragefast is a &lt;a href=\"Mage%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; who can be found in his &lt;a href=\"Ragefast%27s%20Home\"&gt;home&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"West%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;West Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. He is \nso obsessed with the &lt;a href=\"nymph\"&gt;nymph&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Abela%20the%20Nymph\"&gt;Abela&lt;/a&gt; that he is holding her captive in his house until she admits that she loves him. If he perceives the party as a threat to Abela or himself, he will attack.\nIf you have spoken to the mage &lt;a href=\"Ramazith\"&gt;Ramazith&lt;/a&gt; first, he will ask you to bring the nymph to him with the promise of a magical item as a reward.\nNotes.\nIf the player wishes to take a peaceful route, Ragefast's wand of paralyzation and necklace can be pickpocketed for 50 and 80 pickpocket skill respectively. Casting a Charm spell makes this easier. "}
