{"id": "8583", "revid": "26182140", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8583", "title": "Ramazith", "text": "Ramazith is a mage and the owner of &lt;a href=\"Ramazith%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Ramazith's Tower&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"North%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;North Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. Among other things, he is the mage who summoned &lt;a href=\"Green%20Slime\"&gt;green slimes&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Ye%20Olde%20Inn\"&gt;Ye Olde Inn&lt;/a&gt;. If &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; hasn't &lt;a href=\"The%20Captive%20Nymph\"&gt;freed&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Abela\"&gt;Abela&lt;/a&gt; yet and approaches his tower, he will address the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; and ask them to bring him the nymph from the &lt;a href=\"Ragefast%27s%20Home\"&gt;house&lt;/a&gt; of the mage &lt;a href=\"Ragefast\"&gt;Ragefast&lt;/a&gt;, and then retreat into his tower. Otherwise, the party can find him waiting inside his tower, furious that they released his desired nymph. In this last case though, where the party has released the nymph prior to meeting Ramazith, don't enter his tower for the first time while invisible (or in stealth mode) because doing so will make Ramazith disappear from the game after a split second (there has to be a visible party member to whom Ramazith will speak). \nPickpocket.\nIn pre-EE versions of the game, his precious &lt;a href=\"Amulet%20of%20Metaspell%20Influence\"&gt;Amulet of Metaspell Influence&lt;/a&gt; and Ring of Protection +2 can be acquired from Ramazith three separate times. The first time he can be pickpocketed when he approaches the party outside his tower with the job offer. He can then be pickpocketed a second time once he's on the ground floor of his tower. Lastly, challenge him to a fight, which causes him to teleport to the top floor of his tower. Kill him up there to acquire the ring and amulet for a third time.\nIn the EE version this is fixed, it is only possible to get one instance of these items. "}
{"id": "6458", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6458", "title": "Ramazith's Tower", "text": "Ramazith's Tower can be found in the district of &lt;a href=\"North%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;North Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. The tower is the property of the wizard &lt;a href=\"Ramazith\"&gt;Ramazith&lt;/a&gt; who uses it as his home. This tower has six floors, and all except the ground floor are guarded. From bottom to top, the order is &lt;a href=\"Mustard%20Jelly\"&gt;Mustard Jellies&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ghast\"&gt;Ghast&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Hobgoblin%20Elite\"&gt;Hobgoblin Elite&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Kobold%20Commando\"&gt;Kobold Commando&lt;/a&gt;s, and Ramazith himself will be on the top floor, given he was not killed earlier.\nNotably, there is a &lt;a href=\"Tome%20of%20Clear%20Thought\"&gt;Tome of Clear Thought&lt;/a&gt; on the top floor to increase the &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Ability%20Scores\"&gt;ability score&lt;/a&gt; of a &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; member. Also on the top floor, a copy of the book \"&lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Unicorn%20Run\"&gt;History of the Unicorn Run&lt;/a&gt;\" can be found which is required for \"&lt;a href=\"a%20Bard%27s%20Request\"&gt;a Bard's Request&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
