{"id": "52203", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52203", "title": "Random Area - Cave Entrance", "text": ""}
{"id": "45896", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45896", "title": "Random Encounter (BG)", "text": "There are six different Random Encounter areas where the party will be ambushed by enemies during travel in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur\u2019s Gate&lt;/a&gt;. They are all relatively small in size which limits the space available in which to run and regroup. Random encounters do not always trigger, but when they do it is on journey\u2019s that are usually greater than 16 hours in length.\nThe specific area \u201c\"type\"\u201d encountered appears to be determined based both on your current location and your destination location. Extremely long distance travel may result in the party being ambushed in more than one type of random encounter area. The Plains, Grassland, and Road areas are encountered more often than the other three.\nAs is normal with random encounters - the party is not allowed to sleep or save in these areas and once the map is exited the journey can continue in any direction you choose, which can possibly lead to another random encounter before you reach your final destination.\nRandom Encounter Area Types.\nPlains.\nThe \"Plains\" is normally encountered when traveling to or from those areas east of the main road between &lt;a href=\"The%20Friendly%20Arm%20Inn\"&gt;The Friendly Arm Inn&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Wood\"&gt;Spider Wood&lt;/a&gt; to the north and &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Valley%20of%20the%20Tombs\"&gt;Valley of the Tombs&lt;/a&gt; to the south.\n\"Random enemies potentially encountered:\"\nCanyon.\nThe \"Canyon\" is normally encountered when traveling to or from those areas south Nashkel between the &lt;a href=\"Gnoll%20Stronghold\"&gt;Gnoll Stronghold&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bear%20River\"&gt;Bear River&lt;/a&gt; to the west and the &lt;a href=\"Gibberling%20Mountains\"&gt;Gibberling Mountains&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"Valley%20of%20the%20Tombs\"&gt;Valley of the Tombs&lt;/a&gt; to the east.\n\"Random enemies potentially encountered:\"\nCliff.\nThe \"Cliff\" is only encountered when traveling to or from those areas along the Sea of Swords coast between &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Archaeological%20Site\"&gt;Archaeological Site&lt;/a&gt;.\n\"Random enemies potentially encountered:\"\nGrassland.\nThe \"Grassland\" is normally encountered when traveling to or from those areas extending from &lt;a href=\"Wyrm%27s%20Crossing\"&gt;Wyrm's Crossing&lt;/a&gt; to the &lt;a href=\"Lion%27s%20Way\"&gt;Lion's Way&lt;/a&gt; then south to &lt;a href=\"Fisherman%27s%20Lake\"&gt;Fisherman's Lake&lt;/a&gt;, east to the &lt;a href=\"Lonely%20Peaks\"&gt;Lonely Peaks&lt;/a&gt;, and then back north to the &lt;a href=\"Bandit%20Camp\"&gt;Bandit Camp&lt;/a&gt;.\n\"Random enemies potentially encountered:\"\nForest.\nThe \"Forest\" is only encountered when traveling to or from those areas of the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Forest\"&gt;Cloakwood Forest&lt;/a&gt;, which is not accessible until you've reached &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Four\"&gt;Chapter Four&lt;/a&gt;. This is the only random encounter area to contain a trap within its boundary.\n\"Random enemies potentially encountered:\"\nRoad.\nThe \"Road\" is only encountered when traveling to or from those areas along the main road between &lt;a href=\"Wyrm%27s%20Crossing\"&gt;Wyrm's Crossing&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt;.\n\"Random enemies potentially encountered:\""}
