{"id": "45898", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45898", "title": "Random encounter (BG)", "text": ""}
{"id": "41666", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41666", "title": "Random encounter (BG2)", "text": "There are several random encounters during \"\" and , which all use the same maps.\nEncounters.\nSome encounters occur only once and only if the game has not progressed passed a certain chapter. One of the outdoor encounters has four Trolls in addition to the random encounters.\nAs is normal with random encounters - the party is not allowed to sleep or save in these areas and once the map is exited the journey will continue, which can lead to another random encounter.\nRandom encounters do not always trigger, but when they do it is when traveling from one area on the world map to the next.\nSuna Seni.\n &lt;a href=\"Suna%20Seni\"&gt;Suna Seni&lt;/a&gt; is a bounty hunter working for an evil &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;wizard&lt;/a&gt; that is hunting the &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Bhaalspawn&lt;/a&gt; and party. Her &lt;a href=\"Slaver\"&gt;Slaver&lt;/a&gt; group includes a fighter named &lt;a href=\"Eldarin\"&gt;Eldarin&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Slaver%20Wizard%20%28Random%29\"&gt;wizard&lt;/a&gt;.\nShe is an old flame of &lt;a href=\"Valygar%20Corthala\"&gt;Valygar Corthala&lt;/a&gt; and when he's in the party there is some additional dialogue. Valygar tries to convince her not to honor the contract. This inevitably fails, but she does apologize for the inconvenience. Given Valygar's &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;alignment&lt;/a&gt; and Suna's association with slavers, it is not hard to see why the relationship failed.\nThis is the first encounter and you only get one chance to get it. The dialogue with Valygar is therefore obscure, as it takes at least three &lt;a href=\"world%20map\"&gt;world map&lt;/a&gt; journeys (&lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;slums&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20City%20Gates\"&gt;city gates&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt;) to have Valygar join the party.\nRenfeld and the Thugs.\n The second encounter with three &lt;a href=\"Thug%20%28Random%29\"&gt;Thugs&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Mage%20%28Random%29\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt; while traveling between &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's Districts&lt;/a&gt; leaves a &lt;a href=\"Renfeld%27s%20Body\"&gt;body&lt;/a&gt; behind; a man named &lt;a href=\"Renfeld\"&gt;Renfeld&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe short side quest to &lt;a href=\"Bring%20the%20Poisoned%20Man%20to%20his%20Friends\"&gt;bring the poisoned Renfeld to his friends&lt;/a&gt; also leads to another &lt;a href=\"Quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; involving &lt;a href=\"Xzar\"&gt;Xzar&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Find%20out%20What%20Happened%20to%20Montaron\"&gt;finding out what happened to his companion Montaron&lt;/a&gt;.\nSolving that, especially with &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; in the party, leads to yet more &lt;a href=\"quests\"&gt;quests&lt;/a&gt; involving the &lt;a href=\"Harpers\"&gt;Harpers&lt;/a&gt; and a whole lot of misdirection.\nGallery.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod and the \"Improved Random Encounters\" component make revisions to most BG1/BG2/BGEE encounters. From the Mod's Readme:\nThis component adds a little more variety and challenge to the \"You have been waylaid by enemies\" encounters. The main point of this component was not so much to make random encounters more difficult (though it does that too, to some extent) as to make them less repetitive - there are now about a dozen encounters, and the order in which they occur is somewhat randomized."}
{"id": "15398", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15398", "title": "Random treasure", "text": "In addition to fixed items, a great many creatures in game have random treasures in their inventory, those treasures can be stolen, and will drop upon the creatures' death.\nThe exact item(s) generated depends on which random treasure files the creature holds, each placeholder file will generate one item from their pool (row). \"RNDMAG01-03\" &amp; \"RNDTRE01-06\" files have a bell curve, thus more likely to get items in the middle columns, while the others are supposed to have an equal drop chance for all items in the row. If the \u201citems\u201d listed do not exist in-game, or are undroppable, then if chosen by chance, no items will be generated.\nThe item is determined when the creature is loaded once you enter an area for the first time. Only creatures that have respawned or are scripted spawns would randomly generate a different item when reloading an area.\nBG1.\nWith installed\nBG2.\nWith installed\nBG1EE.\nWith installed\nTreasure tables.\nPoor treasure.\n\"Poor\" random treasure can be obtained from &lt;a href=\"creature\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt;s and be found in &lt;a href=\"areas\"&gt;areas&lt;/a&gt; whenever the &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; with the &lt;a href=\"Items\"&gt;code&lt;/a&gt; codice_1 is involved.\nWhile the chances to get nothing are 27% in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" and its add-on \"\", this will not happen in other from the . In the first part, there's a 5%-chance to get a random &lt;a href=\"Scrolls\"&gt;scroll&lt;/a&gt; and a 12%-chance for 2\u202f&lt;a href=\"gp\"&gt;gp&lt;/a&gt;; in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\", the latter is reduced by 3%, which now yield a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20scrolls\"&gt;spell scroll&lt;/a&gt; for \"&lt;a href=\"Identify%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Identify&lt;/a&gt;\" instead of a random one, and the chances to obtain 1\u202fgp are increased by 5%.\nAverage treasure.\n\"Average\" random treasure can be obtained from &lt;a href=\"creature\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt;s and be found in &lt;a href=\"areas\"&gt;areas&lt;/a&gt; whenever the &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; with the &lt;a href=\"Items\"&gt;code&lt;/a&gt; codice_1 is involved.\nWhile the chances to get nothing are 9% in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" and its add-on \"\", this will not happen in other from the . In \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\", a find of 10\u202f&lt;a href=\"gp\"&gt;gp&lt;/a&gt; is replaced with a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20scrolls\"&gt;spell scroll&lt;/a&gt; for \"&lt;a href=\"Identify%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Identify&lt;/a&gt;\", and an &lt;a href=\"Onyx%20Ring\"&gt;Onyx Ring&lt;/a&gt; with a random &lt;a href=\"magical%20item\"&gt;magical item&lt;/a&gt; of low value.\nWell-off treasure.\n\"Well-off\" random treasure can be obtained from &lt;a href=\"creature\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt;s and be found in &lt;a href=\"areas\"&gt;areas&lt;/a&gt; whenever the &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; with the &lt;a href=\"Items\"&gt;code&lt;/a&gt; codice_1 is involved.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\", the &lt;a href=\"Star%20Diopside%20Gem\"&gt;Star Diopside Gem&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Studded%20Necklace%20with%20Ziose%20Gems\"&gt;Studded Necklace with Ziose Gems&lt;/a&gt; are replaced with a random &lt;a href=\"magical%20item\"&gt;magical item&lt;/a&gt; of low value, increasing chances for this by 3%.\nWealthy treasure.\n\"Wealthy\" random treasure can be obtained from &lt;a href=\"creature\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt;s and be found in &lt;a href=\"areas\"&gt;areas&lt;/a&gt; whenever the &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; with the &lt;a href=\"Items\"&gt;code&lt;/a&gt; codice_1 is involved.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\", the chances to find a random &lt;a href=\"magical%20item\"&gt;magical item&lt;/a&gt; of high value are risen by 1% and one of low value by 3%, while there's no chance to find a &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Opal%20Ring\"&gt;Fire Opal Ring&lt;/a&gt; or a &lt;a href=\"Pearl\"&gt;Pearl&lt;/a&gt;.\nRich treasure.\n\"Rich\" random treasure can be obtained from &lt;a href=\"creature\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt;s and be found in &lt;a href=\"areas\"&gt;areas&lt;/a&gt; whenever the &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; with the &lt;a href=\"Items\"&gt;code&lt;/a&gt; RNDTRE05 is involved. In the \"\", it may also be the result of three of the possible rolls during a &lt;a href=\"wild%20surge\"&gt;wild surge&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhile there's no &lt;a href=\"Diamond\"&gt;Diamond&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Emerald\"&gt;Emerald&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Moonbar%20Gem\"&gt;Moonbar Gem&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pearl%20Necklace\"&gt;Pearl Necklace&lt;/a&gt; anymore in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\", chances for a random &lt;a href=\"magical%20item\"&gt;magical item&lt;/a&gt; of low value are risen by 10% and for one of high value by 4%.\nLow-value magical treasure.\n&lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;Magical&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"enchanted%20item\"&gt;enchanted item&lt;/a&gt;s of low value may be gained whenever random &lt;a href=\"%23Average%20treasure\"&gt;average&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"%23Well-off%20treasure\"&gt;well-off&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"%23Wealthy%20treasure\"&gt;wealthy&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"%23Rich%20treasure\"&gt;rich treasure&lt;/a&gt; is found, i.e. obtained from &lt;a href=\"creature\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt;s or found in &lt;a href=\"areas\"&gt;areas&lt;/a&gt;, or \u2013 in the \"\" \u2013 as a result of three of the possible rolls during a &lt;a href=\"wild%20surge\"&gt;wild surge&lt;/a&gt;. The better the random treasure, the better the chances for magical treasure, which go up to 14% if rich treasure is found in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nWhile there's only one &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20of%20Dispelling\"&gt;Arrow of Dispelling&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Bolt%20of%20Polymorphing\"&gt;Bolt of Polymorphing&lt;/a&gt;, +1 &lt;a href=\"ammunition\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; always nets five pieces, opposed to only three for +2 ammunition. Arrows of Dispelling, Bolts of Polymorphing and &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20%2B2\"&gt;arrows&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bolt%20%2B2\"&gt;bolts&lt;/a&gt; +2 are replaced with random equipment of low and medium value in the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20series\"&gt;series's&lt;/a&gt; second part.\nHigh-value magical treasure.\n&lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;Magical&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"enchanted%20item\"&gt;enchanted item&lt;/a&gt;s of high value may be gained whenever random &lt;a href=\"%23Wealthy%20treasure\"&gt;wealthy&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"%23Rich%20treasure\"&gt;rich treasure&lt;/a&gt; is found, i.e. obtained from &lt;a href=\"creature\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt;s or found in &lt;a href=\"areas\"&gt;areas&lt;/a&gt;, or \u2013 in the \"\" \u2013 as a result of three of the possible rolls during a &lt;a href=\"wild%20surge\"&gt;wild surge&lt;/a&gt;. The chances for magical treasure go up to 6% if rich treasure is found in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\".\n&lt;a href=\"Wands\"&gt;Wands&lt;/a&gt; will have ten charges. However, these, together with an &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20of%20Fire\"&gt;Arrow of Fire&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Heroism\"&gt;Potion of Heroism&lt;/a&gt; and the ones for \"giant &lt;a href=\"strength\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt;\" are replaced with random equipment of all values in the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20series\"&gt;series's&lt;/a&gt; second part.\nMagical \"poop\".\nIntroduced with the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" add-on ', though not used in the successor \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\", random &lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"enchanted\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt; \"poop\" becomes only available in ', and only during a single conversation and under certain conditions: as possible reward for the &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Good%20Druids\"&gt;The Good Druids&lt;/a&gt;\". This is also the only opportunity to obtain a random fourth level &lt;a href=\"Scrolls\"&gt;scroll&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Lightning\"&gt;Wand of Lightning&lt;/a&gt; comes with four charges, and there are four &lt;a href=\"Bolts%20of%20Biting\"&gt;Bolts of Biting&lt;/a&gt; and two &lt;a href=\"Arrows%20of%20Ice\"&gt;Arrows of Ice&lt;/a&gt; possible.\n1st-level scrolls.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20scrolls\"&gt;Spell scrolls&lt;/a&gt; for may be gained whenever random &lt;a href=\"%23Poor%20treasure\"&gt;poor&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"%23Average%20treasure\"&gt;average&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"%23Well-off%20treasure\"&gt;well-off&lt;/a&gt; treasure or that of a &lt;a href=\"%23Low-value%20magical%20treasure\"&gt;magical kind with low value&lt;/a&gt; is found, i.e. obtained from &lt;a href=\"creature\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt;s, found in &lt;a href=\"areas\"&gt;areas&lt;/a&gt; or \u2013 in the \"\" \u2013 as a result of three of the possible rolls during a &lt;a href=\"wild%20surge\"&gt;wild surge&lt;/a&gt;. In \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\", one out of four of the possible results is replaced with a scroll for higher .\nExcept for duplicate entries, the chances for each scroll are equal.\n2nd-level scrolls.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20scrolls\"&gt;Spell scrolls&lt;/a&gt; for may be gained whenever random &lt;a href=\"%23Wealthy%20treasure\"&gt;wealthy treasure&lt;/a&gt; or that of a &lt;a href=\"%23Low-value%20magical%20treasure\"&gt;magical kind with low value&lt;/a&gt; is found, i.e. obtained from &lt;a href=\"creature\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt;s, found in &lt;a href=\"areas\"&gt;areas&lt;/a&gt; or \u2013 in the ' \u2013 as a result of three of the possible rolls during a &lt;a href=\"wild%20surge\"&gt;wild surge&lt;/a&gt;. Due to a &lt;a href=\"%23SCRL88\"&gt;bug&lt;/a&gt;, there's a chance of 5% to get nothing in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" and its add-on ', which is fixed in the '. In all three , there's also a chance of 5% to find a &lt;a href=\"Clue%20in%20library\"&gt;certain letter&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 rather than a spell scroll \u2013 that's impossible to obtain otherwise; if its add-on ' is installed on top of the \"Enhanced Edition\", this is replaced with a true spell scroll, also for the main campaign. In \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\", all possible results are replaced with scrolls for higher .\nExcept for duplicate entries, the chances for each scroll are equal.\n3rd-level scrolls.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20scrolls\"&gt;Spell scrolls&lt;/a&gt; for may be gained whenever random &lt;a href=\"%23Rich%20treasure\"&gt;rich treasure&lt;/a&gt; or that of a &lt;a href=\"%23High-value%20magical%20treasure\"&gt;magical kind with high value&lt;/a&gt; is found, i.e. obtained from &lt;a href=\"creature\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt;s, found in &lt;a href=\"areas\"&gt;areas&lt;/a&gt; or \u2013 in the ' \u2013 as a result of three of the possible rolls during a &lt;a href=\"wild%20surge\"&gt;wild surge&lt;/a&gt;. In ', it may also be the result for &lt;a href=\"%23Magical%20%22poop%22\"&gt;magical \"poop\"&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 a possible reward for the &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Good%20Druids\"&gt;The Good Druids&lt;/a&gt;\". Due to a &lt;a href=\"%23SCRL1J\"&gt;bug&lt;/a&gt;, there's a chance of 5% to get nothing in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" and its add-on ', which will not happen in other from the . The very rare scroll for \"&lt;a href=\"Wraithform\"&gt;Wraithform&lt;/a&gt;\" can be obtained as random treasure only in the original base game; it is replaced with a scroll for \"&lt;a href=\"Dire%20Charm\"&gt;Dire Charm&lt;/a&gt;\" with the installation of the original add-on \"Tales of the Sword Coast\", in complete editions and in the \"Enhanced Edition\" campaigns, making it unobtainable at all in the '. In \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\", all possible results are exchanged for scrolls for higher .\nExcept for duplicate entries, the chances for each scroll are equal.\nCut random treasure.\n\"Tales of the Sword Coast\".\nWith the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" add-on \"\", an additional random treasure table is added to the base , named codice_1, and remains throughout the . It is a copy of codice_1 in the series' first part, and is changed to mirror codice_1 for the second part. However, it is not referenced in any of the games.\nAlso, a line \u2013 which is not carried over into the \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\" file \u2013 is added to the codice_8 table, but remains unused in the original game and the ', until one single conversation refers to it during the ' campaign; see &lt;a href=\"%23%23Magical%20%22poop%22\"&gt;magical \"poop\"&lt;/a&gt;.\n\"Siege of Dragonspear\".\n' adds two random treasure &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt;s by the &lt;a href=\"Items\"&gt;code&lt;/a&gt; codice_9 and codice_10 to the game files which could have been used in ways similar to the others: found e.g. on &lt;a href=\"creature\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt;s or in &lt;a href=\"areas\"&gt;areas&lt;/a&gt;, or being obtained via dialogues or as a reward for &lt;a href=\"quests\"&gt;quests&lt;/a&gt;. The add-on for ' also expands the according . Both items, however, are not referenced in-game. In addition, if the new lines in codice_1 were intended to determine the treasure for one or both of these new items, they would not work, and codice_9 wouldn't yield anything if it was used by the game; the treasure for codice_10 is defined correctly in codice_1.\nThe random results from these two new lines in the table only hold certain amounts of &lt;a href=\"gold%20piece\"&gt;gold piece&lt;/a&gt;s, ranging from to , with an average of as treasure.\nIf it would appear in-game or be referenced by any or dialogue, codice_10 would yield one out of four pieces of &lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; jewelry, with equal chances for each of them."}
