{"id": "7203", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7203", "title": "Ras, The Dancing Blade", "text": "Ras, The Dancing Blade or simply Ras, is an enchanted longsword +2 which can attack on its own for 4 rounds. The weapon has a speed factor of 3, weighs 3 lbs and it offers the wearer a &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus of -2 and it deals 1d8+2 slashing damage. This item appears in and . It can be bought in &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Trademeet&lt;/a&gt; after finishing the &lt;a href=\"Dealing%20with%20the%20Trademeet%20genies\"&gt;Dealing with the Trademeet genies&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nGameplay.\nAs a creature Ras is similar to the &lt;a href=\"Mordenkainen%27s%20Sword%20%28creature%29\"&gt;Mordenkainen's Sword&lt;/a&gt;. Notable differences are: slightly worse ThAC0 (12 vs 10), a lot less damage (Ras wields \"itself\" so its enchantment is +2 and damage 1d8+2) and no it has no &lt;a href=\"Greenstone%20Amulet\"&gt;Greenstone Amulet&lt;/a&gt;.\nOn the plus side, unlike Mordenkainen's Sword, Ras has 100% resistance to magic and is equipped with &lt;a href=\"MINHP1.ITM\"&gt;MINHP1.ITM&lt;/a&gt; which means that it is immune to just about every status effect in the game {despite lacking the Greenstone Amulet) and the only way to destroy it is either &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; or stat drain - the latter only in vanilla BG2 as MINHP1.ITM prevents death from stat drain in Enhanced Edition. In fact, the only damage that can affect Ras, is Magical Energy (like a Magic Missile or &lt;a href=\"The%20Victor\"&gt;The Victor&lt;/a&gt; produces), and even if it is damaged by magical energy, the MINHP1.ITM will save it from destruction from that damage."}
