{"id": "24255", "revid": "52857324", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24255", "title": "Rasaad's Journey", "text": "Rasaad's Journey is &lt;a href=\"Rasaad%20yn%20Bashir\"&gt;his&lt;/a&gt; companion quest in .\nWalkthrough.\nBelow is a walkthrough highlighting key points of &lt;a href=\"Rasaad%27s%20Journey\"&gt;Rasaad's Journey&lt;/a&gt;. This is an abbreviated breakdown, and leaves out minor details, some dialogue options and other variable plot elements with only minor repercussions.\nShadows of Amn.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20City%20Gates\"&gt;City Gates&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter &lt;a href=\"Rasaad%20yn%20Bashir%23Recruitment%203\"&gt;recruiting&lt;/a&gt; Rasaad in &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Trademeet&lt;/a&gt;, travel with him to the City Gates of Athkatla (AR0020), the &lt;a href=\"Cloaked%20Figure\"&gt;Cloaked Figure&lt;/a&gt; will appear and speak to you, allowing a few options:\n&lt;a href=\"Abandoned%20Amphitheater\"&gt;Abandoned Amphitheater&lt;/a&gt;.\nTraveling to the secret Abandoned Ampitheater on your World Map has the party entering a new area, with a meandering forest pathway ahead of you. Continue north along the forest path and you'll see a human male figure identified as &lt;a href=\"Geld%20Quickblade\"&gt;Geld Quickblade&lt;/a&gt; (x=1260, y=2330), who demands compensation for the information he has gathered of the scouted route ahead. He demands , which you may bargain down to . If you don\u2019t pay him,\u00a0four large traps (x=800, y=1100) (x=900, y=1050) (x=1000, y=1000) (x=1000, y=900) will appear on the forest pathway further to the north. Beyond the traps several hundred feet away, Geld will confront the party, where he has prepared an ambush. He has command of a pack of wolves that enter the map at coordinates (x=2240, y=1970). You must defend yourself from attack.\nFurther along, and emerging from the forest path, you'll find the Abandoned Amphitheater where various monks gather in hope to join the so called \"Twofold Faith\", which can also be referred to as the \"Twofold Trust\" and is generally associated with members who are titled as a \"Heretic\". It might be confusing as the titles and dialogue aren't always consistent, just like real life.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Amphitheater%20Guard\"&gt;Amphitheater Guard&lt;/a&gt; will speak to you and demand a to know the party's purpose. Speak with &lt;a href=\"Fenuku\"&gt;Fenuku&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Kelner\"&gt;Kehlner&lt;/a&gt; until your journal updates. When ready, head to where &lt;a href=\"Hammerhelm\"&gt;Hammerhelm&lt;/a&gt; is (x=4070, y=750), but his speech will only trigger if you have Rasaad in your party. Several options for the various dialogue choices are:\nLearn the temple's location, either from Hammerhelm himself through specific dialogue options, or by reading the &lt;a href=\"Note\"&gt;Note&lt;/a&gt; looted (or pickpocketed) from his possession (everyone gets 3000XP). If Viconia is in your party, she will respond strongly to the heresy against Shar and will question your choices throughout the scenes.\u00a0\nYou're not done with this area yet, head south on the continuing forest pathway, and eventually spot a group of adventurers calling themselves the \"&lt;a href=\"Vagrant%20Blades\"&gt;Vagrant Blades&lt;/a&gt;\", they're debating who's the rightful owner of the &lt;a href=\"Belt%20of%20Minor%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Belt of Minor Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, a treasure they just found, and your opinions regarding the belt influence the encounter:\u00a0\nThe Wilderness.\nThe next time you travel between areas on the World Map, you\u2019ll encounter the &lt;a href=\"Tears%20of%20Sel%C3%BBne\"&gt;Tears of Sel\u00fbne&lt;/a&gt; in a rainy wilderness clearing. A somewhat complicated dialogue exchange will be presented to the party, you may wind up with the following results:\n&lt;a href=\"Heretic%20Temple\"&gt;Heretic Temple&lt;/a&gt;.\nExterior.\nSouth down the road from where you arrive\u00a0is &lt;a href=\"Herath\"&gt;Herath&lt;/a&gt;, a distressed and wounded Monk\u00a0who has failed initiation in the Heretic Temple.\u00a0If Rasaad is in party, he\u2019ll attempt to help her; you\u00a0may:\nIf Rasaad is not in the party, Herath will wait indefinitely at the entrance of the map until Rasaad is in the party. A reminder - You should have Rasaad in your party to do this questline, as the content and rewards are tilted significantly toward him in your group. Rasaad not in your party will significantly reduce the experience gain and limit dialogue and other options for you.\nFurther south you may encounter a pack of wolves. After defeating them, go further south and observe a Monk standing at the entrance to a bridge or causeway leading to the Heretic Temple proper. The Monk is Heretic Guard who will challenge the party when close enough, and if visible to him.\u00a0You may:\nBy the main Heretic temple door\u00a0another Heretic Guard will challenge and question your purpose;\u00a0you may:\nStill outside, observe a cut-scene featuring &lt;a href=\"Heretic%20Blynnyk\"&gt;Heretic Blynnyk&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Sun%20Soul%20Horvat\"&gt;Sun Soul Horvat&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Heretic%20Coren\"&gt;Heretic Coren&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sun%20Soul%20Lara\"&gt;Sun Soul Lara&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0This scene shows a training and testing-evaluation event with Monks versus beasts in unarmed combat. Next to them is &lt;a href=\"Jolstead\"&gt;Jolstead&lt;/a&gt;, the Beastmaster who's involved in the &lt;a href=\"Where%27s%20Wilson%3F\"&gt;Where's Wilson?&lt;/a&gt; quest.\u00a0 \"Talk\" to the caged bear &lt;a href=\"Wilson\"&gt;Wilson&lt;/a&gt;, who you may free for a 5000 XP reward. You may also:\nContinue east you\u2019ll encounter three bound Sun Soul Monks tethered and staked to the ground, they say they\u2019re undergoing a \u201ctrial\u201d of some sort, a trial of pain. This is apparently part of the heretic initiation process. There are several options here:\n&lt;a href=\"Lemzenn\"&gt;Lemzenn&lt;/a&gt;, is a mysterious figure lurking in the tall grass to the east of the slope. He is immune to charm, so follow the dialog tree 3,4,3,2,1,1 to let him reveal himself as a Dark Moon Monk spy (each party member gets 1000 XP). If you wish, kill him afterwards (4000 XP). All other options either send him away or directly force him to turn hostile.\nHeretic Temple Interior.\nFirst off, it is recommended that Rasaad be in your party. If he isn't, many quest options and dialogue trees will not be present. You could limit your experience gains and reduce the playability of the scenario. There may be bugs and glitches introduced as well. You can always release Rasaad later if you wish to, right after the Heretic Temple quest. In short, it is better to have Rasaad for this quest sequence, than not. \nOnce Inside the &lt;a href=\"Heretic%20Temple%20Interior\"&gt;Heretic Temple Interior&lt;/a&gt;, send at least one party member forward near the center of the area. This will trigger the opening speech from &lt;a href=\"Collus%20Darathon\"&gt;Collus Darathon&lt;/a&gt;. There are numerous statements, potential replies, questions and talk that will form the direction of what will transpire from this quest. It could end in immediate hostility, or you may choose to further infiltrate and learn the inner workings of the Heretic \"Two-Fold Trust\". Several unique and useful items can be gained for the party if you participate and complete the four tests of initiation. It is recommended that you take this path for maximum reward and access the available content. Initiation is the longer and much more rewarding path to take. There are basically two results of the path you take. The first is open hostility from the Heretics, and the second is the Initiation course.\nHostility Path: You'll make\u00a0all non-party Heretic Temple occupants hostile. Blood will be shed, and eventually after a certain point the &lt;a href=\"Master%20of%20Combat\"&gt;Master of Combat&lt;/a&gt; will intercede and implore you to cease the pointless fighting and to stop the madness. You may ignore him and continue the fight. Furthert on as the battle continues, a temple scout will enter the fray, and announce that the followers of Shar, the Sharran's, are nearly at the temple gates and intend to destroy the Heretic Temple and all involved (including your party). More dialogue and choices follow. The most rewarding choice is to choose to fight the Sharrans with the remaining Heretic Two-Fold members. The master of Combat will exit the temple (to see what is going on) outside the temple. You may follow when you are ready. You could buff, or even rest and continue if you wish. In the end you will have to leave the temple anyway.\nInitiation Path: If you choose\u00a0initiation, there are four trials, or tests to complete. Your main character will be the only person allowed in each testing chamber. A brief description of each is as follows:\nThe &lt;a href=\"Master%20of%20Combat\"&gt;Master of Combat&lt;/a&gt; appears after the trials. Go speak with him near the center of the temple to advance the quest.\nAfter the fourth trial, \nNormally the Master will lead the troops against the siege, but if you can manage to convince Rasaad to stand out, he\u2019ll be in charge of the heretic monks. The dialogue with Collus Darathon will also be slightly different (everyone gets 10000 XP for completing this quest section).\nWhen ready, exit the temple to face the Sharrans.\nBattle with the Sharrans.\nThere are a significant number of allies and enemies present.\u00a0If you do not have Rasaad in the party, the pre-battle chatter will be very short. If Rasaad is in the party, it will be longer and you will discover the plot, including that Alorgoth is really Collus\u00a0Darathon.\nBattle Aftermath.\nIf the Master of Combat lives, there will be extra dialogue from him. Of the dialogue options presented, you may choose option 3 indicating \"temporary setback\" which can lead to Rasaad rebuilding and leading the Trust (likely if he led the battle). He will leave the party for the remaining SoA, transferring to you his inventory items (even those exclusive to him). Don't forget to check the bodies for their loot and treasures.\nAfterwards, you can go back inside and talk to the surviving monks or depart the Map and press on with your campaign. This ends the Rasaad Journey portion in SoA. If you have Rasaad in your party for Throne of Bhaal, there is further plot to explore.\nThrone of Bhaal.\nThis part of the quest begins much with a good old fashioned ambush as you traverse the &lt;a href=\"World%20Map\"&gt;world map&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0 Sharran assassins will attack you; after they are dead, a note on one of them adds Deepstone Clanhold to your map, which is where the rest of the quest takes place. &lt;a href=\"Viconia%20DeVir\"&gt;Viconia&lt;/a&gt; will leave party permanently if you would like to proceed this quest.\nThe dwarven Deepstone clan has had its mines and fort taken over by &lt;a href=\"Alorgoth\"&gt;Alorgoth&lt;/a&gt; and his Sharran followers.\u00a0 Upon entering the map, a dwarf named Lemp Coldhearth will ask you what your business here is.\u00a0 If you indicate to him that you are an enemy of the Sharrans, he will take you to a camp to speak with Meems Dugdeep, who asks you to free some of her fellow dwarves from their Sharran captors in the northeast part of the map.\nThere are three ways to get into the fort from here: You can rescue the captive dwarves and take one of them up on his offer to use a downstream entrance; you can use Meems' idea of a tunnel; or you can simply barge through the front gate.\u00a0\nOnce inside the mines be sure to pick up the dwarf named Bentaxe for a gold reward at the end of the quest.\u00a0 No matter which method of entry you use, Alorgoth will be waiting on the bottom floor of the fort, in the mine area.\nUnfortunately, as soon as he spots you, he flees to the Shadow Plane along with his subordinate &lt;a href=\"Yxtrazzal\"&gt;Yxtrazzal&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0 Follow him through the portal he creates, and corner him in the southern part of the map.\u00a0 Undaunted, Algoroth reveals Yxtrazzal to be a Shadow Dragon, and both attack, along with several Shadow Creatures.\u00a0 During this battle, Alorgoth cannot be killed, so focus your attacks on Yxtrazzal and the Shadow Creatures instead.\nOnce Yxtrazzal is dead, she drops an item called the &lt;a href=\"Wheel%20of%20Obliteration\"&gt;Wheel of Obliteration&lt;/a&gt;, and the Shadow Plane begins to deteriorate.\u00a0 You must return to the crystals near where you appeared in the Shadow Plane and use the Wheel of Obliteration (via quick item slot) to create a new portal home.\u00a0 Before you enter this portal, Alorgoth appears, only to fall at the hands of many Shadow Creatures.\u00a0 The Wheel is destroyed when you step through the portal.\nUpon returning to the mine, a dwarf named Bentaxe will reward you with 7,500 gold.\u00a0 Finally, Rasaad declares his revenge to be complete at long last, which ends the quest and grants 20,000 XP.\nOn your way back outside make sure to check the ground floor of Deepstone again. If you have not cleared the place before now all the enemies will be dead and you can loot their bodies. Also, in the northeast corner in Alorgoth's Quarters you can find three very interesting unique items - &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20the%20Dark%20Moon\"&gt;Cloak of the Dark Moon&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Headband%20of%20the%20Devout\"&gt;Headband of the Devout&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Night%20Walkers\"&gt;Night Walkers&lt;/a&gt;."}
