{"id": "5124", "revid": "270135", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5124", "title": "Rasaad yn Bashir", "text": "Rasaad yn Bashir is a lawful good human &lt;a href=\"Monk%23Sun%20Soul%20Monk%20.28EE%20only.29\"&gt;sun soul monk&lt;/a&gt; and a potential &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt; in \nRecruitment.\nRasaad is available from &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Two\"&gt;Chapter Two&lt;/a&gt;. Look for him just outside the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Inn\"&gt;Nashkel Inn&lt;/a&gt;, talk to him and invite him to join. Choosing an option to pay is the only way to trigger the cutscene when he knocks the pretentious Commoner unconscious, though you won't get the gold back, even when recruiting him.\nGameplay.\nRasaad is equipped with &lt;a href=\"Moonlight%20Walkers\"&gt;Moonlight Walkers&lt;/a&gt; when he joins the party. Those boots provide him with +2 AC and can only be used by him.\n\nRecruitment.\nThough Rasaad can be spoken with during your time in Baldur's Gate in , he will not join you due to wanting to investigate the disappearance of several servants of &lt;a href=\"Sel%C3%BBne\"&gt;Sel\u00fbne&lt;/a&gt;.\nRasaad becomes available from , where he can be found at &lt;a href=\"Coast%20Way%20Forest\"&gt;Coast Way Forest&lt;/a&gt; just south of your starting zone. This time he decides to join your march to the &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle&lt;/a&gt; to fight &lt;a href=\"Caelar%20Argent\"&gt;Caelar Argent&lt;/a&gt;'s crusade.\n\nRecruitment.\nRasaad is available from &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt;. Travel to &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Trademeet&lt;/a&gt;, near the fountain at the center of town you'll witness a conflict between him and his fellow sun soul monks, walk away from the spot after the scene and he'll show up and talk to you.\nWhen dismissed, he can be found at various locations in Trademeet's town square, for example just south of the fountain or just east of it.\u00a0\nGameplay.\nRasaad is equipped with &lt;a href=\"Moonlight%20Walkers\"&gt;Moonlight Walkers&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Glimmering%20Bands\"&gt;Glimmering Bands&lt;/a&gt; when he joins the party. The boots provide him with -2 AC bonus and the gloves boost his &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; by -2, both can only be used by him. Being a &lt;a href=\"Monk%23Table%20for%20experience.2C%20hit%20points%20and%20proficiency%20points\"&gt;monk&lt;/a&gt;, Rasaad is a late bloomer, the &lt;a href=\"Celestial%20Fury\"&gt;Celestial Fury&lt;/a&gt; katana, with the ability to stun its opponents, is a good weapon choice for for him early on before he can stand up using his own fists, though the exact timing and weapon choices varies among players and their play styles.\nEquipping him with the &lt;a href=\"Ninjat%C5%8D%20of%20the%20Scarlet%20Brotherhood\"&gt;Scarlet Ninja-To&lt;/a&gt; in the offhand can be a good idea at the initial stages of Shadows of Amn. Come Throne of Bhaal, &lt;a href=\"Angurvadal\"&gt;Angurvadal&lt;/a&gt; can be used instead. In any case, the &lt;a href=\"Gauntlets%20of%20Crushing\"&gt;Gauntlets of Crushing&lt;/a&gt; are one of the best items for him.\nRasaad will not tolerate the party attacking &lt;a href=\"Adalon\"&gt;Adalon&lt;/a&gt; the Silver Dragon in her lair in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;. He will leave the party for good if that happens."}
