{"id": "12590", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12590", "title": "Fuernebol", "text": "Fuernebol was the youngest son of &lt;a href=\"Durlag%20Trollkiller\"&gt;Durlag Trollkiller&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Islanne\"&gt;Islanne&lt;/a&gt;. Like his older brother &lt;a href=\"Kiel%20the%20Legion%20Killer\"&gt;Kiel the Legion Killer&lt;/a&gt;, he was killed by &lt;a href=\"doppelganger\"&gt;doppelganger&lt;/a&gt;s that had infiltrated &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt; but, unlike Kiel, Fuernebol was not an accomplished warrior. He was too young and inexperienced to defend himself well and fell swiftly when the doppelgangers attacked.\nMultiple &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Doppelganger\"&gt;Greater Doppelganger&lt;/a&gt;s in Fuernebol's form can be found on &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28Labyrinth%20Level%20Two%29\"&gt;labyrinth level 2&lt;/a&gt; beneath Durlag's Tower and must be slain repeatedly by &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party just as Durlag was forced to do.\nInteractions.\nThe total number of Fuernebol's encountered is dependent upon the initial forms taken by the two randomly generated doppelgangers that are spawned when triggering silent traps located in certain places on this level. So it is possible to confront up to a total of four Fuernebol's.\nThrone Room.\nDoppelganger forms of Fuernebol and Islanne will enter the room during Durlag's lament for Kiel. Once he finishes with his dialogue, all three will cast spells; Durlag and Fuernebol will cast &lt;a href=\"Stinking%20Cloud\"&gt;Stinking Cloud&lt;/a&gt; and Islanne will cast &lt;a href=\"Cloudkill\"&gt;Cloudkill&lt;/a&gt;. They will then immediately shapeshift into their true greater doppelganger form, cast &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt;, and attack.\nBridge Room.\nThere are two of them located in the Bridge room, standing on seperate bridges, with Islanne between them on another bridge. They will first attack with their bow weapons while maintaining Fuernebol's form. But once they begin to receive damage, they will first shapeshift into Islanne's form, and then with additional damage taken, shapeshift into Kiel's form. However, if the initial damage received is great enough, they will shapeshift into Kiel's form, bypassing Islanne's form.\nRandomly Encountered.\nWhen the silent traps are triggered while exploring this level, two greater doppelgangers will spawn nearby, but out of sight. It is possible that one of the two will be in Fuernebol's form. Once fighting begins, he will cycle through the same form progression as described above when receiving damage.\nIf the greater doppelganger form of Fuernebol is killed fast enough, he will drop &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Mail\"&gt;Chain Mail&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Composite%20Longbow\"&gt;Composite Longbow&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Arrow\"&gt;Arrow&lt;/a&gt;s, and &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure%23RNDTRE05\"&gt;rich random treasure&lt;/a&gt;. If he shapeshifts and then is killed, he will drop the items of whatever shapeshifted form he's currently in."}
{"id": "30169", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30169", "title": "Fuernebol Wardstone", "text": "The Fuernebol Wardstone is an item found in Islanne's room located on &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28Labyrinth%20Level%20Two%29\"&gt;labyrinth level 2&lt;/a&gt; beneath &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt;. It is on a table on the left side of the bed. Adding it to your inventory or removing it from your inventory and back to the table will open or close Door 1.\n\"Caution: removing it from your inventory and putting it on the wrong table in this room will lead to a rather uncomfortable outcome.\""}
