{"id": "5506", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5506", "title": "Full Plate Mail +2", "text": "Full Plate Mail +2 is enchanted and it offers an armor class of -1 and the usual armor class against specific kinds of physical damage. It has a weight of 50 lbs, which means it's lighter than &lt;a href=\"Full%20Plate%20Armor\"&gt;Full Plate Armor&lt;/a&gt;, but heavier than &lt;a href=\"Full%20Plate%20Armor%20%2B1\"&gt;Full Plate Armor +1&lt;/a&gt;. It still requires 15 strength to wear it. This item appears in . It's dropped by &lt;a href=\"Gromnir%20Il-Khan\"&gt;Gromnir Il-Khan&lt;/a&gt; in Saradush and &lt;a href=\"Jamis%20Tombelthen\"&gt;Jamis Tombelthen&lt;/a&gt; in the Oasis.\nIt can also be obtained in as a possible one-time reward from the &lt;a href=\"Limited%20Wish\"&gt;Limited Wish&lt;/a&gt; spell. The value of that particular plate is only .\nBoth sets of armor include unlisted penalties of +1 THAC0 and -2 movement rating in the non-enhanced edition games.\nBugs.\nThere are two versions of Full Plate Mail +2, one of which is a special version available via Wish that doesn't require any lore to identify. Several creatures were using the special version, which has been swapped for the other Full Plate +2. This is identified and corrected in &lt;a href=\"The%20Enhanced%20Edition%20Fixpack%20%28EEFP%29\"&gt;The Enhanced Edition Fixpack (EEFP)&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "39499", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39499", "title": "Full Wineskin", "text": "The Full Wineskin is the full version of the &lt;a href=\"Empty%20Wineskin\"&gt;Empty Wineskin&lt;/a&gt; and is required in the &lt;a href=\"Morning%20Report%20%28quest%29\"&gt;Morning Report (quest)&lt;/a&gt;. The Empty Wineskin can be filled by interacting with the barrels adjacent to &lt;a href=\"Nan\"&gt;Nan&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pedro\"&gt;Pedro&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Exterior\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Exterior&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce you have the Full Wineskin and the &lt;a href=\"Morning%20Report\"&gt;Morning Report&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Deneld\"&gt;Deneld&lt;/a&gt;, speak with &lt;a href=\"Commander%20Dreon\"&gt;Commander Dreon&lt;/a&gt; who will take both items.\nUpon delivery of both items, return to Nan and Pedro to complete the quest."}
{"id": "2067", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2067", "title": "Fuller", "text": "Fuller is an officer of &lt;a href=\"The%20Candlekeep%20Watchers\"&gt;The Candlekeep Watchers&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt;. During the &lt;a href=\"Prologue\"&gt;Prologue&lt;/a&gt;, he can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Barracks\"&gt;barracks&lt;/a&gt;, complaining of a headache. He will ask &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"An%20Errand%20for%20Fuller\"&gt;fetch him&lt;/a&gt; a crossbow bolt. If Fuller's &lt;a href=\"reaction\"&gt;reaction&lt;/a&gt; to Gorion's Ward is greater than 14 (Neutral_Upper), he'll give you a &lt;a href=\"Dagger%20%2B1\"&gt;Dagger +1&lt;/a&gt; instead of 10 . It's also possible to pickpocket the enchanted dagger, but you can't get a second copy as a reward (he still mentions giving you a dagger he no longer has though).\nHe can also be of assistance during the quest for &lt;a href=\"Hull%27s%20Sword\"&gt;Hull's Sword&lt;/a&gt;, pointing Gorion's Ward to the location of the correct chest.\nDuring &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Six\"&gt;Chapter Six&lt;/a&gt; he is found inside the &lt;a href=\"Clinic\"&gt;Clinic&lt;/a&gt;, still friendly as ever, with that hint of military strictness always present. He'll be found one more time inside a small room on the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Catacombs%20Level%202\"&gt;second level&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Catacombs\"&gt;Candlekeep Catacombs&lt;/a&gt;, although this time he's really a doppelganger in disguise. After a brief dialogue, the doppelganger will transform and attack.\nDialogue.\nPrologue.\n\"Ugh, what a mead-filled night. That Hull is just too much. Poor sap had to go man the gate this morning, too. I don't know how he does it... What can I do for you, anyways?\"\nWhen you return with the bolts:&lt;br&gt;\nReaction \u2265 15\nReaction \u2264 14\nIf you speak to Fuller without the bolts:\n\"What, no bolts? Why they let Gorion bring kids like you into this place I'll never know.\"\nChapter Six.\n\"Well, I'll be! If that isn't someone with a tale to tell, I don't know who is. What have you been up to this past while?\"\nAny further conversation attempt:\n\"You probably have more important things to be doing right now. We'll catch up on old times later.\""}
{"id": "8106", "revid": "1476364", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8106", "title": "Fuller's Bolts", "text": ""}
{"id": "24083", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24083", "title": "Fungus", "text": "A Fungus is a type of eukaryotic organism that includes the mushrooms and toadstools along with such microorganisms as the yeasts and molds. They lack chlorophyll and are incapable of photosynthesis. They also lack a true stem, leaves, or roots and mainly derive their nutrients by slowly breaking down organic matter using digestive enzymes and absorbing the dissolved molecules. They are a primary source of decomposition in most ecological systems.\nMost ordinary kinds of fungus are harmless towards other living creatures; however there are some types of fungus that are semi-parasitic and prefer inhabiting and feeding on living creatures. Others have become sentient and ambulatory which has allowed them to better defend themselves against hostile creatures.\nOne of the most common types of fungus encountered throughout the games are the Myconids, also known as fungus ones or fungus folk, which are a somewhat intelligent race of fungus creatures.\n&lt;a href=\"Shrieker\"&gt;Shrieker's&lt;/a&gt; are a plant that resembles a fungi in appearance but, like all plants, are unable to move."}
{"id": "4511", "revid": "78773", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4511", "title": "Furret", "text": "Furret is a &lt;a href=\"halfling\"&gt;halfling&lt;/a&gt; 'merchant' (charlatan) in the &lt;a href=\"Ulcaster\"&gt;Ulcaster&lt;/a&gt; area. He wanders the north-western plateau, and tries to sell you a gem of true seeing for . You have the option to buy it or walk away. If you buy the gem, it turns out that it's just a plain &lt;a href=\"Turquoise%20Gem\"&gt;turquoise gem&lt;/a&gt; with no purpose except to sell at the store for gold. There is no &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt; penalty for killing Furret. The gem can be also pickpocketed from him.\nIf you pickpocket the gem of true seeing, Furret will still go through the motions of selling you the fake gem even though you will not be given another gem he will still take from you.\nDialogue.\n\"Wayfarers! Wait up a moment. I wish to have a word with you. You are adventurers, are you not?\"\nCharmed Dialogue.\n\"I'm a halfling trader who spent the last of my money on this worthless gem that i possess. The gem is cursed you see, and now I must find a way to get rid of it.\""}
