{"id": "8033", "revid": "78773", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8033", "title": "G'axir the Seer", "text": "G'axir the Seer is a patron in the &lt;a href=\"Blade%20and%20Stars\"&gt;Blade and Stars&lt;/a&gt; which is located in the &lt;a href=\"Southeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;southeast&lt;/a&gt; section of the city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate.&lt;/a&gt;\nWhen spoken to, he will provide some foreshadowing of your heritage and terrible future before demanding that you procure a &lt;a href=\"Sphene%20Gem\"&gt;sphene gem&lt;/a&gt; for him from the &lt;a href=\"basilisk\"&gt;basilisk&lt;/a&gt; located in a &lt;a href=\"Warehouses%20%28south%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23AR1207\"&gt;warehouse&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"South%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;South Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. He does not say why he wants one and offers no reward, but expects to get it nonetheless. After speaking to him, the quest G'axir the Seer is added to the &lt;a href=\"Journal\"&gt;Journal&lt;/a&gt;. Upon receiving the sphene gem, he provides more foreshadowing and . This exchange will take a full stack of sphene gems if available, so be sure to isolate one in your inventory (bags are safe).\nSpellbook.\nG'axir has the following spells in his spellbook:\nSide quests.\n&lt;a href=\"G%27axir%20the%20Seer%20%28quest%29\"&gt;G'axir the Seer&lt;/a&gt;.\nG'axir the Seer requests that &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party bring him a sphene gem."}
{"id": "11315", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11315", "title": "G'axir the Seer (quest)", "text": "&lt;a href=\"G%27axir%20the%20Seer\"&gt;G'axir&lt;/a&gt; would like you to bring him a &lt;a href=\"Sphene%20Gem\"&gt;Sphene Gem&lt;/a&gt; for what purpose he will not say.\nYou acquire this quest by speaking to &lt;a href=\"G%27axir%20the%20Seer\"&gt;G'axir the Seer&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Blade%20and%20Stars\"&gt;Blade and Stars&lt;/a&gt; tavern in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. After providing some foreshadowing of your heritage and terrible fate he tells you that he wants you to bring him a &lt;a href=\"Sphene%20Gem\"&gt;Sphene Gem&lt;/a&gt; and suggests getting one from the &lt;a href=\"Basilisk\"&gt;Greater Basilisk&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. There are many &lt;a href=\"Sphene%20Gem\"&gt;Sphene Gem&lt;/a&gt;s in the game but, while any of them will do, taking the one from the &lt;a href=\"Basilisk\"&gt;Basilisk&lt;/a&gt; is convenient. This &lt;a href=\"Basilisk\"&gt;Basilisk&lt;/a&gt; is also the target of the &lt;a href=\"Basilisk%20on%20the%20Loose\"&gt;Basilisk on the Loose&lt;/a&gt; quest. It is located in the northern warehouse in &lt;a href=\"south%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;south Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. \nKilling the Basilisk.\nTo kill the &lt;a href=\"Basilisk\"&gt;Basilisk&lt;/a&gt; you can use\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Mirrored%20Eyes\"&gt;Potion of Mirrored Eyes&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Petrification\"&gt;Protection From Petrification&lt;/a&gt;, or items that provide a bonus to save vs petrification rolls, like\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Adoy%27s%20Belt\"&gt;Adoy's Belt&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0&lt;a href=\"The%20Claw%20of%20Kazgaroth\"&gt;The Claw of Kazgaroth&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0or protection\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20the%20Princes\"&gt;Ring&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Protection%20%2B1\"&gt;Cloak&lt;/a&gt;. It may be best to put put protective spells and items on one &lt;a href=\"Fighter\"&gt;Fighter&lt;/a&gt; who will face the &lt;a href=\"Basilisk\"&gt;Basilisk&lt;/a&gt; in close combat and have other party members attack with ranged weapons to minimize the risk of petrification. Once it is dead you can loot the &lt;a href=\"Sphene%20Gem\"&gt;Sphene Gem&lt;/a&gt; from its body.\nCompletion.\nReturn to &lt;a href=\"G%27axir%20the%20Seer\"&gt;G'axir&lt;/a&gt; with the &lt;a href=\"Sphene%20Gem\"&gt;Sphene Gem&lt;/a&gt; for a reward of 1000 Exp and some more mystic foreshadowing but no monetary or reputation gain."}
