{"id": "52047", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52047", "title": "GOLBRA.ITM", "text": "GOLBRA.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by &lt;a href=\"Brain%20Golem\"&gt;Brain Golem&lt;/a&gt; creatures.\nIt is considered an enchanted item +4 and applies 2d12 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt; (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a range of one foot, and speed factor of 0.\nThe weapon provides the golem with a number of status effect and damage resistance immunities. \nIn many cases these are redundant to similar ones already assigned to the actual creature file code sectors (basically the same things again). \nThe item provides the following immunities: &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Creature\"&gt;Charm Creature&lt;/a&gt; effects, &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Morale\"&gt;Morale&lt;/a&gt; break, &lt;a href=\"Paralyze\"&gt;Paralyze&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hold%20creature%202\"&gt;Hold creature 2&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Sleep%20%28Status%20Effect%29\"&gt;Sleep (Status Effect)&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Unconscious\"&gt;Unconscious&lt;/a&gt; status effect."}
{"id": "50444", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50444", "title": "GOLCLA.ITM", "text": "GOLCLA.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by &lt;a href=\"Clay%20Golem\"&gt;Clay Golem&lt;/a&gt; creatures.\nIt is considered an enchanted item and deals 3d10 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt; (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a range of one foot, and speed factor of 0.\nIt has no animation assigned and other effects. This quick slot weapon is the actual damage dealer when a Clay Golem strikes with a fist.\nIn addition to the combat aspects of this item, it also provides the creature with the following immunities:\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises the typical Clay Golem melee weapon &lt;a href=\"GOLCLA.ITM\"&gt;GOLCLA.ITM&lt;/a&gt;. When the golem hits a target, it applies an instant \"Cursed Wound\" effect (DW#CURSE.SPL).\nThe golem hit inflicts its rolled damage, but that damage is now Cursed. \nUpon a hit, a lighting animation will play over the target, the combat log will show a text display \"\"Cursed\" and another one that says \"Unable to Heal\"\". This means that any damage incurred by this weapon cannot be healed by normal means (such as a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Healing&lt;/a&gt;, or a &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Light%20Wounds%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Cure Light Wounds (spell)&lt;/a&gt;. However, a &lt;a href=\"Regeneration\"&gt;Regeneration&lt;/a&gt; effect can heal this damage.\nIn order to get rid of the \"curse\", you need to apply a &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Curse\"&gt;Remove Curse&lt;/a&gt; spell or similar. Otherwise, this cursed wound is permanent. It also has no saving throw to negate, ignores magic resistance, cannot be dispelled, and has &lt;a href=\"power%20level\"&gt;power level&lt;/a&gt; 0 (so will bypass spell protections).\nThe mod revises the golem's fist attack to provide a range of 2, instead of the unmodified creatures range of 1. This helps regulate the unfair and illogical golem \"choke point\" reach tactic, as a golem can easily strike with the same reach as a humanoid with a staff or spear."}
{"id": "51095", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51095", "title": "GOLFLE.ITM", "text": "GOLFLE.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by &lt;a href=\"Flesh%20Golem\"&gt;Flesh Golem&lt;/a&gt;s and by the &lt;a href=\"Lesser%20Clay%20Golem\"&gt;Lesser Clay Golem&lt;/a&gt;s found in .\nIt is considered an enchanted +3 item and deals 2d8 damage (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a range of one foot, and speed factor of 0.\nIt has no animation assigned and other effects. This quick slot weapon is the actual damage dealer when a Flesh Golem strikes with a fist.\nThe item also provides the flesh golem with the following immunities:\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod and the installation of the \"AI Enhancement's\" component revises this item to provide a range of 2, instead of the unmodified creatures range of 1. This is to implement the Improved Golems (BG2, BG2EE, BGT/EET) component. All golems have a reach of at least 2 with this SCS component. This helps regulate the unfair and illogical golem \"choke point\" reach tactic, as a golem can easily strike with the same reach as a humanoid with a staff or spear."}
{"id": "50447", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50447", "title": "GOLIRO.ITM", "text": "GOLIRO.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Golem\"&gt;Iron Golem&lt;/a&gt; creatures. It's also used by the &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Golem%20%28Guardian%20of%20Ice%29\"&gt;Ice Golem (Guardian of Ice)&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is considered an enchanted item and deals 4d10 damage (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a range of two feet, and speed factor of 0.\nIt has no animation assigned and does provide immunity to &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt; for the golem. This quick slot weapon is the actual damage dealer when an Iron Golem strikes with a fist."}
{"id": "56169", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56169", "title": "GOLMAG01.ITM", "text": "The GOLMAG01 is an equipped item for the &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Golem\"&gt;Magic Golem&lt;/a&gt; as their only attack weapon. It isn't droppable.\nEffects.\nThe weapon is a magical and enchanted +3 item that launches a projectile that has a range of 40 feet.\nThe projectile is the same one used by a &lt;a href=\"Beholder\"&gt;Beholder&lt;/a&gt; and looks the same as the Beholder blast. It can be reflected by the &lt;a href=\"Shield%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;Shield of Balduran&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe projectile is aimed at a single creature and has speed factor of 0.\nIf the projectile strikes an opponent, it deals 3d10 &lt;a href=\"Missile%20damage\"&gt;Missile damage&lt;/a&gt;, augmented by the golem's &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; attribute.\nAny hit on a target will remove one charge from an item in a quick slot or if equipped/worn.\nFor example, a wand will lose a charge, and items that have charges (such as the &lt;a href=\"Helm%20of%20Brilliance\"&gt;Helm of Brilliance&lt;/a&gt;, or the &lt;a href=\"Staff%20of%20Power\"&gt;Staff of Power&lt;/a&gt;) will be affected.\nItems in the backpack inventory or in a container (like gem bag or bag of holding) won't be discharged.\nIf the target has memorized Wizard spells, then one spell will be un-memorized, starting at the highest spell level in memory.\nMultiple hits remove multiple charges and spells.\nThere is no defense against these effects, except to not get hit."}
{"id": "51093", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51093", "title": "GOLSTO.ITM", "text": "GOLSTO.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by &lt;a href=\"Clay%20Golem\"&gt;Clay Golem&lt;/a&gt; and a few other creatures.\nIt is considered an enchanted +4 item and deals 3d8 damage (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a range of one foot, and speed factor of 0.\nIt has no animation assigned and other effects. This quick slot weapon is the actual damage dealer when a Stone Golem strikes with a fist.\nThe weapon also provides the wielder with protection from &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod and the installation of the \"AI Enhancement's\" component revises this item to provide a range of 2, instead of the unmodified creatures range of 1. This is to implement the Improved Golems (BG2, BG2EE, BGT/EET) component. All golems have a reach of at least 2 with this SCS component. This helps regulate the unfair and illogical golem \"choke point\" reach tactic, as a golem can easily strike with the same reach as a humanoid with a staff or spear."}
{"id": "51094", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51094", "title": "GOLSTONE.ITM", "text": "GOLSTONE.ITM is an undroppable ring worn by &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Golem\"&gt;Stone Golem&lt;/a&gt; and a few other creatures.\nThe Item provides various immunities to &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;Status Effects&lt;/a&gt;, and associated text reference strings and animations. \nThe item provides the following immunities:\nImmunities:&lt;a href=\"Sleep%20%28Status%20Effect%29\"&gt;Sleep (Status Effect)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=\"Unconscious\"&gt;Unconscious&lt;/a&gt; effect&lt;a href=\"Charm%20Creature\"&gt;Charm Creature&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=\"Morale\"&gt;Morale&lt;/a&gt; Break&lt;a href=\"Petrified\"&gt;Petrified&lt;/a&gt; effect&lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=\"Slow%20effect\"&gt;Slow effect&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=\"Paralyze\"&gt;Paralyze&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=\"Held\"&gt;Held&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "56107", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56107", "title": "GOLTOME4.ITM", "text": "GOLTOME4.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by &lt;a href=\"Juggernaut%20Golem%20%28Manual%29\"&gt;Juggernaut Golem (Manual)&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is considered an enchanted +2 item and deals 8d8+2 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt; (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a range of one foot, and speed factor of 0.\nIt has no animation assigned and other visual effects. This quick slot weapon is the actual damage dealer when this golem strikes with a fist.\nAdditionally, any hit with this weapon exposes the target creature to a potential &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; effect with a 12 second duration, as well as an extra 2d6 crushing damage.\nA &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Spells will negate both of those effects.\nThe stun effect can't be blocked with a spell protection or magic resistance, nor can it be dispelled. \nThe item also provides the golem with protection from &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "55756", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55756", "title": "GORAIR.ITM", "text": "GORAIR.ITM is an undroppable item that is equipped on the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20of%20Air\"&gt;Guardian of Air&lt;/a&gt; creature to provide protection against certain individual AI game scripted spells.\nThis item protects the wearer from the chain-lightning electricity bolts and the magical fan's air turbulence attack that occurs in the Air Laboratory.\nThe item has no other abilities or powers."}
{"id": "56046", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56046", "title": "GORCAMB.ITM", "text": "GORCAMP.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by the &lt;a href=\"Aesgareth\"&gt;Aesgareth&lt;/a&gt; cambion found on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is considered a magical and +5 enchanted item with a range of 2 feet, and speed factor of 4.\nThe two-handed sword inflicts 1d10+4 &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt;, and the wielder's strength modifier is applicable to any extra damage. The weapon also provides a 4-point &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus to hit.\nA successful hit on a target can expose the victim to one or two effects, based on a random percentile probability:\n0-50%: - &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; effect lasting 3 seconds. A &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spells with a -4 penalty will negate. It the effect works, the combat log will display a \"Stunned\" text string, and the character's portrait will display Icon No. 55, \"Stun\". &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; can block this. A &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect can remove it, but it only lasts 3 seconds.\n51-100%: - The victim is exposed to a triple ability score drain, reducing Strength, Constitution and Dexterity by -1 each and lasting 1 turn. A Saving throw versus Death/poison with a -4 penalty can negate. If the effect works, the character's portrait will display Icon No. 91 \"Ability Score Drained\". Additionally, a brief lighting effect and color fade will animate on the victim's sprite. These effects can be blocked with Magic resistance and can be removed with Dispel magic effects. Cumulative ability score drain can occur from repeated hits and missed saving throw rolls.\n26-75%: - Victim's &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; modifier is reduced by -5%, lasting 5 seconds. This effect can't be blocked and there is no saving throw. Dispel magic cannot remove the effect. No visual or text clues are provided to the player that this has occurred."}
{"id": "55703", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55703", "title": "GORCHR.ITM", "text": "The GORCHR.ITM is a undroppable item equipped by the &lt;a href=\"Chromatic%20Demon\"&gt;Chromatic Demon&lt;/a&gt; to enhance its invulnerabilities and ensure it can't be damaged or destroyed by accident or on purpose by the player - for essential plot purposes.\nThe item provides 77 protections against status effects, string references, certain spells, animation and graphic effects and also implements a &lt;a href=\"Regeneration\"&gt;Regeneration&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nThe item is removed by a dialogue script after the party frees the demon from its magical cage."}
{"id": "55901", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55901", "title": "GORDEM2.ITM", "text": "GORDEM.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by various &lt;a href=\"Velithuu\"&gt;Velithuu&lt;/a&gt; creatures.\nIt is considered a magical and +3 enchanted item and deals 2d8 &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; damage (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a range of one foot, and speed factor of 0.\nThe hit also exposes the target creature to a potential systemic &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; effect, inflicting 1 &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt; per second for 10 seconds. A &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Death with a -2 penalty will negate it. Only resistance to the status effect or to poison damage will block this."}
{"id": "55734", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55734", "title": "GORFIRG.ITM", "text": "GORFIRG.ITM is an undroppable item that is equipped on the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Giant%20%28Guardian%20of%20Fire%29\"&gt;Fire Giant (Guardian of Fire)&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis item protects against a wide variety of status effects, string references, animations associated with those status effects and a large group of arcane and divine spells.\nIt also ensures that the creature never falls below 1 Hit Point health value.\nThis item is removed by script when a certain action is performed by the party, thus stripping the Guardian of Fire from these immunities.\nSee the InfoBox for a listing of immunities provided."}
