{"id": "55660", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55660", "title": "GORMISTI.ITM", "text": "GORMIST.ITM is an undroppable item that is equipped on a few particular non-player creatures to provide a number of immunities and protections against certain &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;Status Effects&lt;/a&gt; and some individual spells.\nThis item protects against several &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;Lightning Bolt&lt;/a&gt; type spells, &lt;a href=\"Chaos\"&gt;Chaos&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Hold Person (priest)&lt;/a&gt;, and others that apply status effects listed in the InfoBox.\nSee the InfoBox for a listing of immunities provided."}
{"id": "55728", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55728", "title": "GORSNAKE.ITM", "text": "GORSNAKE.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Snake%20%28Guardian%20of%20Slime%29\"&gt;Giant Snake (Guardian of Slime)&lt;/a&gt; creature.\nIt is considered a +3 enchanted item and deals 2d6 &lt;a href=\"Piercing%20damage\"&gt;Piercing damage&lt;/a&gt; (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; modifier), with a range of one foot, and speed factor of 0.\nIt's on-hit effects include two potential hazards:\nThe first is a &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; effect on the target lasting 10 seconds. There is no &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt;, it bypasses &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; spell protections such as &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;. The condition is non-magical and can't be removed with a &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nThe second is a &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; effect on the target lasting 6 seconds. It will apply 5 &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt; per second for six seconds. There is no saving throw, it bypasses magic resistance and power level spell protections. The condition is non-magical and can't be removed with a dispel magic effect.\nThe only way to prevent exposure to these effects if the weapon hits is with equipped items or spells/potions or innate immunity to the Stun and Poison status effects.\nThe item has no other abilities."}
{"id": "56620", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56620", "title": "GORWOM1.ITM", "text": "This GORWPM1.ITM is a undroppable melee weapon equipped and used by &lt;a href=\"Nalmissra\"&gt;Nalmissra&lt;/a&gt;. \nIt is similar to the &lt;a href=\"Succubus\"&gt;Succubus&lt;/a&gt; touch/kiss attack weapon &lt;a href=\"DEMSUC01.ITM\"&gt;DEMSUC01.ITM&lt;/a&gt;, but there are some differences.\nThe item has a reach of 1 foot and a 0-speed factor. It is a magical and +2 enchantment weapon that inflicts 1d8 &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; and adds a 2-point &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus to hit. It can be modified by the wielder's &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; attribute.\nIn addition to some physical damage, each hit exposes the victim to several detrimental maladies, including:\n&lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt; two experience levels, without a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; and there are no resistances other than immunity to the effect. The combat screen will incorrectly display a text \"One Level Drained\" instead of two.\nAbility scores drain, -2 from the victim's Dexterity and Constitution attributes. A saving throw vs. Spell with a -4 penalty will negate. This draining can't be blocked with &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; or spell protections. The duration is 5 turns. It can't be dispelled. Subsequent hits are cumulative.\nA saving throw malison penalizing all saving throw modifiers with a 2-point penalty. A saving throw vs. Spell with a -4 penalty will negate. These penalties can't be blocked by anything, and last for 5 turns, nor can they be dispelled. Subsequent hits are cumulative. \nAnd finally, there is a 50% probability of a &lt;a href=\"Charmed\"&gt;Charmed&lt;/a&gt; effect applied to the victim - it only affects humanoid creatures. \nA saving throw vs. Spell with a -8 penalty will negate. If the effect takes hold, the victim will display a Dire Charm icon (No.1) on their portrait - the charm effect lasts 1 turn, but it can be blocked by magic resistance. It can't be dispelled and bypasses spell school and &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; protections.\n&lt;a href=\"Elf\"&gt;Elf&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Half-elf\"&gt;Half-elf&lt;/a&gt; creatures do get their racial resistance to charm effects versus this weapon.\nThis weapon also provides the wielder with protection from the &lt;a href=\"Nature%27s%20Beauty\"&gt;Nature's Beauty&lt;/a&gt; spell."}
{"id": "56619", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56619", "title": "GORWOM2.ITM", "text": "The GORWOM2.ITM is an undroppable enchanted &lt;a href=\"longbow\"&gt;longbow&lt;/a&gt; equipped by &lt;a href=\"The%20Huntress\"&gt;The Huntress&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis missile launcher provides a 4-point &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus to hit with arrow fire.\nThe item is basically a clone of the &lt;a href=\"Elven%20Court%20Bow\"&gt;Elven Court Bow&lt;/a&gt;, so the creature has an appropriate weapon that the game doesn't want to provide as droppbale or stealable loot."}
{"id": "56615", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56615", "title": "GORWOM4.ITM", "text": "GORWOM4.ITM is an undroppable weapon used by &lt;a href=\"Ameralis%20Zauviir\"&gt;Ameralis Zauviir&lt;/a&gt; and is a unique &lt;a href=\"Flail\"&gt;Flail&lt;/a&gt; modeled on the &lt;a href=\"Drow%20Flail\"&gt;Drow Flail&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe flail is a +4 enchanted weapon that inflicts 1d6+4 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt; and an extra +5 &lt;a href=\"Magical%20damage\"&gt;Magical damage&lt;/a&gt; on any successful strike.\nThe weapon applies one of two &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;Status Effects&lt;/a&gt;, each with an even 50% chance of occurring:\nA &lt;a href=\"Slow%20effect\"&gt;Slow effect&lt;/a&gt; lasting 5 rounds - a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Spells with a 4-point penalty negates.\nA &lt;a href=\"Blindness\"&gt;Blindness&lt;/a&gt; effect lasting 5 rounds - a save vs. Death with a 4-point penalty negates.\nBoth effects can be blocked with &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and can also be removed with &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt;.\nBoth effects have 0 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; and for example will therefor bypass spell protections such as &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;."}
