{"id": "10276", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10276", "title": "Gaal", "text": "Gaal is the high priest of his &lt;a href=\"beholder\"&gt;beholder&lt;/a&gt; cult's God, the &lt;a href=\"Unseeing%20Eye\"&gt;Unseeing Eye&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign.\nEncounters.\nFirst.\nGaal is first found preaching to some &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatlan&lt;/a&gt; citizens in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt; and trying to convince them to join a new 'religion' with a new deity. If he is attacked here before he walks away, many further quests and areas become unfinishable.\nSecond.\nAfterwards, the party will be asked to &lt;a href=\"Investigate%20and%20Destroy%20the%20Cult%20of%20the%20Eyeless\"&gt;investigate the cult&lt;/a&gt;. He then can be found in his Cult Domain in &lt;a href=\"The%20Old%20Tunnels\"&gt;The Old Tunnels&lt;/a&gt; accessed from the &lt;a href=\"Sewers%20%28Temple%20District%29\"&gt;Temple District Sewers&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe wants the party to retrieve &lt;a href=\"Rift%20Device\"&gt;one half of a powerful artifact&lt;/a&gt;. Accept the job and he will give you a &lt;a href=\"Gaal%27s%20Key\"&gt;key&lt;/a&gt; to the Lower Reaches. Killing or attacking Gaal before accepting his quest locks you out of several areas and quests!\nThird.\nAfter killing the &lt;a href=\"Unseeing%20Eye\"&gt;Unseeing Eye&lt;/a&gt; it is possible to return to the cult domain and kill him, along some other cultists."}
{"id": "38837", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38837", "title": "Gaal's Key", "text": ""}
{"id": "5909", "revid": "284224", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5909", "title": "Gaelan Bayle", "text": "Gaelan Bayle is a member of the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt; who lives in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Slums%20District\"&gt;Slums District&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign.\nThe first time the party leaves Waukeen's Promenade during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%201\"&gt;Chapter I&lt;/a&gt;, the only option is to enter the Slums District. Immediately after this, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; encounters Gaelan. This encounter is unavoidable. Gaelan claims to knows how to rescue &lt;a href=\"Imoen\"&gt;Imoen&lt;/a&gt; and will take the party to &lt;a href=\"Gaelan%20Bayle%27s%20Home\"&gt;his home&lt;/a&gt; to propose a deal.\nHe will tell the protagonist that a group will help facilitate an opportunity to rescue Imoen for . After the deal is struck, a cut-scene plays, initiating &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Chapter II&lt;/a&gt; of the game. Further into the adventure, he will later reduce the price to . Once the party gathers and actually pays the fee, Gaelan will reveal that he is working for the Shadow Thieves and will refer the Ward to &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt; to further the main quest.\nRelated Quests.\nAfter the initial talk, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; may ask Gaelan for \"help finding work\" to raise gold. Gaelan has several suggestions to get the party started, including the person who can initiate the &lt;a href=\"Stronghold\"&gt;Stronghold&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Quests\"&gt;Quest&lt;/a&gt; most relevant to the PC's class (e.g., for a &lt;a href=\"Fighter\"&gt;Fighter&lt;/a&gt;, he will mention \"\"a girl named &lt;a href=\"Nalia%20de%27Arnise\"&gt;Nalia&lt;/a&gt;\"\" at the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt;). In case of a multi- or dual-class PC, &lt;a href=\"Brus\"&gt;Brus&lt;/a&gt; may direct them towatds the initiator of the Stronghold Quest for their second class upon exiting his house (e.g., for a &lt;a href=\"Fighter%20/%20Mage\"&gt;Fighter / Mage&lt;/a&gt;, Gaelan will mention Nalia and his nephew &lt;a href=\"Madeen\"&gt;Madeen&lt;/a&gt;). Others sources of work mentioned include:\nNotes.\nGaelan has two Creature files, with the only differences as follows:\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; has an optional component regarding Gaelan Bayle:\nIncrease the price asked by Gaelan Bayle (BG2, BG2EE, BGT)\nThis component aims both to make it more realistic for the player to linger in chapter 2 of SoA (which in gameplay terms is often rather tempting but is hard to justify on roleplaying grounds) and to add an extra challenge by restricting the player's wealth in the first part of the game. As everyone knows, in the unmodded game Gaelan asks the player to provide 20,000gp. With this component installed, he will want more - between 40,000gp and 120,000gp, depending on which option you choose during installation.\nGaelan Bayle is also assigned an SCS Thief AI script for improved tactical combat behavior, and weapon proficiencies and thieving skills are adjusted (and used by the script) commensurate with the Rogue's experience level. He will also utilize potions in his inventory for invisibility and backstabbing opportunities, and to heal himself. Backstabbing attacks will be used if he is able to achieve invisibility.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Rebalancing\"&gt;Rogue Rebalancing&lt;/a&gt; mod makes further revisions to Gaelan and provides additional support in his home should he be attacked.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Alternatives\"&gt;Alternatives&lt;/a&gt; mod, if the party accepts the tasks proposed by \"Aster\", then Gaelan Bayle can be attacked and killed. The &lt;a href=\"MINHP1.ITM\"&gt;MINHP1.ITM&lt;/a&gt; is removed from his creature file."}
{"id": "18111", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18111", "title": "Gaelan Bayle's Home", "text": "Gaelan Bayle's Home is a building in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;Athkatla Slums&lt;/a&gt; during \"\".\nThe party is brought here by &lt;a href=\"Gaelan%20Bayle\"&gt;Gaelan Bayle&lt;/a&gt; to make a deal to help them find and go to the location of &lt;a href=\"Imoen\"&gt;Imoen&lt;/a&gt; for \u200b\u200b, thus beginning &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Chapter II&lt;/a&gt;. His relative &lt;a href=\"Brus\"&gt;Brus&lt;/a&gt; will deliver messages to you from Gaelan later in the saga, at various trigger points. \nWhen the party has accrued the funds (reduced to \u200b\u200b), he can be found here again to begin &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%203\"&gt;Chapter III&lt;/a&gt;.\nOn the second floor, a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thief&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"Arledrian\"&gt;Arledrian&lt;/a&gt; runs a shop (see his page for his stock).\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; has an optional component regarding Gaelan Bayle:\nIncrease the price asked by Gaelan Bayle (BG2, BG2EE, BGT)\nThis component aims both to make it more realistic for the player to linger in chapter 2 of SoA (which in gameplay terms is often rather tempting but is hard to justify on roleplaying grounds) and to add an extra challenge by restricting the player's wealth in the first part of the game. As everyone knows, in the unmodded game Gaelan asks the player to provide 20,000gp. With this component installed, he will want more - between 40,000gp and 120,000gp, depending on which option you choose during installation.\nGaelan Bayle is also assigned an SCS Thief AI script for improved tactical combat behavior, and weapon proficiencies and thieving skills are adjusted (and used by the script) commensurate with the Rogue's experience level. He will also utilize potions in his inventory for invisibility and backstabbing opportunities, and to heal himself.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Rebalancing\"&gt;Rogue Rebalancing&lt;/a&gt; mod makes further revisions to Gaelan and provides additional support in his home should he be attacked. The mod also makes a large number of changes to Arledrian, his stock, and makes known that a unique item is carried in his personal inventory - the Dagger \"Silverblaze\", a vampire hunting weapon. Arledrian now functions as a \"fence\" as well."}
{"id": "26995", "revid": "31746286", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26995", "title": "Gaelan Bayle's House", "text": ""}
{"id": "6899", "revid": "1966519", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6899", "title": "Gain the services of Sir Sarles for the temple", "text": "Gain the services of Sir Sarles for the temple is a side-quest for . It can be located in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;. Once the player has started the &lt;a href=\"Find%20and%20Destroy%20the%20Cult%20of%20the%20Unseeing\"&gt;Cult of the Eyeless&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0quest, they can speak to the sub-priest of the temple that has hired them to receive this quest.\nWalkthrough.\nThe Temple of the Helm wishes to commission the services of the famed sculptor, &lt;a href=\"Sir%20Sarles\"&gt;Sir Sarles&lt;/a&gt;, to create a statue to glorify their temple, and sends the party to the &lt;a href=\"Jysstev%20Estate\"&gt;Jysstev Estate&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Government%20District\"&gt;Government District&lt;/a&gt; to persuade him. Enter the Jysstev Estate. Talk to the butler. Sir Sarles will be in the northernmost rooms after that. The arrogant sculptor refuses unless he is provided the medium of his choice: two hundred pounds of pure &lt;a href=\"Illithium%20Ore\"&gt;Illithium Ore&lt;/a&gt;. In pursuit of this, he sends them to &lt;a href=\"Jerlia\"&gt;Jerlia&lt;/a&gt; the Ore Merchant, who runs a stall in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen talking to her, Jerlia explains that pure illithium is very rare and she only deals out 50 pounds of the ore each season herself. She offers to provide an &lt;a href=\"Chunk%20of%20Illithium%20Alloy\"&gt;Illithium Alloy&lt;/a&gt; for 200 gp instead, which she can do in a day. If the party is diplomatic, and sweetens the pot with more, she reveals that she buys her illithium from a &lt;a href=\"Duergar\"&gt;Duergar&lt;/a&gt; trader, &lt;a href=\"Unger%20Hilldark\"&gt;Unger Hilldark&lt;/a&gt;, who operates out of the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt;.\nThere are three routes to complete this quest:\nObtaining fake illithium.\nTelling Jerlia to create the Illithium Alloy prompts her to tell the party to return in a day. However, when they do, she explains that demand from other temples means she must increase the price she originally set, from the original 200 to a new 500. She must be paid this amount to hand over the Alloy.\nUpon returning to Sir Sarles, however, it is unsatisfactory; &lt;a href=\"Keldorn%20Firecam\"&gt;Keldorn Firecam&lt;/a&gt; will admit the Alloy is fake if he is in the party, but even if he is not and you don't admit the truth, Sir Sarles still recognizes the Alloy is fake because it holds smears, something that doesn't happen to pure illithium. Outraged, he leaves Athkatla, forcing the party to return to their Temple and report the failure. However, the Temple's superior sees the Illithium Alloy and mistakes it as Sir Sarles' work, accepting it happily. The party is rewarded with for this route.\nObtaining real illithium.\nSpeaking to Unger Hilldark has him reveal that he can't give you any illithium, as it was stolen from him by an evil demihuman named &lt;a href=\"Neb\"&gt;Neb&lt;/a&gt;. As Hilldark reveals, Neb is hidden inside a &lt;a href=\"Derelict%20House\"&gt;derelict house&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt;. Upon finding him, he reveals himself as the child murderer from Baldur's Gate. An Evil Gorion's Ward can bargain with him to just give them the ore, but &lt;a href=\"Minsc\"&gt;Minsc&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; will force a confrontation. If you choose to fight Neb, he will use invisibility and summon 4 &lt;a href=\"Child%20Spirit\"&gt;Child Spirit&lt;/a&gt;s to attack you.\u00a0 Neb's death rewards the party with , a lesser restoration spell cast on each party member (those spirits can cause level drain, but in the end everyone will be back to normal), and for each Child Spirit that survived the battle (while killing them only rewards per spirit). On his corpse is the Illithium Ore the party seeks, as well as &lt;a href=\"Neb%27s%20Nasty%20Cutter\"&gt;Neb's Nasty Cutter&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Neb%27s%20Head\"&gt;Neb's Head&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\n\"&lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20for%20BG2\"&gt;Unfinished Business for BG2&lt;/a&gt;\" adds the \"Extended Illithium Quest\" which provides an alternative path to complete the quest. You must first rescue Unger Hilldark's brother from the Temple Ruins in the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt; to find how to obtain the real illithium. Still, if you can kill Neb, you can take the ore for yourself.\nPlayer exploits regarding Sir Sarles.\nBelow are some dubious roleplay and immersion twisting pursuits that can be tried to circumvent the quest's intended reward and plot - optional of course:"}
