{"id": "48502", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48502", "title": "Gaius", "text": "Gaius is a member of &lt;a href=\"The%20Hatchetman%27s%20Party\"&gt;The Hatchetman's Party&lt;/a&gt;, a band of heavyweight hitters who are encountered within the &lt;a href=\"Sewers%20%28Temple%20District%29\"&gt;Sewers&lt;/a&gt; located beneath the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt; in the city of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;. \nThis is one mean group of individuals so be prepared for a good fight. Gaius is a 14th level &lt;a href=\"elf\"&gt;elven&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; that will use every spell in his spellbook, so watch out for an &lt;a href=\"Invisible%20Stalker%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Invisible Stalker&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Spawn\"&gt;sword spider&lt;/a&gt; (or two) to potentially join the fight.\nSee The Hatchetman's Party page for tips on how to beat these guys in a fight.\nMod content.\nPeople involved.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some revisions to Gaius. He is changed to a level 14 Invoker and assigned a default SCS \"Smarter Mage\" script for more intelligent combat behavior, threat recognition and targeting decision logic. Arcane spell casting choices are improved with additional memorized spell choices, including pre-battle defensive buff preparation. He also has the following ready to use:&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; loaded with &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; loaded with &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield (spell)&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;\nGaius is an Invoker, so will attempt to blast you with evocation spells (where you will have a -2 to your saving throws). You could be exposed to an &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Storm\"&gt;Ice Storm&lt;/a&gt; cast over your clustered party members, a &lt;a href=\"Disintegrate\"&gt;Disintegrate&lt;/a&gt; spell may be attempted at a vulnerable party member (with no spell protections), a &lt;a href=\"Delayed%20Blast%20Fireball\"&gt;Delayed Blast Fireball&lt;/a&gt; can be used as well. Gaius can also destroy your summoned creatures with a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; and summon his own &lt;a href=\"Mordenkainen%27s%20Sword%20%28creature%29\"&gt;Mordenkainen's Sword (creature)&lt;/a&gt; for assistance."}
{"id": "52253", "revid": "272861", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52253", "title": "Gale (BG3)", "text": "Gale is an &lt;a href=\"Origin%20Characters%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;Origin character&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20III\"&gt;Baldur's Gate III&lt;/a&gt;\". He is a &lt;a href=\"Human%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;Human&lt;/a&gt;, and his &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;class&lt;/a&gt; is &lt;a href=\"Wizard%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt;. He has a &lt;a href=\"Backgrounds%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;background&lt;/a&gt; as a &lt;a href=\"Sage%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;Sage&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe can be chosen as the player's character during &lt;a href=\"Character%20Creation%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;character creation&lt;/a&gt;. His &lt;a href=\"Races%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;race&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;class&lt;/a&gt;, appearance, and background cannot be changed. All other details can be customized, including &lt;a href=\"Ability%20Scores%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;Ability Scores&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Skill%20Points%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;Skill Points&lt;/a&gt;, etc.\nIf not chosen as the player's character, Gale may be encountered on the &lt;a href=\"Ravaged%20Beach%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;Ravaged Beach&lt;/a&gt; and recruited as a &lt;a href=\"Companions%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt;.\nGale Dekarios is adept at utilising the magic of the Weave, and talks about it far, far... FAR too often. \nCharacter details.\nBackground: &lt;a href=\"Sage%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;Sage&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nEyes: Brown&lt;br&gt;\nSkin: ?&lt;br&gt;\nHair: Brown\nProficiencies.\nAttribute Saving Throws:\nWeapons:\nArmour:\nSkills:\nSpellcasting.\nGale's spellcasting is based on Intelligence, and he starts with 2 level 1 spell slots."}
{"id": "2681", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2681", "title": "Galileus", "text": "Galileus is an astrologer who can be found standing in the middle of a field in the &lt;a href=\"Song%20of%20the%20Morning%20Temple\"&gt;Temple&lt;/a&gt; area, observing the skies.\nIf you ask him what they foretell, he explains that it is unclear, but interesting times are ahead. He speculates that even the heavens are looking on with interest. After the conversation, he goes away, never to be seen again.\nDialogue.\n\"Thirty degrees latitude... longitude varying greatly... moons in conjunction with... pardon my lack of focus, but I've been studying the skies for some time now. Now I've a positively wicked kink in my neck, and cannot seem to focus on anything closer than the horizon. Such are the pains of astrology, I suppose.\""}
{"id": "15731", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15731", "title": "Galken", "text": "Galken is hanging out inside the main room of the &lt;a href=\"Ulgoth%27s%20Beard%20Inn\"&gt;inn&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Ulgoth%27s%20Beard\"&gt;Ulgoth's Beard&lt;/a&gt;. He wants you to clear up his 900 tab in return for a &lt;a href=\"Dwarven%20Rune%20Wardstone\"&gt;ward token&lt;/a&gt; that gives entry to the dungeons beneath &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe can be killed after taking up his offer to pay off his debt with no reputation penalty, but you better be fast as he skedaddles rather quickly once the transaction is completed."}
{"id": "40329", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40329", "title": "Galken's Wardstone", "text": "To start this quest speak with &lt;a href=\"Galken\"&gt;Galken&lt;/a&gt;, who is located in the main room of the &lt;a href=\"Ulgoth%27s%20Beard%20Inn\"&gt;Ulgoth's Beard Inn&lt;/a&gt; in the town of &lt;a href=\"Ulgoth%27s%20Beard\"&gt;Ulgoth's Beard&lt;/a&gt;. If you spot him 900 so he can clear his tab with the innkeeper, he will offer to give you a &lt;a href=\"Dwarven%20Rune%20Wardstone\"&gt;ward token&lt;/a&gt; which supposedly provides entry to the dungeons beneath &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt;. However, the wardstone is a fake and will not grant entry to the lower labyrinth levels beneath Durlag's Tower."}
{"id": "48504", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48504", "title": "Gallchobhair", "text": "Gallchobhair is a member of &lt;a href=\"The%20Hatchetman%27s%20Party\"&gt;The Hatchetman's Party&lt;/a&gt;, a band of heavyweight hitters who are encountered within the &lt;a href=\"Sewers%20%28Temple%20District%29\"&gt;Sewers&lt;/a&gt; located beneath the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt; in the city of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis is one mean group of individuals so be prepared for a good fight. Gallchobhair is an 11th level &lt;a href=\"elf\"&gt;elven&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt; who may be equipped with what some might think of as low-level weapons but, with a &lt;a href=\"strength\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt; of 17 and a &lt;a href=\"dexterity\"&gt;dexterity&lt;/a&gt; of 18 combined with that elvish grace and fluidity in battle, he'll be standing in the back slinging arrows left and right. And once his quiver is empty, he will be right in there hacking away.\nSee The Hatchetman's Party page for tips on how to beat these guys in a fight.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some minor revisions to Gallchobhair. He is assigned a default SCS tactical Fighter script for smarter combat behavior, threat recognition and targeting decision logic. He now has 5 pips in Longbow weapon proficiency, and 2 pips in Long Sword. Random SCS treasure is also placed in his inventory. Gallchobhair will focus on missile weapon firing attacks from a distance. If a party member closes to melee range, he will either try and retreat back a bit and continue his missile attacks, or just engage in melee combat. With his grandmastery in bows, high dexterity and elven racial bonus he'll be able to fire 3.5 arrows per round and deal 1d6 +5 missile damage."}
{"id": "7653", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7653", "title": "Gallor", "text": "Gallor is one of the people working for &lt;a href=\"Charleston%20Nib\"&gt;Charleston Nib&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Archaeological%20Site\"&gt;Archaeological Site&lt;/a&gt; area south of &lt;a href=\"Lighthouse\"&gt;Lighthouse&lt;/a&gt;, excavating an ancient temple of the god &lt;a href=\"Kozah\"&gt;Kozah&lt;/a&gt;. Unsatisfied with the non-profit nature of Charleston's excavations, he tries to conspire against his employer. He will approach you after you have spoken to Charleston, offering if you will \"remove\" Mr. Nib and any of the other diggers that remain loyal to him (which is all of them). Evil parties may want to accept his offer, others will likely not want the &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt; penalty for killing the &lt;a href=\"innocent\"&gt;innocent&lt;/a&gt; archeologist.\nInterestingly, Gallor is of &lt;a href=\"neutral%20good\"&gt;neutral good&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;alignment&lt;/a&gt;, while Mr. Nib is &lt;a href=\"lawful%20neutral\"&gt;lawful neutral&lt;/a&gt;.\nThere is no reputation penalty for killing Gallor, and no-one else will turn hostile if you do. He is worth 120 xp, and drops &lt;a href=\"Studded%20Leather%20Armor\"&gt;Studded Leather Armor&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Morning%20Star\"&gt;Morning Star&lt;/a&gt; and . How he would pay the reward that he offers, with only in his pockets, remains a mystery.\nDialogue.\n\"Why, hello there. Could we just step aside a moment and have a little chat away from prying ears?\"\n\"First, my name is Gallor. Second, we never had this conversation. I'm the \"partner\" of that old mister Charleston you met, except I'm none too thrilled about the non-profit aspects of the whole thing. The old man seems to think we should donate all our findings to some museum, whereas I am ever so much more practical. I should think certain people would pay dearly for the magical treasure we are about to unearth, and if they would be so eager, who are we to stand in their way? I would like you to steal the item and \"remove\" Mr. Nib from my little equation. You up to the task?\"\nFrom here, the dialog runs in circles with basically the same options until you accept or decline his offer. He has no real information to offer about the \"magical treasure\" that he expects to find."}
{"id": "37471", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37471", "title": "Gallor's Plot", "text": ""}
{"id": "11407", "revid": "6896023", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11407", "title": "Galoomp's Store", "text": ""}
{"id": "6124", "revid": "283466", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6124", "title": "Galoomp the Bookkeeper", "text": "Galoomp the Bookkeeper is a merchant who, as his name would imply, specializes in books and scrolls. He is located above the &lt;a href=\"Den%20of%20the%20Seven%20Vales\"&gt;Den of the Seven Vales&lt;/a&gt; in the northern part of &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt;.\nSpell Store.\nGaloomp's outdoor Stall is marked as \"Spell Store\" on the player's map.\nMod content.\nPeople involved.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Quest%20Pack\"&gt;Quest Pack&lt;/a&gt; Mod can install the Burglary Of The Bookkeeper component:\nGaloomp the Bookkeeper, has been feeling rather down lately. The reason? Somebody has been stealing scrolls from his store! Solve the mystery to uncover a tale of sadness and rejection in this component originally created by Andyr.\nInstallation of &lt;a href=\"The%20White%20Queen\"&gt;The White Queen&lt;/a&gt; mod places a special book in Galoomp's store. This book will furnish a means to update the &lt;a href=\"World%20Map\"&gt;World Map&lt;/a&gt; with a location for another well-crafted adventure to explore.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Check%20the%20Bodies%20%28CtB%29\"&gt;Check the Bodies (CtB)&lt;/a&gt; mod and or the Helping Melynda the Mute component places two new items in Galoomp's store stock - \"Vellum\" and \"Parchment\". Obtaining either one of these items and having them in the party's inventory opens up dialogue options and helps further the quest introduced by the Mod.\nThe &lt;a href=\"The%20Tweaks%20Anthology\"&gt;The Tweaks Anthology&lt;/a&gt; mod and selection of certain components will change the appearances of containers and ensure they are different in colors for differentiation purposes - this includes Scroll Cases such as provided in Galoomp's Store (and others throughout the saga)."}
{"id": "7517", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7517", "title": "Galtok", "text": "Galtok is a &lt;a href=\"gnome\"&gt;gnome&lt;/a&gt; who is found running away from some &lt;a href=\"kobold\"&gt;kobold&lt;/a&gt;s at &lt;a href=\"Coordinates\"&gt;3034.2833&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;Nashkel Mines&lt;/a&gt; area. He will approach the party upon sight and, depending upon your reply, it's possible that 4 kobolds will spawn near his initial location. Regardless of the dialogue choice, he will flee the area once the conversation is finished.\nHe can be killed without &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt; penalty for his &lt;a href=\"Mage%20Robe%20of%20Fire%20Resistance\"&gt;Mage Robe of Fire Resistance&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"dagger\"&gt;dagger&lt;/a&gt;, but if you want to hear the dialogue and have the 4 kobolds spawn as well, you either have to be quick in killing him before he flees, or charm him and give him any order to prevent him from fleeing before attacking. You can also change his weapon to &lt;a href=\"fist\"&gt;fist&lt;/a&gt; to make him deal less (and non-lethal) damage.\nDialogue.\n\"Hey... wait... please wait. You've gotta help me, they're after me. They'll be here soon.\"\n--kobolds spawn--\n--no kobolds spawn--"}
{"id": "48794", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48794", "title": "Galvarey", "text": "Galvarey is a &lt;a href=\"Harpers\"&gt;Harper&lt;/a&gt; and current self-proclaimed leader of the local Harper organization based out of the &lt;a href=\"Galvarey%20Estate\"&gt;Galvarey Estate&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Athkatla Docks&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign. He is only found during a &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;Companion&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Quests\"&gt;Quest&lt;/a&gt; when &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; is &lt;a href=\"Summoned%20to%20the%20Harper%20Hold\"&gt;Summoned to the Harper Hold&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nWhen &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and Jaheira first encounter Galvarey, he is waiting, along with four of his cohorts, &lt;a href=\"Bessen\"&gt;Bessen&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Iko\"&gt;Iko&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Kail\"&gt;Kail&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Nadinal\"&gt;Nadinal&lt;/a&gt;, just inside of the front door of the estate.\nIn the original game, Galvarey wears &lt;a href=\"Fallorain%27s%20Plate\"&gt;Fallorain's Plate&lt;/a&gt;. It is changed in BG2EE. Technically he has insufficient strength to wield a Composite Longbow.\nHis script allows the quaffing of carried potion for use, and he'll apply an oil of speed and consume potions of healing, if able, when damaged to a specific threshold.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some minor changes to select creature scripts, and abilities. An SCS tactical fighter script is supplied for more intelligent attack and defense behavior, as well as potion use. Galvarey now has 5-pips in Longbow weapon proficiency (and thus has improved to hit and damage, as well as APR). Two-handed sword proficiency remains the same as the unmodified version."}
{"id": "8649", "revid": "284189", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8649", "title": "Galvarey Estate", "text": "The Galvarey Estate is a &lt;a href=\"Harpers\"&gt;Harper&lt;/a&gt; hold run by &lt;a href=\"Galvarey\"&gt;Galvarey&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Athkatla Docks&lt;/a&gt;. You will need to come here often in the Harper Hold quests.\nLayout.\nFront Door.\nPrior to &lt;a href=\"Bring%20the%20Poisoned%20Man%20to%20his%20Friends\"&gt;bringing Renfeld the Poisoned Man to his Friends&lt;/a&gt;, and then accepting Xzar's Quest, the front door will be locked unconventionally and warded against simple spells, barring access to the building.\nGround Floor.\nThe first floor is dominated by a large hall where you find &lt;a href=\"Meronia\"&gt;Meronia&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Pace\"&gt;Pace&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Berinvar\"&gt;Berinvar&lt;/a&gt;. To the southwest is a door to the outside stairway that leads down to a small dock, and up to the roof. At the west end of the hall is the stairway up to the second floor. To the northeast are four study rooms with desks containing various items. A portrait of an eye holds a trap and a &lt;a href=\"Helm%20of%20Charm%20Protection\"&gt;Helm of Charm Protection&lt;/a&gt;. The desk in the last room has a &lt;a href=\"Harper%20Amulet\"&gt;Harper Amulet&lt;/a&gt;.\nSecond Floor.\nThe second floor is a large library. If you have the Harper Amulet, you may ask questions of the &lt;a href=\"Spectral%20Harpist\"&gt;Spectral Harpists&lt;/a&gt; here; if not, they attack. To the south are dining rooms and a pantry. To the southeast is a bunk room with six locked chests. One is trapped. Two stairs lead up to the roof, where there is outside access down to the dock and back into the first floor. To the northeast you hear birds chirping.\"This is an elaborate indoor aviary, filled with exotic plants as well as numerous strange birds. You see a small bird flying through the branches of the aviary. You could catch it if you wish to.\"The bird is required for the side quest, &lt;a href=\"Find%20out%20What%20Happened%20to%20Montaron\"&gt;Find out What Happened to Montaron&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; revises most of the Harpers. It does this by assigining default SCS AI scripts appropriate to the class of the creature such as Fighters, mage, cleric or thief. These scripts enhance tactical decision making and smarter use of spells as well as hazard recognition and avoidance behavior. Often, weapon proficiencies are assigned to match up with their experience level and assigned weaponry. More details are provided on the creature pages."}
{"id": "51225", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51225", "title": "Galvena", "text": "Galvena, sometimes also referred to as \"Mistress Galvena\", is mentioned by several non-player characters in and around &lt;a href=\"Brynnlaw\"&gt;Brynnlaw&lt;/a&gt;. She is known as the head of a Brothel with some unsavory ethics and cruel exploitive practices on the island town. Galvena is allied or at least in partnership with Pirate Lord Desharik. Galvena employs courtesans, guards, bouncers, a pimp, servants and others as part of the Brothel enterprise. She is said to be cruel and vindictive. The woman even has her own private prison in the bowels of her fortified Brothel. \nGameplay.\nDespite so much talk and reference to Galvena by various folks in Brynnlaw, she can only be encountered in the Brothel prison area, and that place can only be accessed if the party gets hold of a specific key located in her private quarters within the Brothel.\nThe plot and purpose of confronting Galvena is covered as part of the &lt;a href=\"Getting%20inside%20the%20asylum\"&gt;Getting inside the asylum&lt;/a&gt; quest. Go to that article for all the steps and associated paths to this subject.\nIf the party manages to eventually make its way to the Brothel Prison area to face Galvena, along with her private guardian/enforcer mage &lt;a href=\"Vadek\"&gt;Vadek&lt;/a&gt; in order to rescue &lt;a href=\"Claire\"&gt;Claire&lt;/a&gt;, then hostilities are about to begin. This is unavoidable in the plot.\nWhen that time comes and dialogue is exhausted, Galvena will engage in close quarters melee combat with the nearest party member she can detect, swinging her enchanted flail as her primary weapon. If she is defeated, her body can be searched and looted for her flail and leather armor, both of which are enchanted and valuable.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a new default SCS Fighter AI script to Galvena, for better targeting and tactical behavior. She is slightly modified to allow sufficient strength to wield a flail (which is technically too low in the unmodified creature version), and also given 4 pips in flail weapon proficiency, as well as 2 pips in single weapon fighting style. This will improve her melee combat slightly."}
{"id": "28303", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=28303", "title": "Galvena's Medallion", "text": "Galvena's Medallion is needed to access &lt;a href=\"Galvena%27s%20Guildhall\"&gt;Galvena's Guildhall&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Brynnlaw\"&gt;Brynnlaw&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Chremy\"&gt;Chremy&lt;/a&gt; near &lt;a href=\"The%20Vulgar%20Monkey\"&gt;The Vulgar Monkey&lt;/a&gt; inn drops it. You do not need to equip it to access the Guildhall."}
