{"id": "19699", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19699", "title": "Gamesman", "text": "A Gamesman can be found wherever gambling is offered in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. One performs the role of a \"Barker\", one is a bartender and proprietor, and three offer various games to play with various odds of winning. On the long run, you will most likely lose more than you earn, but one can get possibly infinite gold by saving and loading since the winning gold is not taken from the gamesmen own inventory. Alternatively, the gamesmen can be killed to retrieve the gold you give them while also keeping the winnings (if any), though the party will suffer reputation loss.\nGAMES.\n&lt;br&gt;\nThis gamesman is only found inside the two large gambling tents in the &lt;a href=\"Carnival\"&gt;Carnival&lt;/a&gt; area. He is near the entrance of the tent and performs the role of a \"Barker\", enticing folks to spend their money on the different games that are available within the tent.\nGAMES2.\n&lt;br&gt;\nThis gamesman is only found inside the two large gambling tents in the &lt;a href=\"Marketplace%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;Marketplace&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Central%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Central Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. He is near the right rear of the tent standing behind a small bar. He comments on how the out of work locals misery keeps him from going hungry. He also promises to set straight anyone who disparages the honesty of his gaming establishment.\nGAMES3.\n&lt;br&gt;\nThis gamesman is only found inside the two large gambling tents in the Carnival and Marketplace. He offers up the game of Roulette for those willing to take a chance.\nGAMES4.\n&lt;br&gt;\nThis gamesman is found on the second floor of the &lt;a href=\"Blushing%20Mermaid\"&gt;Blushing Mermaid&lt;/a&gt;, the captains deck on the &lt;a href=\"Low%20Lantern\"&gt;Low Lantern&lt;/a&gt;, and inside the two large gambling tents in the Carnival and Marketplace areas. He offers up the Big Wheel game which is somewhat similar to roulette except the wheel is vertical instead of horizontal.\nGAMES5.\n&lt;br&gt;\nThis gamesman is found on the second floor of both the Blushing Mermaid and the &lt;a href=\"Generic%20Tavern%20and%20Inn%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23AR1109\"&gt;Tavern and Inn&lt;/a&gt; that's located in &lt;a href=\"Southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Southwest Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and inside the two large gambling tents in the Carnival and Marketplace areas. He offers up the game of craps for those who like to roll the bones."}
{"id": "19700", "revid": "978785", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19700", "title": "Gamesmen", "text": ""}
{"id": "7031", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7031", "title": "Gandolar Luckyfoot", "text": "Gandolar Luckyfoot is the leader of the halfling village in &lt;a href=\"Gullykin\"&gt;Gullykin&lt;/a&gt;. Kobolds threaten the village; he will give 250 to remove the threat. Asking, somewhat imperiously, to be directed to various locations ends up costing money; being polite gets cheaper as well as more harmonious results.\nGandolar can be killed with no &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt; loss.\nDialog.\nGandolar presents a great many dialog options; only the initial sets of options are shown here. In all cases, the key to success is to be polite. If you are rude without actually dismissing Gandolar, he may tell you so himself: \nFirst Dialog.\nThe first time you speak to Gandolar, you may (or may not) get the quest &lt;a href=\"Firewine_Bridge_and_Gullykin%23Firewine_Bridge_and_Gullykin\"&gt;Firewine Bridge and Gullykin&lt;/a&gt;. Option 2 will take you there directly; option 1 will get you there eventually, if you apologize. If you don't get the quest from him now, you can still get it the next time you speak to Gandolar.\n\"Well met, traveler. Gandolar Luckyfoot, at your disposal. To what does our little village owe the pleasure of your visit? Off to Durlag's Tower? Or have you already been, and now ye need your breaks and bruises healed? Many a wanderer comes to town nearly bled to death.\"\nSecond Dialog.\nThe second time you speak to Gandolar, he offers you the quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Firewine%20Ruins\"&gt;The Firewine Ruins&lt;/a&gt; . Accepting it will also give you the Firewine Bridge and Gullykin quest if you didn't get it earlier. Dialog option 3 is the simplest route to the quest(s); option 4 will cause Gandolar to walk away, out of the game.\n\"If I might pull on your coattail a moment more, I have a proposition for you. It's usually nature-quiet by the Firewine ruins, even with its violent bygone. Those who died and did not sleep have mostly found their rest over time. It's a live threat that comes now, with a band of kobolds that moved in. Perhaps we could prevail upon you to rid us of this menace, and in return, a gift from us you shall receive. Keep whatever you find as well.\"\nMore Dialog.\nWhile the quest The Firewine Ruins is incomplete, i.e., the &lt;a href=\"Ogre%20Mage%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20I%29%23OGREMA02%20/%20OGREMA03\"&gt;Ogre Mage&lt;/a&gt; is still alive, Gandolar has just one thing to say:\nWhen you have completed the quest he awaits you with your reward:\nAfter this Gandolar leaves the game."}
{"id": "26801", "revid": "78773", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26801", "title": "Gantolandan", "text": "Gantolandan can be found in his &lt;a href=\"Gantolandan%27s%20Home\"&gt;home&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Southeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Southeast Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, sleeping in a bed on the second floor.\nIf you attempt to rob his home, be aware that he'll stir if you tarry too long while on the second floor. If you pretend you're a cat he'll go back to sleep. If you stick around he'll continue to partially wake up and you can continue to pretend you're a cat but he'll eventually wake up and attack you for trespassing in his home.\nQuest.\nThe house is visited during the side quest &lt;a href=\"Narlen%27s%20Heist\"&gt;Narlen's Heist&lt;/a&gt;. "}
{"id": "26808", "revid": "195101", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26808", "title": "Gantolandan's Home", "text": "Gantolandan's Home is the house where &lt;a href=\"Gantolandan\"&gt;Gantolandan&lt;/a&gt; resides and is located in the district of &lt;a href=\"Southeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Southeast Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. The house is a corner house in the cluster of houses that occupy the center of the district. The &lt;a href=\"Blade%20and%20Stars\"&gt;Blade and Stars&lt;/a&gt; is across the street and a &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28southeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23AR1310\"&gt;generic home&lt;/a&gt; is on its left. The front door is unlocked.\nThe ground floor is unpopulated. The chest is locked with a DC of 50 and contains 29 . The bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Fateful%20Coin\"&gt;History of the Fateful Coin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Ulgarth\"&gt;History of the Ulgarth&lt;/a&gt;.\nOn the second floor, Gantolandan can be found sleeping on the middle bed. The chest of drawers is trapped and locked with a DC of 30 for both and contains a &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Stone\"&gt;Rogue Stone&lt;/a&gt;. The bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20VI\"&gt;History of the North VI&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Waterdeep%20I\"&gt;History of Waterdeep I&lt;/a&gt;.\nQuest.\nThe house is visited during the side quest &lt;a href=\"Narlen%27s%20Heist\"&gt;Narlen's Heist&lt;/a&gt;. "}
