{"id": "41060", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41060", "title": "Garock", "text": "Garock is a and &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;chaotic evil&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"minotaur\"&gt;minotaur&lt;/a&gt; in ' and the ', residing inside the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt;. He and his elder brother &lt;a href=\"Rock\"&gt;Rock&lt;/a&gt; will attack &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; after a brief dialog.\nGameplay.\nThe two minotaurs are simple brute force melee fighters. Garock will attack the nearest detected enemy, while being permanently under the normal &lt;a href=\"haste%20effect\"&gt;haste effect&lt;/a&gt; and immune to &lt;a href=\"backstab\"&gt;backstab&lt;/a&gt; attacks. \nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises the creature's script to allow Potion of Superior Healing use when wounded to a certain threshold (twice). The warrior will also empower itself at the start of combat with its innate &lt;a href=\"Power%20Attack\"&gt;Power Attack&lt;/a&gt; ability. The creature also is assigned two pips in single-weapon fighting style. \nGarock can \"dimension jump\" to two different locations based on what the party positioning is.\nDepending on battle conditions, the warrior is scripted to utilize &lt;a href=\"War%20Cry\"&gt;War Cry&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hardiness\"&gt;Hardiness&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Strike\"&gt;Critical Strike&lt;/a&gt;.\nSCS raises the experience level to 23, and assigns a &lt;a href=\"Fighter\"&gt;Fighter&lt;/a&gt; class, but does not change the ability scores or HP. However, the adjusted &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; is now -9, and &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; is -2. Otherwise, the monster is similar to the unmodified game version."}
{"id": "50501", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50501", "title": "Garoll", "text": "Garoll is a patron seated at a table with a fellow drinking companion in the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nIf you initiate conversation with the well inebriated fellow, you may learn of certain hidden activities and how to get access to them. His companion may interject as well.\nHe's open to you buying him a drink and sitting down at the table. You can ask him questions about the Coronet, or the Cowled Wizards and other topics. Don't expect the most clearly enunciated replies though (*burp*)"}
{"id": "48831", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48831", "title": "Garren Windspear", "text": "Garren Windspear is a human paladin who was the lord of the land that bears his name until all he had was destroyed and his lands taken from him by the red dragon &lt;a href=\"Firkraag\"&gt;Firkraag&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nHe will first appear following the &lt;a href=\"Journey%20to%20the%20Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;monster ambush&lt;/a&gt; that greets the party when they explore the &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt; area for the first time. After some brief dialogue about the exact nature of what the party just encountered in that monster ambush, he'll invite the party to his &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Cabin\"&gt;cabin&lt;/a&gt; where they may find sanctuary while they learn more of the situation that they have become embroiled in.\nA cutscene will transport the party to the front of the cabin; whereupon entering the cabin, you'll discover Windspear and his child waiting for you.\nGarren will fully explain his current state of misery and offer to help the party by traveling to &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; to speak with friends that he has within the &lt;a href=\"Most%20Noble%20Order%20of%20the%20Radiant%20Heart\"&gt;Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart&lt;/a&gt; in hopes of persuading the Order to have mercy upon the party for killing members of the Order in that monster ambush.\nWhile he is away, bandits will invade the cabin and kidnap Windspear's child. After killing off the bandits, Garren will reappear and, after gripping at the party for letting his child be kidnapped, come to the realization that it is all the continued tormenting of Firkraag. He'll ask you to &lt;a href=\"Rescue%20Garren%27s%20child%20from%20Firkraag\"&gt;rescue his child&lt;/a&gt; although he's not sure where the bandits may have taken the child. He'll mention some &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Entrance\"&gt;ruins&lt;/a&gt; to the northeast as a possibility.\nGarren will also mention that the Radiant Heart has heard his pleas of the party's virtue and that they demand justice for the slain knights.\nAlternate Option.\nIf you decide not to enter the cabin or refuse Windspear's \"charity\" after the monster ambush, Garren will appear at the &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Entrance\"&gt;Dungeon Entrance&lt;/a&gt; that is marked on the area map if you attempt to enter this area. He will inform the party that his child has been kidnapped, his cabin trashed and blood splattered, and that he found a &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Challenge\"&gt;note&lt;/a&gt; left by the kidnappers (which will be created and placed in your inventory). This event also begins the \"Rescue Garren's child from Firkraag\" side quest."}
{"id": "2497", "revid": "55770344", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2497", "title": "Garrick", "text": "Garrick is a chaotic neutral human &lt;a href=\"bard\"&gt;bard&lt;/a&gt; and a potential &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt; in .\nRecruitment.\nGarrick is available from &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20One\"&gt;Chapter One&lt;/a&gt;. You will find him waiting outside &lt;a href=\"The%20Burning%20Wizard\"&gt;The Burning Wizard&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0He will ask if you are willing to protect his mistress &lt;a href=\"Silke\"&gt;Silke&lt;/a&gt; for 300 gold; accept his offer and then complete the quest, &lt;a href=\"The%20Silke%20Dilemma\"&gt;The Silke Dilemma&lt;/a&gt;, which leads to Silke's death. Speak to Garrick again and allow him to join. If you help Silke instead during the quest he won't join and will vanish from the game. Also if you turn him down when he asks to join you he will vanish, this can easily be solved by accepting him and then kicking him of if you want, he will be available for recruitment again at any time.\nIf you kill Silke before talking to Garrick, he will not be able to respond, and you will not be able to recruit him. However, preemptively killing Silke does not affect your reputation and can solve a difficult fight with a quick backstab.\n\nGarrick can be found in the first floor of the &lt;a href=\"Elfsong%20Tavern%20%28SoD%29\"&gt;Elfsong Tavern&lt;/a&gt;. While he will chat and shares what he knows about the current situation in Baldur's Gate, he is uninterested in joining the player's party as he is smitten with &lt;a href=\"%22Lady%22%20Alyth%20Elendara\"&gt;\"Lady\" Alyth Elendara&lt;/a&gt;. Garrick's feelings to her seem unrequited. \nHe returns in Baldur's Gate II: Shadows of Amn but not as a party member. He can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Temple%20District\"&gt;Athkatla Temple District&lt;/a&gt; trying (or rather \"failing\") to woo &lt;a href=\"Lady%20Irlana\"&gt;Lady Irlana&lt;/a&gt;, a female &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Most%20Noble%20Order%20of%20the%20Radiant%20Heart\"&gt;Radiant Heart&lt;/a&gt;, with the help of &lt;a href=\"Cyrando\"&gt;Cyrando&lt;/a&gt;, a gnome friend. Nervous, he fumbles the lines being recited and gets to saying inappropriate things. When &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; talks with him, he vaguely remembers them, but he doesn't know how he met the party or any names of party members. After some time has passed, when revisiting the same location, the gnome has married the Lady and Garrick, who was playing at the wedding feast, met a woman from &lt;a href=\"Calimshan\"&gt;Calimshan&lt;/a&gt;, whom he accompanies to that southern nation. He won't be encountered again after this.\nTrivia.\nThe scene referred to with Cyrando, a Gnome (presumably having a Big Gnomish Nose) who is enlisted by his \"would-be\" Bard friend to woo a Lady, is most likely an homage to the play \"\" and its subsequent adaptations."}
{"id": "2652", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2652", "title": "Garrison", "text": "The Garrison in &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt;, is the base of operation for the troop of &lt;a href=\"Amnian%20Soldier%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;Amnish Soldiers&lt;/a&gt; that guard the town.\nOn entering you will be threatened with an ass-kicking and told to leave. For once, if you are rude back to the guard, and threaten him, he will apologize and leave. If you comply he will leave anyway.\nLoot.\nAll of the chests in this building are locked and opening any of them summons 3 additional Amnish Soldiers.\nContainer 1 - &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Dagger\"&gt;Throwing Dagger&lt;/a&gt; , 3 \nContainer 2 - 10 \nContainer 3 - Empty\nContainer 4 - &lt;a href=\"Short%20Sword%20%2B1\"&gt;Short Sword +1&lt;/a&gt;, 3 \nContainer 5 - &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Agility\"&gt;Potion of Agility&lt;/a&gt;, 3 \nContainer 6 - &lt;a href=\"Dagger\"&gt;Dagger&lt;/a&gt;, 4 \n&lt;br&gt;\nDialog.\nAmnian Soldier:&lt;br&gt;\"Hey there! Who told ya that ya could come in here?! This place is only for members of the Amnian soldiery. Little snot noses like you, you're not welcome here. Come on, get outta here 'fore I have to kick your butts.\""}
{"id": "39182", "revid": "244611", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39182", "title": "Garrold", "text": "Garrold is one of six would-be adventurers who answered the call of the Coalition to fight against the Shining Crusade of &lt;a href=\"Caelar%20Argent\"&gt;Caelar Argent&lt;/a&gt; during the events of . Garrold is characterized as extremely intelligent and observant, with a sharp memory.\nTraining.\nDuring the quest &lt;a href=\"Troop%20Train\"&gt;Troop Train&lt;/a&gt;, if &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; is a &lt;a href=\"Wizard\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt;, or if they are accompanied by either &lt;a href=\"Dynaheir\"&gt;Dynaheir&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Edwin\"&gt;Edwin&lt;/a&gt;, they can recognize Garrold's mental acuity makes him better suited for the role of a &lt;a href=\"Wizard\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt; than a &lt;a href=\"Fighter\"&gt;Fighter&lt;/a&gt;. Instructing him to dual-class to Wizard is one of the positive decisions required to successfully complete this quest. Note that Dynaheir's or Edwin's advice will only count for half as many points as a protagonist's general advice (which is worth full points for every recruit)."}
{"id": "49267", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49267", "title": "Garuk", "text": "Garuk is a &lt;a href=\"dwarf\"&gt;dwarf&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt; who used to be a member of the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20the%20Eyeless\"&gt;Cult of the Eyeless&lt;/a&gt;, but has since left them to become one of the Cult Outcasts. He can be found in the Lair of the Cult Outcasts, a closed-off section of &lt;a href=\"The%20Old%20Tunnels\"&gt;The Old Tunnels&lt;/a&gt; that requires &lt;a href=\"Gaal%27s%20Key\"&gt;Gaal's Key&lt;/a&gt; to open the Door to the Inner Chambers.Being an ex-cultist, he is blind and no longer has the benefits of a \"type\" of \"sight\" granted by his former god.\n\"I am an old and proud dwarf, me friend, and I beg of ye to help us stop the beholder! I have no eyes yet I will fight to me last breath to kill it! Please...\"\nGiven the chance he will tell you his story.\n\"I be Garuk, my friend...the good Sassar helped me flee from the cult several weeks ago and we have been running and hiding e'er since. We have tried to retrieve a piece of the mystic rod to defeat the beholder... but we can do little without our eyes or the sight bestowed by the creature. 'Tis frustrating. No clan warrior am I without a set of eyes...Sassar be far better off. Talk to him again... help us gain this rod and stop the beholder. You have the gratitude of an old dwarf, me friend. Anything you could do t' help us would be of great aid!\""}
{"id": "50448", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50448", "title": "Gas Cloud", "text": "Gas Cloud is an innate ability effect available to most &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Golem\"&gt;Iron Golem&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Adamantite%20Golem\"&gt;Adamantite Golem&lt;/a&gt; creatures in the game saga. In some ways, it is similar in function as the 5th-level Wizard Spell &lt;a href=\"Cloudkill\"&gt;Cloudkill&lt;/a&gt;, but it is applied on top the golem, has a smaller area of effect, and only has a chance to apply a &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; effect to opponents. \nEffects.\nThe spell effect is interruptible but takes little time to deploy. The scripted targeting will fire over the golem or it can be aimed at a detected target. All creatures within the area of effect and the cloud animation that are not immune to the &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; effect must make a saving throw vs. Death/poison with a -2 penalty or be subject to a \"poisoned\" status effect. The affected creature will have a \"poisoned\" icon displayed and suffer 1 &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt; per second for 18 seconds. The effect is non-magical, and thus bypasses magic resistance, can't be dispelled, and ignores spell level protections such as &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe duration of the innate poison cloud is 3 rounds.\nThe golem exhales this cloud after two rounds of melee combat, and then again five rounds later and continue that interval. It can be dissipated by &lt;a href=\"Zone%20of%20Sweet%20Air\"&gt;Zone of Sweet Air&lt;/a&gt;, but only in &lt;a href=\"Enhanced%20Edition\"&gt;Enhanced Edition&lt;/a&gt;s.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod's AI revisions for the Iron Golem are more aggressive with the use of this cloud ability. It launches it at greater distances from a detected enemy and reapplies the cloud every three rounds."}
{"id": "22886", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22886", "title": "Gate", "text": "Gate may refer to:"}
{"id": "30591", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30591", "title": "Gate (arcane)", "text": ""}
{"id": "30592", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30592", "title": "Gate (divine)", "text": ""}
{"id": "4746", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4746", "title": "Gate (priest)", "text": "The Gate spell summons forth one of the greatest of all baatezu, the &lt;a href=\"Pit%20Fiend\"&gt;Pit Fiend&lt;/a&gt;. The only differences between this spell and &lt;a href=\"Gate%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;wizard version&lt;/a&gt; are that this version has a much shorter casting time and is a level 7 spell (instead of level 9), meaning Cleric/Mages are able to put it in a &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Contingency\"&gt;Chain Contingency&lt;/a&gt; (as it only accepts spells up to level 8).\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a point on the map location within range where the gated demon shall appear - this is done by using the targeting cursor to designate the point on the map.\nWhen the spell is finished an infernal gate graphic animation renders at the caster's targeting point, and a few seconds later the fiend appears on the map, ready to attack any creatures in its detection range, as determined by the creature's default AI script.\nThis fiend is unable to leave the area map it is teleported to and cannot follow the party to another map area.\nWhen the spell's duration expires the fiend disappears from the material plane, with a brief lighting effect and a text reading \"Pit Fiend: Unsummoned\". \nA summoned fiend killed in combat leaves a corpse behind on the map.\nThis spell interacts with the summoning cap in a way that's different than most summoning spells, in that summoned demons/devils do not add to the total towards the summoning cap (meaning, it's technically possible to summon as many demons/devils as you are able to). \nHowever, the spell still respects the summoning cap, meaning you won't be able to summon a demon if you already have 5 non-demon creatures summoned.\nAs a \"GoodButRed\" creature (i.e. technically allied to the party, but has a red circle), the Pit Fiend gated in by this spell doesn't get a save against &lt;a href=\"Otiluke%27s%20Resilient%20Sphere\"&gt;Otiluke's Resilient Sphere&lt;/a&gt;, just like what happens with regular (blue circle) allied creatures.\nMultiple party summoned demons aren't friendly toward each other - they can and will treat others as enemies - however, a &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Evil%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Protection From Evil (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Evil%2C%2010%27%20Radius\"&gt;Protection From Evil, 10' Radius&lt;/a&gt; can be cast upon these party summoned fiends, so they do not target each other.\nThe player's party do not gain experience for enemies whom this gated fiend kills.\nAny party summoned fiends are technically allied to party and will provoke any neutral NPC to \"agro\" as if you attacked them yourself.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset and the Gate (Priest Spell) requires that the summoner name the creature to come through the gate, and it isn't necessarily an evil being such as a fiend. The spell ages the Priest by 5 years. See the External Links below.\nA player's suggested Solo party member tactic.\nAs mentioned above, unlike the wizard version, this spell is only level 7, meaning it can be put into a Chain Contingency. Normally, summoning multiple demons at once is a bad idea, as they'll fight each other, but it's possible to avoid that via casting some form of protection from evil on every single one of them. With that in mind, it's possible for a high-level Cleric/Mage to have 3 Pit Fiends (or any other combination of demons) out at once, in a convenient way, via use of this spell, the aforementioned Chain Contingency, &lt;a href=\"Contingency\"&gt;Contingency&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Evil%2C%2010%27%20Radius\"&gt;Protection From Evil, 10' Radius&lt;/a&gt;.\nFirst, cast Chain Contingency (any condition, but with target \"myself\") and select any combination of demon-summoning spells you want (e.g. Gate or even one of each: Gate, &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Fiend\"&gt;Summon Fiend&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Cacofiend\"&gt;Cacofiend&lt;/a&gt;). Then, cast Contingency (same condition as before and target \"myself\", once again) and select Protection from Evil 10' Radius as the spell to be used.\nSince the two contingencies have the same condition, they fire off simultaneously and, once it happens, all three gated demons (as well as the player, of course) will immediately be protected against evil (even before their gating process is finished) and won't attack each other.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has replaced Gate (priest) with the spell described below:\nSummon Death Knight\nLevel: 7\nSchool: Necromancy\nSphere: All\nRange: Medium\nDuration: 3 turns\nCasting Time: 1 round\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nBy means of this spell, the caster calls an outer planar creature to attack his foes and himself if not careful. The creature summoned in is a Death Knight, a powerful undead demon. The creature cannot be directly controlled, but the summoner can attempt to compel the demon to perform a service for him for the duration of the spell. Charismatic and powerful casters may bind the creature\u2019s will, intelligent and wise ones may negotiate with it, but dealing with these demonic creatures is always dangerous, and sometimes it may lead to disaster. Priests are warned to be careful of this spell, for a mistreated Death Knight will turn on his summoner at the first available opportunity.\nDeath Knight (13 Hit Dice):\nSTR 18/00, DEX 12, CON -, INT 17, WIS 15, CHA 16; AL Lawful Evil\nHP 112, AC -4, THAC0 1, Saving Throws 5/7/5/9/7\n3 Attacks Per Round, 2d6+11 Slashing Damage (Two-Handed Sword +3)\nSpecial Qualities:\nAura of Fear: creatures in a 5\u2019 radius must save vs. spell each round or flee in terror for 1 round\nImmune to non-magical weapons\nImmune to charm, confusion, hold, stun, sleep, poison, &amp; death effects\nCold Resistance 100%; Physical Resistance 20%; Magic Resistance 75%\nSpecial Abilities:\nSee Invisibility (permanent)\nDispel Magic (once every 5 rounds)\nUnholy Fireball (once per day)\nPower Words: Blind, Stun, or Kill (once per day each)\nSymbols: of Weakness or Death (once per day each)"}
{"id": "16432", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16432", "title": "Gate (wizard)", "text": "When a wizard casts Gate, he summons forth one of the greatest of all baatezu, the &lt;a href=\"Pit%20Fiend\"&gt;pit fiend&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a point on the map location within range where the gated demon shall appear - this is done by using the targeting cursor to designate the point on the map.\nWhen the spell is finished an infernal gate graphic animation renders at the caster's targeting point, and a few seconds later the fiend appears on the map, ready to attack any creatures in its detection range, as determined by the creature's default AI script.\nThis fiend is unable to leave the area map it is teleported to and cannot follow the party to another map area.\nWhen the spell's duration expires the fiend disappears from the material plane, with a brief lighting effect and a text reading \"Pit Fiend: Unsummoned\". \nA summoned fiend killed in combat leaves a corpse behind on the map.\nThis spell interacts with the summoning cap in a way that's different than most summoning spells, in that summoned demons/devils do not add to the total towards the summoning cap (meaning, it's technically possible to summon as many demons/devils as you are able to). \nHowever, the spell still respects the summoning cap, meaning you won't be able to summon a demon if you already have 5 non-demon creatures summoned.\nAs a \"GoodButRed\" creature (i.e. technically allied to the party, but has a red circle), the Pit Fiend gated in by this spell doesn't get a save against &lt;a href=\"Otiluke%27s%20Resilient%20Sphere\"&gt;Otiluke's Resilient Sphere&lt;/a&gt;, just like what happens with regular (blue circle) allied creatures.\nMultiple party summoned demons aren't friendly toward each other - they can and will treat others as enemies - however, a &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Evil%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Protection From Evil (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Evil%2C%2010%27%20Radius\"&gt;Protection From Evil, 10' Radius&lt;/a&gt; can be cast upon these party summoned fiends, so they do not target each other.\nThe player's party do not gain experience for enemies whom this gated fiend kills.\nAny party summoned fiends are technically allied to party and will provoke any neutral NPC to \"agro\" as if you attacked them yourself.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset and the Gate (Wizard Spell) says that casting this spell will age the caster 5-years. See the External Links below.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its duration, effects, and description. See below:\nGate\nLevel: 9\nSchool: Conjuration\nRange: Medium\nDuration: 3 turns\nCasting Time: 1 round\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nBy means of this spell, the caster calls an outer planar creature to attack his foes and himself if not careful. The creature summoned in is a Pit Fiend, the most powerful specimen of the Baatezu. The creature cannot be directly controlled, but the summoner can attempt to compel the demon to perform a service for him for the duration of the spell. Charismatic and powerful casters may bind the creature\u2019s will, intelligent and wise ones may negotiate with it, but dealing with these demonic creatures is always dangerous, and sometimes it may lead to disaster. Mages are warned to be careful of this spell, for a mistreated Pit Fiend will turn on his summoner at the first available opportunity, tear him and his companion's apart piece by piece and then feast on the remains.\nPit Fiend (20 Hit Dice):\nSTR 24, DEX 16, CON 19, INT 20, WIS 16, CHA 25; AL Lawful Evil\nHP 170, AC -8, THAC0 -7, Saving Throws 4/6/4/8/6\n5 Attacks Per Round, 2d6+16 Piercing Damage (Claws, Bite, &amp; Tail +4)\nCombat Abilities (20% chance each):\nDisease: creatures struck by a pit fiend\u2019s bite attack must save vs. death at -4 or be infected with a vile disease known as devil chills, losing 2 points of strength after an incubation period of 12 hours\nPoison: a pit fiend\u2019s bite injects a lethal poison which inflicts 10 points of damage every second for 2 rounds unless a save vs. poison at -4 penalty is made\nConstrict: creatures struck by the pit fiend\u2019s tail must save vs. death at -4 to avoid being stunned for 1 round\nSpecial Qualities:\nImmune to weapons lower than +3 enchantment\nImmune to confusion, fear, poison, &amp; stun effects\nRegeneration: 2hp/round\nFire Resistance 100%; Cold Resistance 50%; Magic Resistance 65%\nSpecial Abilities:\nSee Invisibility (permanent)\nImproved Invisibility (at will)\nFireball (once every 5 rounds)\nDispel Magic (once every 5 rounds)\nSymbol of Weakness (once every 5 rounds)\nUnholy Word (once per day)\nMeteor Swarm (once per day)"}
