{"id": "2069", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2069", "title": "Gatewarden", "text": "The Gatewarden can be found in &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Prologue\"&gt;Prologue&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Six\"&gt;Chapter Six&lt;/a&gt;.\nPrologue.\nHe approaches you as you pass through the south-eastern section of the fortress and offers &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; a session of training, as the leader of an impromptu party, in the &lt;a href=\"Storage%20Cellars\"&gt;Storage Cellars&lt;/a&gt;. This helps you understand how to fight in the game.\n\"Dialogue\".\n\"Soon be gone, will ye? Aye, Gorion arsked me to teach you a whit about the finer arts o' mass combat 'afore ye leave. Can I pique yer int'rest with it, &lt;Gorion's Ward&gt;?\"\nHe offers again:\n\"Are ye sure, little one? It would be best ye took the time to learn it now rather than curse yer ignorance later. Gorion himself arsked me to do this deed and I'll not offer it to ye twice.\"\nIf you refuse his offer both times he walks away, (apparently into the &lt;a href=\"Clinic\"&gt;Clinic&lt;/a&gt;, but you will not find him there if you follow), and does not return. The Storage Cellars then remain inaccessible; not so much as a locked door is to be found.\nIf you accept his offer and follow him:\nIf you speak to him again later:\nChapter Six.\nWhen Gorion's Ward returns to Candlekeep in chapter six, the Gatewarden will be on the sixth floor of the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Library\"&gt;Library&lt;/a&gt;. He will arrest the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; on sight for killing the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt; leaders (whether they actually did or not).\n\"Dialogue\".\n\"You there! Stop and surrender yourself. You are accused of murdering the men Brunos Costak, Thaldorn Tenhevich, and Rieltar Anchev. If you give yourself up now, you will be assured of a fair trial.\"\nAnd with that, it's off to the jail in the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Barracks\"&gt;barracks&lt;/a&gt; for Gorion's Ward and the party."}
{"id": "40668", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40668", "title": "Gather the four scepter keys", "text": "Gather the four scepter keys is a side quest introduced when first entering the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt; main portal room.\nIn terms of classifying this as a \"Side quest\", the reason for that label is that it is not necessary to complete this quest in order for &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; to advance the main story. Watcher's Keep and everything within, pursued, and potentially accomplished is all optional. \nAquisition.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Chromatic%20Demon\"&gt;Chromatic Demon&lt;/a&gt; initiates dialogue with the party as soon as they step through the portal gate from the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Altar Level&lt;/a&gt; to the Elemental level.\nA conversation with the demon occurs, and the player must make dialogue selections to ask questions, and determine what the fiend knows, and why it's in that cage. At some point, regardless of whether the party trusts the demon or not, it is understood that the only way to move forward further into the keep, is to agree to help the demon escape in order for it to provide a means to unlock the portal gate. There is no other way.\nThe party will eventually remark:\nThe demon will reply:\nAt this time the player's Journal registers the side quest:\n\"I have entered into a bargain with a chromatic demon, though I had little choice. I need to gather the four scepter keys to unlock his elemental cage. Only then will he give me access to the level below.\".\nGameplay.\nThe party is unsure how to obtain the scepter keys, nor where they are exactly. \nIt's understood that the scepters are somewhere on this keep's level and must be found. Further exploration is the only option to reveal answers and a solution to this quest.\nSee the walkthrough on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt; page for a step-by-step path to death or glory.\nThere are only two journal entries in this quest. This laid back and simpler journal entry approach is a feature in the Throne of Bhaal portion of the game, as compared to the previous chapters 1 through 7."}
