{"id": "3760", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3760", "title": "Gauntlets of Dexterity", "text": "Gauntlets of Dexterity, also known as The Brawling Hands, set the &lt;a href=\"dexterity\"&gt;dexterity&lt;/a&gt; of the wearer to 18 and gives all related bonuses. If their dexterity is naturally higher, the gauntlets will reduce it. They have a weight of 2 lbs.\nGameplay.\nDue to their nature, party members with low dexterity are the best choice for wearing the gauntlets. They especially benefit melee characters, who gain the most out of the dexterity &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; bonus."}
