{"id": "13816", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13816", "title": "Geas", "text": "A Geas is a spell used to seal an oath or to force someone to do the caster's bidding. Should the target of a geas spell fail in their quest or break their oath, they will suffer dire consequences, like grievous pain and/or death.\nThe geas spell cannot be dispelled by any conventional means like &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Curse\"&gt;Remove Curse&lt;/a&gt;. The only way to remove geas in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;the first game&lt;/a&gt; is to use the &lt;a href=\"Geas%20Removal%20Scroll\"&gt;Geas Removal Scroll&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Jalantha%20Mistmyr\"&gt;Jalantha Mistmyr&lt;/a&gt; during the quest &lt;a href=\"Marek%20and%20Lothander\"&gt;Marek and Lothander&lt;/a&gt;."}
