{"id": "45653", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45653", "title": "Geld Quickblade", "text": "Geld Quickblade is a character in , and part of &lt;a href=\"Rasaad%27s%20Journey\"&gt;Rasaad's Journey&lt;/a&gt; quest. \nGameplay.\nHe appears in the &lt;a href=\"Abandoned%20Amphitheater\"&gt;Abandoned Amphitheater&lt;/a&gt; forest pathway and offers to sell a safe path through the woods for . &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; can bargain the price for or refuse him. \nIf he's refused, he'll activate four hidden traps on the pathway to the north of his starting location. He and his &lt;a href=\"Dire%20Wolf\"&gt;Dire Wolf&lt;/a&gt; allies also ambush the party later if he's refused. He drops some arms and armor, various potions, and a &lt;a href=\"Worn%20Pamphlet\"&gt;Worn Pamphlet&lt;/a&gt; when killed. \nIt is possible to kill Geld before he leaves the starting area - if you are quick and deal enough damage rapidly. Naturally, this stops the ambush sequence and the appearance of all the Dire Wolves. Geld is really only a danger if he succeeds in using a quaffing of invisibility and backstabbing a party member with low hit points."}
{"id": "48376", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48376", "title": "Gellal", "text": "Gellal is one of the vampires encountered in &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs\"&gt;Bodhi's Hideout&lt;/a&gt; during the events of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%203\"&gt;Chapter 3&lt;/a&gt;, if you have &lt;a href=\"Aran%27s%20tasks%20to%20receive%20the%20Shadow%20Thieves%27%20aid\"&gt;decided to side&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt; in the guild war between the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bodhi%27s%20Vampire%20Coven\"&gt;Bodhi's Vampire Coven&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nGellal is found with the Lower Tombs in Chapter 3 and is just one of the protectors in Bohdi's hideout.\nHe has 67 hit points and provides 14,500 XP when killed. Once he is killed, he'll transform into his gaseous form and drift back to his coffin, where he must be &lt;a href=\"Wooden%20Stake\"&gt;staked&lt;/a&gt; to permanently kill him.\nGellal has a simplified script in this encounter that triggers dialogue and a general melee attack plan. He uses no &lt;a href=\"Domination%20%28Innate%29\"&gt;Vampire Domination&lt;/a&gt; abilities. Durst has the hit points and abilities of a &lt;a href=\"Fledgling%20Vampire\"&gt;Fledgling Vampire&lt;/a&gt;, but a much higher experience point reward.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; and the \"Improved Vampires\" component makes some revisions to Gellal. The mod assigns a new default script for the vampire, to recognize party member immunities to level drain and other protections for better targeting and tactics. Gellal is now a level 12/12 Fighter/Thief class, with 20 STR, 20 DEX, 19 CON, 145 HP, an adjusted &lt;a href=\"Attacks%20per%20round\"&gt;Attacks per round&lt;/a&gt; of 2.5, THAC0 3, and Armor Class -3. He can only be struck with +2 enchanted weapons or greater. Gellal may use any of the SCS standard vampire innate abilities such as Vampire Domination, shapeshift to bat or wolf, and has the CON draining melee attack to go along with the level drain."}
{"id": "12688", "revid": "3983911", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12688", "title": "Gellana", "text": ""}
