{"id": "41529", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41529", "title": "General Store (AR1116)", "text": "Some &lt;a href=\"commoner\"&gt;commoner&lt;/a&gt;s browse the wares of the northernmost of the three general stores at varying times of the day, and nobody cares about the &lt;a href=\"short%20sword\"&gt;short sword&lt;/a&gt; being taken out of one of the big shelves or finding the 44 &lt;a href=\"gold%20piece\"&gt;gold piece&lt;/a&gt;s somebody left in another one.\nLayout.\nThis is a single-floor building with a door that opens to the center of &lt;a href=\"Southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Southwest Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, just around the corner from the &lt;a href=\"Seven%20Suns\"&gt;Seven Suns&lt;/a&gt; compound and across the street from the &lt;a href=\"Ye%20Olde%20Inn\"&gt;Ye Olde Inn&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"Potion%20Shop\"&gt;Potion Shop&lt;/a&gt; is located behind it. Generic store furniture \u2013 such as shelves and tables \u2013 divide the single room, break line of sight and create small sections. The &lt;a href=\"Storekeeps%20%28southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;storekeep&lt;/a&gt; can be found standing behind the tables, while the customers are roaming.\n&lt;a href=\"Rogues\"&gt;Rogues&lt;/a&gt; can try to steal from the shop, with a &lt;a href=\"Pick%20Pockets\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; of thirty-five usually being sufficient; if that fails, a &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Enforcer%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23FLAMEN\"&gt;Flaming Fist Enforcer&lt;/a&gt; and two &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Enforcer%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23FLAMEN2\"&gt;comrades&lt;/a&gt; are summoned to arrest the &lt;a href=\"Party\"&gt;thieves&lt;/a&gt;.\nInvolvement.\nThis store offers a standard range of &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20weapons\"&gt;throwing&lt;/a&gt; and other ranged &lt;a href=\"weapons\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;. Of note are the twenty-five &lt;a href=\"arrows%20of%20piercing\"&gt;arrows of piercing&lt;/a&gt; that can be found among regular &lt;a href=\"ammunition\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt;, of which there is an unlimited stock. If it's about selling &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt;s here, a wider range of them is accepted, including melee weapons, &lt;a href=\"armor\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt; and some other stuff; see below for a detailed list of what can be divested at a &lt;a href=\"depreciation%20rate\"&gt;depreciation rate&lt;/a&gt; of only three percent.\n&lt;a href=\"Identify\"&gt;Identification&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"magical%20item\"&gt;magical item&lt;/a&gt;s is not offered."}
{"id": "41525", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41525", "title": "General Store (AR1117)", "text": "This General Store is one of three &lt;a href=\"General%20Store\"&gt;general stores&lt;/a&gt; that are located in &lt;a href=\"Southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Southwest Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. This store is the red building located in a tight cluster of three buildings in the southeast section of the district, with the &lt;a href=\"Merchants%27%20League%20Estate\"&gt;Merchants' League Estate&lt;/a&gt; next door and another &lt;a href=\"General%20Store%20%28AR1112%29\"&gt;general store&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sunin%27s%20Home\"&gt;Sunin's Home&lt;/a&gt; right across the street.\nLayout.\nThis is a single-floor building with two rooms that are comprised of the main shop area and a separate ancillary store room. A single door opens to the south. Besides some shelves, many crates and barrels are lined up along the walls or placed in the corners of the shop. The &lt;a href=\"Storekeeps%20%28southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;storekeep&lt;/a&gt;, who trades all day, all week, stands in the center of his store. From the early morning hours of 5:30 am until 9:30 in the evening, a couple of &lt;a href=\"Commoner\"&gt;men&lt;/a&gt; browse the wares of this general store while later in the day a &lt;a href=\"boy\"&gt;boy&lt;/a&gt; joins them at 7:30 am, followed by a woman who appears at 8:30 am, both of whom leave again at 8:30 pm.\nThievery.\nOnly the barrel to the left of the counter can be examined without risk in the \"\". Opening any &lt;a href=\"Thief%23Open%20Locks\"&gt;locked container&lt;/a&gt; needs a skill of only ten, yielding some &lt;a href=\"experience\"&gt;experience&lt;/a&gt;, but a look inside these containers will summon the authorities if not opened by somebody &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;invisible&lt;/a&gt; or a &lt;a href=\"shadowdancer\"&gt;shadowdancer&lt;/a&gt; using their &lt;a href=\"Shadowstep\"&gt;abilities&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Rogues\"&gt;Rogues&lt;/a&gt; can try to steal from the shop, with a &lt;a href=\"Pick%20Pockets\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; of twenty-five usually being sufficient. But, if stealing or container snooping fails, a &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Enforcer%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23FLAMEN\"&gt;Flaming Fist Enforcer&lt;/a&gt; and two &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Enforcer%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23FLAMEN2\"&gt;comrades&lt;/a&gt; are summoned to arrest the &lt;a href=\"Party\"&gt;thieves&lt;/a&gt;.\nAll of these containers are unsecured in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\".\nInvolvement.\nOnly a few and &lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"weapons\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;, a piece of such &lt;a href=\"armor\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Girdles\"&gt;girdle&lt;/a&gt; are offered, while the range of the store is acquiring includes more ; see &lt;a href=\"%23STO1117\"&gt;below&lt;/a&gt; for a detailed list of what can be divested at a &lt;a href=\"depreciation%20rate\"&gt;depreciation rate&lt;/a&gt; of twenty-five percent.\nAll &lt;a href=\"magical%20item\"&gt;magical item&lt;/a&gt;s can be &lt;a href=\"Identify\"&gt;identified&lt;/a&gt; for the usual rate of one hundred &lt;a href=\"gp\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt;."}
