{"id": "10843", "revid": "78773", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10843", "title": "Generic Tavern and Inn (Baldur's Gate)", "text": "The city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; contains four generic Tavern and Inn buildings which do not serve much purpose in the overall story but do provide additional places to find rest and booze. The purpose of this page is to provide information for all four of these buildings in one place and thereby eliminate the need for separate pages. \nAll of these buildings have a standard layout of two floors with a &lt;a href=\"Bartender\"&gt;bartender&lt;/a&gt; on the ground floor and multiple &lt;a href=\"Commoner\"&gt;commoners and townsfolk&lt;/a&gt; found throughout both floors. Two have bartenders and gaming tables on the second floor while the other two have rooms. All provide rooms ranging from Peasant to Royal and serve the same six kinds of drinks.\nThe two establishments with rooms on the second floor all contain lootable chests, some of which are locked, although not all containers have loot in them. All locks have a difficulty class of 30 for a &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; to be able to &lt;a href=\"Thief%23Open_Locks\"&gt;open them&lt;/a&gt;. The bartenders all carry gold but are virtually impossible to pickpocket. The commoners and gamesman carry no gold.\nThree out of the four taverns also have named NPCs inside although none of them are crucial to the story plot. Speaking with the townsfolk will provide some limited information about current events but nothing of critical importance.\nTavern and Inn.\nThis Tavern and Inn is located against a corner of the inner wall, next to a &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28northwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;generic house&lt;/a&gt; and across from the &lt;a href=\"Entar%20Silvershield%27s%20Estate\"&gt;Entar Silvershield Estate&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Northwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Northwest Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe ground floor has a bartender and two commoners.\nThe second floor has one male townsfolk and six rooms, each with a locked container. Five of the six containers contain the following loot:\nTavern and Inn.\nThis Tavern and Inn is located against the eastern wall next to the &lt;a href=\"Shop%20of%20Silence\"&gt;Shop of Silence&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"East%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;East Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. \nBoth floors have a bartender and three townsfolk. There are no lootable containers within this building and no named NPCs.\nTavern and Inn.\nThis Tavern and Inn is located against the western wall next to &lt;a href=\"Sunin%27s%20Home\"&gt;Sunin's Home&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Southwest Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe ground floor has a bartender and fifteen townsfolk.\nOn the second floor is a gambling den run by a &lt;a href=\"Gamesman\"&gt;Gamesman&lt;/a&gt;, a bartender, and nine townsfolk. The only container in the place is a barrel next to the bar that contains a &lt;a href=\"mace\"&gt;mace&lt;/a&gt;.\nInn and Tavern.\nThis Inn and Tavern is located against the eastern wall across from an abandoned house and &lt;a href=\"Well-Adjusted%20Al%27s%20General%20Store\"&gt;Well Adjusted Al's general store&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Southeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Southeast Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe ground floor has a bartender and five townsfolk. There is a barrel that contains a &lt;a href=\"club\"&gt;club&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor has two female commoners during the day and two sleeping woman at night. There are six rooms, each with a chest, only one of which is locked and contains 23 while the other five are empty. "}
{"id": "38215", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38215", "title": "Generic homes (Beregost)", "text": "The town of &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt; is full of generic homes which do not serve much purpose in the overall story. This list contains information on any home not already named in-game or without a central defining occupant who owns the house (e.g. &lt;a href=\"Firebead%27s%20Home\"&gt;Firebead's Home&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mirianne%27s%20Home\"&gt;Mirianne's Home&lt;/a&gt;, etc.).\nOne convenient method of differentiating between these homes is referring to them by their internal &lt;a href=\"Areas\"&gt;area codes&lt;/a&gt; as defined by the game's developers. All twenty-three homes are listed below in sequential order by their area code. However, the game developers didn't always follow any type of definitive pattern specific to these generic homes when assigning area codes to the homes. The infobox to the right has an area image of Beregost that identifies every generic home by its corresponding number in the infobox name.\nUnless otherwise specified, assume that NPCs carry nothing, containers are unlocked, and that NPCs will call the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Enforcer%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23FLAMEN.cre%2C%20FLAMEN2.cre\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; if they witness the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; looting their containers. Locks all have a specific difficulty class for a &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; to be able to &lt;a href=\"Thief%23Open_Locks\"&gt;open them&lt;/a&gt;, referred to here as the lock's.\nSome of the commoner's present in the homes are given actual names; either gleaned through dialogue or from the greeting choice in the sound dialogue section in the creatures game file. Most of these are not \"true stand-alone\" characters who are given their own named creature file. Exceptions include Alain along with Mr. Colquetle and his Butler. The rest are just typical commoners with names. \nGeneric Home.\nThis house is located to the left of the &lt;a href=\"Thunderhammer%20Smithy\"&gt;Thunderhammer Smithy&lt;/a&gt; and faces the rear of the &lt;a href=\"Jovial%20Juggler\"&gt;Jovial Juggler&lt;/a&gt;. The front door is locked.\nThe ground floor is unpopulated. The chest is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Agni%20Mani%20Necklace\"&gt;Agni Mani Necklace&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Ring\"&gt;Silver Ring&lt;/a&gt;. The chest of drawers contains a &lt;a href=\"Long%20Sword\"&gt;Long Sword&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house has a bright blue roof and is located in the group of houses that contains the fountain and the Jovial Juggler. Generic home ten is on its right, generic home three is to the left, and it faces the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Sheaf\"&gt;Red Sheaf&lt;/a&gt; inn. The front door is unlocked and hidden from view.\nThe ground floor is populated all day and night by two male &lt;a href=\"commoners\"&gt;commoners&lt;/a&gt;. Conversation reveals that one of them is an old man named Solgen and that the house is his. The other commoner's name is never given by either of them. The chest is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Turquoise%20Gem\"&gt;Turquoise Gem&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping elf. Both nightstands are empty. The chest is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Short%20Sword\"&gt;Short Sword&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house has a dark blue roof and is also located in the group of houses that contains the fountain and the Jovial Juggler. Generic home two is on its right, generic home twelve is to the left, and it faces both &lt;a href=\"The%20Burning%20Wizard\"&gt;The Burning Wizard&lt;/a&gt; and the Red Sheaf inn. The front door is unlocked and hidden from view.\nThe ground floor is populated all day and night by a female commoner. The chest is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Dagger\"&gt;Dagger&lt;/a&gt;, a suit of &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Mail\"&gt;Chain Mail&lt;/a&gt; and 9 .\nThe second floor is unpopulated. Both nightstands are empty. The chest is locked and contains 38 and a &lt;a href=\"Sunstone%20Gem\"&gt;Sunstone Gem&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house appears \"L-shaped\" (albeit upside down) and occupies the near corner of the row of houses that face in the direction of the Red Sheaf inn and generic home eight. Generic home one is behind it and generic home five is to its right. The front door is unlocked and hidden from view.\nThe ground floor is populated during the day by a female commoner and at night by a sleeping man and woman. The chest in the far right corner is locked and contains a dagger, a short sword, and a suit of &lt;a href=\"Splint%20Mail\"&gt;Splint Mail&lt;/a&gt;. The chest near the bed is empty.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is the middle one of the three that face in the direction of the Red Sheaf inn. Generic home four is to its left and generic home seven to its right. Generic home eight is directly across the street. The front door is unlocked and hidden from view.\nThe ground floor is populated by a male commoner who introduces himself as Borland of Beregost. Depending on his &lt;a href=\"Reaction\"&gt;Reaction&lt;/a&gt; to you he'll either:\nThe chest next to the first bed is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Axe\"&gt;Battle Axe&lt;/a&gt;. The chest between the two beds is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Necklace\"&gt;Silver Necklace&lt;/a&gt;. The chest of drawers is empty.\nWhen &lt;a href=\"Charmed\"&gt;charmed&lt;/a&gt; all he will say is:\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is located behind the Thunderhammer Smithy and &lt;a href=\"Mirianne%27s%20Home\"&gt;Mirianne's Home&lt;/a&gt; is on its left. Generic homes one and four are situated behind it. The front door is unlocked and hidden from view.\nThe ground floor is populated at night by a sleeping man and woman. The chest next to the first bed is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Gold%20Ring\"&gt;Gold Ring&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Leather%20Armor\"&gt;Leather Armor&lt;/a&gt;. The chest between the two beds contains a dagger. The chest of drawers is empty.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is the far-end house in the row of three that face in the direction of the Red Sheaf inn. Generic home five is on its left and Mirianne's home is located behind it. The front door is unlocked and hidden from view.\nThe ground floor is populated by a male commoner that, depending on his reaction to you, he'll either:\nIf you charm him, he'll provide the following:\nwhich leads to the a &lt;a href=\"Journal\"&gt;Journal&lt;/a&gt; entry in the quest section under the title \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Mage%27s%20School\"&gt;The Wizard's School&lt;/a&gt;\"\nThe chest next to the first bed is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Agility\"&gt;Potion of Agility&lt;/a&gt;. The chest between the two beds is locked and contains a long sword. The chest of drawers contains a dagger.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is located next to the Red Sheaf inn and generic homes five and seven are across the street. The front door is locked.\nThe ground floor is populated all day and night by a male and female commoner. Conversation reveals that they're married and the husband is named Davis. The female commoner's name is never given by either of them. The chest is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Diamond\"&gt;Diamond&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping man. Both nightstands are empty. The chest is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Light%20Crossbow\"&gt;Light Crossbow&lt;/a&gt; and three &lt;a href=\"Bolt\"&gt;Bolt&lt;/a&gt;s.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is tallest house on the far-end of a row of three homes located to the left of the Burning Wizard. It faces towards generic homes fifteen and sixteen. The front door is unlocked and hidden from view.\nThe ground floor is populated all day and night by a male commoner. The barrel in the kitchen is empty.\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping halfling in the smaller bedroom. In the bigger bedroom, both nightstands are empty. The chest of drawers is locked and is\u00a0empty. The bookshelf contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Dragon%20Coast\"&gt;History of the Dragon Coast&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is located in the group of houses that contains the fountain and the Jovial Juggler. Generic home two is on its left and the back-end of the Jovial Juggler is on the right. The front door is unlocked and hidden from view.\nThe ground floor is populated all day and night by female commoner who carries a silver ring. The chest is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Crossbow\"&gt;Heavy Crossbow&lt;/a&gt;. The bookshelves contain copies of the History of the Dragon Coast and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20VI\"&gt;History of Shadowdale VI&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor is populated all day and night by a sleeping man and woman. The chest of drawers is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Mace\"&gt;Mace&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Heroism\"&gt;Potion of Heroism&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Jasper%20Gem\"&gt;Jasper Gem&lt;/a&gt;. The bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Durpar%20and%20Var%20the%20Golden\"&gt;History of Durpar and Var the Golden&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Halruaa\"&gt;History of Halruaa&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is located to the right of the Burning Wizard and faces towards &lt;a href=\"Feldepost%27s%20Inn\"&gt;Feldepost's Inn&lt;/a&gt;. The front door is locked.\nOn the ground floor is a male commoner named &lt;a href=\"Alain\"&gt;Alain&lt;/a&gt;. Upon being spoken too, his first reaction is surprise then disgust at being interrupted. After the third attempt he'll call six &lt;a href=\"Guard\"&gt;Guard&lt;/a&gt;s. If you defeat the guards, your reputation will be reduced to near zero, and the game may crash.\nThe chest is locked and contains a dagger and 14 .\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping woman. The nightstand on the right contains a silver ring and 19 . The other nightstand and the chest are empty.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is located in the group of houses that contains the fountain and the Jovial Juggler. &lt;a href=\"Firebead%27s%20Home\"&gt;Firebead Elvenhair's Home&lt;/a&gt; is on its left and generic home three on the right. It faces towards the obelisk in the center of town and the front door is unlocked and hidden from view.\nWhen you enter the ground floor you'll encounter a &lt;a href=\"Butler\"&gt;Butler&lt;/a&gt; standing in the foyer. &lt;a href=\"Mr.%20Colquetle\"&gt;Mr. Colquetle&lt;/a&gt; is standing in the living room near the fireplace. Speaking with Mr. Colquetle could alter your &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt; for the better or worse and gain the party some XP to boot.\nThe barrel in the kitchen contains 13 .\nThe second floor is populated day and night by a sleeping dwarf in the small bedroom and a sleeping man in the big bedroom. The nightstand next to the sleeping man contains 4 and the other one is empty. The chest of drawers contains 8 and the bookshelf contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20VIII\"&gt;History of Shadowdale VIII&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is on the near-end of the group of houses that contains the fountain and the Jovial Juggler. Firebead Elvenhair's home is on the right and it faces towards the pair of generic homes located on the right side of Feldpost's Inn. The front door is unlocked and hidden from view.\nOn the ground floor there are two female commoners milling about day and night. The chest is locked and contains 11 and a jasper gem. The bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Fateful%20Coin\"&gt;History of the Fateful Coin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Drow%20II\"&gt;History of the Drow II&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor is populated day and night by a young boy and a sleeping man. The trapped and locked chest of drawers contains 11 and a &lt;a href=\"Andar%20Gem\"&gt;Andar Gem&lt;/a&gt;. The bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Last%20March%20of%20the%20Giants\"&gt;History of the Last March of the Giants&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Moonsea\"&gt;History of the Moonsea&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is the middle house on the row of three homes located to the left of the Burning Wizard. Generic home nine is on its right and the back of generic home eleven faces its left side. It faces towards generic home seventeen. The front door is unlocked and hidden from view.\nThe ground floor is unpopulated. The chest is locked and contains 9 . The bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20I\"&gt;History of the North I&lt;/a&gt; and History of the Moonsea.\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping man and woman. The chest of drawers is locked and contains a short sword, a dagger, and 5 . The bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20IV\"&gt;History of the North IV&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20VII\"&gt;History of the North VII&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nIf you were to enter Beregost for the first time from the north this will be the first house you'll encounter. Generic home sixteen is to the right and the house faces towards &lt;a href=\"Travenhurst%20Manor\"&gt;Travenhurst Manor&lt;/a&gt;. The front door is visible when highlighted and is unlocked.\nThe ground floor is populated day and night by a female commoner. In the living room, the armoire is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Spear\"&gt;Spear&lt;/a&gt;, 13 ,\u00a0and a &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Agate%20Gem\"&gt;Fire Agate Gem&lt;/a&gt;. Regarding the two chest of drawers on either side of the fireplace, the left side one is empty\u00a0while the right side one is locked and contains 10 and a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Insight\"&gt;Potion of Insight&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor is populated day and night by a sleeping dwarf and a sleeping man. The chest of drawers is locked and contains 13 and a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Estagund\"&gt;History of Estagund&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house appears to almost be part of generic house fifteen but upon closer inspection it becomes obvious that it is a separate structure (generic house fifteen has the grass and white fence out front). The house also faces in the direction of &lt;a href=\"Travenhurst%20Manor\"&gt;Travenhurst Manor&lt;/a&gt;. The front door is visible when highlighted and is locked.\nThe ground floor is populated day and night by a male commoner. The chest is locked and contains a silver ring and 39 . The bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Chosen%20of%20Mystra\"&gt;History of the Chosen of Mystra&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Dales%20and%20the%20Elven%20Court\"&gt;History of the Dales and the Elven Court&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping man and woman. The chest of drawers is locked and contains a dagger, 31 , and a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Healing&lt;/a&gt;. The bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20III\"&gt;History of the North III&lt;/a&gt; and History of the North IV.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is another one of those houses with the bright blue roof. Generic home sixteen is on the left and generic home nineteen is to its right. It faces towards the obelisk in the center of town. The front door is locked.\nThe ground floor is populated day and night by a female commoner. The chest is locked and contains a dagger, a &lt;a href=\"Halberd\"&gt;Halberd&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaff\"&gt;Quarterstaff&lt;/a&gt;, and 31 .\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is located in the group of houses that are in the cluster with Feldpost's Inn. Generic house twenty-one is on its left and &lt;a href=\"Kagain%27s%20Shop\"&gt;Kagain's Shop&lt;/a&gt; is on the right. It faces towards generic home seventeen. The front door is unlocked and hidden from view.\nThe ground floor is unpopulated. The chest of drawers contains 7 and the chest at the foot of the bed is empty. \nGeneric Home.\nThis house has the purple-ish colored roof and is situated between generic homes seventeen and twenty. The front door is unlocked.\nThe ground floor is populated day and night by a male commoner. Talk to this fella and you've hit the jackpot for information, most of which is trivial, but a few juicy tidbits are also included and lead to quest entries in your Journal. The barrel and shelf in the kitchen are empty.\nThe second floor is populated by a young boy and at night by a sleeping woman in the small bedroom and a sleeping man in the big bedroom. The nightstand to the right contains 3 and the other one is empty. The chest of drawers is locked and contains 11 , a short sword, and a &lt;a href=\"Small%20Shield\"&gt;Small Shield&lt;/a&gt;. The bookshelf contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20II\"&gt;History of the North II&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is the last and tallest house on the left in the group of houses that doesn't contain a named building. Generic home nineteen is on its left. It may be one of the first house's you encounter should you enter Beregost for the first time from the west. The front door is unlocked.\nThe ground floor is populated all day and night by a young boy who carries 2 . The child will \"not\" call the Flaming Fist if the party loots the chest which is locked and contains 86 . However, dialogue with the boy reveals some\nclues to the owners last name and one of their son's names. He gives three different responses based on his reaction to the party.\nAnd when charmed, he says the following:\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping man. The nightstand is empty. The chest is locked and contains 5 and leather armor.\nGeneric Home.\nThis is the house on the far end of the row and it too may be one of the first house's you encounter should you enter Beregost for the first time from the west. Generic home eighteen is on the right and the house faces towards generic homes nineteen and twenty. The front door is unlocked and hidden from view.\nThe ground floor is unpopulated and the barrel in the kitchen contains 4 .\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping man and woman in the smaller bedroom. In the big bedroom, the nightstand on the right is empty and the one on the left is locked and contains a silver necklace. The chest of drawers contains 11 . The bookshelf contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20V\"&gt;History of the North V&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is located on the near-end of the row of houses with generic home twenty-three on the left side. It faces in the direction of generic house thirteen. The front door is locked.\nThe ground floor is unpopulated. The chest at the foot of the bed is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Lynx%20Eye%20Gem\"&gt;Lynx Eye Gem&lt;/a&gt;, a fire agate gem, a turquoise gem, and a sunstone gem. The chest of drawers is empty.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is situated between generic home twenty-two and Feldpost's Inn. It faces towards generic home eighteen. The front door is locked.\nThe ground floor is unpopulated. The chest is locked and contains a dagger, 11 , and a &lt;a href=\"Moonstone%20Gem\"&gt;Moonstone Gem&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor is unpopulated. The nightstand contains 35 and the chest contains a short sword."}
{"id": "46740", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46740", "title": "Generic homes (Gullykin)", "text": "The village of &lt;a href=\"Gullykin\"&gt;Gullykin&lt;/a&gt; has five generic burrow homes which do not serve much purpose in the overall story. This list contains information on any home not already named in-game or without a central defining occupant who owns the house (e.g. &lt;a href=\"Jenkal%27s%20Home\"&gt;Jenkal's Home&lt;/a&gt;).\nOne convenient method of differentiating between these homes is referring to them by their internal &lt;a href=\"Areas\"&gt;area codes&lt;/a&gt; as defined by the game's developers. However, the game developers didn't always follow any type of definitive pattern specific to these generic homes when assigning area codes to the homes. The infobox to the right has an area image of Gullykin that identifies every generic home by its corresponding number in the infobox name.\nUnless otherwise specified, assume that front doors and containers are unlocked and &lt;a href=\"Halfling\"&gt;Halfling&lt;/a&gt;s will call the &lt;a href=\"Halfling%20Enforcer\"&gt;Halfling Enforcer&lt;/a&gt;s if they witness the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; looting their locked containers. Locks all have a specific difficulty class for a &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; to be able to &lt;a href=\"Thief%23Open_Locks\"&gt;open them&lt;/a&gt;, referred to here as the lock's.\nGeneric Home.\nThis is the house closest to the southern wall and the front door also faces towards the wall in a southwesterly direction.\nThe ground floor is unpopulated. The armoire to the left of the front door is empty. The armoire near the stairs is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Sling%20%2B1\"&gt;Sling +1&lt;/a&gt; and 10 . The bookshelf contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Vast\"&gt;History of the Vast&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe basement is unpopulated. The chest is locked and contains 50 . The bookshelves to the right contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Unicorn%20Run\"&gt;History of the Unicorn Run&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Valley%20of%20the%20Gods\"&gt;History of the Valley of the Gods&lt;/a&gt;. The desk contains 13 . The small chest on the left contains a &lt;a href=\"Dagger\"&gt;Dagger&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Sling\"&gt;Sling&lt;/a&gt;, and 3 , the middle chest is empty, and the last chest on the right contains a &lt;a href=\"Greenstone%20Ring\"&gt;Greenstone Ring&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Agni%20Mani%20Necklace\"&gt;Agni Mani Necklace&lt;/a&gt;. The single bookshelf is empty.\nGeneric Home.\nThis is the house on the right, with the \"L-shaped\" storage shed next to it, and generic home 3 to its left. The front door faces towards the wall in a southeasterly direction.\nThe ground floor is populated by a male halfling who carries 1 . The halfling will \"not\" call the Halfling Enforcers if the party loots the containers. The armoire to the left of the front door contains a &lt;a href=\"Tiger%20Cowrie%20Shell%20Necklace\"&gt;Tiger Cowrie Shell Necklace&lt;/a&gt; and the armoire near the stairs contains 11 . The bookshelf contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20IX\"&gt;History of Shadowdale IX&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe basement is populated by a male halfling who carries 1 and during the day by a female halfling who carries 10 . The chest is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Defense\"&gt;Potion of Defense&lt;/a&gt; and 1 . The bookshelves to the right contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Western%20Heartlands\"&gt;History of the Western Heartlands&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Sisters%20of%20Light%20and%20Darkness\"&gt;History of the Sisters of Light and Darkness&lt;/a&gt;. The desk is locked and contains a sling and 35 . The small chest on the left is empty, the middle chest contains a &lt;a href=\"Bluestone%20Necklace\"&gt;Bluestone Necklace&lt;/a&gt; and 11 , and the last chest on the right contains a &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Scroll%20of%20Summon%20Monster\"&gt;Cursed Scroll of Summon Monster&lt;/a&gt;. The single bookshelf is empty.\nGeneric Home.\nThis is the house the middle house of the three and it is almost directly north of generic home 1. The front door faces towards the wall in a southeasterly direction.\nThe ground floor is unpopulated. The armoire to the left of the front door is empty and the armoire near the stairs contains 5 and a short sword. The bookshelf contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20VII\"&gt;History of the North VII&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe basement is populated during the day by a male halfling who carries 1 . The chest is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Magic%20Missiles\"&gt;Wand of Magic Missiles&lt;/a&gt; and 28 . The bookshelves to the right contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Dead%20Three\"&gt;History of the Dead Three&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20VI\"&gt;History of the North VI&lt;/a&gt;. The desk contains 11 and a &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Agate%20Gem\"&gt;Fire Agate Gem&lt;/a&gt;. The small chest on the left contains 3 , the middle chest contains a &lt;a href=\"Angel%20Skin%20Ring\"&gt;Angel Skin Ring&lt;/a&gt; and 11 , and the last chest on the right contains a dagger and a sling. The single bookshelf is empty.\nGeneric Home.\nThis is the house on the left and the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Yondalla%20and%20Alvanhendar%27s%20Fine%20Wines\"&gt;Temple of Yondalla and Alvanhendar's Fine Wines&lt;/a&gt; is just above it. The Gullykin Village sign is just below the house. The front door faces towards the temple and is hidden from view.\nThe ground floor is populated during the day by a male halfling who carries 1 . The armoire to the left of the front door is locked and contains 51 and a &lt;a href=\"Small%20Shield\"&gt;Small Shield&lt;/a&gt;. The armoire near the stairs is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Short%20Sword\"&gt;Short Sword&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Leather%20Armor\"&gt;Leather Armor&lt;/a&gt;. The bookshelf contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20VII\"&gt;History of the North VII&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe basement is unpopulated. The chest is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Chrysoberyl%20Gem\"&gt;Chrysoberyl Gem&lt;/a&gt;, a sling, a short sword, and 3 . The bookshelves to the right contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20III\"&gt;History of Shadowdale III&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20IV\"&gt;History of Shadowdale IV&lt;/a&gt;. The desk contains a &lt;a href=\"Jade%20Ring\"&gt;Jade Ring&lt;/a&gt;. The small chest on the left contains 31 . The middle chest and the last chest on the right are empty. The single bookshelf is empty.\nGeneric Home.\nThis is the house out to the far right of the village and it is completely surrounded by a wooden fence with an open gate. The front door faces towards the rest of the village.\nThe ground floor is unpopulated. The armoire to the left of the front door contains 3 and the armoire near the stairs and the bookshelf are empty.\nThe basement is unpopulated. The chest is locked and is empty. The bookshelves to the right contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Moonsea\"&gt;History of the Moonsea&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20VI\"&gt;History of Shadowdale VI&lt;/a&gt;. The desk contains a &lt;a href=\"Turquoise%20Gem\"&gt;Turquoise Gem&lt;/a&gt;. The small chest on the left and the middle chest are empty and the last chest on the right contains 8 . The single bookshelf is empty."}
{"id": "46705", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46705", "title": "Generic homes (Nashkel)", "text": "The town of &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt; as two generic homes which do not serve much purpose in the overall story. This list contains information on any home not already named in-game or without a central defining occupant who owns the house (e.g. &lt;a href=\"Joseph%27s%20Home\"&gt;Joseph's Home&lt;/a&gt;).\nOne convenient method of differentiating between these homes is referring to them by their internal &lt;a href=\"Areas\"&gt;area codes&lt;/a&gt; as defined by the game's developers.\nUnless otherwise specified, assume that NPCs carry nothing, containers are unlocked, and that NPCs will call the &lt;a href=\"Amnian%20Soldier%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;Amnian Soldiers&lt;/a&gt; if they witness the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; looting their containers. Locks all have a specific difficulty class for a &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; to be able to &lt;a href=\"Thief%23Open_Locks\"&gt;open them&lt;/a&gt;, referred to here as the lock's.\nGeneric Home.\nThis is the house with the wood-shingled roof near the bridge and it has row crop agriculture fields in the front and on its right side. The front door is locked.\nInside is a farmer who is standing in the great room of the house. He will immediately approach the party and tell them to \"get outta here 'fore I have ta hurt ya\". He will begin wandering the premises but once he disappears into the kitchen and bathing area thievery can be quick and thorough. The chest is locked and contains 4 and a &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Ring\"&gt;Silver Ring&lt;/a&gt;. The chest of drawers is empty.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house has the thatched roof and is located north of the row crop agriculture fields. The hidden &lt;a href=\"Ankheg%20Plate%20Mail\"&gt;Ankheg Plate Mail&lt;/a&gt; is located at the edge of the ag field almost directly in line with the front door which is locked.\nThe inside is populated by a family. The son is standing in the great room and the husband and wife are in the bedroom. The husband will approach the party upon sight and tell you to get out. All three then start to wander around the premises, thereby making thievery a bit challenging.\nThe chest next to the first bed is locked and contains 23 and a &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Axe\"&gt;Throwing Axe&lt;/a&gt;. The chest between the beds is locked and contains a suit of &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Mail\"&gt;Chain Mail&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Axe\"&gt;Battle Axe&lt;/a&gt;. The chest of drawers is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Necklace\"&gt;Silver Necklace&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "46606", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46606", "title": "Generic homes (Ulgoth's Beard)", "text": "The town of &lt;a href=\"Ulgoth%27s%20Beard\"&gt;Ulgoth's Beard&lt;/a&gt; has two generic homes that are the first buildings visible upon entering the area. Both of the houses have only a ground floor that is modeled after the two bedroom/six container floor plan found on the second floor of many of the other houses in the game.\nOne convenient method of differentiating between these homes is referring to them by their internal &lt;a href=\"Areas\"&gt;area codes&lt;/a&gt; as defined by the game's developers. The infobox to the right has an area image of Ulgoth's Beard that identifies each generic home by its corresponding number in the infobox name.\nUnless otherwise specified, assume that NPCs carry nothing, containers are unlocked, and that NPCs will call the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; if they witness the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; looting their containers. Locks all have a specific difficulty class for a &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; to be able to &lt;a href=\"Thief%23Open%2520Locks\"&gt;open them&lt;/a&gt;, referred to here as the lock's.\nGeneric Home.\nThis is the slightly bigger house on the right, next to the garden. The front door is locked. \nInside is a female &lt;a href=\"Commoner\"&gt;commoner&lt;/a&gt; who is present day and night. The smaller bedroom contains two lootable nightstands next to each bed. The first one contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Valley%20of%20the%20Gods\"&gt;History of the Valley of the Gods&lt;/a&gt; and the other one is empty. In the bigger bedroom, the nightstand on the right contains a &lt;a href=\"Pearl\"&gt;Pearl&lt;/a&gt; and the other one a &lt;a href=\"Dagger\"&gt;Dagger&lt;/a&gt;. The chest of drawers is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword%20%2B1\"&gt;Bastard Sword +1&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Murky%20Oil%20of%20Speed\"&gt;Murky Oil of Speed&lt;/a&gt;, and 33 . The bookshelf contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20IV\"&gt;History of the North IV&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis is the smaller of the two houses located on the left near the pond. The front door is locked.\nThe house is devoid of people. The smaller bedroom contains two lootable nightstands next to each bed. The first one contains 4 and the other one is empty. In the bigger bedroom, the nightstand on the right contains 9 and the other one is empty. The chest of drawers is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Long%20Sword\"&gt;Long Sword&lt;/a&gt; and a suit of &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Mail\"&gt;Chain Mail&lt;/a&gt;. The bookshelf contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Amn\"&gt;History of Amn&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "37966", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37966", "title": "Generic homes (central Baldur's Gate)", "text": "The city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; is full of generic homes which do not serve much purpose in the overall story. This list contains information on any home not already named in-game or without a central defining occupant who owns the house (e.g. &lt;a href=\"Fenten%27s%20Home\"&gt;Fenten's Home&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gantolandan%27s%20Home\"&gt;Gantolandan's Home&lt;/a&gt;, etc.).\nOne convenient method of differentiating between these homes is referring to them by their internal &lt;a href=\"Areas\"&gt;area codes&lt;/a&gt; as defined by the game's developers. However, the game developers didn't always follow any type of definitive pattern specific to these generic homes when assigning area codes to the homes. The infobox to the right has an area image of Central Baldur's Gate that identifies every generic home by its corresponding number in the infobox name.\nUnless otherwise specified, assume that NPCs carry nothing, containers are unlocked, and that NPCs will call the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; if they witness the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; looting their containers. Locks all have a specific difficulty class for a &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; to be able to &lt;a href=\"Thief%23Open_Locks\"&gt;open them&lt;/a&gt;, referred to here as the lock's.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is located on the corner, behind the house with the blue roof, and faces towards the causeway that leads to the inner portion of the district. There is a empty barrel in front of the house. The front door is locked.\nThe ground floor is populated by a young girl. The chest contains 7 and a &lt;a href=\"Zircon%20Gem\"&gt;Zircon Gem&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping woman. The barrel near the stairs is empty. The nightstand to the left contains 6 and the other one is empty. The chest is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Dagger%20%2B1\"&gt;Dagger +1&lt;/a&gt; and 15 .\nGeneric Home.\nThis house has a blue roof and is located on the opposite corner from the first house. The front door is locked.\nThe ground floor is populated by a male commoner who carries 5 . The barrel in the kitchen contains a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Mirrored%20Eyes\"&gt;Potion of Mirrored Eyes&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor is populated by a female commoner. The nightstand in the corner of the smaller bedroom contains 7 and the other one is empty. In the bigger bedroom, the nightstand next to the bed near the chest of drawers contains 6 and the other one has a single &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Dagger\"&gt;Throwing Dagger&lt;/a&gt;. The chest of drawers is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Tiger%20Cowrie%20Shell%20Necklace\"&gt;Tiger Cowrie Shell Necklace&lt;/a&gt; and 9 and the bookshelf contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Zhentarim\"&gt;History of the Zhentarim&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is the biggest of the three and is located next to the house with the blue roof. An abandoned house (accessible from &lt;a href=\"East%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;East Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;) is on the right side. The front door is locked.\nThe ground floor is populated by a female commoner and a male commoner who carries 5 . The sack on the floor of the kitchen contains a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Defense\"&gt;Potion of Defense&lt;/a&gt;. In the living room, the armoire contains 10 and &lt;a href=\"Leather%20Armor\"&gt;Leather Armor&lt;/a&gt;. Regarding the two chest of drawers on either side of the fireplace, the left side one contains a 6 while the right side one contains 3 .\nThe second floor is populated by a female commoner who will \"not\" call the Flaming Fist if the party loots any of the containers on this floor. The chest of drawers in the sitting room contains 18 and eight &lt;a href=\"Dart\"&gt;Dart&lt;/a&gt;s. The chest of drawers in the closet is empty.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house has slight \"T-shaped\" appearance, faces the inner wall, and is located next to &lt;a href=\"Nadine%27s%20Home\"&gt;Nadine's Home&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe ground floor is populated by a female commoner and a young boy. The chest is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Turquoise%20Gem\"&gt;Turquoise Gem&lt;/a&gt; and 11 .\nThe second floor is unpopulated. Of the two lootable nightstands, the one next to the bed near the chest contains 6 and the other one is empty. The chest contains a &lt;a href=\"Spear\"&gt;Spear&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Halberd\"&gt;Halberd&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house faces towards &lt;a href=\"Oberan%27s%20Estate\"&gt;Oberan's Estate&lt;/a&gt; and the unlocked front door is hidden from view.\nThe ground floor is populated by a young girl. There are three containers in the living room. The armoire is locked and contains a 17 and a suit of &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Mail\"&gt;Chain Mail&lt;/a&gt; armor. Regarding the two chest of drawers on either side of the fireplace, the left side one is empty while the right side one contains 5 and a scroll of &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor is populated all day and night by a sleeping halfling. The chest of drawers is locked and contains 32 , a scroll of &lt;a href=\"Friends\"&gt;Friends&lt;/a&gt;, and 10 throwing daggers.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is located behind the &lt;a href=\"Poultry%20Store\"&gt;Poultry Store&lt;/a&gt; and faces towards the &lt;a href=\"High%20House%20of%20Wonders\"&gt;High House of Wonders&lt;/a&gt;. An abandoned house (accessible from &lt;a href=\"West%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;West Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;) is on the left side. The front door is locked.\nThe ground floor is populated by a female commoner and a male commoner who carries . They will \"not\" call the Flaming Fist if the party loots any of the containers on this floor. The chest is locked and contains and a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Crossbow\"&gt;Heavy Crossbow&lt;/a&gt;. The bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20I\"&gt;History of the North I&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20II\"&gt;History of the North II&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping dwarf. The chest of drawers is locked and contains , a &lt;a href=\"Jasper%20Gem\"&gt;Jasper Gem&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Heroism\"&gt;Potion of Heroism&lt;/a&gt;. The bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Calimshan\"&gt;History of Calimshan&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Cormyr\"&gt;History of Cormyr&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "37967", "revid": "78773", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37967", "title": "Generic homes (east Baldur's Gate)", "text": "The city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; is full of generic homes which do not serve much purpose in the overall story. This list contains information on any home not already named in-game or without a central defining occupant who owns the house (e.g. &lt;a href=\"Fenten%27s%20Home\"&gt;Fenten's Home&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gantolandan%27s%20Home\"&gt;Gantolandan's Home&lt;/a&gt;, etc.).\nOne convenient method of differentiating between these homes is referring to them by their internal &lt;a href=\"Areas\"&gt;area codes&lt;/a&gt; as defined by the game's developers. However, the game developers didn't always follow any type of definitive pattern specific to these generic homes when assigning area codes to the homes. The infobox to the right has an area image of East Baldur's Gate that identifies every generic home by its corresponding number in the infobox name.\nUnless otherwise specified, assume that NPCs carry nothing, containers are unlocked, and that NPCs will call the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; if they witness the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; looting their containers. Locks all have a specific difficulty class for a &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; to be able to &lt;a href=\"Thief%23Open_Locks\"&gt;open them&lt;/a&gt;, referred to here as the lock's.\nGeneric Home.\nThis is the corner house that faces &lt;a href=\"Maltz%27s%20Weapon%20Shop\"&gt;Maltz's Weapon Shop&lt;/a&gt; and is across the street from &lt;a href=\"Sorcerous%20Sundries\"&gt;Sorcerous Sundries&lt;/a&gt;. The front door is locked.\nThe ground floor is populated day and night by a young boy and girl. There are no containers on this floor.\nThe second floor is populated day and night by a sleeping man. All four of the beds have lootable nightstands next to them. The nightstand next to the first bed in the smaller bedroom contains a &lt;a href=\"Bluestone%20Necklace\"&gt;Bluestone Necklace&lt;/a&gt; and the nightstand in the corner has 10 . In the bigger bedroom, a &lt;a href=\"Dagger\"&gt;Dagger&lt;/a&gt; is found on the nightstand next to the bed with the sleeping man and the other one is empty. The chest of drawers contains 14 and the bookshelf contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Bell%20in%20the%20Depths\"&gt;History of the Bell in the Depths&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is situated between &lt;a href=\"Lucky%20Aello%27s%20Discount%20Store\"&gt;Lucky Aello's Discount Store&lt;/a&gt; and an abandoned house. The front door is locked.\nThe ground floor is populated by a young girl. There are three containers in the living room. The armoire contains a suit of &lt;a href=\"Splint%20Mail\"&gt;Splint Mail&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shield\"&gt;Medium Shield&lt;/a&gt;, and 11 .\u00a0Regarding the two chest of drawers on either side of the fireplace, the left side one contains 5 while the right side one contains 25 \u00a0and a dagger.\nThe second floor contains one chest of drawers with ten &lt;a href=\"Dart\"&gt;Dart&lt;/a&gt;s and 15 ."}
{"id": "37964", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37964", "title": "Generic homes (north Baldur's Gate)", "text": "The city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; is full of generic homes which do not serve much purpose in the overall story. This list contains information on any home not already named in-game or without a central defining occupant who owns the house (e.g. &lt;a href=\"Fenten%27s%20Home\"&gt;Fenten's Home&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gantolandan%27s%20Home\"&gt;Gantolandan's Home&lt;/a&gt;, etc.).\nOne convenient method of differentiating between these homes is referring to them by their internal &lt;a href=\"Areas\"&gt;area codes&lt;/a&gt; as defined by the game's developers. However, the game developers didn't always follow any type of definitive pattern specific to these generic homes when assigning area codes to the homes. The infobox to the right has an area image of North Baldur's Gate that identifies every generic home by its corresponding number in the infobox name.\nUnless otherwise specified, assume that NPCs carry nothing, containers are unlocked, and that NPCs will call the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; if they witness the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; looting their containers. Locks all have a specific difficulty class for a &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; to be able to &lt;a href=\"Thief%23Open_Locks\"&gt;open them&lt;/a&gt;, referred to here as the lock's.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is located in a row of three houses that are situated in front of the &lt;a href=\"Ducal%20Palace\"&gt;Ducal Palace&lt;/a&gt;. It is the house on the near-end, closest to the front gates of the Palace, and &lt;a href=\"Rinnie%27s%20Home\"&gt;Rinnie's Home&lt;/a&gt; is the middle house on the right side. The front door is locked.\nThe ground floor is populated by a male commoner who carries . He will \"not\" call the Flaming Fist if the party loots his nearby chest, which is empty.\nThe second floor is populated at all hours of the day by a sleeping man. The nightstand on the right contains and the other one contains . The chest at the foot of his bed is locked and contains , a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Crossbow\"&gt;Heavy Crossbow&lt;/a&gt;, ten &lt;a href=\"Bolt\"&gt;Bolt&lt;/a&gt;s, and six &lt;a href=\"Bolt%20%2B1\"&gt;Bolt +1&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house faces the rear of the palace with &lt;a href=\"Jardak%27s%20Home\"&gt;Jardak's Home&lt;/a&gt; on the right side and another &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28north%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23AR0014\"&gt;generic house&lt;/a&gt; on the left. The front door is unlocked.\nThe ground floor is populated by a young boy. The table in the kitchen is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Dagger\"&gt;Dagger&lt;/a&gt; and .\nThe second floor is devoid of any commoners. In the smaller bedroom, the nightstand between the two beds contains a &lt;a href=\"Jade%20Ring\"&gt;Jade Ring&lt;/a&gt; and and the one in the corner contains . In the bigger bedroom, the nightstand on the right contains a &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Agate%20Gem\"&gt;Fire Agate Gem&lt;/a&gt; and the other one is empty. The chest of drawers is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Stone%20Form\"&gt;Potion of Stone Form&lt;/a&gt; and . The bookshelf contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Dales%20and%20the%20Elven%20Court\"&gt;History of the Dales and the Elven Court&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is the \"T-shaped\" house that faces the tower and a second &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28north%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23AR0016\"&gt;generic house&lt;/a&gt; is on its left. The unlocked front door is not visible.\nThe ground floor is populated by a male commoner who carries . The table in the living room contains .\nThe second floor is populated by a young girl. In the smaller bedroom during the night there is a sleeping woman in the bed near the wall. The nightstand between the beds contains a &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Dagger\"&gt;Throwing Dagger&lt;/a&gt; and and the one in the corner is empty. Oddly enough, the girl will have no problem with the party looting every container on this floor except the nightstand in the smaller bedroom with the loot. In the bigger bedroom, the nightstand on the right contains and the other one is empty. The chest of drawers is locked and contains and an &lt;a href=\"Andar%20Gem\"&gt;Andar Gem&lt;/a&gt;. The bookshelf contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20VII\"&gt;History of the North VII&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is located next to the house above and also faces Ramazith's Tower. Due to the position of the house there isn't a visible door to enter, just a general entrance area with no lock on it.\nThe ground floor is populated by a male commoner who carries . He will \"not\" call the guards if the party loots his bookshelves, which contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20VI\"&gt;History of Shadowdale VI&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20VII\"&gt;History of Shadowdale VII&lt;/a&gt;, but will raise the alarm if they loot his chest which contains and a &lt;a href=\"Large%20Shield\"&gt;Large Shield&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor is populated at night by two sleeping women. The chest of drawers is empty, and the two bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Waterdeep%20V\"&gt;History of Waterdeep V&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Waterdeep%20VI\"&gt;History of Waterdeep VI&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is the one visible to the left of the tower. The front door is locked.\nThe ground floor is populated by a female commoner, a male commoner carrying , and a young boy carrying . Among the three containers in the living room, the chest of drawers to the left of the fireplace (locked) will not trigger a call to the guards if the party loots it, most likely because it is empty. The chest of drawers to the right of the fireplace is locked and contains and a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Explosions\"&gt;Potion of Explosions&lt;/a&gt;. The armoire is locked and contains &lt;a href=\"Leather%20Armor\"&gt;Leather Armor&lt;/a&gt; and .\nThe second floor is devoid of commoners. The chest of drawers is locked and contains and a &lt;a href=\"Rainbow%20Obsidian%20Necklace\"&gt;Rainbow Obsidian Necklace&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is the one visible to the right of the tower. The front door is locked.\nThe ground floor is populated by a female commoner. She will \"not\" call the guards if the party loots her bookshelves, which contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Dragon%20Coast\"&gt;History of the Dragon Coast&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Ulgarth\"&gt;History of the Ulgarth&lt;/a&gt;. The chest is locked and contains and a &lt;a href=\"Small%20Shield%20%2B1\"&gt;Small Shield +1&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor is populated at night by two sleeping men. The chest of drawers is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Mace\"&gt;Mace&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Jasper%20Gem\"&gt;Jasper Gem&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Heroism\"&gt;Potion of Heroism&lt;/a&gt;. The bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Waterdeep%20II\"&gt;History of Waterdeep II&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Waterdeep%20III\"&gt;History of Waterdeep III&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "37965", "revid": "78773", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37965", "title": "Generic homes (northeast Baldur's Gate)", "text": "The city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; is full of generic homes which do not serve much purpose in the overall story. This list contains information on any home not already named in-game or without a central defining occupant who owns the house (e.g. &lt;a href=\"Fenten%27s%20Home\"&gt;Fenten's Home&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gantolandan%27s%20Home\"&gt;Gantolandan's Home&lt;/a&gt;, etc.).\nOne convenient method of differentiating between these homes is referring to them by their internal &lt;a href=\"Areas\"&gt;area codes&lt;/a&gt; as defined by the game's developers. However, the game developers didn't always follow any type of definitive pattern specific to these generic homes when assigning area codes to the homes. The infobox to the right has an area image of Northeast Baldur's Gate that identifies every generic home by its corresponding number in the infobox name.\nUnless otherwise specified, assume that NPCs carry nothing, containers are unlocked, and that NPCs will call the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; if they witness the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; looting their containers. Locks all have a specific difficulty class for a &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; to be able to &lt;a href=\"Thief%23Open_Locks\"&gt;open them&lt;/a&gt;, referred to here as the lock's.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is located north of the &lt;a href=\"Blushing%20Mermaid\"&gt;Blushing Mermaid&lt;/a&gt; and backs up to the outer wall in the west portion of &lt;a href=\"Northeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Northeast Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. The front door is locked.\nThe ground floor is populated by a female commoner. The chest is locked and contains and a &lt;a href=\"Flamedance%20Ring\"&gt;Flamedance Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping halfling. The table near the stairs contains a &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Dagger\"&gt;Throwing Dagger&lt;/a&gt;. The barrel is empty. The open book on the nightstand in the small bedroom is empty. The shelf in the nearby bathroom holds a &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Protection%20%2B1\"&gt;Cloak of Protection +1&lt;/a&gt;. In the big bedroom, the nightstand to the right contains . The one on the left is locked and contains . The chest at the foot of the bed is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Halberd\"&gt;Halberd&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Spear\"&gt;Spear&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is located against the outer wall, north of a &lt;a href=\"Shop%20%28Northeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;generic store&lt;/a&gt;, in the east portion of Northeast Baldur's Gate. The front door is unlocked.\nThe ground floor is devoid of any people. The armoire is locked and is empty. The two chest of drawers on either side of the fireplace are empty as well. \nThe second floor is also unpopulated. The single chest of drawers is locked and is empty."}
{"id": "37963", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37963", "title": "Generic homes (northwest Baldur's Gate)", "text": "The city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; is full of generic homes which do not serve much purpose in the overall story. This list contains information on any home not already named in-game or without a central defining occupant who owns the house (e.g. &lt;a href=\"Fenten%27s%20Home\"&gt;Fenten's Home&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gantolandan%27s%20Home\"&gt;Gantolandan's Home&lt;/a&gt;, etc.).\nOne convenient method of differentiating between these homes is referring to them by their internal &lt;a href=\"Areas\"&gt;area codes&lt;/a&gt; as defined by the game's developers. However, the game developers didn't always follow any type of definitive pattern specific to these generic homes when assigning area codes to the homes. The infobox to the right has an area image of Northwest Baldur's Gate that identifies every generic home by its corresponding number in the infobox name.\nUnless otherwise specified, assume that NPCs carry nothing, containers are unlocked, and that NPCs will call the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; if they witness the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; looting their containers. Locks all have a specific difficulty class for a &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; to be able to &lt;a href=\"Thief%23Open_Locks\"&gt;open them&lt;/a&gt;, referred to here as the lock's.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is located in a row of three houses that are situated between &lt;a href=\"Entar%20Silvershield%27s%20Estate\"&gt;Entar Silvershield's Estate&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Degrodel%27s%20Home\"&gt;Degrodel's Home&lt;/a&gt;. It is the house in the middle with &lt;a href=\"Pheirkas%27s%20Home\"&gt;Pheirkas's Home&lt;/a&gt; on the left and another generic house on the left. It is one of the only houses in the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;city&lt;/a&gt; with an upper and lower entrance. Both doors are locked.\nThe ground floor is populated by a male &lt;a href=\"commoner\"&gt;commoner&lt;/a&gt; who carries . The chest is locked and contains a suit of &lt;a href=\"Splint%20Mail\"&gt;Splint Mail&lt;/a&gt;. The two bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Valley%20of%20the%20Gods\"&gt;History of the Valley of the Gods&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Vast\"&gt;History of the Vast&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping man and sleeping halfling. A chest of drawers contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Ulgarth\"&gt;History of the Ulgarth&lt;/a&gt; and . The two bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Western%20Heartlands\"&gt;History of the Western Heartlands&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Zhentarim\"&gt;History of the Zhentarim&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is located next to &lt;a href=\"Quinn%27s%20Home\"&gt;Quinn's Home&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Helm%20and%20Cloak\"&gt;Helm and Cloak&lt;/a&gt; is across the street. The front door is not locked.\nThe ground floor is populated by a female commoner. She will \"not\" call the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; if the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; loots the nearby barrel, which is empty.\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping man and sleeping elf. In the smaller bedroom, the nightstand between the two beds contains a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Healing&lt;/a&gt; and the one in the corner contains . In the bigger bedroom, the nightstand on the right contains three &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Dagger\"&gt;Throwing Dagger&lt;/a&gt;s and the other one is empty. The chest of drawers is locked and contains and a &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaff\"&gt;Quarterstaff&lt;/a&gt;. The bookshelf contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Chosen%20of%20Mystra\"&gt;History of the Chosen of Mystra&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is located next to a generic &lt;a href=\"Generic%20Tavern%20and%20Inn%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23AR0165\"&gt;Tavern and Inn&lt;/a&gt; and faces &lt;a href=\"Entar%20Silvershield%27s%20Estate\"&gt;Entar Silvershield's Estate&lt;/a&gt;. The front door is not locked.\nThe ground floor is populated by a male commoner who carries . He will \"not\" call the Flaming Fist if the nearby containers are looted. The armoire is locked and contains . Regarding the two chest of drawers on either side of the fireplace, the left side one is lockedand contains while the right side one contains and a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Insight\"&gt;Potion of Insight&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping man. The chest of drawers is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Bloodstone%20Gem\"&gt;Bloodstone Gem&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Dagger\"&gt;Dagger&lt;/a&gt;, and .\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is also located in the row of three houses that are situated between &lt;a href=\"Entar%20Silvershield%27s%20Estate\"&gt;Entar Silvershield's Estate&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Degrodel%27s%20Home\"&gt;Degrodel's Home&lt;/a&gt;. It is the house on the left next to the outer wall with the generic house &lt;a href=\"%23AR0155\"&gt;above&lt;/a&gt; on the right. The front door is not locked. The barrel near the front door contains 16 .\nThe ground floor is populated by a female commoner. The shelf in the kitchen contains &lt;a href=\"The%20Protector\"&gt;The Protector +1&lt;/a&gt; necklace.\nThe second floor is populated at night by two sleeping men and two sleeping women. In the smaller bedroom, the nightstand between the two beds contains a &lt;a href=\"Tiger%20Cowrie%20Shell%20Necklace\"&gt;Tiger Cowrie Shell Necklace&lt;/a&gt; and the one in the corner is empty. In the bigger bedroom, the nightstand on the right contains and the other one is empty. The chest of drawers is locked and contains and a &lt;a href=\"Light%20Crossbow\"&gt;Light Crossbow&lt;/a&gt;. The bookshelf contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Moonsea\"&gt;History of the Moonsea&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "37969", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37969", "title": "Generic homes (south Baldur's Gate)", "text": "The city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; is full of generic homes which do not serve much purpose in the overall story. This list contains information on any home not already named in-game or without a central defining occupant who owns the house (e.g. &lt;a href=\"Fenten%27s%20Home\"&gt;Fenten's Home&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gantolandan%27s%20Home\"&gt;Gantolandan's Home&lt;/a&gt;, etc.).\nOne convenient method of differentiating between these homes is referring to them by their internal &lt;a href=\"Areas\"&gt;area codes&lt;/a&gt; as defined by the game's developers. However, the game developers didn't always follow any type of definitive pattern specific to these generic homes when assigning area codes to the homes. The infobox to the right has an area image of South Baldur's Gate that identifies every generic home by its corresponding number in the infobox name.\nUnless otherwise specified, assume that NPCs carry nothing, containers are unlocked, and that NPCs will call the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; if they witness the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; looting their containers. Locks all have a specific difficulty class for a &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; to be able to &lt;a href=\"Thief%23Open_Locks\"&gt;open them&lt;/a&gt;, referred to here as the lock's.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is the biggest of the three, has a teal-colored roof, and is separated by grass from the other two. The front door is locked.\nAs soon as you enter the ground floor you will encounter five &lt;a href=\"Ogre%20Mage\"&gt;Ogre Mage&lt;/a&gt;s. Two are visible (OGREMA_A &amp; OGREMA_C) and the other three (OGREMA, OGREMA_B, OGREMA_D) are invisible courtesy of non-droppable &lt;a href=\"Sandthief%27s%20Ring\"&gt;Sandthief's Ring&lt;/a&gt;s. All three invisible ogre mages can be detected with a &lt;a href=\"Detect%20Evil\"&gt;Detect Evil&lt;/a&gt; spell but only two (OGREMA &amp; OGREMA_B) become visible with a &lt;a href=\"Detect%20Invisibility\"&gt;Detect Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nAnd with that statement the battle begins. Upon death they all drop three &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure%23RNDTRE05\"&gt;rich random treasure&lt;/a&gt; items and a &lt;a href=\"Scimitar\"&gt;Scimitar&lt;/a&gt; (except OGREMA_D who is equipped with a &lt;a href=\"Katana\"&gt;Katana&lt;/a&gt; and has no scimitar in its inventory).\n\"Positioning:\".\nThe ogre mages are positioned inside the house as depicted here by their creature code:\n OGREMA_A\n Second OGREMA_C\n Floor | | | OGREMA Front\n Stairs OGREMA_B Door\n OGREMA_D\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"Spell Casting:\".\nThe Ogre Mages will cast the following spells (race script.bcs):\n&lt;br&gt;\nOnce each Ogre Mage has cycled through their spells they will switch to melee attack using a &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword\"&gt;Bastard Sword&lt;/a&gt; which isn't dropped upon death (except OGREMA_D who is equipped with a katana which is dropped upon death).\nThe display case in the reading/leisure room on the left contains 31 . The display case in the left side library contains a &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hands\"&gt;Burning Hands&lt;/a&gt; scroll. The bookshelf in the right side reading/leisure room contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20VII\"&gt;History of the North VII&lt;/a&gt; and the bookshelf in the right side library contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Red%20Ravens\"&gt;History of the Red Ravens&lt;/a&gt;.\nOn the second floor the single lootable desk contains 29 .\nGeneric Home.\nThis is the middle house with the single white/black-striped window awning. The front door is locked.\nThe ground floor is populated during the day by a female commoner and a male commoner who carries 5\u202f. The barrel in the kitchen has 1 and the the shelf is empty.\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping man and woman. All four of the beds have lootable nightstands next to them. The nightstand next to the first bed in the smaller bedroom contains 1 and the one in the corner is empty. In the big bedroom, a &lt;a href=\"Dagger\"&gt;Dagger&lt;/a&gt; is found on the nightstand to the right and the other one is empty. The chest of drawers contains a &lt;a href=\"Short%20Sword\"&gt;Short Sword&lt;/a&gt; and the bookshelf is empty.\nGeneric Home.\nThis is the corner house with the brick-colored striped window awnings. The front door is locked.\nThe ground floor is populated during the day by a young boy and girl, a female commoner, and a male commoner who carries 5\u202f. The chest contains 2 .\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping man and woman. The nightstand on the right contains 1 and the other one is empty. The chest contains a &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaff\"&gt;Quarterstaff&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Club\"&gt;Club&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is the small building located between the &lt;a href=\"Warehouses%20%28south%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;warehouse&lt;/a&gt; where &lt;a href=\"Noralee\"&gt;Noralee&lt;/a&gt; can be found and &lt;a href=\"Ghorak%27s%20Home\"&gt;Ghorak's Home&lt;/a&gt;. The front door is locked.\nAs soon as you enter the ground floor you will encounter two dead residents of the house and &lt;a href=\"Larriaz\"&gt;Larriaz&lt;/a&gt; who warns the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; to stay away and let her die alone. See her creature page for a full account of her dilemma. The single chest contains a &lt;a href=\"Turquoise%20Gem\"&gt;Turquoise Gem&lt;/a&gt;.\nOn the second floor you'll find two more dead bodies. Both beds have lootable nightstands next to them which are empty. The chest is locked and contains 1 ."}
{"id": "37970", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37970", "title": "Generic homes (southeast Baldur's Gate)", "text": "The city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; is full of generic homes which do not serve much purpose in the overall story. This list contains information on any home not already named in-game or without a central defining occupant who owns the house (e.g. &lt;a href=\"Fenten%27s%20Home\"&gt;Fenten's Home&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gantolandan%27s%20Home\"&gt;Gantolandan's Home&lt;/a&gt;, etc.).\nOne convenient method of differentiating between these homes is referring to them by their internal &lt;a href=\"Areas\"&gt;area codes&lt;/a&gt; as defined by the game's developers. However, the game developers didn't always follow any type of definitive pattern specific to these generic homes when assigning area codes to the homes. The infobox to the right has an area image of Southeast Baldur's Gate that identifies every generic home by its corresponding number in the infobox name.\nUnless otherwise specified, assume that NPCs carry nothing, containers are unlocked, and that NPCs will call the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; if they witness the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; looting their containers. Locks all have a specific difficulty class for a &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; to be able to &lt;a href=\"Thief%23Open_Locks\"&gt;open them&lt;/a&gt;, referred to here as the lock's.\nGeneric Home.\nThis is the white house located next to &lt;a href=\"Well-Adjusted%20Al%27s%20General%20Store\"&gt;Well-Adjusted Al's General Store&lt;/a&gt; and has the &lt;a href=\"Warehouses%20%28southeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;warehouse&lt;/a&gt; where &lt;a href=\"Nadarin\"&gt;Nadarin&lt;/a&gt; can be found located behind it. On the left side is &lt;a href=\"Ghorak%27s%20Home\"&gt;Ghorak's Home&lt;/a&gt; which is accessible from &lt;a href=\"South%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;South Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. The front door is locked.\nThe ground floor is populated during the day by two young boys, a female commoner, and a male commoner who carries 5\u202f. The female commoner is present twenty-four hours. The chest is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Short%20Sword\"&gt;Short Sword&lt;/a&gt;. The bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Dales%20and%20the%20Elven%20Court\"&gt;History of the Dales and the Elven Court&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Fateful%20Coin\"&gt;History of the Fateful Coin&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping man and woman. The chest of drawers contains a &lt;a href=\"Mace\"&gt;Mace&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Healing&lt;/a&gt;. The two bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20II\"&gt;History of the North II&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20IV\"&gt;History of the North IV&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis is the house with the blue roof that faces the &lt;a href=\"Warehouses%20%28southeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;warehouse&lt;/a&gt; where &lt;a href=\"Nadarin\"&gt;Nadarin&lt;/a&gt; can be found and is across the street from the generic house with the brick-colored striped window awnings. The front door is locked.\nThe ground floor is populated during the day by a young boy, a female commoner, and a male commoner who carries 5\u202f. The male commoner is present twenty-four hours. There are no containers on the ground floor.\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping man and woman. All four of the beds have lootable nightstands next to them but only one to the right in the big bedroom contains 2 and the others are empty. The chest of drawers contains a &lt;a href=\"Dagger\"&gt;Dagger&lt;/a&gt; and the bookshelf is empty.\nGeneric Home.\nThis is the corner house with the brick-colored striped window awnings located next to &lt;a href=\"Gantolandan%27s%20Home\"&gt;Gantolandan's Home&lt;/a&gt;. The front door is locked.\nThe ground floor is populated by a young girl. There are three containers in the living room. The armoire contains a &lt;a href=\"Spear\"&gt;Spear&lt;/a&gt; and 17 . Regarding the two chest of drawers on either side of the fireplace, the left side one is empty while the right side one contains 12 and a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Insight\"&gt;Potion of Insight&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping man and woman. The chest of drawers is locked and contains 14 and a short sword.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is the tall middle one with the blue railings in front of it. The front door is unlocked.\nThe ground floor is populated all day and night by a young boy and a female commoner during the day. The chest contains a mace and 5 .\nThe second floor is populated during the day by a young girl and at night by a sleeping woman. The chest of drawers is locked and contains a short sword and &lt;a href=\"Leather%20Armor\"&gt;Leather Armor&lt;/a&gt;. The two nightstands are empty.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is the one with the non-descript looking exterior next to the tall middle one with the blue railings in front of it. The front door is unlocked.\nInside is are a pair of thieves named &lt;a href=\"Taxek\"&gt;Taxek&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Michael\"&gt;Michael&lt;/a&gt;. Taxek will initiate dialogue on sight. Options include giving them your money, taking their money, or duking it out. There are no containers on the ground floor.\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping man and woman. Of the six containers, only the chest of drawers contains any loot: a &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaff\"&gt;Quarterstaff&lt;/a&gt; and four &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Axe\"&gt;Throwing Axe&lt;/a&gt;s. The bookshelf has a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Waterdeep%20II\"&gt;History of Waterdeep II&lt;/a&gt;. The four nightstands are empty."}
{"id": "37968", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37968", "title": "Generic homes (southwest Baldur's Gate)", "text": "The city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; is full of generic homes which do not serve much purpose in the overall story. This list contains information on any home not already named in-game or without a central defining occupant who owns the house (e.g. &lt;a href=\"Fenten%27s%20Home\"&gt;Fenten's Home&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gantolandan%27s%20Home\"&gt;Gantolandan's Home&lt;/a&gt;, etc.).\nOne convenient method of differentiating between these homes is referring to them by their internal &lt;a href=\"Areas\"&gt;area codes&lt;/a&gt; as defined by the game's developers. However, the game developers didn't always follow any type of definitive pattern specific to these generic homes when assigning area codes to the homes. The infobox to the right has an area image of Southwest Baldur's Gate that identifies every generic home by its corresponding number in the infobox name.\nUnless otherwise specified, assume that NPCs carry nothing, containers are unlocked, and that NPCs will call the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; if they witness the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; looting their containers. Locks all have a specific difficulty class for a &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; to be able to &lt;a href=\"Thief%23Open_Locks\"&gt;open them&lt;/a&gt;, referred to here as the lock's.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is the biggest of the four, has bluish-colored roof, and is one of the very few generic houses that has named NPC's within. The front door is locked. The floor plan follows that of the &lt;a href=\"Merchants%27%20League%20Counting%20House\"&gt;Merchants' League Counting House&lt;/a&gt;. \nAs soon as you enter the ground floor a thief named &lt;a href=\"Wiven\"&gt;Wiven&lt;/a&gt; will approach you and demand all of your money. You can either give it to her or engage in combat. She has three companions, &lt;a href=\"Dirk\"&gt;Dirk&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Meakin\"&gt;Meakin&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Sath\"&gt;Sath&lt;/a&gt; who are hiding in the shadows and will join the battle. Killing them yields 1800 XP and the following loot:\nLooting the ground floor containers yields the following:&lt;br&gt;\nThe display case in the left side reading/leisure room is empty. The display case in the left side library contains 22 and the bookshelf contain a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Gondegal%20the%20Lost%20King\"&gt;History of Gondegal the Lost King&lt;/a&gt;. The display case near the stairs in the main room has a scroll of &lt;a href=\"Identify\"&gt;Identify&lt;/a&gt;. The bookshelf in the library on the right side contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Drow%20I\"&gt;History of the Drow I&lt;/a&gt;. The bookshelf in the right side reading/leisure room contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Luiren\"&gt;History of Luiren&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor contains four large, lootable desks which contain the following (starting with the red carpet room and moving clockwise): the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Cormyr\"&gt;History of Cormyr&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Friends\"&gt;Friends&lt;/a&gt; scroll, empty desk, and 13 .\nGeneric Home.\nThis is the smaller house located next door to the blue-roofed house. The front door is locked.\nThe ground floor is populated during the day by a young boy and girl and a male commoner who carries 5\u202f. The chest is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Crossbow\"&gt;Heavy Crossbow&lt;/a&gt;. The bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Dragon%20Coast\"&gt;History of the Dragon Coast&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20VI\"&gt;History of Shadowdale VI&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping man and woman. The chest of drawers is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Healing&lt;/a&gt;, 12 , and a &lt;a href=\"Club\"&gt;Club&lt;/a&gt;. The two bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Dambrath\"&gt;History of Dambrath&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Sembia\"&gt;History of Sembia&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis is the bigger house on the opposite side of the cluster of houses, next to the second house, and it's front door is locked and faces towards &lt;a href=\"Sunin\"&gt;Sunin&lt;/a&gt;'s home.\nThe ground floor is populated day and night by a male commoner who carries 5\u202f and, during the day, by a female commoner and two young girls. The armoire contains 13 and a &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Axe\"&gt;Battle Axe&lt;/a&gt;. Two smaller chest of drawers flank the fireplace with the one on the right containing 15 and a potion of &lt;a href=\"Antidote\"&gt;Antidote&lt;/a&gt; while the one on the left is empty.\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping woman. The chest of drawers contains 13 and the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20XIII\"&gt;History of Shadowdale XIII&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneric Home.\nThis house is behind the second house and its front door, which is hidden from view and unlocked, faces the Flaming Fist Headquarters.\nThe ground floor is populated during the day by a male commoner who carries 5\u202f, a female commoner, and four young girls. The chest contains 3 .\nThe second floor is populated at night by a sleeping man and woman. The chest contains four &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Dagger\"&gt;Throwing Dagger&lt;/a&gt;s. Both nightstands are empty."}
{"id": "23759", "revid": "50459896", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23759", "title": "Genie", "text": "A Genie is an extra-planar being, native to the one of the various Elemental Planes (not just limited to those known as Djnni from the plane of Air). Several different types can be encountered and summoned during the \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20Wiki\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" games.\nGenies and their associated elemental planes include:\nCategories.\nAlso see Categories for various Genies in the game, and to understand the difference between \"Genies\" as a Race, and \"Djnni\" as a Class."}
{"id": "55124", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55124", "title": "Genie (Circus Tent)", "text": "This Genie is encountered twice inside the &lt;a href=\"Circus%20Tent\"&gt;Circus Tent&lt;/a&gt; during the events of the &lt;a href=\"Investigate%20the%20circus%20tent\"&gt;Investigate the circus tent&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nThe first encounter takes place after the party has entered the tent. The genie is on a bridge that leads to the first floor entrance of a blue-domed tent. He will ask the party to correctly answer a riddle before being allowed to continue over the bridge. If the riddle is answered correctly the party gains 19500 &lt;a href=\"XP\"&gt;XP&lt;/a&gt; and the genie disappears. Should the party fail to answer the riddle correctly, the genie will give the party a second chance and pose another riddle to be solved. Correctly answering this riddle will net the party 14500 XP and the genie disappears. The genie will turn hostile if the party fails to provide the correct answer to the second riddle.\nThe second encounter takes place on the second floor of the blue-domed tent. The genie will appear on the stairs that lead up to the entrance to the third floor of the tent. This time he will congratulate the party on their progress and then teleports away for good."}
