{"id": "7964", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7964", "title": "Genthore", "text": "Genthore is a human fighter and one of four adventurers, led by &lt;a href=\"Drasus\"&gt;Drasus&lt;/a&gt;, encountered during \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". Their group has been hired to defend the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mine\"&gt;Cloakwood\u00a0Mine&lt;/a&gt; from \"anyone that is foolish enough to challenge [them]\" - namely, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;.\nGenthore is the toughest opponent of the four, having the highest armor class and second highest &lt;a href=\"hit%20point\"&gt;hit point&lt;/a&gt;s. Despite this, he prefers attacking from range with his various selection of throwing weapons; axes, darts, and daggers. He will not turn hostile until attacked himself or after the party finishes speaking with Drasus, just like his magi colleagues positioned directly behind him; &lt;a href=\"Kysus\"&gt;Kysus&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Rezdan\"&gt;Rezdan&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "35232", "revid": "276456", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35232", "title": "Gentrus's Hand Mirror", "text": "Gentrus's Hand Mirror is a found in \"\"\nAcquisition.\nIt can be found inside the burnt and abandoned inn at the &lt;a href=\"Coast%20Way%20Crossing\"&gt;Coast Way Crossing&lt;/a&gt;, but may require passing a check to see it.\nFunction.\nThis mirror, the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20the%20Beluir%20Watch\"&gt;Cloak of the Beluir Watch&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"the%20Suncatcher\"&gt;the Suncatcher&lt;/a&gt; may be turned in to &lt;a href=\"Takos\"&gt;Takos&lt;/a&gt; for the &lt;a href=\"Halfling%20Treasures\"&gt;Halfling Treasures&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nIn addition, it has three charges per &lt;a href=\"rest\"&gt;rest&lt;/a&gt; that can be used to cast &lt;a href=\"Identify%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Identify&lt;/a&gt; on unidentified items, acting as a rechargeable scroll of Identify."}
{"id": "13261", "revid": "54563043", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13261", "title": "Gerard Travenhurst", "text": "Gerard Travenhurst is a nobleman who occupies &lt;a href=\"Travenhurst%20Manor\"&gt;Travenhurst Manor&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt;, along with his guards &lt;a href=\"Carl\"&gt;Carl&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Jurgen\"&gt;Jurgen&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe is reasonably welcoming to parties with Popular &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt; (even though his voice track is rude and dismissive to everyone), complaining of social isolation. But however politely you reply, he quickly dismisses you, saying he has important things to do. He clearly has serious social issues.\nDialogues.\n\"Hold your place. No need for us to get off on the wrong foot. I rather like company occasionally, but most of the townsfolk are a bit standoffish.\""}
{"id": "7747", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7747", "title": "Gerde", "text": "Gerde is a female human who will give you a lecture about the ecological place of &lt;a href=\"ankheg\"&gt;ankheg&lt;/a&gt;s, saying they aerate the soil and thereby increase crop yields. She wants their population thinned, but will warn you not to kill too many of them. When spoken to a second time, she will give you a bounty for helping."}
