{"id": "51790", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51790", "title": "Gerg", "text": "Gerg is a &lt;a href=\"hobgoblin\"&gt;hobgoblin&lt;/a&gt; who's found in the cave area that's located within the northwest section of &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Maze\"&gt;Firkraag's Maze&lt;/a&gt;. He and an unnamed small troll are in the process of being berating by a &lt;a href=\"wolfwere\"&gt;wolfwere&lt;/a&gt; known as &lt;a href=\"Captain%20%28Firkraag%27s%20Maze%29\"&gt;Captain&lt;/a&gt; for their failure to satisfactorily clean &lt;a href=\"Firkraag\"&gt;Firkraag&lt;/a&gt;'s golems.\nFollowing a brief dialogue between the three, the Captain will transform into his wolfwere form and attack the orc and troll, concentrating on Gerg first. The outcome of this battle has three possibilities:\nIt is also possible for the party to intervene in the battle:\nIf you attack the orc and troll but the wolfwere is killed, they will attack the party since attacking either of them during the battle turns both of them hostile."}
{"id": "8624", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8624", "title": "Gervisse", "text": "Gervisse is a male elven mage who is accused of being the bogeyman by the twins &lt;a href=\"Laerta\"&gt;Laerta&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Louise\"&gt;Louise&lt;/a&gt;. They claim that he looks into their window at night and this sets up the short side quest &lt;a href=\"Laerta%20and%20Louise\"&gt;Laerta and Louise&lt;/a&gt;. Gervisse will try to convince the party that a shape-shifting druid named &lt;a href=\"Voltinabulai\"&gt;Voltine&lt;/a&gt; is the real villain.\nThis results in an entry in your &lt;a href=\"Journal\"&gt;Journal&lt;/a&gt; under the quest titled \"Laerta and Louise\":\nSpeaking with Voltine provides the party a chance to decide who's telling the truth and who's lying and of course it's Gervisse who is the bogeyman and must be eliminated."}
