{"id": "55101", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55101", "title": "Getting inside the Palace in Suldenessellar", "text": "This is part of the main quest for &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%207\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 7&lt;/a&gt;. \nAquisition.\nWhen the party first enters &lt;a href=\"Suldanessellar\"&gt;Suldanessellar&lt;/a&gt; and dialogue with &lt;a href=\"Elhan%20-%20Suldanessellar\"&gt;Elhan&lt;/a&gt; is finished - the player has this quest registered in their Journal, as follows:\nWalkthrough (abbreviated).\nElhan says to seek queen &lt;a href=\"Ellesime\"&gt;Ellesime&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Priestess%20Demin\"&gt;Priestess Demin&lt;/a&gt; to find out if they know what to do about this invasion or to stop Irenicus.\nIt may not be apparent now, but only Demin can be contacted as the queen is secured below &lt;a href=\"The%20Palace\"&gt;The Palace&lt;/a&gt;, and the Palace can't be entered without certain actions taken.\nLooking at the player's world map shows the location of &lt;a href=\"Demin%27s%20House\"&gt;Demin's House&lt;/a&gt;. This is a solid clue that she might be there. So, make a visit and enter the house to find out.\nSave the priestess from destruction by destroying the rakshasas that threaten her. Demin will be ablet to provide information about getting the leaf lord Rillifane to open the sealed palace and access to Irenicus and Ellesime. If by chance Demin is slain during the battle, search her body for &lt;a href=\"Demin%27s%20Note\"&gt;Demin's Note&lt;/a&gt; - this will give the bare bones information needed to complete the quest.\nIn order to awaken the &lt;a href=\"Avatar%20of%20Rillifane\"&gt;Avatar of Rillifane&lt;/a&gt;, several artifacts must be placed on the altar in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Rillifane\"&gt;Temple of Rillifane&lt;/a&gt;. Demin outlines that the artifacts can be found in the Suldanessellar environs.\nTo open the main door of &lt;a href=\"The%20Palace\"&gt;The Palace&lt;/a&gt;, you will need:\nAfter collecting the artifacts, return to the Temple of Rillifane and place each item on the altar. This action will awaken the Avatar of Rillifane. After the Leaflord finishes its dialogue, one of the outcomes that occurs is to unlock the Palace door."}
{"id": "27778", "revid": "25646820", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27778", "title": "Getting inside the asylum", "text": "Getting inside the asylum is a main storyline quest in and its Enhanced Edition. It begins when the party reaches &lt;a href=\"Brynnlaw\"&gt;Brynnlaw&lt;/a&gt; at the start of Chapter 4, and takes up the first half of the chapter, before giving way to &lt;a href=\"Escaping%20the%20asylum\"&gt;Escaping the asylum&lt;/a&gt;.\nThere are two versions to this quest, depending on if the party arrived at Brynnlaw thanks to &lt;a href=\"Saemon%20Havarian\"&gt;Saemon Havarian&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt;. The Bodhi provided arrival is almost the same, just a wee bit less fighting and experience offered.\nExperienced players can also metagame by simply going straight after &lt;a href=\"Perth%20the%20Adept\"&gt;Perth the Adept&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Desharik\"&gt;Desharik&lt;/a&gt;, but this will forfeit some of the experience to be gained, especially if the Saemon path was taken.\nGameplay.\nThere are two main paths or routes the party can follow to gain access to &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;. These are the Saemon Havarian/Bodhi path or the Pirate Lord Desharik paths. From a strictly party experience reward viewpoint, the Saemon Havarian path provides more XP than the Pirate Lord Desharik path. Note, however, that none of the paths are mutually exclusive. For example, one can rescue Claire, kill Perth, and kill the Pirate Lord in order to fully maximize XP and loot.\nSaemon Havarian path.\nAfter Saemon's ship docks at Brynnlaw, the Shadow Thief representative &lt;a href=\"Sime\"&gt;Sime&lt;/a&gt; will confess that they do not trust Saemon. This distrust proves warranted when Saemon brings three &lt;a href=\"vampire\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt;s onto the deck - &lt;a href=\"Valen\"&gt;Valen&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Del\"&gt;Del&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Parisa\"&gt;Parisa&lt;/a&gt; and then flees. Because of the vampire presence, regardless of the actual time calculation in Brynnlaw, the opening arrival will always be at Nighttime.\nOnce the party has defeated the vampires, Sime instructs them to head to the local tavern, known as &lt;a href=\"The%20Vulgar%20Monkey\"&gt;The Vulgar Monkey&lt;/a&gt;, and speak to a man named &lt;a href=\"Sanik\"&gt;Sanik&lt;/a&gt;, before she heads off to scout.\nSanik is a merchant who supplies the Asylum with basic materials, such as food and spell components, but he states that he is leaving town because of a certain \"misunderstanding\" with the local brothel mistress, &lt;a href=\"Galvena\"&gt;Galvena&lt;/a&gt;.\nBefore he can explain the matter further, an assassin appears and kills him with an arrow \u2014 then attacks the party. Dispatch the murderer to end the encounter.\nThe innkeeper will be angered about the assassination and will explain to the party the situation of Galvena's business and that Sanik was killed because he had an affair with one of the Lady's brothel employees, &lt;a href=\"Claire\"&gt;Claire&lt;/a&gt;. The innkeeper suggests that Claire may be killed by Galvena, and that perhaps she knows how to enter the Asylum. He also explains that you will need some help to enter Galvena's Brothel \u2014 either using violence or talking to a &lt;a href=\"Courtesan\"&gt;Courtesan&lt;/a&gt; just outside her festhall brothel.\nThe Brothel.\nWhen you first reach Brynnlaw, the Brothel, or sometimes referred to as \"\"Festhall\" (or even \"Parlor\" and also \"Galveena's Festhall\"\" - \"seriously\") will be closed to customers/visitor and the courtesans will shun you away, but it will become available after the events in The Vulgar Monkey with Sanik. \nThe courtesan (either a male or a female, depending on the party leader) will either take you inside the building or explain how one can enter by using &lt;a href=\"Galvena%27s%20Medallion\"&gt;Galvena's Medallion&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe party Journal will update and display:\nIf you choose the medallion, you will have to find &lt;a href=\"Chremy\"&gt;Chremy&lt;/a&gt; and then fight him to acquire it. There's no need to wear the medallion, just keep it in your inventory and enter the Brothel, where the frontman/greeter will stop you. \nOnce inside, you will have dialogue with the frontman. \nBasically, to get past him you have three choices to do so:\nFirst, Tell him you are a new employee, and he'll let the party pass through the door to the interior (which is the &lt;a href=\"Cellar%20of%20Brothel\"&gt;Cellar of Brothel&lt;/a&gt; area). If you try this without Galvena's medallion, he'll know you lie, and hostilities will commence. This will not only make him hostile, but any guards further into the interior of the brothel. Basically, your ruse will have failed, and your only course of action is entering as an aggressor and use of force. \nSecond, tell him you are here to hire some companionship. The greater will then say \"Of course! Just out the door of our fine establishment, you shall find a selection of courtesans such as the world has never seen. For a small fee, they shall take care of you.\" Go outside a speak with a courtesan. You may then attempt to try and convince a courtesan to get you inside - you will go to their room. It becomes apparent that Lady Galvena is a horrible person and cruel boss. They will urge you to end Lady Galvena's operations and will suggest that you go speak with the cook &lt;a href=\"Ellie\"&gt;Ellie&lt;/a&gt;, who dislikes the whole state of affairs, and then give her a \"Sleeping Draught\" to use and assist the party getting past some Brothel guards.\nThird, take a chance by using no subterfuge, and attack the &lt;a href=\"Brothel%20Front%20%28greeter/guard%29\"&gt;frontman&lt;/a&gt;. He'll fight back, and two pirate lackey fighters will appear to assist him. Assuming the party wins the fight (of course they will!), if you search the fallen will find the &lt;a href=\"Guild%20House%20Key\"&gt;Guild House Key&lt;/a&gt;. Now access to the brothel cellar is in your hands. When ready, enter the interior. The locked door to the interior of the brothel can be lockpicked, and the key won't be needed. However, if this is done, an alarm script will cause the frontman to become hostile, and a group of pirate fighters will appear to assist, and any guards within the brothel will be alerted and hostile. In other words, the jig is up, and no subterfuge or other plan will work except for brute force methods. \nWithin the brothel cellar are five doors on the long hallway, which is shown on the &lt;a href=\"Cellar%20of%20Brothel\"&gt;Cellar of Brothel&lt;/a&gt; page. The first door leads to the Brothel entrance (the one the party entered from); the second is to the courtesan's room; the third to the kitchen; the fourth to Galvena's private bed chamber quarters; the fifth door is locked and leads to a small dungeon where Claire is being held and tortured. There are two guards by the fourth and fifth doors, and as soon as you reach the third door, they will inquire who you are - they are very suspicious and hard to avoid. The party might avoid detection by stealthing past the guards while hidden or invisible. If you have the &lt;a href=\"Galvena%27s%20Medallion\"&gt;Galvena's Medallion&lt;/a&gt; and the correct dialogue choices, you can convince the guard you are a new employee. If the guards are already hostile, due to previous fighting or picking of the locked door in the Brothel entrance area, then none of this will apply. Those guards will attack the party on sight.\nIn the kitchen, talk with Ellie and her aide. She will agree to apply the draught (obtained from the courtesan you spoke with earlier in the courtesan's room) to the Brothel guard's ale. Ellie's aide will hand it to them. Exit the kitchen and observe as the guards in the hallway and their captain in Galveena's HQ/bed chamber fall peacefully asleep in a drugged slumber. You may now search that room for Galvena's Key, to open the Brothel prison/dungeon door. Afterwards, while the &lt;a href=\"Guard%20%28Brothel%20Cellar%29\"&gt;Guard (Brothel Cellar)&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Guard%20Captain%20%28Brothel%29\"&gt;Guard Captain (Brothel)&lt;/a&gt; are under the effects of the spiked ale with the sleeping potion, if the party desires they may attack them. The guards will arise and try to fight back. Don't forget to return and speak with Ellie after lady Galvena has been vanquished, to inform her of your deeds, for a XP reward. \nAlternatively, the party can just use violence and take out the Brothel guards through force of arms on your way to find Claire the Brothel dungeon. The fight shouldn't be difficult at this stage of the saga. One of the guards wields a &lt;a href=\"Halberd%20%2B2\"&gt;Halberd +2&lt;/a&gt;. You'll need Galvena's Key to get into the Brothel prison/dungeon area, which is found in one of the hallway side rooms. if you decide to do it this way, then Ellie the cook and all that other Sleeping Draught business is now over. You may safely ignore Ellie and company.\nGalvena's Key to open the Brothel prison doorway is inside Galvena's/HQ bedchamber.\nRescuing Claire.\nWith the key in hand, gather your party and enter the Brothel Prison map. As soon as you open the eastern door, you will see Galvena, &lt;a href=\"Vadek\"&gt;Vadek&lt;/a&gt; and Claire. After some dialogue, hostilities will ensue. Note that combat in small spaces can be tricky, so expect a confined area with little room for maneuver. \nVadek is a wizard and will engage in spell casting if able when hostilities begin. See his article page for details. Galvena will engage in melee combat and is less of a potential menace. Suggest that the party pay attention to Vadek as a priority. If defeated, Valdek drops a score of Darts +1 and a Quarterstaff +2; Galvena drops a Studded Leather Armor +3 and a Flail +2.\nAddress Claire inside the cell and she will then soon transition with the party to the docks so she can escape Brynnlaw. It is assumed the party helps her do this, as one of her legs has been broken during torture. A friend of Sanik's, named &lt;a href=\"Golin\"&gt;Golin&lt;/a&gt;, will greet Claire, then thank the party for her rescue, Claire will board his ship. Golin then will finally explain to &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; how to access the Asylum: First, with a specific ward stone possessed by the Island's administrative Cowled Wizard, &lt;a href=\"Perth%20the%20Adept\"&gt;Perth the Adept&lt;/a&gt;. The second path would be to petition the Pirate Lord Desharik to allow entry.\nThe Bodhi path.\nAs soon as the party arrives on Brynnlaw, Saemon Havarian tells you to find &lt;a href=\"Sanik\"&gt;Sanik&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"The%20Vulgar%20Monkey\"&gt;The Vulgar Monkey&lt;/a&gt; inn. The same information will be furnished to the party as above, and the same path to get more information will be presented.\nPerth the Adept and the wardstone path.\n&lt;a href=\"Perth%20the%20Adept\"&gt;Perth&lt;/a&gt; is a mage that lives in the eastern part of Brynnlaw. Enter the &lt;a href=\"CW%27s%20House\"&gt;Cowled Wizard's residence&lt;/a&gt; and dialogue will begin \u2014 leading to an inevitable confrontation. Do not give him much time to act, as he can cast powerful spells. He will drop the &lt;a href=\"Wardstone%20for%20Asylum\"&gt;Wardstone for Asylum&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Book%20of%20Infinite%20Spells\"&gt;Book of Infinite Spells&lt;/a&gt; if slain. See his article page for more details.\nWardstone in hand, head to the northeastern exit of the town, where you can find\u00a0your trusted escort &lt;a href=\"Sime\"&gt;Sime&lt;/a&gt; once again. Speak to her then proceed to Spellhold. The party will enter a new map. \nPirate Lord Desharik path.\nDesharik is within his home. A guard outside his residence will need to be persuaded to let you have an audience with the Pirate lord. Once inside, then the party may take an alternate path to gain entry into Spellhold. You'll require either &lt;a href=\"Minsc\"&gt;Minsc&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Wilson\"&gt;Wilson&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Yoshimo\"&gt;Yoshimo&lt;/a&gt; in your party, or a player character with superior charisma (16+).\nAs Golin explained, &lt;a href=\"Desharik\"&gt;Desharik&lt;/a&gt; has been using his position to throw anyone he considers a threat in the Asylum as a \"deviant\". His enemies, but also the mentally ill, wind up in Spellhold. You must convince him that you belong there. Telling him \"I'm mad\" is not enough by itself. He'll require further proof. See Desharik's page for the details.\nAs such, having either Minsc (a ranger who talks with a hamster) and/or Wilson (a brown bear who speaks with &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;) in the party is enough to convince him. Or another possible way: the captain will recognize Yoshimo (Yoshimo suspiciously claims the pirate lord must \"believe he owes him from a previous debt\").\nIf this goes well, you will be granted entrance to the Asylum without having to obtain the Wardstone or confront the Cowled Wizard representative."}
