{"id": "50835", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50835", "title": "Ghaunadaur Priest", "text": "Ghaunadaur Priest is a drow priestess and is amongst a group of Ghaunadaur cultists with their various monsters and slimes. They have gathered on a large circular platform in &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt;. The cultists will be hostile and attempt to slay any who intrude within range of their group. The leader is accompanied by another two drow - a cleric leader and mage.\nThe Priestess will begin combat with an attempt to cast a defensive buff, and then go on the offensive with a choice of ranged spells. Any opponent in range may be engaged in melee and or touch range attacks with &lt;a href=\"Cause%20Serious%20Wounds\"&gt;Cause Serious Wounds&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Cause%20Critical%20Wounds\"&gt;Cause Critical Wounds&lt;/a&gt;. It will try and heal itself from damage when wounded at 50% with a &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Medium%20Wounds\"&gt;Cure Medium Wounds&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some changes to this priestess. The default AI is changed to a \"Smarter Priest\" SCS version, which will allow for evaluating threats and looking for vulnerabilities in opponents, which in turn influences spell casting choice and attack/defense options. An entire new repertoire of available priest spells is included.\nSCS will trigger an opening preparatory self buff including &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Draw Upon Holy Might (spell)&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Free Action (spell)&lt;/a&gt;. Afterwards the AI will react to its gathered threat and vulnerability assessments and make appropriate offensive and disabling spell casts. If engaged in melee range, the cleric will fight with its flail and try to get off touch range &lt;a href=\"Cause%20Serious%20Wounds\"&gt;Cause Serious Wounds&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Cause%20Critical%20Wounds\"&gt;Cause Critical Wounds&lt;/a&gt; spells. It may also try to conjure a summoned creature to assist.\nThe Priest is assigned one pip in flail weapon proficiency and one in single weapon fighting style. A random SCS treasure is included in the inventory."}
{"id": "50833", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50833", "title": "Ghaunadaur Priest Leader", "text": "Ghaunadaur Priest leader is a drow priestess and is amongst a group of Ghaunadaur cultists with their various monsters and slimes. They have gathered on a large circular platform in &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt;. The cultists will be hostile and attempt to slay any who intrude within range of their group. The leader is accompanied by another two drow - a cleric and mage.\nThe Priestess will begin combat with a contingency of helpful buffs. It will then attempt further spell casts if able - to harm or disable opponents, or to assist and heal allies. If engaged in melee combat, will defend itself with equipped flail, and try a &lt;a href=\"Righteous%20Magic\"&gt;Righteous Magic&lt;/a&gt; to better perform in close quarters combat.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some changes to this priestess. The default AI is changed to a \"Smarter Priest\" SCS version, which will allow for evaluating threats and looking for vulnerabilities in opponents, which in turn influences spell casting choice and attack/defense options. An entire new repertoire of available priest spells are included.\nSCS will trigger an opening preparatory self-buff including &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Free Action (spell)&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt;. It will also recognize if a party member is invisible, under stealth or sanctuary, and then attempt a divination spell. All other actions are wide open depending on threat assessments by the Priestess, including healing self, healing allies, casting offensive spells, disabling spells, or summoning creatures to help. If attacked in melee combat, the priestess will attempt flail strikes and or touch range attacks like &lt;a href=\"Cause%20Critical%20Wounds\"&gt;Cause Critical Wounds&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Harm\"&gt;Harm&lt;/a&gt;. Allies that are under certain status effects like &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Paralyze\"&gt;Paralyze&lt;/a&gt; will be noticed, and she may try to remove it. \nThe Priest is assigned one pip in flail weapon proficiency and one in single weapon fighting style. A random SCS treasure is included in the inventory."}
{"id": "49948", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49948", "title": "Ghell Rando", "text": "The Sun Soul Monk Ghell Rando is a character from and part of the &lt;a href=\"Rasaad%27s%20Journey\"&gt;Rasaad's Journey&lt;/a&gt; quest line.\nGameplay.\nHe is one of the members of the &lt;a href=\"Tears%20of%20Sel%C3%BBne\"&gt;Tears of Sel\u00fbne&lt;/a&gt; which intercepts the party in the wilderness after visiting and then exiting the &lt;a href=\"Abandoned%20Amphitheater\"&gt;Abandoned Amphitheater&lt;/a&gt; area map. \nGhell is one of four Sun Soul Monks who confront the party (\"the Tears of Selune\") and state that Rasaad is a known murderer. Various dialogue options are presented. These dialogue selections will determine the direction of the encounter in the Wilderness. \nGhell has all the abilities, immunities and special bonuses afforded to a Sun Soul Monk kit commensurate with his 12th Level experience.\nIn battle he will quaff a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Extra%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Extra Healing&lt;/a&gt; when damaged to a 50% threshold.\nA &lt;a href=\"Lay%20On%20Hands%20%28monk%29\"&gt;Lay On Hands (monk)&lt;/a&gt; ability is used if original HP damage exceeds 60%.\nHe fights with unarmed attacks, hands and feet in melee combat, these attacks count as a +2 &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20item\"&gt;Enchanted item&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe'll possibly enable the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fists\"&gt;Flaming Fists&lt;/a&gt; spell ability when opponents are detected at a specific range.\nA &lt;a href=\"Sun%20Soulbeam\"&gt;Sun Soulbeam&lt;/a&gt; may be attempted if an opponent is in range and has less than 50% Magic or Fire resistance - and later a &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Sun\"&gt;Greater Sun&lt;/a&gt; if a target is within 30'."}
{"id": "9047", "revid": "4896558", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9047", "title": "Ghlouralk", "text": "Ghlouralk is a &lt;a href=\"beholder\"&gt;beholder&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Baeloth%20Barrityl\"&gt;Baeloth's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"The%20Black%20Pits\"&gt;Black Pits&lt;/a&gt;. He can give the player advice on their next battle. However, in the final battle, he helps the &lt;a href=\"drow\"&gt;drow&lt;/a&gt; when he is called (after &lt;a href=\"Elan%20Garaq\"&gt;Elan Garaq&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Thardek\"&gt;Thardek&lt;/a&gt; are dead). He may be hard to defeat. He is a standard beholder \u2014 not as weak as a &lt;a href=\"Gauth\"&gt;Gauth&lt;/a&gt;, and not as powerful as an &lt;a href=\"Elder%20Orb\"&gt;Elder Orb&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "8125", "revid": "281375", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8125", "title": "Ghorak", "text": "Ghorak is a cursed man who can be found in his &lt;a href=\"Ghorak%27s%20Home\"&gt;house&lt;/a&gt; in the southeast section of &lt;a href=\"south%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;south Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. He was cursed with a rotting disease for killing his brother, Kereph. Now Ghorak looks and moves like a &lt;a href=\"Zombies\"&gt;zombie&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; might hear about him and his brother in the streets of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;br&gt;\nCommoner: \"\"Alas, the rot's got poor Ghorak. I doubt he'll be with us much longer.\"&lt;br&gt;\nWhen spoken to, Ghorak will warn you away, shouting that he is diseased. \nIf you offer to cure him, it will start his &lt;a href=\"Ghorak%20the%20Diseased\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;. He tells you that potions and spells are useless, but then asks you to find the &lt;a href=\"Skull%20of%20Kereph\"&gt;skull of his brother&lt;/a&gt; and take it to the &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%27s%20Hall\"&gt;The Lady's Hall&lt;/a&gt; if you want to help him.\nDialogue.\nDepending on what you say to him, you might miss the quest.\nThis starts the quest.\nGhorak will exit the house and never return."}
{"id": "46573", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46573", "title": "Ghorak's Home", "text": "Ghorak's Home is the home where &lt;a href=\"Ghorak\"&gt;Ghorak&lt;/a&gt; can be found and is located between a &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28south%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;generic house&lt;/a&gt; where &lt;a href=\"Larriaz\"&gt;Larriaz&lt;/a&gt; can be found and a second &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28southeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;generic house&lt;/a&gt; which is accessible from &lt;a href=\"South%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;South Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. The front door is unlocked.\nOn the ground floor you'll find Ghorak wandering about the premises. The chest is locked with a DC of 30 and contains a potion of &lt;a href=\"Antidote\"&gt;Antidote&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Short%20Sword\"&gt;Short Sword&lt;/a&gt;. The bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Dragon%20Coast\"&gt;History of the Dragon Coast&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20VI\"&gt;History of Shadowdale VI&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second floor has a unlocked chest which contains 43 and twelve &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Dagger\"&gt;Throwing Dagger&lt;/a&gt;s. The bookshelves contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Dead%20Three\"&gt;History of the Dead Three&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20XIII\"&gt;History of Shadowdale XIII&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "11098", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11098", "title": "Ghorak the Diseased", "text": "&lt;a href=\"Ghorak\"&gt;Ghorak&lt;/a&gt; is afflicted by an unnamed, flesh-eating disease which gives him the appearance of a zombie (whether he actually \"is\" a zombie or not is unclear.) Many years ago he was cursed by the goddess &lt;a href=\"Tymora\"&gt;Tymora&lt;/a&gt; for the brutal slaying of his brother Kereph. Perhaps there is a way to lift his curse.\nThis quest is given by Ghorak who can be found in his &lt;a href=\"Ghorak%27s%20Home\"&gt;house&lt;/a&gt; in the district of &lt;a href=\"South%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;South Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. When spoken to he will warn the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; away, shouting that he is diseased. If the party offers to cure him, he will tell them that there is no cure. Then he will ask the player to find his brother's skull and take it to &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%27s%20Hall\"&gt;The Lady's Hall&lt;/a&gt; if they really want to help.\nIf the party states that they cannot help him, he will exit the house and disappear forever.\nFinding and Returning the Skull.\nThe\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Skull%20of%20Kereph\"&gt;Skull of Kereph&lt;/a&gt; is in the &lt;a href=\"Three%20Old%20Kegs\"&gt;Three Old Kegs&lt;/a&gt; tavern in &lt;a href=\"North%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;North Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, hidden behind a painting on the second floor. Once the party has the skull, they must take it to the The Lady's Hall in &lt;a href=\"West%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;West Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and give it to &lt;a href=\"Agnasia\"&gt;Agnasia&lt;/a&gt;, a priestess of Tymora. \nWhen the party gives the skull to Agnasia she expresses surprise at seeing it and will explain Ghorak's full story. It turns out his brother Kereph was a priest of Tymora and had so much good fortune in his life that \"people\" became jealous and murdered him. His body was torn apart and his head was cut off and taken so that it could not be buried with him. Agnasia then thanks the party for returning it and rewards them, and advises that they return to Ghorak as she believes the curse will now be lifted.\nCompletion.\nWhen the player returns to Ghorak and tells him that his brother's skull has been returned to the The Lady's Hall, his curse is lifted. He gives the player his thanks but nothing else. The only rewards for this quest are 1000 XP and a one point &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt; increase, which have been already given by Agnasia."}
{"id": "5003", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5003", "title": "Ghost Armor", "text": "Ghost Armor creates a magical field of force around the caster roughly equal to \"plate mail +1\".\nGameplay.\nThe spell is applied to the caster only.\nOnce cast, the spell will render a series of 3D graphic effects over the caster's sprite, and the display a text reading \"Armor\".\nA player character will display an icon (No. 127) titled \"Ghost Armor\" on their portrait as well as a color glow pulse effect for the spell's duration.\nAdditionally, a sound effect will audible when the spell expires.\nThe spell sets the caster's base &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; to 2, however, if the spell recipient's base armor class is already better than that, the spell won't change it.\nGhost Armor can be removed with various &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects and the &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its effects, area of effect, duration and school. See below for description:\nGhost Armor\nLevel: 3\nSchool: Illusion\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 10 turns\nCasting Time: 3\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen this spell is cast, the wizard creates an insubstantial but quasi-real suit of armor. This semi-illusory material covers the subject and actually gives some real protection provided that opponents don\u2019t actively disbelieve in the armor (detecting the illusion) and neither a dispel magic nor detect illusion spell is cast upon it. Until dispelled or disbelieved, the armor sets the recipient\u2019s base armor class to 2. This spell will not function with any other form of magical armor, but it is cumulative with dexterity bonuses and, in the case of fighter/mages, with the shield bonus. The ghost armor does not hinder movement, adds no weight or encumbrance, nor does it prevent spellcasting. A favorite among mage/thieves, the ghostly nimbus of light which surrounds the recipient grants +20% bonus to Hide in Shadows."}
{"id": "42287", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42287", "title": "Ghost Dragon Guardian", "text": "Ghost Dragon Guardian is a side quest that can only be accessed by exploring the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River\"&gt;Underground River&lt;/a&gt; area in Chapter 10 of .\nAcquiring.\nIn the far southwest of the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River\"&gt;Underground River&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; will encounter a ghost dragon named &lt;a href=\"Halatathlaer\"&gt;Halatathlaer&lt;/a&gt; outside of the entrance to the ruins of &lt;a href=\"Kanaglym\"&gt;Kanaglym&lt;/a&gt;. She will warn them not to approach her, saying that she is compelled to guard the entrance. No matter what the player says to her, she keeps returning to this basic point.\nCompleting.\nIf the player chooses to attack Halatathlaer, she is worth 10,500 EXP and the gateway to Kanaglym is open. She is, however, a difficult battle.\nIf the player simply ignores her and walks past her, she will thank them; the &lt;a href=\"necromancer\"&gt;necromancer&lt;/a&gt; who bound her made a mistake in their commands, compelling her to \"threaten\" potential intruders, but not to actually \"attack\" them. She warns that the necromancer resides within the ruins, and as long as they hold her essence, she can be compelled to attack the player. If they proceed into Kanaglym, they will be attacked by the resident necromancers; if &lt;a href=\"Kherriun\"&gt;Kherriun&lt;/a&gt; is sufficiently damaged, she will drop the talisman that allows her to control the ghost dragon and Halatathlaer will begin attacking the enemy creatures within Kanaglym - otherwise, she will attack the player's party until either released or slain. Once the Cabal is dead, she will thank the player for freeing them and, after instructing them to seek out &lt;a href=\"Daeros%20Dragonspear\"&gt;Daeros Dragonspear&lt;/a&gt; and tell him that she waits for him in the Fugue Plane, will pass on to the afterlife, rewarding the party with 32,000 EXP.\nRegardless of which outcome occurs, entering Kanaglym is necessary to begin and complete the quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Cabal\"&gt;The Cabal&lt;/a&gt;.\nHalatathlaer's Hatchlings.\nHalatathlaer's children are the &lt;a href=\"Blind%20Albino%20Wyrmling\"&gt;Blind Albino Wyrmling&lt;/a&gt;s in the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20Wyrm%20Cavern\"&gt;Underground Wyrm Cavern&lt;/a&gt; area. If she is approached whilst the party has the &lt;a href=\"Journal%20of%20Ithtaerus\"&gt;Journal of Ithtaerus&lt;/a&gt; in their inventory, she will give unique dialogue depending on when this happens.\nIf it is done before slaying the cabal, she will directly tell the party that she will aid them if they free her from Kherriun's control, assuming they do not mock her for the death of her children"}
{"id": "32072", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32072", "title": "Ghost Jar", "text": "The Ghost Jar is carried by &lt;a href=\"Kherriun\"&gt;Kherriun&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Kanaglym\"&gt;Kanaglym&lt;/a&gt; in . The ghost jar will shatter when Kherriun is seriously injured (hitpoints below 30%) and free the ghost dragon &lt;a href=\"Halatathlaer\"&gt;Halatathlaer&lt;/a&gt;, who can assist in combat against the other &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Magician\"&gt;Dark Magician&lt;/a&gt;s."}
{"id": "7713", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7713", "title": "Ghost Knight", "text": "The Ghost Knight is the soul of an ancient knight that was defending Firewine, cursed to remain in its undead state until it is able to rejoin with the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Knight\"&gt;Undead Knight&lt;/a&gt;. A total of six are found inside the &lt;a href=\"Firewine%20Ruins\"&gt;Firewine Ruins&lt;/a&gt; and their story is told in &lt;a href=\"Poe\"&gt;Poe's&lt;/a&gt; epic ballad \"The Knights of Days Hence\" which he will gladly recite to you. Poe is found near the middle of the Firewine Bridge in the &lt;a href=\"Firewine%20Bridge\"&gt;Firewine Bridge&lt;/a&gt; area.\nSynopsis.\nThe knights came to the Ruins to fight \"a hellish wrath from deep below whence fires came.\" The knights finally won the battle but were killed in their sleep by a fellow knight who \"made foe with gold in mind to take and plunder riches won.\" So now they \"wait in time for one that ran to face the crime...til honor's need someone dost fill.\" It seems that the &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Armor\"&gt;Ancient Armor&lt;/a&gt; from the Undead Knight will free the \"heroes lost below that haunt in sleep with ghostly glow.\"\nUpon speaking to any one of the six Ghost Knights:\nIf you do not have the armor they need they say:\nIf you have the armor they say:\n...and fade into peaceful oblivion.\nGameplay.\nThe six knights are totally immune to all types of damage except &lt;a href=\"poison\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt;, and have all saving throws at 1. The easiest solution to kill one of them is to cast &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Resistance%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Magic Resistance&lt;/a&gt; on it (available only to a single-class Druid level 9 within BGEE experience cap) to actually lower its magic resistance, then have a Mage cast a few &lt;a href=\"Cloudkill\"&gt;Cloudkills&lt;/a&gt; in the room (tested successfully). All the items are marked as droppable and can be looted on the ground when the knights are killed.\nItems.\nAll of the knights are equipped with a &lt;a href=\"Helm%20of%20Charm%20Protection\"&gt;Helmet of Charm Protection&lt;/a&gt;."}
