{"id": "11013", "revid": "50459896", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11013", "title": "Ghoul", "text": "Ghouls are undead creatures that, according to folklore, are said to be created after the death of a man or woman who engaged in cannibalism.\nDescription.\nThey are weaker, more common versions of &lt;a href=\"ghast\"&gt;ghast&lt;/a&gt;s, and can be easily distinguished by their green skin as opposed to the brown skin of the latter\nGameplay.\nGhouls are immune to poison, charm, confusion, hold, paralysis, poison, and many other effects and spells.\nThey attack three times per round for 1d6 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt;, with each hit forcing a saving throw to avoid being &lt;a href=\"Paralyze\"&gt;paralyzed&lt;/a&gt; for 30 seconds."}
{"id": "49284", "revid": "50459896", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49284", "title": "Ghoul Lord", "text": "A Ghoul Lord is a more powerful version of a &lt;a href=\"Ghoul\"&gt;Ghoul&lt;/a&gt; and can be encountered during the \"\" campaign. They can be found in &lt;a href=\"Ghoul%20Town\"&gt;Ghoul Town&lt;/a&gt; below &lt;a href=\"The%20Old%20Tunnels\"&gt;The Old Tunnels&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nGhoul lords attack three times a round with a more powerful melee attack than the average &lt;a href=\"GHOUL1.ITM\"&gt;Ghoul Touch&lt;/a&gt;. It is considered a &lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; weapon of &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20item\"&gt;enchantment&lt;/a&gt; level 2 dealing 1d6 &lt;a href=\"Piercing%20damage\"&gt;piercing&lt;/a&gt; damage, with a range of one foot and a speed factor of 3.\nEach successful hit upon a living creature has the following effects, none of which offer a saving throw, but all of which can be dispelled, do not bypass resistance, and have a duration of 100 seconds:\nIn addition, a &lt;a href=\"dwarf\"&gt;dwarf&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"gnome\"&gt;gnome&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"half-elf\"&gt;half-elf&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"halfling\"&gt;halfling&lt;/a&gt; or human target must &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;save vs death&lt;/a&gt; to avoid being &lt;a href=\"Paralyze\"&gt;Paralyzed&lt;/a&gt; for 30 seconds."}
{"id": "4983", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4983", "title": "Ghoul Touch", "text": "A successful Ghoul Touch attack allows the caster to paralyze any creature he touches.\nGameplay.\nThis spell is cast on self only.\nAfter the spell is finished, the casters main hand weapon is replaced by a magically created weapon (&lt;a href=\"GOULT.ITM\"&gt;GOULT.ITM&lt;/a&gt;), lasting 5-rounds - the caster's sprite will briefly render a 3D graphic effect at this time indicating the spell is complete and the weapon is ready to use.\nThe main hand weapon can strike with reach range of 1, and the weapon is classified a +6 &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20item\"&gt;Enchanted item&lt;/a&gt; for the purposes of what it may strike.\nThe ghoul touch weapon provides a hidden behind the scenes 4-point &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus to hit as it is considered a \"touch attack\" - this feature was added by an earlier in-game update version in the Enhanced Edition.\nThis touch weapon requires no weapon proficiency, so there are no applicable bonuses or penalties to hit.\nA successful hit on a target inflicts 1d2 non-lethal (fist) stunning damage, which can be modified by the attacker's &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; attribute, and the victim is exposed to a &lt;a href=\"Paralyze\"&gt;Paralyze&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nThe victim is allowed a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spells to negate the paralysis.\nA failed saving throw will make the target immobile and rigid and in a &lt;a href=\"Helpless\"&gt;Helpless&lt;/a&gt; state - the target will have a brief lighting effect and color fade render on their sprite, a sound effect will audible, and a text will display \"Paralyzed\" - the paralysis lasts for 5-rounds.\nWhen the paralysis expires, another sound effect audibles to signify that the effect is finished.\nThe ghoul touch paralysis is classified as magical, and thus it can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, and any &lt;a href=\"Spell%20protections%20type\"&gt;Spell protections type&lt;/a&gt; defense such as a &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, as well as a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Necromancy&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe paralysis can also be removed by a &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Ghoul Touch\" not only may cause those touched with paralysis, but the victim takes on a horrible stench that can affect those nearby with nausea. The Pen and Paper spell version only works on human, dwarf, gnome, half-elf or halfling targets. Only necromancers may use this spell.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its effects, damage type, duration, and saving throw. See below for description:\nGhoul Touch\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Necromancy\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 2\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: Death partial\nWhen the caster completes this spell, a red glow encompasses his hand. On a successful touch from the wizard, the spell inflicts 1d8 points of magic damage and paralyzes the target for 5 rounds unless a successful save vs. death at a -1 penalty is made. The wizard gains a +4 bonus to hit the target and his touch is considered to be of +1 enchantment to determine what it can hit."}
{"id": "22863", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22863", "title": "Ghoul Town", "text": "Ghoul Town is an optional area buried deep in the &lt;a href=\"Pit%20of%20the%20Faithless\"&gt;Pit of the Faithless&lt;/a&gt;, that can only be visited during the &lt;a href=\"Investigate%20and%20Destroy%20the%20Cult%20of%20the%20Eyeless\"&gt;Investigate and Destroy the Cult of the Eyeless&lt;/a&gt; side quest if the Cult Traitor &lt;a href=\"Tad\"&gt;Tad&lt;/a&gt; has granted the party access to the pit.\nEntrances.\nThere are two entrances to Ghoul Town, both from the &lt;a href=\"Pit%20of%20the%20Faithless\"&gt;Pit of the Faithless&lt;/a&gt;. Outside in the pit are two ramshackle buildings: one to the northeast (\"a \"structure..surrounded by the stench of decay and filth\"\"), and one to the northwest ( a \"crude dwelling..perched precariously over the abyss below\").\nEntering from the western side places you right before a silent trigger that spans the whole middle section. Crossing it spawns a level-dependent group of undead up beyond the three steps on the north side.\nEntering from the eastern side lands you on the upper-east platform of Ghoul Town.\nMayor of Ghoul Town.\nThe inhabitants of this town have become more sophisticated and have stopped eating the living. With a steady supply of the Faithless thrown down into the pit, they have no issues sticking to their diet... as long as they're not confronted with \"the good stuff\", that is.\nHere you will be addressed by &lt;a href=\"Theshal\"&gt;Mayor Theshal&lt;/a&gt; who is neutral at the moment:\"Hsss! Why do you come amongst usss? I begsss you to leave! The sssmell...the sssmell of food makesss usss wild!\"You might have only one chance to ask a question before Mayor Teshal loses his very limited self-control and turns hostile:\"...the...sssmell...it isss too much! I cannot ssstand it any moresss!! HsssSSS!!\"One line of questioning is to ask: \"Tell us where the passage to the beholder lair is and I'll be out of your hair quickly enough.\"\"You...wantsss to sssee the Great Feeder?\"Followed by: \"The...Great Feeder? If you're referring to the one who throws you down all the dead bodies then, yes, I suppose so.\"\"The...the Great Feeder isss beyond the bridge, he isss...we goesss there to ssserve him and cleansss him...\"Teshal is flanked by a &lt;a href=\"Zombie\"&gt;Zombie&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Ghoul%20Lord\"&gt;Ghoul Lord&lt;/a&gt;.\nLayout.\nBelow the Mayor's platform to the southwest is a larger area with another &lt;a href=\"Zombie\"&gt;Zombie&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ghoul%20Lord\"&gt;Ghoul Lord&lt;/a&gt;.\nTo the northwest, are three steps leading to the third and final area. It contains a spawn point that activates only once, and produce a group of &lt;a href=\"Mummy\"&gt;Mummies&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ghast\"&gt;Ghasts&lt;/a&gt; .\nIf the silent trigger below was activated, it spawns an additional, different group of undead depending upon current experience points accrued by &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;.\nContainers.\nThere are three containers in this area."}
