{"id": "55658", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55658", "title": "Giant Snake (Guardian of Slime)", "text": "Giant Snake is the \"Guardian of Slime.\" It will spawn in the Slime Chamber/laboratory in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt; when the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20of%20Air\"&gt;Guardian of Air&lt;/a&gt; is defeated. It spawns along with &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Mist\"&gt;Poison Mist&lt;/a&gt; creatures and special &lt;a href=\"Green%20Slime%20%28WK%20Elemental%20level%29\"&gt;Green slime&lt;/a&gt; jellies with higher-than-normal resistances.\nGameplay.\nThis one-of-a-kind creature poses a threat from the melee attacks it will do in close quarters combat.\nGetting struck can be an issue, due to the no saving throw automatic &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; effect, and the &lt;a href=\"poison\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nFirst time players that just rush in and start swinging with no specific protections applied can be at risk here.\nBest to not get struck by this snake at all. Try killing it with ranged weapons or spell attacks but pay attention to its immunities and protections listed on the InfoBox.\nWhen it's dead, the player can retrieve the &lt;a href=\"Slime%20Scepter\"&gt;Slime Scepter&lt;/a&gt; from the body."}
{"id": "11140", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11140", "title": "Giant Spider", "text": "The Giant Spider is the strongest common variety of &lt;a href=\"Spiders\"&gt;Spiders&lt;/a&gt;, mostly encountered during \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" with only a few encounters during \"\".\nDescription.\nThey are almost always encountered within the depths of a forest, particularly during waylaid encounters between such areas, and are distinguishable from their brethren by way of a green body with grey legs - pointedly different from the more powerful &lt;a href=\"Phase%20Spider\"&gt;Phase Spider&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nLike most spiders, they can &lt;a href=\"poison\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt; their enemies and are immune to &lt;a href=\"Web\"&gt;Web&lt;/a&gt;. They are essentially a step up from the &lt;a href=\"Huge%20Spider\"&gt;Huge Spider&lt;/a&gt;, while not yet evolving any special abilities often found among the higher-tiered spiders. They also have a relatively low mobs-per-spawn rate, with a high level party only ever encountering as many as two, comparable in this regard to the &lt;a href=\"Cave%20Bear\"&gt;Cave Bear&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Wraith%20Spider\"&gt;Wraith Spider&lt;/a&gt; while pointedly being worth significantly less experience than either.\nSummoned.\nGiant spiders can be summoned by a 7th or 8th level &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt; casting the 4th level Wizard spell &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Spawn\"&gt;Spider Spawn&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "30605", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30605", "title": "Giant Spider Leg", "text": "A Giant Spider Leg is a in \"\".\nAcquisition.\nThe leg will drop from the &lt;a href=\"Seven-Legged%20Spider\"&gt;Seven-Legged Spider&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Cave\"&gt;Spider Cave&lt;/a&gt;, a subsection of the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Wyrms\"&gt;Forest of Wyrms&lt;/a&gt;.\nFunction.\nIt is used in the quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Call%20of%20the%20Wild%20Mage\"&gt;The Call of the Wild Mage&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrivia.\nFor unknown reasons, like &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Silk\"&gt;Spider Silk&lt;/a&gt;, this item cannot be placed in a &lt;a href=\"Bag%20of%20Holding\"&gt;Bag of Holding&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "24782", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24782", "title": "Giant Troll", "text": "Giant Trolls are &lt;a href=\"humanoid\"&gt;humanoid&lt;/a&gt; in \"Baldur's Gate II\".\nAs a result of cross-breeding &lt;a href=\"Troll\"&gt;Troll&lt;/a&gt;s with &lt;a href=\"Hill%20Giant\"&gt;Hill Giant&lt;/a&gt;s, they are taller than regular trolls, but keep the slender, hunched figure and the disproportionately long arms, characteristic for the species. They are also not very diverse statistically from other trolls, being able to regenerate quickly and, once brought to \"almost dead\" status, falling into a stupor and becoming impervious to all damage save for &lt;a href=\"Acid%20damage\"&gt;acid&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt;. If not finished quickly with those elements, they regain their health and raise up to fight again.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises the Giant Troll. A default SCS AI script is assigned so that the creature will have smarter tactical behavior in combat, including opponent threat assessment and for better targeting.\nThe mod also places additional Giant Trolls in certain areas of the De'Arnise Keep if the Tactical Challenges for BG2 \"Tougher De'Arnise Keep\" component is added to your game. "}
