{"id": "11984", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11984", "title": "Glabrezu (Shadows of Amn)", "text": "Glabrezus are &lt;a href=\"tanar%27ri\"&gt;tanar'ri&lt;/a&gt; that specialize in the temptation of mortals, although they are considered a middle-class demon of the Abyss.\nThis group of glabrezus are encountered as stand-alone creatures in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Rillifane\"&gt;Temple of Rillifane&lt;/a&gt; \"(DEMGLAB2.cre)\" during or are spawned by hidden proximity traps in the &lt;a href=\"Guarded%20Compound\"&gt;Guarded Compound&lt;/a&gt; \"(DEMGLASU.cre)\" and the &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple\"&gt;Ruined Temple&lt;/a&gt; \"(DEMGLA01.cre)\" during .\nCreature \"(DEMGLASU)\" is also the glabrezu that is \"Gated\" by a mage or other powerful being who is capable of utilizing the 8th-level &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Fiend\"&gt;Summon Fiend&lt;/a&gt; spell. This creature is not banished by a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt;.\nCreatures \"(JONDEM01.cre)\" and \"(JONDEM03.cre)\" appear with &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus%20%28Abyss%29\"&gt;Jon Irenicus&lt;/a&gt; in the final battle in &lt;a href=\"The%20Abyss\"&gt;The Abyss&lt;/a&gt;. These demons are the weakest version of glabrezu in the game, with no innate or spell casting ability, and they can't see invisible creatures.\nGameplay.\nThey are &lt;a href=\"IMMUNE2.ITM\"&gt;immune to weapons&lt;/a&gt; of less than +2 enchantment and deal 3d4 damage with their &lt;a href=\"BL3-12M4.ITM\"&gt;pincer-like claws&lt;/a&gt; that protrude from the end of their massive main limbs. While boasting high &lt;a href=\"hit%20point\"&gt;hit point&lt;/a&gt;s and a low &lt;a href=\"armor%20class\"&gt;armor class&lt;/a&gt;, glabrezus are also capable of casting several different offensive spells that can wreak havoc on unprepared adventuring parties.\nThis group of glabrezus will cast the following spells in combat:\n\"DEMGLA01:\"\n\"DEMGLAB2:\"\n\"DEMGLASU:\"\nA glabrezu's immunities can vary slightly from one creature type to the next, but they all possess an &lt;a href=\"RINGDEMN.ITM\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; in their ring slot which provides the following protections:\nWhile most of these glabrezu possess the ability to see hidden and invisible creatures, specialized effects applied to this group of creatures include the following:\n\"DEMGLA01:\"\n\"DEMGLAB2 &amp; DEMGLASU:\"\n\"JONDEM01 &amp; JONDEM03:\"\nWeaknesses \u2014 The following spells and status effects are potentially effective against glabrezus:\nMod Content.\nMods:.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod, and the \"Improved Fiends\" component will Improve the Glabrezu as follows:\nGlabrezu (cast at 17th level):&lt;br&gt;\nTeleport without Error, Mirror Image, and Remove Magic, at will&lt;br&gt;\nPower Word: Stun, Unholy Blight, and Confusion, all at will\nThe &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod gated fiend available to the player and opponent mages who use the \"Summon Fiend\" arcane spell has the following abilities:\nGlabrezu (15 Hit Dice - casts at level 15, Level 17 with SCS &amp; SR):&lt;br&gt;\nSTR 20, DEX 10 (18 with SCS), CON 21, INT 16, WIS 17, CHA 16 (22 with SCS &amp; SR); AL Chaotic Evil&lt;br&gt;\nHP 164, AC -6 (-11 with SCS), THAC0 -1, Saving Throws 6/8/6/10/8 (6/6/6/8/6 with SCS &amp;SR)&lt;br&gt;\n4 Attacks Per Round, 2d6+12 Piercing Damage (Pincers &amp; Claws +4), Adjusted damage is 17-27 with SCS &amp; SR&lt;br&gt;\nSpecial Qualities:&lt;br&gt;\nSpecial Abilities:&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "55962", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55962", "title": "Glabrezu (TELTAN1)", "text": " \nThis Glabrezu demon is unique in the game and has a deep crimson tint/hue. \nIt is only encountered within the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20-%20Obelisk%20%28AR3010%29\"&gt;Watcher's Keep - Obelisk (AR3010)&lt;/a&gt; area.\nGameplay.\nThe demon (and its blue colored &lt;a href=\"Glabrezu%20%28TELTAN2%29\"&gt;cohort&lt;/a&gt;) are hostile and will begin their actions when a party member is detected. It can &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;, so hiding won't prevent this. \nThe demon is scripted to summon one &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Fire%20Elemental%20%28Watcher%27s%20Keep%29\"&gt;Greater Fire Elemental (Watcher's Keep)&lt;/a&gt; elemental each round, until five of these creatures have been produced. Killing the demon stops this process obviously.\nTo help facilitate this conjuration plan, the demon will attempt to move away/retreat from an enemy to continue this single-minded summoning tactic.\nOnce it has produced five of the elementals, the glabrezu is free to cast other spells in its repertoire (See the InfoBox) and can advance and attack a party member in melee combat as well.\nMost of the demon's spells are \"ForceSpell\" or \"ApplySpell\" actions and aren't interruptible by damage - the exception being the &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt;.\nNote that the demon is under a permanent normal &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Haste effect&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes revisions to the creature's spell use AI to a certain extent. This is especially evident if the \"Improved Fiends and Celestials\" component is installed.\nThe creature is now a 17 Hit dice creature (spell casts at level 17). The haste effect is removed, and a +2-movement modifier is substituted.\nIt retains the same Fire elemental summoning script actions, but its other spells are reworked to provide a different selection, including:&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"True%20Seeing\"&gt;True Seeing&lt;/a&gt; innate, 1x/day&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Confusion\"&gt;Confusion&lt;/a&gt; innate, at will&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Power%20Word%2C%20Stun\"&gt;Power Word, Stun&lt;/a&gt;, at will&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt; innate, at will&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt; innate, at will&lt;br&gt;\n\"Teleport without error\", at will&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Unholy%20Blight\"&gt;Unholy Blight&lt;/a&gt; innate, at will&lt;br&gt;\nInstant prep with &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Fireshield%20%28Red%29\"&gt;Fireshield (Red)&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "55963", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55963", "title": "Glabrezu (TELTAN2)", "text": " \nThis Glabrezu demon is unique in the game and has a deep aquamarine blue tint/hue. \nIt is only encountered within the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20-%20Obelisk%20%28AR3010%29\"&gt;Watcher's Keep - Obelisk (AR3010)&lt;/a&gt; area.\nGameplay.\nThe demon (and its red colored &lt;a href=\"Glabrezu%20%28TELTAN1%29\"&gt;cohort&lt;/a&gt;) are hostile and will begin their actions when a party member is detected. It can &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;, so hiding won't prevent this. \nThe demon is scripted to summon one &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Salamander\"&gt;Ice Salamander&lt;/a&gt; elemental each round, until five of these creatures have been produced. Killing the demon stops this process obviously.\nTo help facilitate this conjuration plan, the demon will attempt to move away/retreat from an enemy to continue this single-minded summoning tactic.\nOnce it has produced five of the elementals, the glabrezu is free to cast other spells in its repertoire (See the InfoBox) and can advance and attack a party member in melee combat as well.\nMost of the demon's spells are \"ForceSpell\" or \"ApplySpell\" actions and aren't interruptible by damage - the exception being the &lt;a href=\"Cone%20of%20Cold\"&gt;Cone of Cold&lt;/a&gt;.\nNote that the demon is under a permanent normal &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Haste effect&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes revisions to the creature's spell use AI to a certain extent. This is especially evident if the \"Improved Fiends and Celestials\" component is installed.\nThe creature is now a 17 Hit dice creature (spell casts at level 17). The haste effect is removed, and a +2-movement modifier is substituted.\nIt retains the same Ice Salamander summoning script actions, but its other spells are reworked to provide a different selection, including:&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"True%20Seeing\"&gt;True Seeing&lt;/a&gt; innate, 1x/day&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Confusion\"&gt;Confusion&lt;/a&gt; innate, at will&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Power%20Word%2C%20Stun\"&gt;Power Word, Stun&lt;/a&gt; at will&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt; innate, at will&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt; innate, at will&lt;br&gt;\n\"Teleport without error\", at will&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Unholy%20Blight\"&gt;Unholy Blight&lt;/a&gt; innate, at will&lt;br&gt;\nInstant prep with &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Fireshield%20%28Blue%29\"&gt;Fireshield (Blue)&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "49332", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49332", "title": "Glabrezu (Watcher's Keep/ToB)", "text": "Glabrezus are &lt;a href=\"tanar%27ri\"&gt;tanar'ri&lt;/a&gt; that specialize in the temptation of mortals, although they are considered a middle-class demon of the Abyss.\nThis group of glabrezus are encountered in the following situations:\n\"DEMOSUM3.cre\"\n\"DGLAB01.cre\"\n\"GORTAN4.cre\" \n\"MELSUM01.cre\"\nGameplay.\nThey are &lt;a href=\"IMMUNE2.ITM\"&gt;immune to weapons&lt;/a&gt; of less than +2 enchantment and deal 3d4 damage with their &lt;a href=\"BL3-12M4.ITM\"&gt;pincer-like claws&lt;/a&gt; that protrude from the end of their massive main limbs. Creatures \"DEMOSUM3\", \"(GORTAN4)\" and \"(MELSUM01)\" are also &lt;a href=\"HELMNOAN.ITM\"&gt;protected from critical hits&lt;/a&gt;. These creatures are somewhat fragile with only moderate &lt;a href=\"hit%20point\"&gt;hit point&lt;/a&gt; values but do have effective &lt;a href=\"armor%20class\"&gt;armor class&lt;/a&gt; ratings. The demon is also capable of casting several different offensive spells that can wreak havoc on unprepared adventuring parties.\nThis group of glabrezus will cast the following spells in combat:\n\"DEMOSUM3, DGLAB01, GORTAN4:\"\n\"MELSUM01:\"\nGlabrezu's immunities can vary slightly from one creature type to the next, but they all possess the following &lt;a href=\"RINGDEMN.ITM\"&gt;undroppable item&lt;/a&gt; in their ring slot which provides the following protections:\nWhile all glabrezus can &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt; specialized effects applied to this group of glabrezus include &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt; and immunity to &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt;.\nWeaknesses: The following spells and abilities are effective against Glabrezus in combat."}
{"id": "29635", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29635", "title": "Glaicas", "text": ""}
{"id": "12531", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12531", "title": "Glaicus", "text": "Glaicus is Lord de'Arnise's bodyguard. He is encountered in a hidden and locked away room on the second floor of the &lt;a href=\"De%27Arnise%20Keep\"&gt;de'Arnise Keep&lt;/a&gt; and is under some sort of enchantment forcing his servitude to the &lt;a href=\"Trolls\"&gt;invaders&lt;/a&gt; of the keep.\nOnce discovered, he will proclaim his loyalty to his &lt;a href=\"TorGal\"&gt;new master&lt;/a&gt; and attack the party. His enchantment can be &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;dispelled&lt;/a&gt; or he can be &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Creature\"&gt;charmed&lt;/a&gt; and then talked to for extra quest experience. Note that he is entitled to &lt;a href=\"saving%20throw\"&gt;saving throw&lt;/a&gt;s and may resist being charmed.\nIf you kill Glaicus, he will drop the &lt;a href=\"Flail%20Head%20%28Acid%29\"&gt;acid flail head&lt;/a&gt;, which is one of the heads required to create the &lt;a href=\"Flail%20of%20Ages\"&gt;Flail of Ages&lt;/a&gt;. If you charm him, he will give you the item unless &lt;a href=\"TorGal\"&gt;TorGal&lt;/a&gt; is dead; if the party has already killed the trolls, he must be killed for the item. (In the he will give you the head when charmed.)\nNote.\nIn , he bears the Glaicas tooltip name, but is still called Glaicus during dialogue with other NPCs.\nBugs.\nEnhanced Edition.\nIn the Enhanced Edition, Glaicus' behavior is handled by the area script and a special status effect that forces allegiance to \"Enemy\". It lasts for 50 game days, but as a caster level 1 effect has a 99% chance to be dispelled successfully by a level 11+ spellcaster.\nUnfortunately that special status effect is bugged and unreliable, and it is possible that a successful dispel will fail to return Glaicus' allegiance to \"Neutral\". This should be fixable with the following command. Do make sure to dispel him first, then execute the command to turn him \"Neutral\":\n C:Eval('ActionOverride(\"kpglai01\",ChangeEnemyAlly(Myself,NEUTRAL))')\nAnother approach is to successfully dispel Glaicus, and \"then only\" &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Creature\"&gt;\"gentle\" charm&lt;/a&gt; him using the &lt;a href=\"Nymph%20Cloak\"&gt;Nymph Cloak&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Human%20Influence\"&gt;Ring of Human Influence&lt;/a&gt;. Avoid other charms because they turn the victim hostile when they wear off.\nEither way, once Glaicus has been dispelled and been made either \"Neutral\" or \"Ally\", the area script should kick in and finish the job: Glaicus should initiate dialogue on his own. If that fails, the party may force the dialogue themselves. If that \"still\" doesn't work, execute the following console command and then speak to him again:\n C:SetGlobal(\"KPGlai01Talked\",\"AR1303\",1)\nOriginal Edition.\nIn the Original Edition, the bugged status effect is not involved and Glaicus is simply turned hostile \"the normal way\" after his initial dialogue. The area script will then only turn him back if he gets charmed, but it may fail to ready him up completely. In that case, make sure he was charmed with the Nymph Cloak or Ring of Human Influence, and just wait for it to end or dispel it. He should become \"Neutral\", at which point he can be talked to. If talking to neutral Glaicus still fails, execute the following console command and talk to him again:\n CLUAConsole:SetGlobal(\"KPGlai01Talked\",\"AR1303\",1)\nIt's possible Glaicus won't become neutral even if you follow these instructions. It is unfortunately not possible to talk to charmed creatures in the original BG2, so a Neutral allegiance is necessary. Reload and make sure you never do anything to him besides casting \"gentle\" charms. Avoid crowd controls, just run around. Once charmed, wait until it wears off. If by then he doesn't turn blue but red, you're certain that the area script failed to change his allegiance back to Neutral.\nThere is little to do beyond reloading a few times hoping for the area script to stop failing. Use of &lt;a href=\"Near%20Infinity\"&gt;Near Infinity&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Save%20Editors\"&gt;Shadow Keeper&lt;/a&gt; seems to be the only solution, but first a saved game is needed, so follow the above instructions until the end and then instead of reloading, flee so that you can save the game in a separate slot. You'll need to use one of the tools mentioned above to locate the creature file \"of the right saved game\". In that save, this creature file has its allegiance set to , whereas outside that save, it is . So find the right file, set its allegiance back to , save that tweak and reload the saved game. Should work now. If blue Glaicus doesn't want to talk, execute the console command as explained earlier and talk to him again.\nMod content.\nMods:.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes a few revisions to Glaicus. A default SCS AI fighter script is assigned for smarter tactical behavior and targeting. He also has Grandmastery with his sword and 2 pips in two handed weapon fighting style, which improves damage, speed factor and critical hit percentage with the great sword. Glaicus will quaff an &lt;a href=\"Oil%20of%20Speed\"&gt;Oil of Speed&lt;/a&gt; and also a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Fire%20Giant%20Strength\"&gt;Potion of Fire Giant Strength&lt;/a&gt; once an opponent is observed, unless prevented in some manner. Once the Oil of speed is applied, then the warrior will be dishing out rapid blows to any in melee range, so be aware of that - it could be unexpected for an early SoA party with limited experience. Up to 5 attacks per round can be expected, dealing heavy slashing damage. If wounded, the warrior will also utilize his Potions of Extra Healing."}
