{"id": "51276", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51276", "title": "Glass Dust", "text": "Glass Dust is an innate ability effect available to most &lt;a href=\"Dust%20Mephit\"&gt;Dust Mephit&lt;/a&gt; creatures in the game saga. \nEffects.\nThe spell effect is uninterruptable and takes almost no time to deploy. A projectile is launched at a single target in range, but it has an area of effect that can also apply the detrimental glass dust to any enemy in that radius (allies are not affected). A &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Breath will negate.\nIf the target fails the saving throw the affected creature will have a \"Glass Dust\" icon displayed on the portrait, and suffer the penalties stated above for a duration of 5 rounds. The effects can be removed with a &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt;. As the glass dust has the equivalent of 1 spell power, several low-level spell protections such as &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or similar will stop it, as well as &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;."}
