{"id": "24409", "revid": "261241", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24409", "title": "Glint Gardnersonson (quest)", "text": "Glint Gardnersonson is a in \"\".\nAcquisition.\nThis eponymous quest is gained upon first recruiting &lt;a href=\"Glint%20Gardnersonson\"&gt;Glint&lt;/a&gt; into the party.\nWalkthrough.\nLike most &lt;a href=\"gnome\"&gt;gnome&lt;/a&gt;s, Glint has a very large family. His personal quest in is to track down a handful of his kinsmen and -women who live in the area, to make sure they are okay. Each stage requires having Glint in party when talking to any of his family:\nThere is no end reward for meeting all the relatives with Glint in the party, and, in fact, one reward may be missed instead. Rhonda gives out her &lt;a href=\"Nimblefinger%20Gloves\"&gt;Nimblefinger Gloves&lt;/a&gt; to any party without Glint. If Glint is in the party, the party needs to have already progressed past the two ogres for her to offer them."}
{"id": "5872", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5872", "title": "Glitterdust", "text": "The Glitterdust spell creates a cloud of glittering golden particles within the area of effect. Should they fail a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;save&lt;/a&gt; vs Spell, this will remove the effect of creatures on impact, as well as &lt;a href=\"Blinded\"&gt;blind&lt;/a&gt; them for 4 &lt;a href=\"Time%20System\"&gt;rounds&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe caster fires a projectile (170 Sparkle Area Gold Not Party (SPARGONP) at the desired target point in range. \nWhen the rapidly moving projectile reaches the point designated by the caster (up to a 20' distance) the sparkling area of effect manifests in a 15-foot radius from the target spot.\nAll enemy creatures in the area of effect are exposed to the sparking particles unless a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spell is made. If the save is made the conjuration has no effect on that particular creature.\nIf the saving throw check is failed, then the creature:\n- Suffers a &lt;a href=\"Blindness\"&gt;Blindness&lt;/a&gt; effect lasting 4 rounds. A text string will display \"Blinded\".\n- If hidden, the creature is revealed (including normal and improved invisibility, &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Stealth\"&gt;Stealth&lt;/a&gt;). \n- The creature is also unable to attain being hidden for 4 rounds (when the glittering particles wear off). \nThis spell's effects are classified as a \"Conjuration\" spell school, and a \"Battleground\" secondary type. The individual effects of glittering dust are considered magical and therefore are affected by &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects and &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;. Additionally, the effects are assigned a 2 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; and thus can be blocked by a &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;.\nSee also.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Glitterdust\"&gt;Wand of Glitterdust&lt;/a&gt; fires a slightly different version of this spell. It has a greater range, bypasses Magic Resistance, can't be dispelled, but isn't party friendly.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons Wizard \"Glitterdust\" spell allows the effect to last longer as the caster gains experience levels. See the External links for further reading.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its effects, and saving throw. See below for description:\nGlitterdust\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Conjuration\nRange: Medium\nDuration: 4 rounds\nCasting Time: 2\nArea of Effect: 10\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: Special\nThis spell creates a cloud of glittering golden particles within the area of effect. The sparkling dust dazzles all opponents in the area (-2 penalty to attack rolls) for 4 rounds and reveals any opponents who are invisible. Those affected must also save vs. breath to avoid becoming completely covered by the dust, which cannot be removed and continues to sparkle for 4 rounds. Those failing the save remain unable to successfully hide themselves until the dust fades."}
{"id": "4054", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4054", "title": "Glittering Beljuril Gemstone", "text": "The Glittering Beljuril Gemstone is the item described by &lt;a href=\"Avarice\"&gt;Avarice&lt;/a&gt;, one of the four dwarven wards guarding the stairs to &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28Labyrinth%20Level%20Two%29\"&gt;Labyrinth Level 2&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt;. You must give it to him as part of the process to advance to the next lower level."}
