{"id": "11038", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11038", "title": "Goblin (Baldur's Gate EE)", "text": "Goblins are a small, cunning race of goblinoids that are a plague across all of &lt;a href=\"Faer%C3%BBn\"&gt;Faer\u00fbn&lt;/a&gt;, though they are generally not dangerous unless encountered in very large numbers, or if they have had time to prepare an ambush. These particular goblins are encountered in the of Baldur's Gate.\nBugs.\nIn the original goblins are classified by race as either &lt;a href=\"hobgoblin\"&gt;hobgoblin&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"kobold\"&gt;kobold&lt;/a&gt; and classified by class as either hobgoblin or &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt;. This is not fixed in the Enhanced Edition of either game. However, it is fixed in the where goblins are now properly classified as race: Goblin and class: Fighter.\nFor the sake of proper classification within this wiki and to follow the correct D&amp;D classification, goblins are classified using the Siege of Dragonspear classifications. Fighter is chosen over &lt;a href=\"rogue\"&gt;rogue&lt;/a&gt; (even thought \"thief\" is a class given to several goblin creatures) because thieves are unable to weld composite longbows, bastard swords or axes and due to the nature of their disposition when encountered in the games. "}
{"id": "54991", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54991", "title": "Goblin (Baldur's Gate II)", "text": "Goblins are a small, cunning race of goblinoids that are a plague across all of &lt;a href=\"Faer%C3%BBn\"&gt;Faer\u00fbn&lt;/a&gt;, though they are generally not dangerous unless encountered in very large numbers, or if they have had time to prepare an ambush. These particular goblins are encountered in and the .\nBugs.\nIn the original Shadows of Amn goblins are classified by race as either &lt;a href=\"hobgoblin\"&gt;hobgoblin&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"kobold\"&gt;kobold&lt;/a&gt; and classified by class as either hobgoblin or &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt;. This is not fixed in the Enhanced Edition of either game. However, it is fixed in the where goblins are now properly classified as race: Goblin and class: Fighter.\nFor the sake of proper classification within this wiki and to follow the correct D&amp;D classification, goblins are classified using the Siege of Dragonspear classifications. Fighter is chosen over &lt;a href=\"rogue\"&gt;rogue&lt;/a&gt; (even thought \"thief\" is a class given to several goblin creatures) because thieves are unable to weld composite longbows, bastard swords or axes and due to the nature of their disposition when encountered in the games. "}
{"id": "55035", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55035", "title": "Goblin (Siege of Dragonspear)", "text": "Goblins are a small, cunning race of goblinoids that are a plague across all of &lt;a href=\"Faer%C3%BBn\"&gt;Faer\u00fbn&lt;/a&gt;, though they are generally not dangerous unless encountered in very large numbers, or if they have had time to prepare an ambush.\nThese two particular goblins are encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River%20Entrance\"&gt;Underground River Entrance&lt;/a&gt; during the events pf the . They are members of a group of &lt;a href=\"goblinoid\"&gt;goblinoid&lt;/a&gt; \"bandits\" that are lead by a hobgoblin named &lt;a href=\"Battuks%20Softbelcher\"&gt;Battuks Softbelcher&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "52338", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52338", "title": "Goblin Cave", "text": "The Goblin Cave is an in \"\".\nAccess.\nThis small cave is reachable through a difficult to notice entrance at the northeast end of &lt;a href=\"Boareskyr%20Bridge\"&gt;Boareskyr Bridge&lt;/a&gt;.\nLayout.\nThis cave is positively swarming with goblins, housing 9 &lt;a href=\"Goblin%20Archer\"&gt;Goblin Archer&lt;/a&gt;s, 8 &lt;a href=\"Goblin%20Warrior\"&gt;Goblin Warrior&lt;/a&gt;s, a &lt;a href=\"Goblin%20Witch%20Doctor\"&gt;Goblin Witch Doctor&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Goblin%20Chieftain\"&gt;Goblin Chieftain&lt;/a&gt;. Core difficulty will add 4 &lt;a href=\"Goblin%20Sharpshooter\"&gt;Goblin Sharpshooter&lt;/a&gt;s and 1 &lt;a href=\"Goblin%20Veteran\"&gt;Goblin Veteran&lt;/a&gt;, Hard 7 and 2, and Insanity 12 and 3, respectively.\nIn the back of the cave is a rock hiding a random gem or jewelry item, some gold, and the &lt;a href=\"Circlet%20of%20Lost%20Souls\"&gt;Circlet of Lost Souls&lt;/a&gt;, possibly taken from the nearby shaman's body that once carried a &lt;a href=\"Club\"&gt;Club&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Buckler\"&gt;Buckler&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Clarity\"&gt;Potion of Clarity&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "55003", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55003", "title": "Goblin Commando", "text": "Goblins are a small, cunning race of goblinoids that are a plague across all of &lt;a href=\"Faer%C3%BBn\"&gt;Faer\u00fbn&lt;/a&gt;, though they are generally not dangerous unless encountered in very large numbers, or if they have had time to prepare an ambush. This particular Goblin Commando is only encountered within the &lt;a href=\"Kobold%20Room%20%28Spellhold%20Test%29\"&gt;Kobold Room&lt;/a&gt;, which is located somewhere within &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;, during the events of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%204\"&gt;chapter 4&lt;/a&gt; in .\nUnlike most other goblins, Goblin Commando's are equipped with &lt;a href=\"Leather%20Armor\"&gt;Leather Armor&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Basic%20Helmets%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29%23Helmet\"&gt;Helmet&lt;/a&gt; and swing a &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword\"&gt;Bastard Sword&lt;/a&gt; in melee combat.\nBugs.\nIn the original Shadows of Amn goblins are classified by race as either &lt;a href=\"hobgoblin\"&gt;hobgoblin&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"kobold\"&gt;kobold&lt;/a&gt; and classified by class as either hobgoblin or &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt;. This is not fixed in the Enhanced Edition of either game. However, it is fixed in the where goblins are now properly classified as race: Goblin and class: Fighter.\nFor the sake of proper classification within this wiki and to follow the correct D&amp;D classification, goblins are classified using the Siege of Dragonspear classifications. Fighter is chosen over &lt;a href=\"rogue\"&gt;rogue&lt;/a&gt; (even thought \"thief\" is a class given to several goblin creatures) because thieves are unable to weld composite longbows, bastard swords or axes and due to the nature of their disposition when encountered in the games. "}
