{"id": "54941", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54941", "title": "Gofus", "text": "Gofus is an NPC introduced during the \"\" saga and the enhanced edition. \nGameplay.\nGofus only appears during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; with two other Shadow Thieves, including &lt;a href=\"Arkanis%20Gath\"&gt;Arkanis Gath&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Yeanasha\"&gt;Yeanasha&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe thieves appearance only occurs if &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; asked for assistance against the vampire coven when seeing &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail%27s%20Hideout\"&gt;Aran Linvail's Hideout&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf Aran agreed, then all the thieves will appear in the central chamber (with the large table) in the &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs\"&gt;Lower Tombs&lt;/a&gt;.\nGofus is not controllable by the player, but the creature's script will follow the PC and engage in melee combat with red circled enemies when they are detected.\nThe thief's actions are centered around combat outcomes with &lt;a href=\"Tanova\"&gt;Tanova&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hareishan%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;Hareishan&lt;/a&gt; vampires while the party is present in the same area. When those two are defeated, Arkanis Gath will dismiss Gofus and Yeanasha and they'll depart the area.\nThe thief functions as dual wielding short sword melee combatants only. No backstabbing attempts or special thief skills are scripted.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some changes to Gofus. The thief is now properly configured as a level 16 &lt;a href=\"Swashbuckler\"&gt;Swashbuckler&lt;/a&gt; kit, with all the commensurate passive kit bonuses revised into his abilities. Since some SCS vampires require +3 weapons to hit them, Gofus now dual wields &lt;a href=\"Long%20Sword%20%2B3\"&gt;Long Sword +3&lt;/a&gt;. The enchanted leather armor is removed and replaced by studded leather.\nA &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20the%20Princes\"&gt;Ring of the Princes&lt;/a&gt; is now provided.\nSeveral potions are now supplied for scripted use by the swashbuckler to boost abilities at the start of combat and heal itself when damage is accrued to a set value. A scroll is also available to use in the quick slot.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Rebalancing\"&gt;Rogue Rebalancing&lt;/a&gt; mod Gofus is furnished with an undroppable \"Hide in Shadows\" amulet to improve that skill."}
