{"id": "19609", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19609", "title": "Ogremoch", "text": "Ogremoch, a purported Prince of the Earth (see also &lt;a href=\"Sunnis\"&gt;Sunnis&lt;/a&gt; for another Prince of Earth), is a massive &lt;a href=\"Earth%20Elemental\"&gt;Earth Elemental&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Sendai%27s%20Lair%20Diaytha%20Abishai\"&gt;Sendai's Lair - Diaytha's sanctum&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nAfter &lt;a href=\"Diaytha\"&gt;Diaytha&lt;/a&gt; speaks with the party and spits out her hatred of you the Bhaalspawn, she says:\nShe then exits the map, and the party must defeat whatever lies ahead in \"Ogremoch's chamber\". \nWithin that area which is a short distance away through a doorway and corridor will be found a pair of &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Earth%20Elemental\"&gt;Greater Earth Elemental&lt;/a&gt; creatures, and they're hostile, as well as a hidden trap just behind them (careful!).\nAbout 30 feet away from the trap is Ogremoch. When within sight distance the player combat screen log will display what the Prince rumbles, saying \"Who calls Ogremoch, Prince of Earth?\", which is just a rhetorical comment, not a dialogue. The battle will now commence.\nThere is nothing particularly special about this brute, except he'll open up with a &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; defense, and it can be reapplied several times on an interval. At least +3 enchantment weapons will be required to hit it. \nThe prince will strike with bludgeoning blows, that actually do hit frequently for a significant amount of crushing damage. Note that any hit will apply a &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; 10 &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect on the target. If the elemental strikes an illusionary creature, like a &lt;a href=\"Mislead\"&gt;Mislead&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Project%20Image\"&gt;Project Image&lt;/a&gt; clone, it will be destroyed on hit. Details can be reviewed on the &lt;a href=\"ELEMIMIX.ITM\"&gt;Ogremoch's Weapon&lt;/a&gt; page.\nIf the battle continues several rounds, Ogremoch will launch his &lt;a href=\"Earthquake\"&gt;Earthquake&lt;/a&gt; spell. \nMod Content.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod installed Ogremoch has a few revisions for improving the challenge. Its hit points are raised to 480. The creature's coloring is changed to a medium purple color, and it is immune to &lt;a href=\"Web\"&gt;Web&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Entangle\"&gt;Entangle&lt;/a&gt; effects. Nothing else is really changed from the unmodified game creature, as it has the same THAC0, weapon. APR and status effect immunities as the InfoBox displays. The AI for the elemental will be smarter, with a better threat assessment and vulnerability recognition included.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod revises elementals in the game and assigns physical damage resistances to the creatures. Ogremoch will have some resistance to damage with this mod installed."}
