{"id": "11012", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11012", "title": "Ogrillon", "text": "Ogrillons are the misbegotten offspring of &lt;a href=\"ogre\"&gt;ogre&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"orc\"&gt;orc&lt;/a&gt;s. They can often be found working with ogres in many places around the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nEven at lower levels, ogrillons pose little threat unless they get within melee range. They are best dealt with using magic and ranged weapons, or by using summoned monsters or animals to distract them while warrior classes hammer them up close. &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt; is also very efficient in dispatching them.\nAs for those ogrillions that encountered in ; by this stage of the game, these creatures are unable to provide any meaningful challenge whatsoever.\nSide quests.\nOne of two ogrillons encountered along the Coast Way road in the &lt;a href=\"South%20Beregost%20Road\"&gt;South Beregost Road&lt;/a&gt; area carries the &lt;a href=\"Note%20from%20Mirianne%27s%20husband\"&gt;note&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Mirianne%27s%20Husband\"&gt;Mirianne's Husband&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "29201", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29201", "title": "Ogrillons", "text": ""}
{"id": "3487", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3487", "title": "Oil of Fiery Burning", "text": "When an Oil of Fiery Burning is directed or 'thrown' at a point on the map, it causes a fiery explosion.\nGameplay.\nThis potion is placed in one of the character's \"Quick Items\" slots, and selected, then designate a point on the area map where the potion will be \"thrown\" or directed to.\nOnce the targeting cursor is \"clicked' a fireball projectile flies from the user to the designated point, and a fireball blast animation explodes in a 15-feet radius circle - despite the item's description, using the potion has no associated throwing motion animation by the user, nor is there a bottle tumbling through the air in flight.\nThere is an associated sound effect that audibles for the explosion.\nAll creatures in the blast radius are exposed to 5d6 &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nA &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Breath Weapon is allowed to reduce the damage.\nThis potion's effect is subject to &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nHowever, the potion explosion has a 0 spell &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; and thus can't be stopped with a spell protection such as &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; and is unaffected by a creature's innate immunity to spell levels, such as a &lt;a href=\"Lich\"&gt;Lich&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Rakshasa\"&gt;Rakshasa&lt;/a&gt; have.\nAs the potion has no assigned Spell School or Secondary type, a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt; is useless, as is the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Mirroring\"&gt;Cloak of Mirroring&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4209", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4209", "title": "Oil of Speed", "text": "Oil of Speed grants the &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Normal Haste effect&lt;/a&gt; for 1 hour or until dispelled. This potion lasts considerably longer than its spell &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;counterpart&lt;/a&gt; and doesn't cause &lt;a href=\"Fatigue\"&gt;Fatigue&lt;/a&gt;. Repeated uses don't stack.\nGameplay.\nOne of the most useful potions in the game.\nAfter quaffing this, the user gets what's stated in the description. A boost to movement rate and an extra attack per round, per the normal &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Haste effect&lt;/a&gt;. \nDrinking this potion will neuter a &lt;a href=\"Slow\"&gt;Slow&lt;/a&gt; effect. A &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28status%20effect%29\"&gt;Free Action (status effect)&lt;/a&gt; will undo the potion's effects.\nConversely, a &lt;a href=\"Slow%20effect\"&gt;Slow effect&lt;/a&gt; will neuter the haste effect afforded by the potion. They basically cancel each other.\nWhen the potion is consumed a \"gulp\" text display is shown, a lighting effect and color fade is played over the user's sprite, and a sound effect is audible. When the potion expirers another sound effect is played. The party member's portrait will also have a \"Haste\" icon (No. 38) displayed while its active. This potion is subject to &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects."}
{"id": "13560", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13560", "title": "Olaf Rassmusen", "text": "Olaf Rassmusen is an orog-looking orc &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt; who is found on the second floor of the &lt;a href=\"Guarded%20Compound\"&gt;Guarded Compound&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party intrude and decide to explore the second floor, Olaf will attack along with the rest of his group, including &lt;a href=\"Sion\"&gt;Sion&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ketta\"&gt;Ketta&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Maferan\"&gt;Maferan&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stalman\"&gt;Stalman&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Koshi\"&gt;Koshi&lt;/a&gt;, providing the party with quite a tough battle.\nGameplay.\nIn battle, Olaf is protected by &lt;a href=\"Full%20Plate%20Mail%20%2B1\"&gt;+1 Full Plate&lt;/a&gt;, wields a &lt;a href=\"Two-handed%20Sword%20%2B2\"&gt;+2 Two-Handed Sword&lt;/a&gt;, and is resistant to &lt;a href=\"Charmed\"&gt;Charm&lt;/a&gt; by his &lt;a href=\"Helm%20of%20Charm%20Protection\"&gt;Helmet&lt;/a&gt;.\nOlaf will quaff his &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Regeneration\"&gt;Potion of Regeneration&lt;/a&gt; when his &lt;a href=\"hit%20point\"&gt;hit point&lt;/a&gt; total reaches 20% of maximum, so it might not be found in the loot after the battle. As a high-level fighter with &lt;a href=\"Strength%23Exceptional%20strength\"&gt;exceptional strength&lt;/a&gt; and +4 additional hit points per level from his high &lt;a href=\"constitution\"&gt;constitution&lt;/a&gt;, he can be a tough opponent.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; revises Olaf. A Berserker kit is assigned with one use of the &lt;a href=\"Enrage\"&gt;Enrage&lt;/a&gt; ability. The Two-handed sword proficiency is raised to 5 pips, and 2 pips in two-handed weapon fighting style is awarded. As a result, Olaf's THACO, weapon damage, attacks per round, weapon speed factor, and critical hit chances will be slightly better. Additionally, all saving throws are improved by 1 point."}
