{"id": "24185", "revid": "3539497", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24185", "title": "Ooze", "text": ""}
{"id": "49502", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49502", "title": "Ooze's Lounge", "text": "Ooze's Lounge is a mod for &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Shadows of Amn&lt;/a&gt; that adds a new underground venue to &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is part of Lava Del'Vortel's \"Athkatlan Grounds\" mod series.\nOverview.\nThe Ooze's Lounge contains a child innkeeper, &lt;a href=\"Beholder\"&gt;Beholder&lt;/a&gt; merchant, and other curiosities.\nThe few side-quests you get here lead you both to existing areas, and to the caverns beneath the lounge.\nHow to get there.\nEnter the sewers via the grate in the outdoors map of the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;Slums district&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;\n\"(Requires the \"Slime-covered Key\", which you can loot from the &lt;a href=\"Tanner%20Shop\"&gt;Tanner's house&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Solve%20the%20%22skinner%22%20murders%20in%20the%20Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District Murders&lt;/a&gt; quest.)\"\nSimilar mods.\nThis mod is part of Lava Del'Vortel's \"Athkatlan Grounds\" series, which also includes these mods:\nExternal links.\n\"(For the mod's main website/forum/download page, see the infobox above.)\""}
{"id": "48970", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48970", "title": "Ooze Mephit", "text": "An Ooze Mephit is an extra-planar \"outsider\" (i.e., linked to various Elemental, Quasi-Elemental and Outer planes of existence). These creatures are similar to &lt;a href=\"Imp\"&gt;Imps&lt;/a&gt;, and can be found during the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;\"Baldur's Gate II\"&lt;/a&gt; game.\nGameplay.\nAn Ooze Mephit can attack twice per round in melee for 1d3 damage. It also has the &lt;a href=\"Stinking%20Cloud%20%28Innate%29\"&gt;Stinking Cloud (Innate)&lt;/a&gt; ability. \nThe mephit will initiate the \"Stinking Cloud\" attack, which launches a cloud projectile at an area in which an observed target is detected. The Ooze Mephit can only attempt this innate ability attack every 5 rounds after the initial launch, meaning that it will likely be dead well before its second attempt. \nThe cloud can cause a nausea effect, which is implemented as making the party member &lt;a href=\"Unconscious\"&gt;Unconscious&lt;/a&gt; unless a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Death (with a +2 bonus) is made. The effect can last for 9 seconds - during which time the character will be in the &lt;a href=\"Helpless\"&gt;Helpless&lt;/a&gt; state, and if damaged it will Not \"wake up\" the affected creature. Any party member in the cloud must make a saving throw each round it is exposed to the cloud.\nThe ooze Mephit has no magic resistance, however it does retain fire and physical damage resistances. The InfoBox summarizes their special abilities and immunities to certain status effects. The game has the creature with a memorized &lt;a href=\"Blur\"&gt;Blur&lt;/a&gt; spell but it isn't scripted to use it, so it is probably just a developer creature file copy-paste remnant."}
{"id": "55736", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55736", "title": "Ooze Puddle", "text": "The Ooze Puddle creature seems to have been removed or not used in the Enhanced Edition game. It may have been planned for use in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt;, most likely in the Slime laboratory.\nThe creature would split into two, and so on and so forth, if any of the puddles were reduced to 0 HP by damage. The exception would be from &lt;a href=\"Electricity%20damage\"&gt;Electricity damage&lt;/a&gt;, which would stop the creature from splitting into two creatures. \nGameplay.\nThe potentially endless splitting into two creatures is a cool idea but is also a candidate for a glitchy game engine response. In the end, this creature was dropped from being in the game.\nThere are however the &lt;a href=\"Fission%20Slime\"&gt;Fission Slime&lt;/a&gt; creatures, which mechanically operate in a different way."}
{"id": "50137", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50137", "title": "Opcode", "text": "The and technically minded communities of the Baldur's Gate games often use the term opcode, followed by a number. \nThis term has \"stuck\" and is used by the Infinity Engine Structures Description Project, or &lt;a href=\"IESDP\"&gt;IESDP&lt;/a&gt;, and it also referred to as an \"\"effect\" or \"state\"\" as well, even on the IESDP Index page.\nIt can simply be thought of as an Identifier (ID), a numeric label assignment referring to a specific &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt;. For example, opcode 16 refers to the &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Haste effect&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt could be argued that this is a misuse of the notion of operation code, but it has taken root a long time ago and is now common language in the English communities."}
{"id": "27615", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27615", "title": "Open Locks", "text": ""}
{"id": "29904", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29904", "title": "Open locks", "text": ""}
{"id": "40655", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40655", "title": "Open the portal to the temple's lower levels", "text": "This is quest initiated through talking with &lt;a href=\"Archivist%20Giltham\"&gt;Archivist Giltham&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 or rather his spirit. He's very cold and not very talkative when you first meet him, but he becomes more at ease once the hearth is lit.\nThis quest guides you through the steps needed to open the portal to &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt;, awarding quest experience in various steps:\nGameplay quest walkthrough (abbreviated).\nFind the tinderbox hidden behind a statuette in the Bedchamber . It's used to light the kitchen fireplace/hearth. While you're there, get the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Slippers\"&gt;Old Slippers&lt;/a&gt; from the bookcase.\nConverse with &lt;a href=\"Archivist%20Giltham\"&gt;Archivist Giltham&lt;/a&gt; and inquire about the lower levels and the ritual (or question his sanity). He must be summoned in the Kitchen by reigniting the Fireplace using the &lt;a href=\"Tinderbox\"&gt;Tinderbox&lt;/a&gt; before any dialogue can occur.\nObtain the &lt;a href=\"Key%20%28Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level%29\"&gt;Key (Watcher's Keep Altar Level)&lt;/a&gt; to open the Crypt door to the &lt;a href=\"Priest%20%28WK%20Altar%20Level%29\"&gt;priest's&lt;/a&gt; sarcophagus. \nThere are two &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20Golem\"&gt;Guardian Golem&lt;/a&gt; creatures within the Crypt. If you don't want to fight these two defenders, ensure that the stones are possessed by the party. The golem's respective &lt;a href=\"Wardstone%20%28Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level%29\"&gt;wardstones&lt;/a&gt;: green for left (north), blue for the other. The cryptic handwritten notes refer to these.\nInteract with the sarcophagus to summon the undead lich-priest. The Golems will attack, unless the wardstones are in the party inventory.\nIf you brought the Old Slippers (have them in a party member inventory), the creature will know, and he'll ask for them. If given freely he will forgive your intrusion and award you to each member. He'll also invite inspection of the contents of his final resting place. Refuse, and the creature will become hostile.\nIf the slippers are provided each party member gains another .\nFollowing the instructions written on the &lt;a href=\"Tattered%20Parchment\"&gt;Tattered Parchment&lt;/a&gt; found throughout this keep's level. First, a party member with the Bell and Candle in their inventory must place them upon the altar (walk up close to it and transfer the items onto the altar container).\nThe altar Holy Ritual requires:\nHowever, interacting with the altar by moving any items to or from the altar at this stage of the game will activate the first defending phase of the &lt;a href=\"Statues%20%28WK%20Altar%20Level%29\"&gt;Statues&lt;/a&gt; that are located closest to the altar. This statue activation interrupts the item placement temporarily. The statues are dangerous opponents, and the party will need to take care and defend itself. They can do some real harm, especially to an under leveled party. Expect competent melee combat from the warrior statues, and buffs as well as &lt;a href=\"Insect%20Plague\"&gt;Insect Plague&lt;/a&gt; type attacks from the cleric statues.\nAfter the first wave of statues are dealt with - the party is probably suspicious of the remaining statues. What if they activate later? Now is the time to prepare and be ready for that likely event. Do whatever actions are deemed necessary to be able to deal with the remaining statues.\nWhen ready, continue placing the items on the altar. When all items are placed, the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20%28Altar%29\"&gt;Guardian (Altar)&lt;/a&gt; engages in dialogue and begins the Holy Ritual.\nAs prompted by the Altar Guardian, select the correct ritualist steps as described in the tattered parchments and the verse read from the Priest's sarcophagus. \nIf the player selects an incorrect response - the Guardian will boom out a response \"THE RITUAL HAS BEEN DEFILED!\". \nThis results in 50 &lt;a href=\"Magical%20damage\"&gt;Magical damage&lt;/a&gt; to the offender, and all the objects on the altar are removed and placed back in the PC's inventory. The player will now have to try again.\nThe section below is a \"Spoiler\". Click on the \"Reveal\" button if you want to be provided the answers to the altar ritual. Don't do it if you want to figure this out on your own, like a first-time player was meant to.\nThe correct order of action during the ritual is:\nNote that the statues will animate in two phases as part of the Holy Ritual, and they'll be hostile and attack the party as the altar ritual is being performed. \nThis is unavoidable and seems to be part of the defense of the Portal to the lower reaches. These opponents are the strongest opposition faced on this dungeon level.\nWhen the first group of statue defenders is finished, return to the Altar and ensure all the items are on the Altar, placing the missing ones as required. \nOnce that has occurred, and the correct dialogue selections are made to perform the ritual in the right sequence, the player gets a Journal update and quest experience is awarded for performing this action.\nThe player must now face the second statue group, who have begun to activate after the ritual was finished properly. \nAfter defeating all the statues, the portal can be accessed and used to travel to the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt;, the player's next dungeon goal. \nJournal Entries.\nUpon talking to Archivist Giltham about the lower levels:\nUpon insulting the man or asking about the ritual:\nUpon inspecting the sarcophagus after talking to the &lt;a href=\"Priest%20%28WK%20Altar%20Level%29\"&gt;Priest (WK Altar Level)&lt;/a&gt;:\nUpon completion:"}
