{"id": "5832", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5832", "title": "Oracle", "text": "The Oracle spell will dispel all Illusion spells of 5th level and lower that affect the caster's enemies.\nGameplay.\nThe caster initiates the spell and when finished it is cast upon self only.\nOnce cast, the spell radiates a projectile that has a large area of effect, about a 120' radius.\nEnemy non-party creatures within the area of effect are the only ones are the spell will affect.\nCreatures under the protections of certain spell or effects with Illusionist spell school or secondary type Illusionary protection classifications are targeted by this spell.\nThe spell instantly removes or cures all of the spells in the description as well as creatures under the Hide in Shadow ability or a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Invisibility\"&gt;Potion of Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;.\nAdditionally, although not mentioned in the description, the spell cause creatures that are illusionary, such as a &lt;a href=\"Mislead\"&gt;Mislead&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Project%20Image\"&gt;Project Image&lt;/a&gt; clones to destroy themselves instantly, even if they were created by spells above the 5th level.\nAfter the spell has processed the instant spell removal effects, creatures in the area may reapply or recast illusionary spells as normal, such as quaffing another potion, or casting an invisibility spell.\nOne of the few illusion spells not removed by Oracle is &lt;a href=\"Mass%20Invisibility\"&gt;Mass Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset has no Wizard spell titled \"Oracle\". This spell is an invention of the BG video game developers.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its effects, and Area of Effect. See below for description:\nOracle\nLevel: 5\nSchool: Divination\nRange: Personal\nDuration: Instant\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: 30\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen this spell is cast, an area roughly 30 feet in radius around the caster will be affected. All hostile illusion/phantasm spells in this area will be dispelled. This spell only affects one\u2019s enemies.\nThe spells that are affected by this are: Reflected Image, Invisibility, Blur, Mirror Image, Ghost Armor, Invisibility Sphere, Improved Invisibility, Shadow Door, Pixie Dust, Mislead, Project Image, and Mass Invisibility."}
{"id": "11345", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11345", "title": "Orc", "text": "This is the most common Orc encountered throughout the campaign. A few are found as static creatures while a good majority will appear as random spawns which are always in groups of six; three orcs and three &lt;a href=\"Orc%20Archer\"&gt;Orc Archers&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis orc creature wears &lt;a href=\"Leather%20Armor\"&gt;Leather Armor&lt;/a&gt; and swings a &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword\"&gt;Bastard Sword&lt;/a&gt; (even though the in-game animation shows it equipped with a &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Axe\"&gt;Battle Axe&lt;/a&gt;.) It also drops one item of &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure%23Well-off%20treasure\"&gt;well-off random treasure&lt;/a&gt;. "}
