{"id": "46859", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46859", "title": "Orc Archer", "text": "This is the most common Orc Archer encountered throughout the campaign. A few are found as static creatures while a good majority will appear as random spawns which are always in groups of six; three &lt;a href=\"Orc\"&gt;Orc&lt;/a&gt;s and three orc archers.\nThis orc creature wears &lt;a href=\"Leather%20Armor\"&gt;Leather Armor&lt;/a&gt; and utilizes a &lt;a href=\"Longbow\"&gt;Longbow&lt;/a&gt; to fire &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20%2B1\"&gt;+1 Arrows&lt;/a&gt; at its target. They carry no melee weapon, so engaging them in hand to hand combat is probably a good idea for low level parties. They also drop one item of &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure%23Well-off%20treasure\"&gt;well-off random treasure&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "49148", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49148", "title": "Orc Archer (Black Pits II)", "text": "This Orc Archer is encountered in the . Three are encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Battleground%20Graveyard\"&gt;Battleground Graveyard&lt;/a&gt; and in the &lt;a href=\"Staging%20Area%20%28Gladiators%20of%20Thay%29\"&gt;Staging Area&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "56390", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56390", "title": "Orc Archer (Challenge room)", "text": "Three of these Orc Archers are initially encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20%E2%80%93%20Challenge%20Room%20%28Orcs%29\"&gt;Watcher's Keep \u2013 Challenge Room (Orcs)&lt;/a&gt; on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Final%20Seal\"&gt;Final Seal&lt;/a&gt; level of &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nThe Orc archer is a missile firing opponent, armed with a &lt;a href=\"Longbow\"&gt;Longbow&lt;/a&gt;, quiver of &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20%2B1\"&gt;+1 arrows&lt;/a&gt; and wearing a helmet and &lt;a href=\"Leather%20Armor\"&gt;Leather Armor&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhenever one of these orc archers is killed, another similar creature spawns at a predetermined spawn point (nearly instantly) on the challenge room map.\nIt is possible that a total of up to nine archers can be encountered during this challenge in total.\nThe orc archer will move just enough to be in range of the nearest detected enemy and engage in missile fire combat.\nThe archer will prioritize firing at a mage class enemy over other opponents in range.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes a few revisions to these orc archers.\nA &lt;a href=\"Long%20Sword\"&gt;Long Sword&lt;/a&gt; is provided for melee combat ability, and 2 pips in weapon proficiency.\nLongbow proficiency is adjusted to 2 pips.\nA new AI script is provided for better tactical combat behavior, targeting, including melee and missile combat decision logic."}
{"id": "22956", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22956", "title": "Orc Archer (Firkraag's Maze)", "text": "Eight of these Orc Archer's are waiting to ambush the party as soon as they enter &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Maze\"&gt;Firkraag's Maze&lt;/a&gt;. There are four of them on either side of the room and they are shooting through tiny arrow slits that are located on the walls.\nThese orc archers are unique in that they are the only ones that are equipped with &lt;a href=\"Plate%20Mail\"&gt;Plate Mail&lt;/a&gt; and will swing a &lt;a href=\"Morning%20Star\"&gt;Morning Star&lt;/a&gt; when engaged in melee combat. They will use their twenty normal &lt;a href=\"Arrow\"&gt;Arrow&lt;/a&gt;s first before switching to their ten &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20of%20Fire\"&gt;Arrows of Fire&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "49146", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49146", "title": "Orc Archer (Saradush)", "text": "A total of six of these Orc Archers are found in the &lt;a href=\"Sewers%20beneath%20Saradush\"&gt;sewers&lt;/a&gt; located below the city of &lt;a href=\"Saradush\"&gt;Saradush&lt;/a&gt;.\nOne each of the creatures (SEWARC01.cre) and (SEWARC02.cre) are found in the circular, central nexus area along with an &lt;a href=\"Elite%20Orog\"&gt;Elite Orog&lt;/a&gt; and two &lt;a href=\"Duergar%20Sapper\"&gt;Duergar Sapper&lt;/a&gt;s. Four of the (SEWYAG02.cre) creatures are found scattered along the northern and western tunnels of the sewer.\nAll three have the same stats except for differences in &lt;a href=\"hit%20point\"&gt;hit point&lt;/a&gt;s, dexterity, and AI scripts. These orc archers are one of the few creatures with the &lt;a href=\"Archer%23Called%20Shot\"&gt;Called Shot&lt;/a&gt; and the default script \"CARCH20B.bcs\" allows them to actually utilize this spell."}
{"id": "49125", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49125", "title": "Orc Archer (Umar Hills\u2014Ranger)", "text": "Two of these Orc Archer's are members of a group of &lt;a href=\"%23Trivia\"&gt;t&lt;/a&gt; raiders that have come down from the hills and attacked the village of &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale\"&gt;Imnesvale&lt;/a&gt; during the events of the second &lt;a href=\"Ranger-Protector%20of%20the%20Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Ranger-Protector of the Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt; stronghold quest. They are found along with some &lt;a href=\"Orog\"&gt;Orog&lt;/a&gt;s near the entrance to the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Cave\"&gt;cave&lt;/a&gt; located northwest of the village.\nTrivia.\nOgrons are not creatures found in any D&amp;D creature manual. They are creatures that were created for the BBC program \"Doctor Who\"."}
{"id": "6996", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6996", "title": "Orc Leather", "text": "Orc Leather is enchanted studded leather armor +3. It offers an armor class of 4 and the normal armor class modifiers which come with studded leather armor. This armor also provides 10% missile weapons resistance, but the looks of the armor lower the &lt;a href=\"Charisma\"&gt;Charisma&lt;/a&gt; of the wearer by 1 point. This item appears in and . This item can be found in the Cellars of the &lt;a href=\"De%27Arnise%20Keep\"&gt;De'Arnise Keep&lt;/a&gt;."}
