{"id": "56391", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56391", "title": "Orc Mage (Challenge room)", "text": "Two of these Orc Mage creatures are initially found in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20%E2%80%93%20Challenge%20Room%20%28Orcs%29\"&gt;Watcher's Keep \u2013 Challenge Room (Orcs)&lt;/a&gt; on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Final%20Seal\"&gt;Final Seal&lt;/a&gt; level of &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe orc mage is a 12 HD creature with a 10th level mage spell book.\nWhenever one of these mages is killed, another similar creature spawns at a predetermined spawn point (nearly instantly) on the challenge room map.\nIt seems that a total of up to six mages can be encountered in this challenge in total.\nThe initial two orc mages will open up with a quick &lt;a href=\"True%20Seeing\"&gt;True Seeing&lt;/a&gt; spell cast which can't fail and is uninterruptible.\nSee the InfoBox for the memorized and used spells that can be attempted by each orc mage.\nThe various offensive damage dealing area of effect spells available to the mage will be used without regard to harming other orcs in the room. They will probably damage and destroy a number their brethren if able to fire off these spells. They don't care.\nThe orc mage will only use their melee weapons if out of spells.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises the orc mage - they get a randomly assigned specialty mage kit {Conjurer, Enchanter, Invoker or Necromancer).\nThe assigned kit determines the improved spell casting script and spell book contents.\nThese orcs are now proper level 12 mage spell casters with 22 different level 1-6 wizard spell choices, as well as a prepared &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;.\nExpect more advanced initial spell protections, summoned creatures to contend with, &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Thrust\"&gt;Spell Thrust&lt;/a&gt; use, banishment of party summoned creatures and more varied attack spells."}
