{"id": "25579", "revid": "52031043", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=25579", "title": "Ostentatious Boots", "text": "The Ostentatious Boots are a pair of &lt;a href=\"boots\"&gt;boots&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nLocation.\nOn the third floor of &lt;a href=\"Three%20Old%20Kegs\"&gt;Three Old Kegs&lt;/a&gt; you will meet three conspirators. Killing or blackmailing them will grant you the boots."}
{"id": "4864", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4864", "title": "Otiluke's Resilient Sphere", "text": "When a wizard casts Otiluke's Resilient Sphere, he encloses a creature in a globe of shimmering force.\nGameplay.\nThe caster directs this spell at a single creature in range, including self.\nWhen the casting is finished, the spell attempts to apply the sphere upon the creature - if the target is under the control of the party, or a party member, or cast on self, then the sphere is applied. \nIf the target is unwilling, or isn't a party member, then the creature is allowed a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spells to negate the sphere.\nThis spell is flagged as \"Hostile\" if cast on non-party targets- it will \"agro\" neutral creatures in the vicinity of the spell cast, even if the target makes their saving throw.\nUnwilling targets can block this spell with &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Alteration&lt;/a&gt;, and any spell protection with the capacity to withstand a 4 spell &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; effect, such as &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Minor Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen this sphere is applied to a creature the following will occur:\nSo, in summary the sphere will make a creature invisible, un-targetable, immobile, and unable to act in any way for the duration of the spell, and all the while the sphere prevents harm to the creature inside it.\nDespite all of this, you can still be \"hit\" by a few abilities that can have certain side-effects. For example, a dragon's &lt;a href=\"Wing%20Buffet\"&gt;Wing Buffet&lt;/a&gt; is a nonmagical effect that can still \"hit\" (for no damage) the protected character through the sphere and can even inflict its short duration nonmagical \"unconsciousness\" effect on the character. \nA few noteworthy consequences of this are the fact that such abilities that \"hit\" you through the sphere: \na) Will trigger contingencies with the condition \"hit\". \nb) Will cause a Project Image clone to disappear, if the \"hit\" character is the one who originally cast the spell. \nAs of version 2.6 of the Enhanced Editions, this spell has been changed so that there's no save against the effect when cast on an ally or yourself. This includes so-called \"GoodButRed\" (as they're referred to behind-the-scenes) creatures who are technically allied to the party, but have red circles, such as the Demons gated in by the spells &lt;a href=\"Cacofiend\"&gt;Cacofiend&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Fiend\"&gt;Summon Fiend&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Gate\"&gt;Gate&lt;/a&gt;. That means you can easily (i.e. without a save and ignoring magic resistance) stop them after they've served their purpose by casting Otiluke's Resilient Sphere on them.\nThis spell can be removed with any &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its saving throw and description. See below for description:\nOtiluke\u2019s Resilient Sphere\nLevel: 4\nSchool: Alteration\nRange: Long\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 4\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: Spell negates\nWhen this spell is cast, the result is a globe of shimmering force that encloses the subject creature if it fails to successfully save vs. breath at a -4 penalty. The resilient sphere will contain its subject for the duration of the spell. The sphere is completely immune to all damage. Actually, the only method of removing the sphere is a successful dispel magic. Hence, the creature caught inside the globe is completely safe from all attacks, but at the same time is completely unable to affect the outside world.\nThe caster has the option of using the spell to protect her allies. Resistances and saving throws are bypassed when the target is willing."}
{"id": "12196", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12196", "title": "Otyugh", "text": "Otyughs are foul, revolting creatures that feed primarily on offal and carrion. They are capable of both &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;slowing and inflicting disease&lt;/a&gt; upon their victims.\nGameplay.\nThe creature has a basic attack script and will advance and attack in melee range any enemy it can detect. Otyugh's are highly resistant to &lt;a href=\"Missile%20damage\"&gt;Missile damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe beast's flapping tentacles strike with 1d8 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt;. This attack is assigned a +3 enchantment level in terms of what it can strike. The reach of the attack is 2, and the speed factor is 1. Otyugh's &lt;a href=\"Attacks%20per%20round\"&gt;Attacks per round&lt;/a&gt; rating is 3.\nIn addition to the crushing damage, each hit inflicts a &lt;a href=\"Disease\"&gt;Disease&lt;/a&gt;, that offers no &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; nor is it blocked by magic resistance or spell protections. The effect last for 90 seconds (15 rounds).\nThe disease causes 1 damage every round (this is &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt;). It also infects the target with a &lt;a href=\"Slow%20effect\"&gt;Slow effect&lt;/a&gt;. \nMultiple strikes from an otyugh's attack will cumulatively apply the poison damage and refresh the duration of the &lt;a href=\"slow%20effect\"&gt;slow effect&lt;/a&gt;.\nRemoving the disease before it runs its course can be achieved with a &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Disease\"&gt;Cure Disease&lt;/a&gt; spell or item which applies a cure disease effect. \nLocations.\n\"Shadows of Amn\".\nThe ones in the &lt;a href=\"De%27Arnise%20Hold\"&gt;de'Arnise Hold&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Maze\"&gt;Firkraag's Maze&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt; differ slightly from this base &lt;a href=\"creature\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt;.\nBugs.\nAs of BG2EE 2.6 the &lt;a href=\"Slow%20effect\"&gt;Slow effect&lt;/a&gt; caused by an otyugh hit is implemented as a &lt;a href=\"Disease\"&gt;Disease&lt;/a&gt; effect but is not being alleviated by various disease cures. \nReference: (iotyugh.itm, ohrslng1.itm, otyugh.itm)"}
