{"id": "2655", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2655", "title": "Oublek", "text": "Oublek is the local \"vital relations link\". He pays bounties to adventurers who complete side quests for him.\nWhen you first speak to him, he assumes you are the bounty hunter &lt;a href=\"Greywolf\"&gt;Greywolf&lt;/a&gt;, come to collect your reward. How you deal with this mistake affects your future interactions with Oublek.\nIf you kill Oublek after delivering the emeralds, his inventory will correctly include the emeralds but have 300 fewer gold pieces. If you took the reward claiming to be Greywolf, he will have 200 fewer gold pieces.\nDialogue.\nOn first meeting:.\n\"No, say not another word. I would not think of making you wait but a moment for your just reward. When council told me that they procured GREYWOLF to rid the woods of bandit Tonquin, I knew we could expect swift justice. I would not have predicted success this quickly, but who else could it be striding into town looking, ah, looking as you do? Please accept this meager sum of 200 gold pieces, as well as the heartfelt thanks of all of Nashkel.\"\n1: Uhhh, YES! Yes, I would be Greywolf. That's me all right. None other than Greywolf. I'll take that reward because... of what I di! I'm Greywolf and I deserve it! Thank you. \"Excellent doing business with you, Greywolf. We shall not hesitate to call upon you if any other thieving miscreants make their presence known.\"\n2: You must have made some mistake. I am not this Greywolf. Keep your money, it's not mine to take. \"You are not Greywolf the bounty hunter? Oh, sweet Helm, I almost gave 200 gold pieces to a complete stranger?! The captain best not hear of this; he'd have my hide. Thanks be for your honesty, stranger. There are those who would not have done as such.\"\nIf claimed to be Greywolf:.\n\"Best you state your business and go!\"\n1: I've come to turn in a bounty and collect the reward that is duly mine. \"You'll have no reward here, you thievin' scoundrel! The Captain chewed my head off over you! It's only because you did us this service that I don't have you thrown in the stocks! Get out of my sight!\"\n2: What do you do here, exactly? \"I have neither time nor will to deal with you today.\"\nIf rejected the money:.\n\"Ahh, my fine and honest friend. What can I do for you today?\"\n1: What do you do here, exactly? \"Me? Why, I am what binds the guard to the public! A vital relations link, I am. Indispensable.\" "}
