{"id": "32165", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32165", "title": "Overgold Renwellyn", "text": "Overgold Renwellyn is a priest and a merchant in &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Trademeet's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Waukeen%20%28Trademeet%29\"&gt;Temple of Waukeen&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign.\nGallery.\nRenwellyn has the usual Curative services and also runs a Shop.\nTemple Services.\nRenwellyn takes donations and offer services within the Temple of Waukeen.\nBuy and Sell.\nRenwellyn runs a shop called Waukeen's Wares, from which the protagonist can purchase restorative potions and scrolls. Renwellyn also sells the Druid's Ring (aka, Ring of Animal Friendship). However, he does not buy anything from the party. He can identify items, but does not permit stealing."}
{"id": "51482", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51482", "title": "Overseer Handmaiden", "text": "Overseer Handmaiden is a &lt;a href=\"Drow\"&gt;Drow&lt;/a&gt; Priestess located atop the stairs that descend to the torture platform, where &lt;a href=\"Dola%20Fadoon\"&gt;Dola Fadoon&lt;/a&gt; the Genie is held captive. Four drow mages are being instructed and supervised by the Overseer Handmaiden to inflict pain and damage on the poor creature, in a controlled manner so as to not destroy its physical form.\nThis Overseer can be engaged in conversation by the party.\nIf she is attacked, or any of the drow mages, then this will make the entire city of Ust Natha hostile to the party, ending all quests, and preventing any other potential questlines from being sought.\nIf you have destroyed the Genie's physical form in an act of mercy, then the Hand maiden will address the party and more on this is discussed on the &lt;a href=\"The%20Trapped%20Genie\"&gt;The Trapped Genie&lt;/a&gt; encounter page.\nGameplay.\nThis Overseer can be engaged in conversation by the party.\nIf she or any of the drow mages are attacked, then this will make the entire city of Ust Natha hostile to the party, ending all associated quests, and preventing any other potential questlines from being sought.\nIf you have destroyed the Genie's physical form in an act of mercy, then the Handmaiden will angrily address the party. More on this is discussed on the &lt;a href=\"The%20Trapped%20Genie\"&gt;The Trapped Genie&lt;/a&gt; encounter\npage.\nIf later on in the future the party and the city of Ust Natha are hostile to each other, this powerful Cleric (and all other drow) will attempt to attack and fight the party if they are in detection range."}
