{"id": "55032", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55032", "title": "P1-10.ITM", "text": "P1-10.ITM is an undroppable item equipped by some great cats, such as the &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Tiger\"&gt;Wild Tiger&lt;/a&gt;, as their primary melee attack weapon.\nThe item behaves as a non-magical item in regard to what it can strike.\nThe item can inflict 1d10 &lt;a href=\"Piercing%20damage\"&gt;Piercing damage&lt;/a&gt; and can be modified by the creature's &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; attribute.\nIt has a range of 1, and a speed factor of 0. It has no other special abilities or characteristics."}
{"id": "51803", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51803", "title": "P1-2P.ITM", "text": "P1-2P.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by some in-game creatures, such as the &lt;a href=\"Diseased%20Rat\"&gt;Diseased Rat&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is considered a magical +3 enchanted item and deals 1d2 &lt;a href=\"Piercing%20damage\"&gt;Piercing damage&lt;/a&gt; (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus).\nThe attack has a range of one foot, and speed factor of 0. \nEach successful hit on a target will apply a &lt;a href=\"Disease\"&gt;Disease&lt;/a&gt; effect, with no &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; allowed.\nThe target creature will incur 1% of current hit point damage per second, for six consecutive seconds. The disease effect uses &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt; as the damage type.\nAs the disease is a non-magical source, no &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; can block it, and spell level protections aren't applicable. The disease can't be removed with &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhile diseased, the target creature will display a \"Nauseated \"portrait icon number 7, for one round.\nThe disease can be cured with a spell or item that does that. \nIt has no animation assigned. The item has no other powers or abilities."}
{"id": "51566", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51566", "title": "P2-8.ITM", "text": "P2-8.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by various biting attack creatures.\nIt is considered a non magical and unenchanted item and deals 2d4 damage (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; modifier), with a range of one foot, and speed factor of 0.\nIt has no animation assigned. The item has no other powers or abilities."}
