{"id": "53714", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53714", "title": "PLANETAR.ITM", "text": "PLANETAR.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by &lt;a href=\"Planetar\"&gt;Planetar&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Planetar\"&gt;Dark Planetar&lt;/a&gt; creatures.\nThe attack weapon applies a 2d10 +3 &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; to the target. The weapon also provides the wielder with -3 &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus. The Planetar's strength modifier will improve the to hit chance and damage of each blow.\nThe weapon strikes as a +3 enchanted item for the purposes of what it can strike, but the item is also flagged as magical.\nEach blow from this weapon has a 25% chance to:\n&lt;a href=\"Kill%20target\"&gt;Decapitate the target&lt;/a&gt; unless they save versus Death at a -2 penalty. If a target is killed by this ability, it suffers a \"chunked\" death animation, which will preclude revival of the body. Turning off the \"gore\" option can prevent this.\nDestroy the target if it is an , like a &lt;a href=\"Project%20Image\"&gt;Project Image&lt;/a&gt; clone.\nApply &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Dispel&lt;/a&gt; effects on the target. The method used to code the dispel power of this item is not set to use the caster's level (which would be 25 for a Planetar), but instead assigns the level as 0. A zero value in BG2EE equates to the default caster level of 10 (the same for scrolls cast by non-Wizard/Cleric characters). Regardless, the dispel effect will always cure &lt;a href=\"Deafness\"&gt;Deafness&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Feeblemindedness\"&gt;Feeblemindedness&lt;/a&gt; on the struck creature.\nThese effects bypass &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and spell &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; protections.\nThe weapon also implements some visual effects when it strikes a creature and the dispel effect is triggered. A 3D effect is played over the target when the dispel effect is applied, as well as a text string in the combat log reading \"Dispel Effects\", and finally a sound effect. \nIf the target misses a saving throw vs. the &lt;a href=\"Kill%20target\"&gt;Kill target&lt;/a&gt; then a Lighting graphic effect is also played on the target, and a color fade effect. \nAnd finally, this item bestows the Planetar with its always on normal &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Haste effect&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns new two-handed swords to both the &lt;a href=\"Planetar\"&gt;Planetar&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Planetar\"&gt;Dark Planetar&lt;/a&gt; creatures. They have been toned down in power and have no dispelling function."}
