{"id": "37518", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37518", "title": "Page from Sarevok's Notes", "text": "The Page from Sarevok's Notes is an information scroll from . It is concealed in a secret chamber in &lt;a href=\"Korlasz%27s%20Tomb\"&gt;Korlasz's Tomb&lt;/a&gt;, and contains memories from &lt;a href=\"Sarevok\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt; whilst he was studying the information hidden there by the Korlasz family. It serves as a clue to find the secret room in the &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;Ruined Temple of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt; near &lt;a href=\"Boareskyr%20Bridge\"&gt;Boareskyr Bridge&lt;/a&gt;, which will grant access to the &lt;a href=\"Fractal%20Blade\"&gt;Fractal Blade&lt;/a&gt;.\n\"- My research into the Lord of Murder has begun to bear its tainted fruit.The dreams come every night now,dreams of floods and eruptions,earthquakes and devastation.I descend deeper into the dreams each time,combing clues from their chaff.I'll use what they teach me to bring a living nightmare to this land. I've learned all i can in the city.While my plans for the Iron Throne gain traction,i go to visit a temple of Bhaal overtaken by the faithful of he who murdered my father-leaving the way clear for ME to take his place. There i shall find out more regarding my dark heritage and the prophecy. If i have time,i shall also look into the hidden room rumored to have been constructed by Mask.The Lord of Shadows is cunning.The marks he has left behind number 3,1 and 4.\""}
{"id": "6977", "revid": "35642161", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6977", "title": "Pai'Na", "text": "Pai'Na is a &lt;a href=\"female\"&gt;female&lt;/a&gt; half-&lt;a href=\"drow\"&gt;drow&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"hivemaster\"&gt;hivemaster&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"druid\"&gt;druid&lt;/a&gt; who resides in &lt;a href=\"Pai%27Na%27s%20Lair\"&gt;her lair&lt;/a&gt; which is located inside of the Spider's Nest, a large web-chamber in the center of the &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs\"&gt;Lower Tombs&lt;/a&gt; underneath the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Graveyard District&lt;/a&gt;. The doorway to the interior is guarded by several forms of giant including a &lt;a href=\"Wraith%20Spider\"&gt;Wraith Spider&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Phase%20Spider\"&gt;Phase Spider&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Spider\"&gt;Sword Spider&lt;/a&gt;.\nPai'Na is found near the center of her lair and is surrounded by her unseen &lt;a href=\"spider\"&gt;spider&lt;/a&gt; brood which is currently feeding on four peasant male humans named Bene, Philbert, Samar and Treddin. She reacts with immediate hostility upon sighting the party and calls forth the brood to protect their home. Each of the four peasants will die and a group of five spiders will appear next to each of the four dead bodies and move to attack the party. These twenty spiders must be killed quickly, as while frail, they pack a very potent venom in their bites.\nWhen Pai'Na is killed, she will drop a &lt;a href=\"Black%20Spider%20Figurine\"&gt;Black Spider Figurine&lt;/a&gt;, and a hidden cache in the center of the lair conceals a &lt;a href=\"Pale%20Green%20Ioun%20Stone\"&gt;Pale Green Ioun Stone&lt;/a&gt; and scrolls of &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Spawn\"&gt;Spider Spawn&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod Content.\nIf the player has \"&lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20for%20BG2\"&gt;Unfinished Business for BG2&lt;/a&gt;\" installed, however, Pai'Na is more diplomatic and can potentially give the player the quest &lt;a href=\"Pai%27Na%20and%20Spider%27s%20Bane\"&gt;Pai'Na and Spider's Bane&lt;/a&gt;. In this installation, a party that includes &lt;a href=\"Viconia%20DeVir\"&gt;Viconia&lt;/a&gt; will recognize Pai'Na as a half-, rather than a full-blooded drow. As a reward for fulfilling this quest and not being hostile to her, Pai'Na provides a unique Wand, called the &lt;a href=\"Web%20Sack\"&gt;Web Sack&lt;/a&gt;. "}
{"id": "15578", "revid": "35642161", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15578", "title": "Pai'Na's Lair", "text": "Pai'Na's Lair is a small cocoon-like structure made of spider web in the midst of the &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs\"&gt;Lower Tombs&lt;/a&gt; which are located below the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Graveyard District&lt;/a&gt; in the city of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is where the half-&lt;a href=\"drow\"&gt;drow&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"hivemaster\"&gt;hivemaster&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Pai%27Na\"&gt;Pai'Na&lt;/a&gt; breeds her arachnid companions. Four broods consisting of five &lt;a href=\"Spider\"&gt;Spider&lt;/a&gt;s each are feeding on four peasant humans - Bene, Philbert, Samar and Treddin.\nUpon entering the area Pai\u2019Na takes offence of the disturbance and attacks the party, summoning the twenty spiders to her aid. The &lt;a href=\"druid\"&gt;druid&lt;/a&gt; is the main threat in the ensuing battle, as the spiders are low level and relatively harmless, unless they successfully poison a &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;party member&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Pai%27Na%20and%20Spider%27s%20Bane\"&gt;Pai'Na and Spider's Bane&lt;/a&gt; - in the \"&lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20for%20BG2\"&gt;Unfinished Business for BG2&lt;/a&gt;\" mod is available for an add on quest. It adds captured/charmed humans to the area, including Bene, Philbert, Samar and Treddin. The mod can award the special item &lt;a href=\"Web%20Sack\"&gt;Web Sack&lt;/a&gt; - a kind of \"wand of Webs\", but more potent.\nInstallation of the \"&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt;\" mod gives new default SCS AI scripts for the various spiders and for the Hive Master. She will have an assigned \"Smarter Priest\" script for better tactical spell usage, target vulnerability assessments and will self-buff via contingency at the start of hostilities. The spiders will fire their web attacks, Phase Spiders will phase shift to attack those not immune to poison first, and Sword Spiders will engage as well. \nWith the \"&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt;\" mod, the scrolls in the niche will be a different SR variety.\nPortraits from \"&lt;a href=\"Portraits%20Portraits%20Everywhere\"&gt;Portraits Portraits Everywhere&lt;/a&gt;\":"}
{"id": "6979", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6979", "title": "Pai'Na and Spider's Bane", "text": "Pai'Na and Spider's Bane is a side quest that can be undertaken in if the player has installed the \"&lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20for%20BG2\"&gt;Unfinished Business for BG2&lt;/a&gt;\" mod. It can be started by talking to &lt;a href=\"Pai%27Na\"&gt;Pai'Na&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the player proves to not be hostile, Pai'Na explains her current problem, and the paranoia it gives her. Athkatla has recently appointed some Giant Spider-slayers in the Sewers underneath the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt;, who have been going about their job with relentless gusto. As a &lt;a href=\"Hivemaster\"&gt;Hivemaster&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt;, this incenses Pai'Na, but she cannot get close enough to stop them, as they have access to a powerful anti-spider weapon. She charges the player with retrieving it from them; whether they kill the exterminators or not is up to Gorion's Ward.\nThe exterminators that Pai'Na wants dealt with are the simple-minded Hurg and Jaeggar, who are in the central-western chamber of the Temple Sewers, Upper Level. The player may either fight them or offer to bribe them. Though the choice ranges are 50, 200 and 1000, they will turn 50 down as being too low and reject the player outright at 1000, as they don't believe anyone could possibly have that much gold. (Actually, perhaps due to a high charisma or some unknown trigger, they will accept 50 after an amusing haggle with Jaeggar). \nAs of the most recent version of the Mod, if you attack and slay these two fighters (each is only worth 165 XP), then the blade you seek will not be available/dropped. You will not be able to complete the quest. You can get the blade only by purchasing it from Hurg. \nUnfortunately, the two of them have misused &lt;a href=\"Spider%27s%20Bane\"&gt;Spider's Bane&lt;/a&gt; as a common implement, and so they have destroyed it; its only worth is to be handed over to Pai'Na, who rewards the party with 15000 EXP, the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Spider%20Figurine\"&gt;Black Spider Figurine&lt;/a&gt;, and her &lt;a href=\"Web%20Sack\"&gt;Web Sack&lt;/a&gt; wand (WAND14.itm). The party may also take Scrolls of &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Spawn\"&gt;Spider Spawn&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt; from her cache.\nWithin Pai'Na's hive are four captured or charmed human males named Bene, Philbert, Samar and Treddin. Perhaps they are envenomed by paralytic poison. These creatures have something to do with previous spider hunting activities. Additionally, there are two of each &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Spider\"&gt;Giant Spider&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Phase%20Spider\"&gt;Phase Spider&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Spider\"&gt;Sword Spider&lt;/a&gt; in the chamber should you attack her.\nTrivia.\nIn the final release of the game (unmodded), the &lt;a href=\"Contact%27s%20Note\"&gt;Contact's Note&lt;/a&gt; states that the city exterminators have been bribed to stop them from hunting spiders. This might be the reason why this quest was cut from the final game for consistency reasons.\nGallery.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod installed, both scrolls available as treasure are different and are the SR equivalent spell scrolls."}
