{"id": "5606", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5606", "title": "Paladin (Baldur's Gate)", "text": "This page about paladins is specifically made for &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. See &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; for a version for and .\nPaladins are warriors devoted to law, justice, piety and chivalry and are an example to others in society. That is reason only the lawful good &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;alignment&lt;/a&gt; is available to them. They can use all kinds of weapons and armor and have abilities to fight and protect others from evil. Only humans can become paladins and there are no multi-class combinations possible or any dual-class possibilities, as the available dual-class combinations are the same as multi-class combinations.\nSpecial abilities of the paladin.\n- &lt;a href=\"Turn%20Undead\"&gt;Turn Undead&lt;/a&gt;.\nPriests and paladins have the ability to turn undead creatures. When this mode is activated and the undead creatures are in range of the character, there is a possibility the undead will stop attacking their targets and run away from the character until the effect is worn off. At higher levels, this mode may destroy undead.\n- &lt;a href=\"Lay%20on%20Hands%20%28paladin%29\"&gt;Lay on Hands&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis is a healing spell which heals 2 hit points for each level of the paladin. A paladin of level one will heal only 2 hit points, while at level two this ability heals 4 hit points, 6 at paladin level three etc.\n- Detect evil.\nThis ability is like the spell &lt;a href=\"Detect%20Evil\"&gt;Detect Evil&lt;/a&gt;. All evil aligned creatures will glow red.\n- Protection from evil.\nThis ability is like the spell &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Evil%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Protection From Evil&lt;/a&gt;. All evil aligned creatures will receive a -2 penalty to their attack roll when targeting creatures protected by the spell, the protected creature receive +2 bonus to all saving throws from when targeted by evil creatures and also prevents creatures summoned by spells as &lt;a href=\"Cacofiend\"&gt;Cacofiend&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Fiend\"&gt;Summon Fiend&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Gate\"&gt;Gate&lt;/a&gt;.\n- Saving throws bonus.\nThey gain +2 bonus to all saving throws."}
{"id": "21280", "revid": "1966519", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21280", "title": "Paladin Stronghold Duties", "text": "Obtaining an invitation to the Order.\n&lt;a href=\"Rescue%20Garren%27s%20child%20from%20Firkraag\"&gt;Rescue Garren's child&lt;/a&gt; as intended and do not propose to obtain the &lt;a href=\"Deed%20to%20the%20Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Deed to the Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"Firkraag\"&gt;Firkraag&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0After the rescue, &lt;a href=\"Garren%20Windspear\"&gt;Garren Windspear&lt;/a&gt; will offer &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; protagonists a place in the &lt;a href=\"Most%20Noble%20Order%20of%20the%20Radiant%20Heart\"&gt;Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart&lt;/a&gt; so they can become paladins with a patron, holy warriors with a &lt;a href=\"stronghold\"&gt;stronghold&lt;/a&gt;.\nTravel back to &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;, go to the &lt;a href=\"Most%20Noble%20Order%20of%20the%20Radiant%20Heart%20building\"&gt;Radiant Heart building&lt;/a&gt; in the SE part of the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt;, and talk to &lt;a href=\"Prelate%20Wessalen\"&gt;Prelate Wessalen&lt;/a&gt; in the top side room. Agree to what he says, then walk back to the hall to meet &lt;a href=\"Sir%20William%20Reirrac\"&gt;Sir William Reirrac&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0You are now an official member of the Order and will next need to contribute through four events, detailed below.\nEvent 1:\u00a0 Rescue the Knights.\nGo to &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0within three days. In order to make it in time, you must leave Athkatla immediately when you receive the quest. When you get there, a runner will take you to the site of the battle, where three knights of the Order are battling Orcs, Ogre Mages and Ettins. Kill these enemies quickly and try to keep the other Knights alive. Once done, return to Reirrac to get your &lt;a href=\"Experience%20Tables\"&gt;XP&lt;/a&gt; reward. After you turn in the first quest, Reirrac will give you your next task.\nThe XP reward is based on whether or not Shamus, Grady, and Squire Elotte survive.\nEvent 2: Deal with Squatters.\nReirrac wants you to return to Umar Hills to meet &lt;a href=\"Baron%20Metrich\"&gt;Baron Metrich&lt;/a&gt; within the &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale%20Inn\"&gt;Imnesvale Inn&lt;/a&gt;, who has had problems dealing with squatters on his land. \nWhen you arrive, a knight of the order named Crolus will meet you and urge you to follow him. Crolus makes it known that you should not speak with the squatters in front of the Imnesvale Inn, as the Baron does not wish you to hear their lies - indeed the Baron doesn't want you to become tainted by the squatter's version of their illegal activity. (&lt;a href=\"Brunson\"&gt;Brunson&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Pardo\"&gt;Pardo&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Moreno\"&gt;Moreno&lt;/a&gt;) are outside the Inn. You can disobey Crolus's warning without any negative outcomes if you want to speak with the squatters. \nIn fact, if you talk to the \"squatters\", they will reveal that they are actually farmers, that the Baron has stolen their land from them, and that they were forced to resist with violence, else lose their land and livelihood. \nNext, meet the Baron within the tavern area. He will be accompanied by his assistant &lt;a href=\"Lanka\"&gt;Lanka&lt;/a&gt;, another assistant named &lt;a href=\"Lette\"&gt;Lette&lt;/a&gt;, and two guards (&lt;a href=\"Metrich%20Footman\"&gt;Metrich Footman&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Metrich%20Yeoman\"&gt;Metrich Yeoman&lt;/a&gt;). Also is a mage, named &lt;a href=\"Sorcerous%20Amin\"&gt;Sorcerous Amin&lt;/a&gt;. From there, you have two choices: \nHowever, if you talked to at least one \"squatter,\" then the \"refuse\" option is replaced with this choice:\nReturn to Sir Reirrac. Your rewards and outcome for this quest depend on what happened and how you choose to respond to him.\nIf you completed this quest to Reirrac's satisfaction, he will immediately give you your third assignment.\nEvent 3: Tyrianna\u2019s Family.\nThe Morningales were slaughtered for opposing the slave trade, with &lt;a href=\"Tyrianna\"&gt;Tyrianna&lt;/a&gt; as the sole survivor. Reirrac wants you to protect her. Head out to the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Docks&lt;/a&gt; district and enter the safe house, which is just to the right of the Temple of Oghma. Once inside you get to meet the \"pleasant\" Tyrianna, and soon you will be attacked by assassins. After the battle, a man arrives claiming to be Tyrianna's godfather &lt;a href=\"Hurgis%20Baltezan\"&gt;Hurgis Baltezan&lt;/a&gt;.\nThere is a 50/50 chance that \"Hurgis\" is either the real deal or an impostor. You can either send Tyrianna with him or refuse, but if you make the wrong choice, you will lose your stronghold. The key is to use &lt;a href=\"Detect%20Evil\"&gt;Detect Evil&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Know%20Alignment%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Know Alignment&lt;/a&gt; on him. The impostor will show as Evil; the real Hurgis will not. Kill the impostor or tell Tyrianna to go with Hurgis. Either way, once this is done, report back to Reirrac to get your reward: &lt;a href=\"Pride%20of%20the%20Legion\"&gt;Pride of the Legion&lt;/a&gt; +2 and a &lt;a href=\"Large%20Shield%20%2B2\"&gt;Large Shield +2&lt;/a&gt;. If you had the \"Fallen Paladin\" status, then your paladin abilities will be regained. He will give you one final task.\nEvent 4: The Dragon Slayer.\nYou\u2019re to retrieve the &lt;a href=\"Carsomyr\"&gt;Holy Avenger&lt;/a&gt; from Firkraag.\u00a0 Head back to the dragon's lair and fight for glory!\nNote: Petrifying or disintegrating Firkraag can leave you with nothing but experience reward and gold. Beware!\nOnce you kill the dragon, return to Reirrac and report your success. He will officially entrust the Holy Avenger to you and reward you with 35,000 experience.\nCongratulations on being a proven top-notch paladin of the realm. A paladin whose father is Bhaal, Lord of Murder. Carry on and find out what is in store for your existence in the rest of the Saga. \nGallery.\n\"Portraits from &lt;a href=\"Portraits%20Portraits%20Everywhere\"&gt;Portraits Portraits Everywhere&lt;/a&gt;\""}
