{"id": "50362", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50362", "title": "Panic", "text": "Panic is a &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; caused by things like the spell &lt;a href=\"Horror\"&gt;Horror&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nBesides methods that directly cure the effect (see infobox to the right), if the panic effect is caused by a spell (like &lt;a href=\"Horror\"&gt;Horror&lt;/a&gt;), as it commonly is, then it can also be removed by a successful &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt;. Likewise, in this case the effect could be prevented by blocking the spell before it hits (e.g. &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;...).\nBugs.\nUnfortunately, some enemies' scripts prevent them from acting correctly when panicked, causing them to continue to act normally despite the panic effect (eg attacking the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; relentlessly). This is the case with enemies like most and &lt;a href=\"mephit\"&gt;mephit&lt;/a&gt;s and is caused by those scripts missing the line \"ActionListEmpty()\" within their IF conditions.\nFor example, in &lt;a href=\"Irenicus%27%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irenicus' Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;, goblins carrying &lt;a href=\"shortbow\"&gt;shortbow&lt;/a&gt;s will always react appropriately to being under the effect of 'panic', while goblins carrying &lt;a href=\"axe\"&gt;axe&lt;/a&gt;s (all of whom have a different script: KOBOLDF.BCS) will always ignore the condition. Merely adding the missing line to the axe-carrying goblins' script fixes the issue."}
{"id": "55029", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55029", "title": "Panther", "text": "Panther is a type of great cat animal creature found in and the saga.\nThey are typically added to wilderness and forested areas as wandering creatures, such as the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Tethir\"&gt;Forest of Tethir&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nThis animal attacks when an enemy, or certain other animals are detected.\nWhen this Hunter class creature detects a Food Creature class (such as a deer or rabbit), the panther will chase it down and attack it after a slight delay.\nIf the creature detects a party member, that will override the food prey script, and the cat will attack.\nThe beast strikes up to 3 times per round with a claw/bite that's rated as a +1 enchanted weapon for the purposes of what it can strike. See the &lt;a href=\"CATJAG.ITM\"&gt;CATJAG.ITM&lt;/a&gt; for weapon attack/damage details."}
