{"id": "49901", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49901", "title": "Parchment (BDMISC50.itm)", "text": "The Parchment is found within a chest in the &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;Ruined Temple of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt;. It is written by &lt;a href=\"Madele\"&gt;Madele&lt;/a&gt; about her devotion to &lt;a href=\"Bhaal\"&gt;Bhaal&lt;/a&gt;, revenge fantasies awaiting &lt;a href=\"Akanna\"&gt;Akanna&lt;/a&gt; if Madele's ever let free. And about hearing whispers, believing them to be from her returned dead god."}
{"id": "2116", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2116", "title": "Parda", "text": "Parda is a human monk and a close friend to the protagonist. He appears in &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Prologue\"&gt;Prologue&lt;/a&gt; and again during the events of &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Six\"&gt;Chapter Six&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce you have defended yourself against &lt;a href=\"Shank\"&gt;Shank&lt;/a&gt; and left the &lt;a href=\"Priests%27%20Quarters\"&gt;Priests' Quarters&lt;/a&gt;, Parda will approach you with concern for your current state of mind. After your explaination, he'll advise you to find &lt;a href=\"Gorion\"&gt;Gorion&lt;/a&gt; as soon as possible.\nWhen &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; returns to Candlekeep in chapter six, Parda is found in the &lt;a href=\"Bunkhouse\"&gt;Bunkhouse&lt;/a&gt;. Again he will approach you and initiate conversation. This time he gives pretty obvious hints that &lt;a href=\"doppelganger\"&gt;doppelganger&lt;/a&gt;s have invaded Candlekeep. When the brief dialogue is complete he'll exit the building and disappear. This interaction will result in an entry in your &lt;a href=\"Journal\"&gt;Journal&lt;/a&gt;.\nParda will make one more appearance inside a small room on the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Catacombs%20Level%202\"&gt;second level&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Catacombs\"&gt;Candlekeep Catacombs&lt;/a&gt;, although this time he's really a doppelganger in disguise. After a brief dialogue, the doppelganger will transform and attack.\nWhen Parda transforms into a doppelganger, the only changes are his hit points (30) and XP (420). He also carries one item of random treasure.\nDialogue.\nPrologue.\n\"&lt;Gorion's Ward&gt;, you cut yourself above the brow, there\u2014 What is wrong, child? Something in your eyes tells me that something is very wrong indeed.\"\nBunkhouse.\n\"Oh, &lt;Gorion's Ward&gt;, I heard you had returned! If only it weren't in such dark times. Something is afoot in Candlekeep\u2014there is an unvoiced panic amongst those of us who still call these haunted halls our home. You must help us, I pray you.\"\nCatacombs.\nThe doppelganger Parda will approach the party upon sight:\n\"Seek my comfort, will you? Aye, I'll show you a sweet and silent comfort if ye'll let me, wasteling.\"\nGameplay (community).\nParda's advice to supply yourself quickly and be off as soon as possible falls squarely into the category of Bad Advice. &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt; is where you learn to play the game, and the adventure that awaits is unaffected by the amount of time that you spend preparing for it. \nGallery.\n&lt;br&gt;\nParda (right) \"had a sense &lt;a href=\"Someone%20wishes%20me%20dead%21\"&gt;something like this&lt;/a&gt; might happen\"&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "50535", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50535", "title": "Pardo", "text": "Pardo is a so called \"squatter\" gathered in Imnesvale, along with &lt;a href=\"Moreno\"&gt;Moreno&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Brunson\"&gt;Brunson&lt;/a&gt;. All three are assembled outside the &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale%20Inn\"&gt;Imnesvale Inn&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Baron%20Metrich\"&gt;Baron Metrich&lt;/a&gt; does not want you to speak with these individuals and has labelled them as illegal 'squatters\" on his land and wants them removed. If you do speak with Pardo, then you will gain additional information, that could very well refute what the Baron has stated. This NPC is part of a task in the &lt;a href=\"Paladin%20Stronghold%20Duties\"&gt;Paladin Stronghold Duties&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nPardo is also a fighter with some skills and weapons and armor. It appears that the developers assigned this fighter with erroneous THAC0 and saving throws (that of a level 1 Fighter). \nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a default SCS Fighter script for smarter tactical behavior. The mod also revises short sword weapon proficiency to 4 pips and 2 pips in sword and shield fighting style. Appropriate THAC0 and saving throws are also corrected. Finally, SCS random treasures are added to the inventory."}
{"id": "8607", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8607", "title": "Pargus", "text": "Pargus is one of the members of the '&lt;a href=\"Maulers%20of%20Undermountain\"&gt;Maulers of Undermountain&lt;/a&gt;,' an adventuring party which will become hostile if the confrontational dialogue option is chosen when approached by &lt;a href=\"Gretek\"&gt;Gretek&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn the \"\", the Maulers will attack regardless of which dialogue option is chosen."}
{"id": "48418", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48418", "title": "Parisa", "text": "Parisa is female &lt;a href=\"Vampires\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; and a loyal member of &lt;a href=\"Bodhi%27s%20Vampire%20Coven\"&gt;Bodhi's Vampire Coven&lt;/a&gt;.\nEncounters.\nChapters 2 or 3.\nBefore &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%204\"&gt;Chapter 4&lt;/a&gt;, she may appear in any district of the city during a night cycle (midnight to dawn), talking to a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thief&lt;/a&gt; in an attempt to get him to leave the shadow thief guild and join the vampire guild.\nParisa appears neutral during this encounter, and she will &lt;a href=\"Domination\"&gt;dominate&lt;/a&gt; the thief when dialogue has ended. Parisa will also be aware of the party's nearby presence during this encounter and, depending on which side you may have taken in the guild war, she'll either disappear with the thief after the encounter is over or she and the dominated thief will become hostile and attack the party.\nIf the party desires and acts quickly enough, she can be attacked, making her hostile. \nEven though she appears to have been killed when the fighting is done, she is one of the only vampires that doesn't revert to its gaseous form and disappear. Instead, her corpse will remain on the ground. Killing Parisa will result in 8,500 XP but she doesn't permanently die.\nChapter 4.\nWhen you arrive in &lt;a href=\"Brynnlaw\"&gt;Brynnlaw&lt;/a&gt; during the beginning of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%204\"&gt;Chapter 4&lt;/a&gt;, if you sided with the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt;, Parisa, along with two other vampires named &lt;a href=\"Del\"&gt;Del&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Valen\"&gt;Valen&lt;/a&gt;, will attack the party. Killing Parisa, again, will result in another 8,500 XP and this time she does permanently die (in the context that she won't re-appear anymore in the game). This second version of the vampire is a less durable and able opponent than the first version.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod with the \"Improved Vampires\" component revises both appearances of Parisa. See the &lt;a href=\"Vampire\"&gt;Vampire&lt;/a&gt; article and the \"Mod content\" section for a discussion of the mod's revisions to vampires (including Parisa) in the game.&lt;br&gt;\nThe first version of this vampire (VVPARIS.CRE) is a level 11/11 Fighter/Thief with 145 HP, STR 20, DEX 20, CON 19. She has 2.5 &lt;a href=\"Attacks%20per%20round\"&gt;Attacks per round&lt;/a&gt;, THAC0 3 and -3 Armor Class. A default SCS script is assigned allowing Vampire Domination ability every 2 rounds, and attacks with either a 3 level drain or \"\"Blood Drain\" temporarily reducing CON by 3. She can only be struck by +2 or better weapons. She can shape change into bat or wolf form, and summon bats, rats or wolves with the \"children of the night\"\" ability.\nThe second version of this vampire (PPPARIS.CRE) is a level 10/10 Fighter/Thief with 116 HP, STR 19, DEX 19, CON 18. She has 1.5 attacks per round, THAC0 5 and -1 Armor Class. Her melee strike drains 2 experience levels or 3 CON. She also has a different default script, making her akin to an ancient vampire, that has all the abilities of the former version plus the innate &lt;a href=\"Vampire%20Fear\"&gt;Vampire Fear&lt;/a&gt; ability and the \"Mesmerize\" feeblemindedness attack. She will recognize opponents protected from level drain and charm and many other \"buffs\" for intelligent targeting."}
{"id": "23474", "revid": "8506165", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23474", "title": "Party", "text": "The party in all games of the \"Baldur's Gate\" series consists of &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and a variable number of &lt;a href=\"companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt;, even if they haven't any. There are a maximum of six party members, including Gorion's Ward.\nIt's the single one or the group of controllable (and, due to certain &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;status effects&lt;/a&gt;, temporarily uncontrollable) characters, presented by the portraits on the right side of the .\nOther uses.\nAnother use of the term might refer to \"any\" group of adventurers, mercenaries or similar characters, the player's party might encounter during their voyages through the &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Realms\"&gt;realms&lt;/a&gt;."}
