{"id": "42377", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42377", "title": "Pellan's Shield", "text": "Pellan's Shield (Pellan's Shield +2 in game) is a magical large shield +2.\nThis shield and the &lt;a href=\"Shield%20of%20the%20Falling%20Stars\"&gt;Shield of the Falling Stars&lt;/a&gt; are the best shields found in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. While this shield has a better general AC bonus, the Shield of the Falling Stars offers better protection against missiles.\nLocation.\nBaldur's Gate and Baldur's Gate: Enhanced Edition.\nIt can be found in &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt; on the &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28Labyrinth%20Level%20Four%29\"&gt;fourth underground level&lt;/a&gt; in the rune carpet room.\nBaldur's Gate II and Baldur's Gate II: Enhanced Edition.\nIn Baldur's Gate 2 it can be found in the room of &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Maze\"&gt;Firkraag's Maze&lt;/a&gt; past all the guardians, along with &lt;a href=\"Peridan\"&gt;Peridan&lt;/a&gt;. In this game, however, Pellan's Shield is identical in every way to the generic &lt;a href=\"Large%20Shield%20%2B2\"&gt;Large Shield +2&lt;/a&gt; that can be found in abundance across the game. Despite its description of being exceptionally light, both Pellan's Shield and the Large Shield +2 require 10 Strength to wield and weigh 4 pounds. It seems that despite the item description of weight 4 pounds it actually weighs 10 pounds.\nDescription.\nAs a magical item, this shield needs to be identified and has two separate descriptions."}
