{"id": "5284", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5284", "title": "Peridan", "text": "Peridan, also known as Dragonslayer, is an enchanted &lt;a href=\"long%20sword\"&gt;long sword&lt;/a&gt; +2. This weapon deals 1d8+2 points of slashing damage, which is doubled when fighting a &lt;a href=\"dragon\"&gt;dragon&lt;/a&gt;. It also gives the wearer immunity from fear and restores 1 hit point per turn when wielded. It has a -2 bonus to &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;, a weight of 3 lbs and a speed factor of 3. This item appears in .\nLocation.\nIt can be found in a part of the &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Maze\"&gt;Firkraag's Maze&lt;/a&gt;, which are only accessible when accepting the &lt;a href=\"Samia%27s%20Proposal\"&gt;Samia's Proposal&lt;/a&gt; side quest from &lt;a href=\"Samia\"&gt;Samia&lt;/a&gt; herself. The &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Scale%20Shield\"&gt;Dragon Scale Shield&lt;/a&gt; is found at the same place."}
