{"id": "8540", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8540", "title": "Perter", "text": "Perter is a Fletcher and a Merchant at the &lt;a href=\"Armorer/Fletcher\"&gt;Armorer/Fletcher&lt;/a&gt; shop in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign. He shares shop space with &lt;a href=\"Arnolinus\"&gt;Arnolinus&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe most notable Ammunition in Perter's Shop includes &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20of%20Dispelling\"&gt;Arrows of Dispelling&lt;/a&gt; as well as &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20of%20Fire\"&gt;Arrows of Fire&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20of%20Ice\"&gt;Ice&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20of%20Biting\"&gt;Biting&lt;/a&gt;, in addition to &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20%2B1\"&gt;+1&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20%2B2\"&gt;+2&lt;/a&gt; varieties. His other stock consists of mundane Launchers, Missile Weapons, Studded Leather, Bucklers, and a few Potions.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Tweaks%20Anthology\"&gt;The Tweaks Anthology&lt;/a&gt; mod can add an Ammo Belt to Perter's inventory, as well as other containers with other merchants."}
{"id": "6578", "revid": "25646820", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6578", "title": "Perth the Adept", "text": "Perth the Adept is the &lt;a href=\"Cowled%20Wizards\"&gt;Cowled Wizards&lt;/a&gt; administrative official stationed on the island and has a home in &lt;a href=\"Brynnlaw\"&gt;Brynnlaw&lt;/a&gt;. He is the primary attendant to facilitate the transition of those sent to the &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt; asylum sent by his superiors. Or at least he was. It is not clear whether the Pirate Lord &lt;a href=\"Desharik\"&gt;Desharik&lt;/a&gt; is allowed to do this as well. \nGameplay.\nPerth is inside the Cowled Wizard residence. As soon as the party enters then dialogue will commence. If Edwin, Aerie, Yoshimo or Nalia is in the party each may have an interjection as well. \nDepending on the dialogue and replies, determines how much back and forth occurs. However, Perth's off-kilter behavior and general mannerisms are disturbing, and then highly unusual - as if he is not in control of his actions. Eventually, the encounter leads to a hostile reaction, and blood will likely be spilled.\nAt the opening of hostilities the mage will fire off a self-buff contingency containing &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;, followed by either &lt;a href=\"True%20Sight\"&gt;True Sight&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Vocalize\"&gt;Vocalize&lt;/a&gt; if silenced. Another instant preparation my launch soon after with a &lt;a href=\"Mislead\"&gt;Mislead&lt;/a&gt; copy and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt; on self. After that offensive or disabling spells will be cast at applicable observed party members, with the closest being the priority target.\nPerth can instantly launch a few more triggers to protect himself during a battle, including more stoneskins and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, and another &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;. A &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt; can be used to buy time if he is in trouble.\nThe spells listed in the InfoBox are all scripted for use. Power Word spells have a casting time of 1 and will be directed at the nearest enemy, so look out for Stun and Kill Power Words. As is usually the case when the party combats a single powerful spell caster, the sheer number of available party actions aimed at the mage can overwhelm it quickly. A well-timed Secret Word, Pierce magic and a Breach spell can render the mage defenseless for long enough to take him down. Perth has no means to destroy summoned creatures, and weak against AoE spells and or elemental damage. Use these for expected good results.\nOnce defeated, you can find two important items on his twitching corpse - &lt;a href=\"Book%20of%20Infinite%20Spells\"&gt;Book of Infinite Spells&lt;/a&gt; and the sought after Wardstone for Asylum.\nBugs.\nPerma-killing (chunking) Perth appears to lead to a bug where he \"survives\" as a flying rotating chunk of meat (known bug). In which case he becomes non-targetable (and apparently non-killable), but still fully active and continuing to cast his spells. It's advisable to save before entering the door.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises this mage with a different set of memorized spells and new default \"Smarter Mage\" AI. At the outset of the hostilities a self-buff extrapolation automatically launches containing &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt;. A second later while the mage is invisible will be added &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fireshield%20%28Blue%29\"&gt;Fireshield (Blue)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fireshield%20%28Red%29\"&gt;Fireshield (Red)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20The%20Elements\"&gt;Protection From The Elements&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity Divination&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt;. This will all take place in the first seconds of the battle.\nNow while protected Perth will conjure an &lt;a href=\"Invisible%20Stalker\"&gt;Invisible Stalker&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe mage has other contingency spells ready when certain protections are removed, such as PfMW, Absolute Immunity and more stoneskins. Perth may use &lt;a href=\"Melf%27s%20Minute%20Meteors\"&gt;Melf's Minute Meteors&lt;/a&gt; or even &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Blades%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Energy Blades (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; to conduct missile fire in the same rounds as spell casts.\nWhen the mage attempts offensive spell casts, those are determined by the SCS Smarter Mage AI based on available targets and their vulnerabilities. A number of damage dealing spells are in the mage's library and mostly conjuration types like &lt;a href=\"Melf%27s%20Acid%20Arrow\"&gt;Melf's Acid Arrow&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Arrow\"&gt;Flame Arrow&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Chromatic%20Orb\"&gt;Chromatic Orb&lt;/a&gt;. As a conjurer, Perth can summon help in the form of a Djinni, and several types of Elementals. On the higher game difficulty setting, he will attempt to use his &lt;a href=\"Imprisonment\"&gt;Imprisonment&lt;/a&gt; spell, as well as his &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Planetar\"&gt;Summon Planetar&lt;/a&gt;. So, beware those.\nIn addition to the previous spell casting, Perth also has prepared the following for instant release:\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod installed Perth's spells will be the SR versions. Examples include \"Dispelling Screen \" for Spell Immunity, \"Mesthil's Acid Sheath\" in lieu of the Fireshield, \"Mind Blank\" and \"Moment of Prescience\". \nWith the &lt;a href=\"Golem%20Construction%20for%20Spellcasters\"&gt;Golem Construction for Spellcasters&lt;/a&gt; mod installed, Perth has a loyal &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Golem\"&gt;Stone Golem&lt;/a&gt; ally in his home for support."}
{"id": "7683", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7683", "title": "Peter", "text": "Peter, alongside &lt;a href=\"Lindin\"&gt;Lindin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Baerin\"&gt;Baerin&lt;/a&gt;, is a member of &lt;a href=\"Kirian\"&gt;Kirian's&lt;/a&gt; adventuring party in the &lt;a href=\"Mutamin%27s%20Garden\"&gt;Mutamin's Garden&lt;/a&gt; area. They are arrogant Waterdhavians that enjoy picking fights with \"rustic local\" adventuring parties such as your own.\nPeter is a fighter/cleric who relies on spells such as &lt;a href=\"Rigid%20Thinking\"&gt;Rigid Thinking&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Hold Person&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Entangle\"&gt;Entangle&lt;/a&gt; to disrupt his opponents."}
{"id": "7951", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7951", "title": "Peter of the North", "text": "Peter of the North is a unique \"woodsman\" in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". He is responsible for the training of &lt;a href=\"Wyvern\"&gt;Wyvern&lt;/a&gt;s intended for the defense of the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mine\"&gt;Cloakwood Mine&lt;/a&gt;. Peter is the \"fool\" that &lt;a href=\"Izefia\"&gt;Izefia&lt;/a&gt; refers to, and spends his time within a cave in the &lt;a href=\"Third%20Cloakwood\"&gt;Third Cloakwood&lt;/a&gt; area, along with two &lt;a href=\"Baby%20Wyvern\"&gt;Baby Wyvern&lt;/a&gt;s.\nWhen encountered by &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;, he will pretend to be a woodsman, but will struggle under continued questioning, eventually admitting to the facade, only to attack despite whichever dialogue options are chosen. Interestingly, his equipment is practically identical to that of a &lt;a href=\"Blacktalon%20Elite\"&gt;Blacktalon Elite&lt;/a&gt;, only without the notorious &lt;a href=\"Bandit%20Scalp\"&gt;Bandit Scalp&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue.\n\"Move along, friends, nothing to see here. Just a humble woodsman doing a little spelunking.\""}
{"id": "46235", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46235", "title": "Petrification", "text": ""}
{"id": "41342", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41342", "title": "Petrified", "text": "The &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;effect&lt;/a&gt; petrified or petrification is caused by a &lt;a href=\"Basilisk\"&gt;Basilisk&lt;/a&gt;'s gaze and the spell &lt;a href=\"Flesh%20to%20Stone\"&gt;Flesh to Stone&lt;/a&gt;. The affected creature is instantly turned to stone as are their items. If the creature is part of the party it is removed from it.\nAny further hostile action aimed at the creature will cause the creature and its items to shatter to pieces.\nImmunity.\nThe spell &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Petrification\"&gt;Protection From Petrification&lt;/a&gt; will prevent the effect from taking hold. In addition a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Mirrored%20Eyes\"&gt;Potion of Mirrored Eyes&lt;/a&gt; can be used, but beware of the significantly lower duration of only 1 turn. The high-level abilities &lt;a href=\"Avoid%20Death\"&gt;Avoid Death&lt;/a&gt; (Thief, Bard) and &lt;a href=\"Favored%20of%20the%20Spirits\"&gt;Favored of the Spirits&lt;/a&gt; (Shaman) also provide immunity.\nIn addition, if the &lt;a href=\"Flesh%20to%20Stone\"&gt;Flesh to Stone&lt;/a&gt; spell is the origin of petrification, it can be blocked by any &lt;a href=\"Spell%20protections%20type\"&gt;Spell protection&lt;/a&gt; that targets level 6 spells or above, like &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20of%20the%20Archons\"&gt;Shield of the Archons&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt;: Alteration, or by high &lt;a href=\"magic%20resistance\"&gt;magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nCure.\nThe spell &lt;a href=\"Stone%20to%20Flesh\"&gt;Stone to Flesh&lt;/a&gt; reverses the effect. It should be noted that this is the only way to cure this effect. &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Paralysis\"&gt;Remove Paralysis&lt;/a&gt; will not work. If &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;the protagonist&lt;/a&gt; is affected by petrification, they can not be cured, it's instant game over."}
{"id": "8353", "revid": "3045005", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8353", "title": "Petrine", "text": "Petrine is in the southwest corner of &lt;a href=\"north%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;north Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. She is a child that ran away from her &lt;a href=\"Bheren\"&gt;uncle&lt;/a&gt;. She will ask &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; to get a &lt;a href=\"Angel%20the%20Cat%27s%20Angel%20Skin%20Ring\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; which &lt;a href=\"Angel%20the%20Cat\"&gt;her cat&lt;/a&gt; likes playing with, so it will come back to her from her &lt;a href=\"Bheren%27s%20Home\"&gt;uncle's house&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 which starts the side &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Petrine%27s%20Cat\"&gt;Petrine's Cat&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "10851", "revid": "51239487", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10851", "title": "Petrine's Cat", "text": "This side quest is given to the party by the girl &lt;a href=\"Petrine\"&gt;Petrine&lt;/a&gt; standing outside &lt;a href=\"Bheren%27s%20Home\"&gt;her uncle's house&lt;/a&gt; in the southwestern &lt;a href=\"north%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;north Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. After getting the quest from Petrine, enter the house behind her.\nIn the first room is her uncle, &lt;a href=\"Bheren\"&gt;Bheren&lt;/a&gt;. You can choose to talk to him or simply walk upstairs. Downstairs there is a locked wardrobe containing , a table with &lt;a href=\"Murky%20Oil%20of%20Speed\"&gt;Murky Oil of Speed&lt;/a&gt;, and a matching table containing 10 &lt;a href=\"Bullet%20%2B1\"&gt;Bullet +1&lt;/a&gt;, none of which Bheren seems to mind you taking. Bheren won't talk unless you talk to him. He will then complain about Petrine's &lt;a href=\"Angel%20the%20Cat\"&gt;cat&lt;/a&gt; and perhaps \u2013 depending on your &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 offer a favor for a favor.\nBheren: Damnable cat! I figured Petrine would take the beast with her, but life isn't that kind, is it?\nBheren: Damnable cat! I'll give you the cloak off my back if you can kill the pesky thing.\nIf you decide to help out Uncle Bheren by 'eliminating' his cat problem, go upstairs and kill &lt;a href=\"Angel%20the%20Cat\"&gt;Angel the Cat&lt;/a&gt; where you will get 1 xp. When you tell Bheren how you helped him out, and to complete the side quest, his response will depend on your reputation.\nBheren: I'm not usually a man who honors his words too much, but you wouldn't believe how glad I am to be rid of that crazy cat! Here, take my cloak and good riddance.\nHe will then give you his &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Protection%20%2B1\"&gt;Cloak of Protection +1&lt;/a&gt;. In the \"\" only, you also gain 400 XP.\nBheren: You didn't think I was serious, did you? Cripes, you go find my niece Petrine and tell her you killed her stinking cat, 'cause I'm sure not going to!\nYou will gain 400 XP, but your &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Party Reputation&lt;/a&gt; gets reduced by 1.\nKilling Bheren gives you &lt;a href=\"Leather%20Armor\"&gt;Leather Armor&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Protection%20%2B1\"&gt;Cloak of Protection +1&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Short%20Sword\"&gt;Short Sword&lt;/a&gt;, and 600 XP, while reducing your &lt;a href=\"Reputation%23Actions%20and%20deeds\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt;.\nThere is a dialogue option with Duke &lt;a href=\"Liia%20Jannath\"&gt;Liia Jannath&lt;/a&gt; where you can confess the killing of the uncle and ask her to take care of the girl, to which she will agree. There are no other consequences from that dialogue.\nUpstairs is the cat Angel, who only meows, and a chest of drawers containing a &lt;a href=\"Skydrop%20Gem\"&gt;Skydrop Gem&lt;/a&gt;, , and &lt;a href=\"Angel%20the%20Cat%27s%20Angel%20Skin%20Ring\"&gt;Angel the Cat's Angel Skin Ring&lt;/a&gt; (a common &lt;a href=\"Angel%20Skin%20Ring\"&gt;Angel Skin Ring&lt;/a&gt; in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\"). There's also a Sleeping Elf upstairs in bed but no other loot.\nPetrine: You found the ring... now Angel will come back... and we can live together forever and ever. I wish I had something to give you for finding her ring but I really and truly don't. Maybe she'll give you some good luck, though.\nYou don't have to actually tell Petrine, and the game won't let you as she remains oblivious while waiting for her cat to return.\n In the enhanced edition you are forced to confess if you decide to talk to her and she'll run off crying. Your reputation is also decreased by 1. You can decide not to talk to her and the quest is already marked as finished in the conversation with Bheren.\nPetrine: You... you killed Angel... Waaaaaaaaa...!"}
{"id": "6339", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6339", "title": "Phaere", "text": "Phaere is a female &lt;a href=\"Drow\"&gt;Drow&lt;/a&gt; who resides in &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt;. She's a member of the \"Despana\" house in the city.\nThe Handmaiden &lt;a href=\"Imrae\"&gt;Imrae&lt;/a&gt; orders &lt;a href=\"Solaufein\"&gt;Solaufein&lt;/a&gt; and the party to rescue &lt;a href=\"Phaere\"&gt;Phaere&lt;/a&gt;, captured by the Illithid in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;. The party will later learn that earlier in her life she also had feelings for Solaufein, but &lt;a href=\"Matron%20Mother%20Ardulace%20Despana\"&gt;Matron Mother Ardulace Despana&lt;/a&gt; tortured, punished and indoctrinated her for it. Now Phaere seems to despise him.\nShe introduces and requires completion of several tasks and quests relevant to the main plot of getting the protagonist and party back to the surface from the Underdark. She also attempts to sleep with male protagonists; this can end some &lt;a href=\"romance\"&gt;romance&lt;/a&gt; actions. \nNote that it is very unlikely the party will face Phaere in combat action, as this would most likely end all open quests and make the city of Ust Natha hostile. But it can certainly occur if the player pursues that goal and will have to deal with the consequences."}
{"id": "7979", "revid": "4896558", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7979", "title": "Phaersis", "text": "Phaersis is one of many slaves found in the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines\"&gt;Cloakwood Mines&lt;/a&gt; during \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". He's a bit more courageous and knowledgeable than most slaves, willing to risk telling &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; about potentially &lt;a href=\"Flooding%20the%20Cloakwood%20Mine\"&gt;Flooding the Cloakwood Mine&lt;/a&gt; - despite not having anything to do with the actual quest.\nDialogue.\n\"Psst... there be a plug somewhere that seals this mine from the river's torrent. Find it and maybe you can render this hell no more than a watery memory of its former self.\""}
{"id": "43407", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43407", "title": "Phaerus", "text": "Phaerus was a mercenary employed by the &lt;a href=\"Shining%20Crusade\"&gt;Shining Crusade&lt;/a&gt; during the events of . Although he never crossed paths with &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Bhaalspawn\"&gt;Bhaalspawn&lt;/a&gt; learned of his existence by speaking to three Crusader guards; &lt;a href=\"Anji\"&gt;Anji&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bardyla\"&gt;Bardyla&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Spensse\"&gt;Spensse&lt;/a&gt;, who recounted the tale of how Phaerus once got drunk and accidentally dropped a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Fire%20Breath\"&gt;Potion of Fire Breath&lt;/a&gt; into their campfire, resulting in a massive explosion and a cloud of nauseating fumes, much to the anger of &lt;a href=\"Turin%20Brassbreaker\"&gt;Turin Brassbreaker&lt;/a&gt;.\nBy replicating this feat, Gorion's Ward was able to access &lt;a href=\"The%20Warrens\"&gt;The Warrens&lt;/a&gt; that lay beneath &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle&lt;/a&gt;, with Turin openly blaming the chaos on Phaerus as she swept past them."}
{"id": "8332", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8332", "title": "Phandalyn", "text": "Phandalyn is a &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt; who can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Generic%20Tavern%20and%20Inn%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23AR1109\"&gt;Tavern and Inn&lt;/a&gt; located against the western wall in &lt;a href=\"Southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Southwest Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; between the hours of 4:30 am to 8:30 pm. He will initiate dialogue upon sight. If you have no evil party members, he will say,\n\"Your party is free of the taint of evil. Please pass unmolested.\"\nHe will attack the party if it has at least one evil member.\n\"I sense evil in your party, friend. I cannot allow you or your evil companions to threaten the good people of Baldur's Gate.\"\nIf your party has a reputation of&lt;br&gt;15 or less &lt;br&gt;10 or less &lt;br&gt;and you happen to explore the &lt;a href=\"Three%20Old%20Kegs\"&gt;Three Old Kegs&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"North%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;North Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; before exploring the generic tavern and inn, a hafling named &lt;a href=\"Bellamy\"&gt;Bellamy&lt;/a&gt; will hail you upon sight and warn you about Phandalyn."}
{"id": "5883", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5883", "title": "Phantom Blade", "text": "Phantom Blade creates a blade-shaped construct of magical force extending from the fingers of one of the wizard's hands.\nGameplay.\nThe caster receives a magically created item (see second InfoBox) that is automatically placed in the main hand weapon slot, for the duration of the spell or until it is dispelled.\nDuring its existence, the magical weapon cannot be moved from the main hand slot.\nA &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect applied to the wielder can destroy this blade.\nNo weapon proficiency affects this weapon (only fighting styles, such as &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Proficiency\"&gt;single weapon style&lt;/a&gt;, do). \nIn BG2EE, most magical weapons let you dual wield without a &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; penalty, making two weapon fighting style redundant when using this spell. \nMoreover, while dual wielding, the effects of single weapon style apply to both weapons, meaning both main and offhand weapons score critical hits on attack rolls of 19 or higher. The +2 AC bonus, however, only applies once.\nModifiers from the wielder's strength attribute apply to both to-hit and rolled damage.\nAny creature with the &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; classification that is struck by this blade will suffer an additional +10 &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nNotes.\nIn the original Baldurs Gate this weapons category is longsword and is affected by things like the elf race trait +1 bonus to longswords and long sword proficiencies.\nThe created weapon's on-hit anti-undead damage bonus is of the &lt;a href=\"Offensive%20damage%20type\"&gt;Offensive damage type&lt;/a&gt; \u2014 blockable by the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Mirroring\"&gt;Cloak of Mirroring&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its effects, duration and school. See below for description:\nPhantom Blade\nLevel: 5\nSchool: Illusion\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 1 round/level\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nThis spell creates a translucent, weightless, shadowlike sword made of material from the Plane of Shadow that extends 3 feet from the caster\u2019s hand. The caster wields the phantom blade as if it was a long sword but he suffers no penalty for non-proficiency. The sword deals 1d12+4 points of magic damage to its victims, and an additional 10 points of magical damage against undead creatures. Due to its ethereal nature, strength bonuses do not apply, but attacks with the phantom blade are considered melee touch attacks, and thus gain a +4 bonus to hit. Furthermore, a successful strike temporarily scrambles magic, causing any spells the target casts in the next round to fail (save vs. spell at a -4 penalty negates). The blade is considered to be of +4 enchantment when determining what it can hit, but it cannot harm inorganic things because it has no solid existence. The phantom blade can only be used by the caster and remains in his/her hand for the duration of the spell or until dispelled."}
{"id": "11298", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11298", "title": "Phase Spider", "text": "The Phase Spider is one of three different high-level &lt;a href=\"Spiders\"&gt;Spiders&lt;/a&gt; encountered in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\", the other two being the &lt;a href=\"Wraith%20Spider\"&gt;Wraith Spider&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Spider\"&gt;Sword Spider&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nThey are one of the more interesting enemies to be found, as they exhibit some fairly deadly and unique abilities. They are fairly rare, usually only found within the depths of various forests, and are distinguishable from their brethren by way of a bright-green body and dark-green legs - pointedly different from the much more common &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Spider\"&gt;Giant Spider&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nLike most spiders, they can &lt;a href=\"poison\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt; their enemies and are immune to &lt;a href=\"Web\"&gt;Web&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Entangle\"&gt;Entangle&lt;/a&gt;. It's essentially a more powerful Giant Spider, with the unique ability to quickly 'blink' short distances, likely much closer to &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; than they'd otherwise prefer. Unlike most spiders which can normally be pulled by a specific party member and/or drawn into a trap, the Phase Spider will often teleport behind or within the parties formation, likely striking (and poisoning) a few weaker party members before the player is able to dispatch it. Most specimens encountered in-game are pre-generated, meaning that there likely won't be a consideration made for the strength of the player, making for a very difficult fight regarding unprepared low-level parties.\nSummoned.\nPhase spiders can be summoned by a 9th or higher level &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt; casting the 4th level Wizard spell &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Spawn\"&gt;Spider Spawn&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn a summoned phase spider's attack damage is adjusted for Strength bonus, however the spider's strength is only 14 which provides no bonus; unless it becomes the target of a &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; spell, in which case a +3 damage bonus would apply."}
