{"id": "49203", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49203", "title": "Phlydian", "text": "Phlydian is a female &lt;a href=\"Vampire%20%28Elder%29\"&gt;Vampire&lt;/a&gt; who's found in the &lt;a href=\"Saradush%20Prison\"&gt;Saradush Prison&lt;/a&gt; which is located underneath the besieged city of &lt;a href=\"Saradush\"&gt;Saradush&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nShe's lurking near the exit point to the &lt;a href=\"Castle%20Saradush%20Basement\"&gt;basement&lt;/a&gt;. Phlydian will engage the party in some brief dialogue before turning hostile, along with some lower-level vampire cohorts.\nThis creature has the usual attacks, resistances and innate abilities as all vampire creatures do in BG2, as well as a slight physical damage resistance and a high magic resistance. She won't try any vampire innate abilities such as &lt;a href=\"Domination%20%28Innate%29\"&gt;Domination&lt;/a&gt;.\nShe packs a wallop due to the impressive strength attribute.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod and the \"Improved Vampire\" component makes a few revisions to Phlydian. She is a level 25/25 fighter/thief class. Her HP is raised due to this. Her THAC0 and APR are a little better. Phlydian also possesses the \"Blood Drain\" attack which will be selected if the target is protected from level drain. She has more innate abilities to use, and her revised script incorporates them. At least +3 enchanted weapons are needed to strike her with this mod. She is configured as a &lt;a href=\"Vampire%20%28Ancient%29\"&gt;Vampire (Ancient)&lt;/a&gt; creature in SCS."}
{"id": "5205", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5205", "title": "Phoenix Guard", "text": "Phoenix Guards are hostile humanoids encountered in &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt; (after being summoned by &lt;a href=\"Daer%27Ragh\"&gt;Daer'Ragh&lt;/a&gt;) and on &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28Labyrinth%20Level%20Three%29\"&gt;Labyrinth Level Three&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nTrue to their name, they are capable of rising indefinitely after being killed, though the odds of them doing so are dependent on the circumstances in which they are encountered. If they fail their attempt to reincarnate, they will unleash a fiery blast similar to a &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt; from their corpse, dealing 5d6+5 fire damage. There is no saving throw against this explosion and &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; will not block damage."}
{"id": "41426", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41426", "title": "Phossey Dugdeep", "text": "Phossey Dugdeep was an eccentric female dwarven alchemist in the service of &lt;a href=\"Torsin%20de%20Lancie\"&gt;Torsin de Lancie&lt;/a&gt;, who partook in the events of on the behalf of the coalition. She is the creator of the &lt;a href=\"Barrel%20of%20Bwoosh%21\"&gt;Barrel of Bwoosh!&lt;/a&gt;, an alchemical mega-explosive that is needed to breach the defenses of &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle&lt;/a&gt;."}
