{"id": "4750", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4750", "title": "Physical Mirror", "text": "Physical Mirror creates an invisible disk that reflects successful missile attacks against the caster back to the sender. It is very similar to the &lt;a href=\"Reflection%20Shield\"&gt;Reflection Shield&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nReflected attacks by type.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Baldur's Gate II=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;\nIn addition, the following &lt;a href=\"Game%20Terminology%23N\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt;-only attacks are also reflected:\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its effects, duration and description. See below for description:\nPhysical Mirror\nLevel: 6\nSchool: Alteration\nSphere: Numbers\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 2 turns\nCasting Time: 6\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nThis spell causes a localized folding of space. The folded space takes the form of an invisible disk that protects the caster but also distorts his appearance as if a mirrored image of the caster traveled alongside him. Any missile attack that intersects the disk is instantaneously deflected, while there is a 50% chance that a melee attacker will attack the mirrored image and a 50% chance that he will attack the caster."}
