{"id": "2298", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2298", "title": "Plate Mail", "text": "Plate Mail is the second most protective non-magical armor you can buy. It offers an armor class of 3 and nearly all plate mails in the games of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, , and also offer a -3 bonus to armor class against slashing attacks.\nThe plate weighs 50 lbs, which means that a character with decent strength loses a quite amount of carrying capacity while wearing it. It requires at least 12 &lt;a href=\"strength\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt; to wear plate mail and it can only be worn by &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"ranger\"&gt;ranger&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s.\nLocations.\n\"Baldur's Gate\".\nIt is sold at the &lt;a href=\"Friendly%20Arm%20Inn\"&gt;Friendly Arm Inn&lt;/a&gt;, the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Thunderhammer%20Smithy\"&gt;Thunderhammer Smithy&lt;/a&gt;, the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Store\"&gt;Nashkel Store&lt;/a&gt; and at general stores in the city of\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. It's also worn as standard body armor by Flaming Fist Soldiers.\nIf you rest in Candlekeep before leaving with Gorion, a Candlekeep Watcher will spawn and tell you to get a room. Kill the watcher and he'll drop Plate Mail armor. Since you killed an innocent, your reputation will also go down significantly and the amount varies depending on your party's current reputation. Still, if you're open to exporting your character or party after your rest killing spree, you can get a \"lot\" of early game Plate Mail armors easily, and by starting a new game with an imported character, your party's reputation also resets! (Alleluia!)\n\"Shadows of Amn\".\nIt's sold at the &lt;a href=\"Adventurer%27s%20Mart\"&gt;Adventurer's Mart&lt;/a&gt;, by &lt;a href=\"Jayes\"&gt;Jayes&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ikert\"&gt;Ikert&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hes\"&gt;Hes&lt;/a&gt; and other merchants.\n\"Throne of Bhaal\".\nIt's sold at the &lt;a href=\"Tankard%20Tree\"&gt;Tankard Tree&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "6778", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6778", "title": "Plate Mail (PLAT99)", "text": "Plat99 is no ordinary &lt;a href=\"Plate%20Mail\"&gt;plate mail&lt;/a&gt; by any chance; this plate mail armor can alternate between a 'chest-girdle' allowing full spell-casting ability and normal plate mail with the same protection as the standard variety.\nLocation.\nPlat99 can only be spawned in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and and within Baldur's Gate Enhanced Edition via the &lt;a href=\"Console%20Commands\"&gt;console commands&lt;/a&gt;.\nDetails.\nThis obscure suit of armor has two descriptions: the one for regular plate mail and describing it as a cursed spear +3 as a chest-girdle. "}
