{"id": "48863", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48863", "title": "Plath Rededge", "text": "Plath Rededge is a human cleric and the leader of a group of bandits who appear in the &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Cabin\"&gt;Windspear Cabin&lt;/a&gt; during the events of the &lt;a href=\"Journey%20to%20the%20Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Journey to the Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt; side quest.\nGameplay.\nShe will address the party, following the abduction of &lt;a href=\"Garren%20Windspear\"&gt;Garren Windspear&lt;/a&gt;'s child, that hints at the reason for &lt;a href=\"Firkraag\"&gt;Lord Firkraag's&lt;/a&gt; interest in ruining &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;'s name and reputation. When the dialogue concludes, Plath and the remaining bandits will turn hostile and attack the party. \nPleth will attempt to cast offensive spells only, except for &lt;a href=\"Death%20Ward\"&gt;Death Ward&lt;/a&gt;. If not disrupted, she will try and cast &lt;a href=\"Slay%20Living\"&gt;Slay Living&lt;/a&gt;, followed by &lt;a href=\"Harm\"&gt;Harm&lt;/a&gt;, and then &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Strike\"&gt;Flame Strike&lt;/a&gt;. If still functional, she may attempt a second &lt;a href=\"Slay%20Living\"&gt;Slay Living&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Hold Person (priest)&lt;/a&gt;.\nShe is accompanied by a 12th level dwarven fighter with helm, plate mail, battle axe and large shield. The dwarf is quite strong. Two 6th level orcs (also with 18+ strength) are also part of the bandit band. One orc is wielding a bastard sword, and the other focuses on missile fire with Composite Longbow and arrows.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises this evil cleric, and most noticeably applies a group of (previously cast) spells upon herself, including: &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Draw Upon Holy Might (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Free Action (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt;. \nShe can use a potion in her inventory for quaffing, and can attempt a &lt;a href=\"Heal\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt; or various cure wounds spells on self. She'll attack party members with spells, some targeting will be influenced by what protections and vulnerabilities are recognized by the AI. Perhaps a &lt;a href=\"Finger%20of%20Death%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Finger of Death (priest)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mental%20Domination\"&gt;Mental Domination&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Hold Person (priest)&lt;/a&gt;."}
