{"id": "23806", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23806", "title": "Pocket Plane (ability)", "text": "&lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; acquires the ability to open portals to and from the &lt;a href=\"Pocket%20Plane%20%28area%29\"&gt;Pocket Plane&lt;/a&gt; early in the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%208\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 8&lt;/a&gt; of \"Throne of Bhaal\" campaign. This ability can be used any time the player is not in battle.\nThis ability provides a quick way to retreat from danger, as well as ready access to a safe haven where the player may resupply, use the service of &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt;, heal, apply magic, replenish depleted spells, and otherwise recuperate.\nWhen the ability is used, it automatically selects all current party members to travel as a group."}
{"id": "6607", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6607", "title": "Pocket Plane (area)", "text": "The Pocket Plane is an area &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; able to access beginning in the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%208\"&gt;first chapter&lt;/a&gt; of the \"Throne of Bhaal\" campaign.\nBackstory.\nThe Pocket Plane is an extra-dimensional room originally created by &lt;a href=\"Bhaal\"&gt;Bhaal&lt;/a&gt;. It is all that remains of Bhaal's power since the God of Murder's death during the &lt;a href=\"Time%20of%20Troubles\"&gt;Time of Troubles&lt;/a&gt;, though its precise connection to &lt;a href=\"Bhaal%27s%20Domain\"&gt;Bhaal's Domain&lt;/a&gt; from is unknown.\nFunction.\nThe plane is an enclosed, hellish-looking series of chambers, where the imp &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt; is found and any party members that Gorion's Ward has asked the &lt;a href=\"Fate%20Spirit\"&gt;Fate Spirit&lt;/a&gt; to summon there for later recruitment. The Pocket Plane serves as a vital link-way between various areas during the events of the \"Throne of Bhaal\" storyline. After completing the first challenge, Gorion's Ward and party may come and go from the Pocket Plane at will (as long as they're not in battle), making it very convenient for healing up and changing/rememorizing spells.\u00a0For example, one might start\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Sendai%27s%20Enclave\"&gt;Sendai's Enclave&lt;/a&gt; with a set of general spells for dealing with large groups of enemies and then warp to the plane and refresh their spells before fighting &lt;a href=\"Sendai\"&gt;Sendai&lt;/a&gt; herself.\nA Gorion's Ward with a good alignment who has completed the second trial will find that the trial-room has become a healing pit, allowing for passive health regeneration of any party member standing inside of it.\nBhaalspawn Challenges.\nThe Pocket Plane is the source of five challenges throughout the events of \"Throne of Bhaal\". These must be completed to progress through the game. Each challenge is triggered by defeating a member of &lt;a href=\"The%20Five\"&gt;The Five&lt;/a&gt;.\nChallenge #1: Retribution.\nThis challenge is triggered after defeating &lt;a href=\"Illasera\"&gt;Illasera&lt;/a&gt;. The player must speak with the shade of a Bhaalspawn human peasant turned murderer, Gavid, and then face multiple waves of enemies dependent upon their alignment.\nCompleting this challenge grants Gorion's Ward 30.000 Quest EXP and each member of the party 25.000 Quest EXP, as well as giving Gorion's Ward the Pocket Plane ability.\nChallenge #2: Possibilities.\nThis challenge is triggered after defeating &lt;a href=\"Yaga-Shura\"&gt;Yaga-Shura&lt;/a&gt;. The player must confront an alternative version of Gorion's Ward, one who was not saved by Gorion, who leads a party comprised of Tamoko, Semaj and Angelo. \nThe chamber hosting the challenge will start either as a rocky place with pools of lava that burn anyone stepping into them, or as an oasis with pools of healing water. The lava chamber will greet Gorion's Ward if they answered in a Good-aligned way to the Solar prior to the challenge. It will be the oasis chamber otherwise.\nAfter the challenge is completed, the place is remodeled into its \"other\" state, Gorion's Ward receives 30,000 XP, and other party members are awarded 25,000 XP each. \nIf the player has either the &lt;a href=\"Ascension\"&gt;Ascension&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29%20\"&gt;Unfinished Business (Baldur's Gate II) &lt;/a&gt; mods installed, they will acquire a new Bhaalspawn power, depending on whether they made the \"Good\" or \"Evil\" responses to the Solar before undertaking the challenge.\nChallenge #3: Doubts.\nThis challenge is triggered after defeating &lt;a href=\"Sendai\"&gt;Sendai&lt;/a&gt;. The player must fight their incarnated doubt/lingering innocence (depending on alignment), which takes the form of the Slayer and attacks them. It focuses exclusively on attacking Gorion's Ward and has the ability to &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;drain levels&lt;/a&gt; with its attacks.\nIf the player has either the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Ascension\"&gt;Ascension&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0or\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Unfinished Business (Baldur's Gate II)\u00a0mods&lt;/a&gt; installed, they will acquire a new Bhaalspawn power, depending on whether they made the \"Good\" or \"Evil\" responses to the Solar before undertaking the challenge.\nChallenge #4: Cyric, God of Murder..\nThis challenge is triggered after defeating &lt;a href=\"Abazigal\"&gt;Abazigal&lt;/a&gt;. The player must defeat three &lt;a href=\"Favored%20of%20Cyric\"&gt;Favored of Cyric&lt;/a&gt;, which are high-levelled Assassins.\nIf the player has either the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Ascension\"&gt;Ascension&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0or\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Unfinished Business&lt;/a&gt; installed, they will acquire a new Bhaalspawn power, depending on whether they made the \"Good\" or \"Evil\" responses to the Solar before undertaking the challenge:\nChallenge #5: The Ravager.\nThis challenge is triggered after defeating &lt;a href=\"Balthazar\"&gt;Balthazar&lt;/a&gt;. The party must defeat &lt;a href=\"The%20Ravager\"&gt;The Ravager&lt;/a&gt;, the ultimate incarnation of Bhaal's bloody power.\nIf the player has either the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Ascension\"&gt;Ascension&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0or\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Unfinished Business (Baldur's Gate II)\u00a0mods&lt;/a&gt; installed, they will acquire a new Bhaalspawn power, depending on whether they made the \"Good\" or \"Evil\" responses to the Solar before undertaking the challenge:"}
