{"id": "25678", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=25678", "title": "Poe's Tale of Firewine", "text": "Journal Entry.\nNear the &lt;a href=\"Firewine%20Bridge\"&gt;Firewine Bridge&lt;/a&gt; ruins I met a bard who told a rousing tale of swordsmen, one of whom betrayed the others, whose spirits will not rest until they find him again.\u00a0\nRelated Quest.\nYou can ask &lt;a href=\"Poe\"&gt;Poe&lt;/a&gt; about the truth of that tale. And you can find it out yourself.\nInside the Firewine dungeon you find the haunting ghosts and they will reveal that they cannot rest until they are united with their lost brother. You find the missing swordsman in the corridors north of them and can release him by killing him.\nWhen you bring back his armor to the others their souls are all laid to rest and they vanish."}
{"id": "30655", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30655", "title": "Poison", "text": "Poison is a status effect that causes &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt; over time, ticking like a clock. It is able to interrupt spellcasting.\nPoison is sometimes called the Bleeding effect, but they are one and the same.\nBug.\nIn BG2EE Items with poison effects block their own effects on a poison-immune target. However, in some cases, they are also blocking other, non-poison-related effects which should still apply. This will be fixed in the pending Enhanced Edition Fix Pack (EEFP) - example POTN48.ITM)"}
{"id": "5114", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5114", "title": "Poison (spell)", "text": "Mod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this Divine spell, revising its effects, saving throw, and description. See below:\nPoison\nLevel: 4\nSchool: Necromancy\nSphere: Healing\nRange: Short\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 4\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: Poison partial\nThrough this spell, the caster can poison a single victim. The damage dealt by the poison depends upon the level of the priest casting the spell.\n7th level: 4d4 + 1 every 4 seconds\n9th level: 5d5 + 1 every 3 seconds\n12th level: 6d6 + 1 every 2 seconds\n15th+ level: 8d8 + 1 every 1 second\nThe victim cannot avoid the initial damage unless it is completely immune to the effects of poison, but a successful save vs. poison at -2 will negate the ongoing damage."}
{"id": "33287", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33287", "title": "Poison Mist", "text": "A Poison Mist is a mist monster that is encountered during the \"\" campaign.\nThey are summoned by &lt;a href=\"Barl\"&gt;Barl&lt;/a&gt; inside the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Waukeen%20%28Trademeet%29\"&gt;Temple of Waukeen&lt;/a&gt; located in &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Trademeet&lt;/a&gt; if he is attacked during the &lt;a href=\"Save%20Mazzy%27s%20Sister%2C%20Pala\"&gt;Save Mazzy's Sister, Pala&lt;/a&gt; side quest. They will spawn in the Slime laboratory when the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20of%20Air\"&gt;Guardian of Air&lt;/a&gt; is defeated in the Air laboratory, located on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey may also randomly spawn in locations where other mist monsters such as &lt;a href=\"Vampiric%20Mist\"&gt;Vampiric Mist&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Crimson%20Death\"&gt;Crimson Death&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Mist%20Horror\"&gt;Mist Horror&lt;/a&gt; are encountered.\nPoison Mists are immune to acid and poison damage. They have 25% resistance to all forms of &lt;a href=\"Physical%20damage\"&gt;Physical damage&lt;/a&gt; and are immune to non-magical weapons.\nA Poison Mist's only weapon is a 1d2 &lt;a href=\"slashing%20damage\"&gt;slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; attack delivered by their elongated tentacle-like fingers. A successful hit inflicts 1d10 &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt;, with the additional hazard of causing a &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; status effect. The victim of this mist's melee attack must achieve a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Death with a -2 penalty or suffer 2 points of &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt; per second for 5 seconds. "}
{"id": "15105", "revid": "271001", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15105", "title": "Poison Weapon", "text": "Poison Weapon is a special ability available to &lt;a href=\"Assassin\"&gt;Assassin&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Blackguard\"&gt;Blackguard&lt;/a&gt;s. It grants on-hit &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt; and inflicts a &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison effect&lt;/a&gt;.\nClassic versions.\nThe next hit with that weapon will inject the poison into the target (no save), dealing out 1 damage per second for 24 seconds (3 damage for the first 6 seconds). A &lt;a href=\"saving%20throw\"&gt;saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. poison limits damage to 12 total.\nEnhanced Editions.\nEach successful hit within the next 5 &lt;a href=\"Game%20Terminology%23R\"&gt;rounds&lt;/a&gt; will inject poison into the target. The immediate poison damage is applied with every hit, but the additional periodic damage can only be present once on a target. Additional applications do stack, however, the effect can only be applied on a particular creature once per round (that goes for both the 'no save' instant damage and the damage/second part of it). The amount of poison damage depends on the character's level:\n1st - Target suffers 1 poison damage per second for 6 seconds (Save vs. Death at -1 bonus negates)\n5th - Target suffers 1 poison damage per second for 12 seconds (Save vs. Death negates), and also immediately suffers 2 poison damage (no save)\n9th - Target suffers 1 poison damage per second for 18 seconds (Save vs. Death at +1 penalty negates), and also immediately suffers 4 poison damage (no save)\n13th - Target suffers 1 poison damage per second for 24 seconds (Save vs. Death at +2 penalty\u00a0negates), and also immediately suffers 6 poison damage (no save)\n\"Note: As an \"innate spell\", &lt;a href=\"Multi-class\"&gt;multi&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dual-class\"&gt;dual&lt;/a&gt;-classed characters \"cast\" Poison Weapon at the average of their class levels, rounded up.\""}
{"id": "32666", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32666", "title": "Poison damage", "text": "&lt;onlyinclude&gt;Poison damage is a type of &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20damage\"&gt;Elemental damage&lt;/a&gt;. Like other types of damage, it can be partly or completely resisted, with for example the &lt;a href=\"Helm%20of%20the%20Rock\"&gt;Helm of the Rock&lt;/a&gt;. \nNote: \"Poison damage is independent from the &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; status effect and should not be confused with it. Taking Poison damage will not cause a Poison effect. However, when this effect is successfully applied to a creature, that creature will take Poison damage over time which can be resisted. Finally, as seen in the screenshot, the in-game character sheet lists resistance to Poison damage as \"Poison\". This is *not* the status effect.\"&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;"}
