{"id": "41661", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41661", "title": "Poison the Crusaders", "text": "Poison the Crusaders is a side quest available in . It can be gained at the start of Chapter 10, and must be completed before the end of Chapter 10.\nGaining.\nAfter speaking to &lt;a href=\"Torsin%20de%20Lancie\"&gt;Torsin de Lancie&lt;/a&gt; to receive the main storyline quest for Chapter 10, planting the &lt;a href=\"Barrel%20of%20Bwoosh%21\"&gt;Barrel of Bwoosh!&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River\"&gt;Underground River&lt;/a&gt;, the leader of Waterdeep's forces will ask &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; to go a step further and infiltrate the &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Basement\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Basement&lt;/a&gt;, so they can poison the stockpiled food and water.\nThe player has four options once this happens:\nThis event may be referenced in dialogue later in the game, depending on the discussion with Torsin and rationale used to accept or reject the task. In particular, the protagonist may choose to bring it up to help determine the ending of the game.\nIf the quest is accepted, it is entered into the journal and the player is given a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Potion of Terror&lt;/a&gt;.\nCompleting.\nTo complete the quest, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; must enter the &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Basement\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Basement&lt;/a&gt; area. A storeroom can be found in the central-east area of the map containing food, whilst a door in the western corner of the map leads to a water cask. Interacting with both the supply crates in the food chamber and the cask will grant the player the option to dose that source with the Potion of Terror.\nRewards.\nEach party member will earn for each target poisoned. In addition, as long as at least one target is poisoned, the &lt;a href=\"achievement\"&gt;achievement&lt;/a&gt; \"Blessed By Talona\" will be unlocked and the crusaders in the &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Exterior\"&gt;outer area of the castle&lt;/a&gt; will be weakened when faced during the events of &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Eleven%20%E2%80%93%20Dragonspear%20Castle%20Battle\"&gt;Chapter 11&lt;/a&gt;, receiving a +2 penalty to &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;."}
