{"id": "6993", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6993", "title": "Poisoned Throwing Dagger", "text": "Poisoned Throwing Daggers are a vicious variation of the normal version. Each hit they can inflict poison damage, unless the target makes their saving throw. Each poisoned wound inflicts its own damage, which can result in a large drop in health each second. The poison bypasses &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, but can be mitigated with &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;poison resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is sold by &lt;a href=\"Arledrian\"&gt;Arledrian&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Gaelan%20Bayle\"&gt;Gaelan Bayle&lt;/a&gt;'s home and by &lt;a href=\"Maheer\"&gt;Maheer&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocations.\n\"Throne of Bhaal\".\nUsed by &lt;a href=\"Phreya\"&gt;Phreya&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Hexxat%27s%20request\"&gt;Hexxat's request&lt;/a&gt;."}
