{"id": "3486", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3486", "title": "Potion of Magic Blocking", "text": "Potion of Magic Blocking grants 5 rounds of immunity to spell levels 1-5 in the &lt;a href=\"Enhanced%20Edition\"&gt;Enhanced Edition&lt;/a&gt; and 1-9 in Original &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;BG1&lt;/a&gt; &amp; . \nIt also applies a &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect upon the imbiber.\nGameplay.\nThe in-game description in the Enhanced Edition is not completely accurate. \nThe imbiber will be protected against all effects with a spell &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; between 1 and 5, no matter the source; spells, wands, potions, items, innate spells etc.\nThe potion also specifically blocks certain spells from affecting the user (for better game engine implementation). These include &lt;a href=\"Call%20Lightning\"&gt;Call Lightning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Glyph%20of%20Warding\"&gt;Glyph of Warding&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Smite\"&gt;Holy Smite&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Unholy%20Blight\"&gt;Unholy Blight&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Skull%20Trap\"&gt;Skull Trap&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stinking%20Cloud\"&gt;Stinking Cloud&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Web\"&gt;Web&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Entangle\"&gt;Entangle&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe potion will dispel all effects on the imbiber, as long as the effect can be subject to a &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects. Essentially, it removes all magic regardless of power.\nIt will also cure &lt;a href=\"Deafness\"&gt;Deafness&lt;/a&gt; on the user.\nThis potion's protective effects are subject to removal with &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe potion user will have portrait icon (no. 28 \"Protection from Magic\") displayed when in effect. A sound effect is audible upon quaffing the potion and another one plays when the potion's duration expires."}
{"id": "4139", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4139", "title": "Potion of Magic Protection", "text": "Potion of Magic Protection bestows the imbiber with a +50% &lt;a href=\"magic%20resistance\"&gt;magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; temporarily. \nGameplay.\nThis potion can be used by all classes, and it will last 10 turns (2 game hours) or until it is dispelled. Like most potions, effects from quaffing multiple doses are additive, although magic resistance values above 100% are rarely necessary.\nThe potion's magic resistance boost is not categorized as any spell school and has no secondary type, which means that, for example, a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Thrust\"&gt;Spell Thrust&lt;/a&gt; won't affect it, but it can be removed by &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects (which are themselves not subject to magic resistance).\nWhen imbibed the user will have icon (No. 63 \"Magic Resistance\") displayed on the portrait. A lighting effect plays over the user, as well as an audible sound effect. Another one plays when the potion's duration expires.\nLocations.\n\"Baldur's Gate\".\nTreasure"}
{"id": "11079", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11079", "title": "Potion of Magic Shielding", "text": "Potion of Magical Shielding protects the imbiber from certain damage types, increasing their resistance to all &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20damage\"&gt;Elemental damage&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Magical%20damage\"&gt;Magical damage&lt;/a&gt; by 50%. Additionally, an added 20 bonus to all &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; types is included. The effects last three turns. The bonus to damage resistances is cumulative while the bonus to saving throws are not.\nGameplay.\nWhile the item description claims that \"all saving throws are automatically successful\", this is technically implemented as a bonus of 20 to all saves. In practical terms, however, this does usually translate to all saves being successful.\nThis high bonus to saving throws is very useful in situations where you expect save-or-die spells to be cast, especially on &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;, like &lt;a href=\"Finger%20of%20Death\"&gt;Finger of Death&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Wail%20of%20the%20Banshee\"&gt;Wail of the Banshee&lt;/a&gt;. This makes the potion useful against &lt;a href=\"Kangaxx\"&gt;Kangaxx&lt;/a&gt; or inside the &lt;a href=\"Twisted%20Rune\"&gt;Twisted Rune&lt;/a&gt;.\nFor clarity, this potion does NOT increase &lt;a href=\"magic%20resistance\"&gt;magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, but only resistance to &lt;a href=\"magical%20damage\"&gt;magical damage&lt;/a&gt;. To increase general magic resistance, use the &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Magic%20Protection\"&gt;Potion of Magic Protection&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe potion's protective effects are subject to being &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;dispelled&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen the user quaffs this potion, a sound effect is heard in game, and another will be audible when the potion's duration expires. The user's portrait will display an icon (no. 15 \"Shielded\") for the duration. Certain lighting effects and a color fade also are played over the user after drinking the potion."}
{"id": "3817", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3817", "title": "Potion of Master Thievery", "text": "Consuming a Potion of Master Thievery grants the imbiber the abilities of a master thief, improving pickpocketing and lockpicking by +40% for three hours. It's only usable by bards and thieves.\nStacks with &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Perception\"&gt;Potion of Perception&lt;/a&gt; and itself up to the cap of 280."}
{"id": "38840", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38840", "title": "Shadow Altar", "text": "The Shadow Altar is an altar to the deceased solar deity &lt;a href=\"Amaunator\"&gt;Amaunator&lt;/a&gt; that has been corrupted by the &lt;a href=\"Shade%20Lord\"&gt;Shade Lord&lt;/a&gt;, transforming it into a portal to the &lt;a href=\"Plane%20of%20Shadow\"&gt;Plane of Shadow&lt;/a&gt;. The altar serves as a component in the \"boss fight\" for the quest &lt;a href=\"Investigate%20the%20Deaths%20in%20the%20Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Investigate the Deaths in the Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt;. It is located in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20Ruins\"&gt;Temple Ruins&lt;/a&gt; area south of the entrance to the &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple\"&gt;Ruined Temple&lt;/a&gt; surrounded by an impenetrable grove of trees immersed in shadow. It is only accessible by working your way through the Ruined Temple dungeon and either defeating or sneaking past the Shadow Dragon &lt;a href=\"Thaxll%27ssillyia\"&gt;Thaxll'ssillyia&lt;/a&gt; in his &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Dragon%20Lair\"&gt;lair&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe altar becomes accessible within the Temple Ruins area after the Shade Lord has been defeated.\nCombat.\nThe Shadow Altar cannot attack directly. Instead, it periodically spawns a &lt;a href=\"Shadow\"&gt;Shadow&lt;/a&gt; to attack the party, in a manner similar to the &lt;a href=\"Mephit%20Portal\"&gt;Mephit Portal&lt;/a&gt;s from &lt;a href=\"Irenicus%27s%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irenicus's Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "3766", "revid": "5653418", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3766", "title": "Shadow Armor", "text": "Shadow Armor (Shadow Armor +3 in-game) is the best body armor for &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thieves&lt;/a&gt; and its dual- and multi-classes in Baldur's Gate. Compared to normal &lt;a href=\"Studded%20Leather%20Armor\"&gt;studded leather armor&lt;/a&gt;, Shadow Armor weighs 17 lbs less, has an armor class three points lower and it offers +15% bonus to hide in shadow. It still has the same modifiers as the normal studded leather armor and requires 6 strength to wear this armor.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revised this armor to allow arcane spell casting while it is equipped.\nThe &lt;a href=\"https%3A//www.gibberlings3.net/mods/items/item_rev/\"&gt;Item Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod also has optional components to apply various changes to the ways armor affects spell casting, casting speed, movement, dexterity and thieving skills."}
