{"id": "7764", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7764", "title": "Shadow Druids", "text": "Shadow Druids are a druidic cult which believes that nature should drive out civilization with violence. They are active along the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt; with bases of operations in the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Druids\"&gt;Cloakwood Forest&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Druid%20Grove\"&gt;Druid Grove&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "41055", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41055", "title": "Shadow Fiend", "text": "Shadow Fiends are a tougher variety of of the &lt;a href=\"Shadow\"&gt;Shadow&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThey cannot be harmed by non-magical weapons. Shadow fiends have the same ability scores and saving throws as shadows (including their poor save vs spells of 16), but more hit points, and changes in resistances; they are immune to fire, but severely vulnerable to electricity damage (-128%).\nSo, for example, in the Enhanced Editions, a single well-aimed &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;Lightning Bolt&lt;/a&gt; can easily clear an entire pack of them.\nTheir touch attack deals 1d6 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt; with a range of one foot and a speed factor of three.\nEach successful hit upon a living target forces a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Death to negate being &lt;a href=\"Paralyze\"&gt;paralyzed&lt;/a&gt; for 30 seconds. A \"Held\" icon displays on the character's portrait. The effect can be dispelled and does not bypass resistance."}
{"id": "16811", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16811", "title": "Shadow Form", "text": "Shadow Form is a &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; usable by &lt;a href=\"http%3A//baldursgate.wikia.com/wiki/Thief%23Shadowdancer_.28Enhanced_Edition_Only.29\"&gt;Shadowdancer&lt;/a&gt; only.\nIt grants an &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Invisibility\"&gt;Improved Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; effect and +50% resistance to all &lt;a href=\"Physical%20damage\"&gt;Physical damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe effect works the same way as a &lt;a href=\"shaman\"&gt;shaman&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Form\"&gt;Spirit Form&lt;/a&gt;."}
