{"id": "39640", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39640", "title": "Shadow Thief Cellar Key", "text": "Shadow Thief Cellar Key is needed to open a secret door within the ground floor of the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thief%20Guildhall\"&gt;Shadow Thief Guildhall&lt;/a&gt;. \nThis key is needed during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%203\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 3&lt;/a&gt; if siding with Bodhi for help, or the key is needed in Chapter 2 if deciding to go with the Shadow Thieves offer for help.\nAquisition.\nIf the party has sided with Bodhi and are currently undertaking part of the final task set forth in the &lt;a href=\"Perform%20Bodhi%27s%20Tasks%20to%20Receive%20Her%20Aid\"&gt;Perform Bodhi's Tasks to Receive Her Aid&lt;/a&gt; questline, then this key can be acquired from &lt;a href=\"Gaelan%20Bayle\"&gt;Gaelan Bayle&lt;/a&gt; only by force of arms.\nIf you've decided to side with the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Collect%20the%20fee%20for%20Gaelan%20Bayle\"&gt;Collect the fee for Gaelan Bayle&lt;/a&gt; questline, and then actually paid the required fee to &lt;a href=\"Gaelan%20Bayle\"&gt;Gaelan Bayle&lt;/a&gt; for help to rescue &lt;a href=\"Imoen\"&gt;Imoen&lt;/a&gt;, then this key will be given to the party by Gaelan during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "48324", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48324", "title": "Shadow Thief Cloak", "text": "The Shadow Thief Cloak is an item needed to satisfy &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Perform%20Bodhi%27s%20Tasks%20to%20Receive%20Her%20Aid%23The%20Choice\"&gt;second task&lt;/a&gt; if you've decided to side with her and her vampires instead of &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt; in your quest to find &lt;a href=\"Imoen\"&gt;Imoen&lt;/a&gt; during the events of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%203\"&gt;Chapter 3&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second task is a choice between killing &lt;a href=\"Senior%20Armagaran%20Vulova\"&gt;Senior Armagaran Vulova&lt;/a&gt; or rescuing &lt;a href=\"Palern%20Flynn\"&gt;Palern Flynn&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thief%20Guildhall\"&gt;Shadow Thief Guildhall&lt;/a&gt;. If you've decided to kill the nobleman, Bodhi will have you plant the cloak and a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thief%20Dagger\"&gt;dagger&lt;/a&gt; in the fountain in &lt;a href=\"Vulova%20Estate\"&gt;Vulova's Estate&lt;/a&gt; after you carry out the deed, in order to implicate the Shadow Thieves in the murder."}
{"id": "48327", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48327", "title": "Shadow Thief Dagger", "text": "The Shadow Thief Dagger is an item needed to satisfy &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Perform%20Bodhi%27s%20Tasks%20to%20Receive%20Her%20Aid%23The%20Choice\"&gt;second task&lt;/a&gt; if you've decided to side with her and her vampires instead of &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt; in your quest to find &lt;a href=\"Imoen\"&gt;Imoen&lt;/a&gt; during the events of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%203\"&gt;Chapter 3&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second task is a choice between killing &lt;a href=\"Senior%20Armagaran%20Vulova\"&gt;Senior Armagaran Vulova&lt;/a&gt; or rescuing &lt;a href=\"Palern%20Flynn\"&gt;Palern Flynn&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thief%20Guildhall\"&gt;Shadow Thief Guildhall&lt;/a&gt;. If you've decided to kill the nobleman, Bodhi will have you plant the dagger and a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thief%20Cloak\"&gt;cloak&lt;/a&gt; in the fountain in &lt;a href=\"Vulova%20Estate\"&gt;Vulova's Estate&lt;/a&gt; after you carry out the deed, in order to implicate the Shadow Thieves in the murder."}
{"id": "12735", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12735", "title": "Shadow Thief Guildhall", "text": "The Shadow Thief Guildhall is one of the largest buildings in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Docks District&lt;/a&gt; and serves as the base of operations for the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt; in the city of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;. Inorder to enter, you must be invited inside by the Door Sentry. This can be expedited if &lt;a href=\"Yoshimo\"&gt;Yoshimo&lt;/a&gt; is in the party.\nGameplay.\nIn , The first time you pass near the guildhall entrance, a Shadow Thief sentry will let you know that you may enter if you wish. Perhaps your agreement with Gaelan Bayle had something to do with this invitation. Additionally, if &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; is a &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;Thief&lt;/a&gt;, then &lt;a href=\"Gaelan%20Bayle\"&gt;Gaelan Bayle&lt;/a&gt; will directly refer you to &lt;a href=\"Renal%20Bloodscalp\"&gt;Renal Bloodscalp&lt;/a&gt; and recommend you speak with him here at the guildhall. If &lt;a href=\"Yoshimo\"&gt;Yoshimo&lt;/a&gt; is in your party upon entering the Docks, he will suggest a visit here to see Renal in order to pay a debt and with promises of a reward. Otherwise, you will have to find the Guildhall yourself while exploring the city.\nTo begin , if you side with the Shadow Thieves in the guild war, you will need to come here to meet with &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt; in his &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail%27s%20Hideout\"&gt;hideout&lt;/a&gt;, which is accessible from the guildhall. If you side with &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt;, you have come through here to access the hideout and kill him.\nLayout.\nFirst Floor.\nThe warm welcome by a rather obvious fence called &lt;a href=\"Black%20Market%20Thief\"&gt;Black Market Thief&lt;/a&gt;, followed up by storage space and a set of stairs at the back wall that leads to the second floor of the guildhall. Be sure not to call &lt;a href=\"Sidge\"&gt;Sidge&lt;/a&gt; a thief, for he is something totally different.\nSecond Floor.\nThe second floor is the place of business of the Shadow Thieves' local leader, &lt;a href=\"Renal%20Bloodscalp\"&gt;Renal Bloodscalp&lt;/a&gt;. Again, lots of storage space for items unknowingly or involuntarily donated to the Shadow Thief cause. For those willing to take a chance, there are some containers with riches. Maximized disarm and unlock abilities are advised.\nOther loot.\n\"Chapter 2\".\nIf you're able to access every container within the guildhall, you'll come away with:\n\"Chapter 3 (side w/ Bodhi)\".\nIf you're able to access every container within the guildhall, you'll come away with:\nMod content.\nMods:.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Rebalancing\"&gt;Rogue Rebalancing&lt;/a&gt; Mod provides a number of new and or revised content to the Shadow Thief Guildhall and characters. The Black Market Thief is renamed to \"Marina\" and gets a major revised inventory of goods for sale, as well as a special category of Rogue centric enchanted and magical items. Having a thief in your party can allow access to these special wares without having to pay an extra fee (using Thieves Cant).\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Alternatives\"&gt;Alternatives&lt;/a&gt; Mod provides you a major option to decide if you wish to side with neither the Shadow Thieves nor Bohdi, and take a different path altogether to reach Imoen and rescue her.\nOn the second floor you can meet &lt;a href=\"Kim%20the%20Pirate\"&gt;Kim the Pirate&lt;/a&gt;, an NPC with a friendship feature and an epic extra quest. She will challenge the player character but only becomes recruitable after Renal's quest has been completed."}
{"id": "47844", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47844", "title": "Shadow Thief Prison Key", "text": "The Shadow Thief Prison Key is in the possession of the resident &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thief&lt;/a&gt; jailor and torturer &lt;a href=\"Booter\"&gt;Booter&lt;/a&gt;. He is found in the torture chamber in &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail's&lt;/a&gt; secret &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail%27s%20Hideout%20%28sided%20with%20Bodhi%29\"&gt;hideout&lt;/a&gt; that's accessible from the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thief%20Guildhall\"&gt;Shadow Thief Guildhall&lt;/a&gt;. If you've sided with &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; and her &lt;a href=\"vampire\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt;s instead of the Shadow Thieves in their guild war, the key is needed to open the door to the prison chamber where &lt;a href=\"Tizzak\"&gt;Tizzak&lt;/a&gt; is located and the other locked door that leads to the training areas within the hideout."}
{"id": "6090", "revid": "50459896", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6090", "title": "Shadow Thieves", "text": "The Shadow Thieves are an organization that operate through agents all over Western Faerun among their many bases. Their head base is in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Athkatla Docks&lt;/a&gt; in the city of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;, and their highest leader is &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt;. They thrive in criminal activity.\n\"Baldur's Gate\".\nThe Shadow Thieves make a brief appearance in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. In &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Seven\"&gt;Chapter Seven&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Husam\"&gt;Husam&lt;/a&gt; reveals that the Shadow Thieves are being falsely accused of murdering &lt;a href=\"Entar%20Silvershield\"&gt;Entar Silvershield&lt;/a&gt;, after a mark that resembles their organization is left on his body, as intended by the real assassins &lt;a href=\"Slythe\"&gt;Slythe&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Krystin\"&gt;Krystin&lt;/a&gt;.\n\"Baldur's Gate II: Shadows of Amn\".\nIn , the Shadow Thieves are more involved with the main plot. They are first seen storming &lt;a href=\"Irenicus%27s%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irenicus's Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;, for unknown reasons, and a few of their assassins are then seen in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; attacking Irenicus himself. In &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt;, the player must choose whether to side with &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; and her vampires or Aran Linvail and his Shadow Thieves. When the choice is made, this starts &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%203\"&gt;Chapter 3&lt;/a&gt;. If the player sides with Bodhi then their main objective will be to kill Aran. If the player sides with the Shadow Thieves then their &lt;a href=\"Aran%27s%20tasks%20to%20receive%20the%20Shadow%20Thieves%27%20aid\"&gt;main objective&lt;/a&gt; will be to destroy the vampire guild and kill Bodhi. In &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt;, the player can get help from the Shadow Thieves in the attempt to finally kill Bodhi."}
