{"id": "16813", "revid": "50907129", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16813", "title": "Shadow Twin", "text": "Shadow Twin is a &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; usable by &lt;a href=\"http%3A//baldursgate.wikia.com/wiki/Thief%23Shadowdancer_.28Enhanced_Edition_Only.29\"&gt;Shadowdancer&lt;/a&gt; only.\nThe in-game description for this ability incorrectly states that the clone lasts for 2 turns. In practice, the duration is 1 turn (or 10 rounds).\nGameplay.\nSimilar to Simulacrum, a Shadow Twin inherits the special abilities, spells and items of the caster with a few exceptions listed below.\nA Shadow Twin is able to create another single Shadow Twin clone ad infinitum provided they have a use of the Shadow Twin ability.\nSecond and later generations of Shadow Twins no longer inherit the items of the caster, leaving them unarmed.\nAll generations of Shadow Twins created from a Simulacrum or Project Image do not incur a 60% level penalty, as a result they retain all spells and stats."}
